)@@G@@* . THE @ASG'S ARE DONE IN TWO GROUPS: AN INITIAL GROUP AND A MAIN:@@@B]JJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@* . GROUP.  THE INITIAL GROUP CAUSES THE FRONT PART OF THE FILE TOJK
)@@G@@:@@@BG@G@@@@* . BE SPREAD OUT IN SMALLER INCREMENTS OVER A NUMBER OF DEVJL
)@@G@@ICES AND    :@@@BQ@F@@@@* . SUBSYSTEMS; THIS IS DONE BECAUSE A HIGH PERCJM
)@@G@@ENTAGE OF MAPPER'S:@@@B)@F@@@@* . I/O IS DONE TO THIS PART OF THE FILE. JN
)@@G@@THE MAIN GROUP ALLOCATES:@@@B%@G@@@@* . THE REMAINDER OF THE FILE ACROSSJO
)@@G@@ ALL UNITS IN LARGER INCREMENTS.    :@@@B4@[@@@@* .   :@@@B"@B@@@@* . FIJP
)@@G@@LSIZ HAS FOUR PARAMETRIC SUBFIELDS: :@@@CC@[@@@@* .   :@@@CM@E@@@@* .   JQ
)@@G@@SUBFIELD 1: THE INITIAL RESERVE INCREMENT FOR THE MAIN:@@@CW@A@@@@* .   JR
)@@G@@               GROUP OF @ASG'S:@@@C&@A@@@@* .   SUBFIELD 2: THE MAX TRACJS
)@@G@@K SIZE:@@@C0@F@@@@* .   SUBFIELD 3: THE NUMBER OF TRACKS IN THE INITIAL JT
)@@G@@@ASG GROUP  :@@@C'@F@@@@* .   SUBFIELD 4: THE NUMBER OF DEVICES ONTO WHIJU
)@@G@@CH THE INITIAL    :@@@D^@D@@@@* .                  @ASG GROUP IS TO BE AJV
)@@G@@LLOCATED    :@@@DI@[@@@@* .   :@@@DS@F@@@@* . FIELD 6, SUBFIELD 1 ON THEJW
)@@G@@ DEVICE SGSES INDICATES THE TRACK   :@@@D+@F@@@@* . AVAILABILITY ON THE JX
)@@G@@DEVICE AT THE TIME THE CKMSALL WAS RUN.   :@@@D?@F@@@@* . ALLOCATIONS AGJY
)@@G@@AINST EACH DEVICE ARE DEDUCTED FROM THIS FIGURE,:@@@D6@F@@@@* . AND THE JZ
)@@G@@DEVICE IS DROPPED FROM THE ALLOCATION ROTATION WHEN   :@@@E@@F@@@@* . INKA
)@@G@@SUFFICIENT SPACE REMAINS FOR FURTHER ALLOCATIONS.  AN ERROR :@@@EE@G@@@@KB
)@@G@@* . TERMINATION COULD STILL RESULT IF THE SPACE AVAILABILITY SHOULD     KC
)@@G@@:@@@EO@F@@@@* . DECREASE SIGNIFICANTLY BETWEEN THE CKMSALL AND THE @ASG'KD
)@@G@@S.    :@@@EY@[@@@@* .   :@@@E*@F@@@@* . ASGCNT IS THE NUMBER OF @ASG IMAKE
)@@G@@GES NEEDED IN THE MAIN GROUP  :@@@E2@G@@@@* . INITSIZ IS THE INITIAL RESKF
)@@G@@ERVE INCREMENT ON THE INITIAL @ASG IMAGES :@@@E/@G@@@@* . INITRK IS THE KG
)@@G@@SIZE OF INITIAL RESERVE ON THE CURRENT @ASG IMAGE     :@@@FA@F@@@@* . THKH
)@@G@@E DEVICE SGSES LIST THE CURRENT AVAILABLE UP'D DISK UNITS   :@@@FK@B@@@@KI
)@@G@@* . J IS A POINTER INTO THE DEVICE LIST   :@@@FU@H@@@@* . PASS NUMBER INKJ
)@@G@@DICATES HOW MANY TIMES WE'VE GONE THROUGH THE DEVICE LIST   :@@@F=@[@@@@KK
)@@G@@*EJECT:@@@F,@#@@@@*DEFINE CHECKAVAIL:@@@F8@[@@@@* .   :@@@G]@G@@@@* . ONKL
)@@G@@ EACH PASS THROUGH THE DEVICE LIST, THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO     :@@@GGKM
)@@G@@@G@@@@* . VERIFY THAT THERE IS SUFFICIENT ROOM ON EACH DEVICE TO ALLOCATKN
)@@G@@E     :@@@GQ@G@@@@* . THE NEXT SEGMENT OF MAPER0 ON THE DEVICE.  IF THERKO
)@@G@@E IS INSUFFICIENT :@@@G)@G@@@@* . ROOM, THE DEVICE IS REMOVED FROM THE LKP
)@@G@@IST AND A MESSAGE DISPLAYED.  :@@@G%@[@@@@* .   :@@@G4@F@@@@* . INPUT PAKQ
)@@G@@RAMETER: SIZE (INCREMENT) OF NEXT ALLOCATION SEGMENT  :@@@G"@[@@@@* .   KR
)@@G@@:@@@HC@D@@@@*SET PASS TO PASS+1                    . BUMP PASS #  :@@@HMKS
)@@G@@@F@@@@*INCREMENT I FROM [DEVICE] TO 1 BY -1  . THROUGH THE DEVICE LIST  KT
)@@G@@:@@@HW@D@[@@*IF +[DEVICE,I,6,2] > +[#1]  . AVAILABILITY > NEEDED? @D@]@[KU
)@@G@@*IF +[DEVICE,I,3,1] > +[#1]  . AVAILABILITY > NEEDED? @D@#@]*IF +[DEVICEKV
)@@G@@,I,4,1] > +[#1]  . AVAILABILITY > NEEDED? @D@@@#*IF +[DEVICE,I,3,1] > +[KW
)@@G@@#1]  . AVAILABILITY > NEEDED? :@@@H&@B@[@@*SET [DEVICE,I,6,2] TO [DEVICEKX
)@@G@@,I,6,2]-[#1]@B@]@[*SET [DEVICE,I,3,1] TO [DEVICE,I,3,1]-[#1]@B@#@]*SET [KY
)@@G@@DEVICE,I,4,1] TO [DEVICE,I,3,1]-[#1]@B@@@#*SET [DEVICE,I,3,1] TO [DEVICEKZ
)@@G@@,I,3,1]-[#1]:@@@H0@F@@@@*ELSE                                  . IF NOT,LA
)@@G@@ THEN THROW IT OUT:@@@H'@G@[@@#MSG,N [DEVICE,I,3,1] DROPPED FOR UNAVAILALB
)@@G@@BLE TRACKS ON PASS [*PASS]    @G@]@[#MSG,N [DEVICE,I,2,1] DROPPED FOR UNLC
)@@G@@AVAILABLE TRACKS ON PASS [*PASS]    @G@#@]#MSG,N [DEVICE,I,3,1] DROPPED LD
)@@G@@FOR UNAVAILABLE TRACKS ON PASS [*PASS]    @G@@@##MSG,N [DEVICE,I,2,1] DRLE
)@@G@@OPPED FOR UNAVAILABLE TRACKS ON PASS [*PASS]    :@@@I^@^@@@@*REMOVE SGS LF
)@@G@@DEVICE,I    :@@@II@[@@@@*END  :@@@IS@D@@@@*LOOP                         LG
)@@G@@         . END I LOOP   :@@@I+@F@@@@*SET J TO 1                         LH
)@@G@@   . REINITIALIZE FILE POINTER:@@@I?@E@@@@*END                          LI
)@@G@@         . END CHECKAVAIL     :@@@I6@[@@@@* .   :@@@J@@#@@@@*DEFINE ASGLLJ
)@@G@@OOP   :@@@JE@[@@@@* .   :@@@JO@D@@@@* . THIS ROUTINE HANDLES A GROUP OF LK
)@@G@@@ASG'S, AS DEFINED:@@@JY@ @@@@* . BY THE INPUT PARAMETERS:  :@@@J*@[@@@@LL
)@@G@@* .   :@@@J2@D@@@@* .           [#1] := NUMBER OF @ASG'S TO BE DONE     LM
)@@G@@:@@@J/@E@@@@* .           [#2] := INITIAL RESERVE INCREMENT ON EACH @ASGLN
)@@G@@:@@@KA@[@@@@* .   :@@@KK@F@@@@*INCREMENT I TO [#1]                   . PLO
)@@G@@ARAM #1 CONTROLS COUNT  :@@@KU@G@@@@*SET J TO J+1                       LP
)@@G@@   . BUMP TO NEXT DEVICE POINTER    :@@@K=@G@@@@*IF +J > [DEVICE] OR +J LQ
)@@G@@= 1            . AT BOTTOM OF DEVICE TABLE?     :@@@K,@F@@@@*PROCESS CHELR
)@@G@@CKAVAIL [#2]               . REVALIDATE AVAILABILITY  :@@@K8@[@@@@*END  LS
)@@G@@:@@@L]@E@@@@*PROCESS DOASG [#2],[*J]               . GO DO THE @ASG     LT
)@@G@@:@@@LG@C@@@@*IF [*INITRK] = [FILSIZ,1,1,2]         . AT END?:@@@LQ@F@@@@LU
)@@G@@*SET I TO [#1]                         . CLOSE LOOP INCREMENTER   :@@@L)LV
)@@G@@@[@@@@*END  :@@@L%@D@@@@*LOOP                                  . END I LLW
)@@G@@OOP   :@@@L4@D@@@@*END                                   . END ASGLOOP  LX
)@@G@@:@@@L"@[@@@@* .   :@@@MC@#@@@@*DEFINE DOASG     :@@@MM@[@@@@* .   :@@@MWLY
)@@G@@@A@@@@* . ROUTINE TO ACTUALLY DO THE @ASG :@@@M&@[@@@@* .   :@@@M0@^@@@@LZ
)@@G@@* . INPUT PARAMETERS    :@@@M'@[@@@@* .   :@@@N^@C@@@@* .           [#1]MA
)@@G@@ := INITIAL RESERVE INCREMENT :@@@NI@B@@@@* .           [#2] := DEVICE TMB
)@@G@@ABLE INDEX  :@@@NS@[@@@@* .   :@@@N+@H@@@@*SET INITRK TO INITRK+[#1]    MC

)@@G@@SGCNT TO ASGCNT+1                . ROUND UP     :@@@Q)@[@@@@*END  :@@@Q%MP
)@@G@@@E@@@@*DIVIDE [FILSIZ,1,1,3] BY [FILSIZ,1,1,1] GIVING GRP1SIZ     :@@@Q4MQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@*SET ASGCNT TO ASGCNT-GRP1SIZ          . REDUCE BY INITIAL GROUP SMR
)@@G@@IZE   :@@@Q"@E@@@@*DIVIDE [FILSIZ,1,1,3] BY [FILSIZ,1,1,4] GIVING INITSIMS
)@@G@@Z     :@@@RC@H@@@@*INCREMENT I TO [DEVICE]               . LOOP TO INITIMT
)@@G@@ALIZE DEVICE COUNTERS   :@@@RM@H@[@@*SET [DEVICE,I,6,2] TO [DEVICE,I,6,1MU
)@@G@@]-100  . USE DEVNAME AS VARIABLE NAME     @H@@@[*SET [DEVICE,I,3,1] TO [MV
)@@G@@DEVICE,I,4,1]-100  . USE DEVNAME AS VARIABLE NAME     :@@@RW@D@@@@*LOOP MW
)@@G@@                                 . END I LOOP   :@@@R&@F@@@@*CLEAR PASS MX

)@@G@@@A@@@O@COPY,S USE*DAVE.MAPFIL/SGSES,TPF$. @A@@@O@COPY,S USE*DAVE.DEVICE/NK
)@@G@@SGSES,TPF$. @[@@@O@ .   :@@@[,@G@@@O@ . THIS JCL IS USED TO DELETE THE MNL
)@@G@@APER0 FILE THEN RECATALOG IT AND    :@@@[8@E@@@O@ . SPREAD THE FILE IN 2NM
)@@G@@56 TRACK CHUNKS TO ALL UPPED UNITS. :@@@]]@F@@@O@ . IT DOES THE SPREAD TNN
)@@G@@HROUGH THE USE OF ABSOLUTE UNIT ASSIGNS.  :@@@]G@E@@@O@ . UNFORTUNATELY NO
)@@G@@IF ONE OF THE UNITS IS FULL, THE EXEC WILL:@@@]Q@E@@@O@ . PCT ABORT THE NP
)@@G@@JOB. (NO WAY TO AVOID).  IF THIS HAPPENS, :@@@])@F@@@O@ . REDUCE THE NUMNQ
)@@G@@BER OF BATCH JOBS AND DEMAND JOBS ON THE SYSTEM :@@@]%@G@@@O@ . AND RERUNR
)@@G@@N THE JOB.  IF AFTER RERUNNING IT SEVERAL TIMES, IT STILL   :@@@]4@G@@@ONS
)@@G@@@ . CONTINUES TO ERROR ON AN @ASG,A REQUEST THEN @ADD THE CREATENEW     NT
)@@G@@:@@@]"@F@@@O@ . JCL FROM A DEMAND JOB.  THE DEMAND JOB SHOULD BE SIGNED NU
)@@G@@ON    :@@@#C@E@@@O@ . UNDER THE MAPPER USERID (NOT ABSOLUTELY ESSENTIAL)NV
)@@G@@.     :@@@#M@G@@@O@ . AS A LAST RESORT IF A DEMAND PORT IS NOT AVAILABLENW
)@@G@@, SIMPLY RUN THE  :@@@#W@F@@@O@ . JOB AND LET IT ERROR.  MAPPER CAN THENNX
)@@G@@ BE BROUGHT UP, HOWEVER,:@@@#&@F@@@O@ . THE FILE SPREAD WILL BE INCOMPLENY
)@@G@@TE AND HENCE PERFORMANCE WILL :@@@#0@F@@@O@ . SUFFER.  PLEASE ADVISE PERNZ
)@@G@@FORMANCE MANAGEMENT IN THIS CASE.   :@@@#'@[@@@O@ .   :@@@^^:@@@^I@^@@@OOA

)@@G@@          ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@]EHEXV$*   . @ @@@]          OFF     IV
)@@G@@  1-ASCII   @H@]@@AHEXV$*   LNA,U     A3,1                LOAD -1 FOR INIW
)@@G@@ITIAL CHARACTER COUNT   @H@@@]          LNA,U     A3,1                LOIX
)@@G@@AD -1 FOR INITIAL CHARACTER COUNT   @F@@@@AHEXV1    AA,U      A3,1      IY
)@@G@@          INCREMENT CHARACTER COUNT @E@@@@          DSL       A0,4      IZ
)@@G@@          MOVE A BYTE INTO A1 @F@@@@          JNZ       A0,AHEXV1       JA
)@@G@@    HAS ALL DATA BEEN MOVED ? @F@@@@AHEXV2    LA,U      A2              JB
)@@G@@    YES.  CLEAR STORE REGISTER@F@@@@          LDSC      A1,4            JC
)@@G@@    MOVE NEXT BYTE INTO A2    @F@@@@          LA        A2,HEXCHT,A2    JD
)@@G@@    LOAD HEX REPRESENTATION   @ @@@]          ON        ASCII     @F@@@@JE
)@@G@@          PARITY    .                   COMPUTE PARITY, IF DESIRED@ @@@]JF
)@@G@@          OFF       ASCII     @F@@@@          STORE     .               JG
)@@G@@    STORE CHARACTER INTO LINE @E@@@@          JGD       A3,AHEXV2       JH
)@@G@@    LOOP FOR ALL BYTES  @C@@@@          J         0,X11               REJI
)@@G@@TURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         FIXED LENGTH HEXADECIMAL EDIT   @[@@@@JJ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@]          ON        ASCII     @]@@@]AHEXF$*   . @ @@@]      JK
)@@G@@    OFF       ASCII     @ @@@]          ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@]EHEXF$JL
)@@G@@*   . @ @@@]          OFF       1-ASCII   @E@]@@AHEXF$*   LA,U      A3,,JM
)@@G@@A1              LOAD CHARACTER COUNT@E@@@]          LA,U      A3,,A1    JN
)@@G@@          LOAD CHARACTER COUNT@G@@@@          LSSL      A1,2            JO
)@@G@@    CHANGE CHARACTERS TO BITS (X 4) @G@@@@          DSL       A0,,A1    JP
)@@G@@          SHIFT OFF PROPER NUMBER OF BITS @F@@@@          ANA,U     A3,1JQ
)@@G@@                DECREMENT COUNT BY ONE    @F@@@@          J         AHEXJR
)@@G@@V2              ENTER PROCESSING LOOP     @[@@@@.     @ @@@]          ONJS
)@@G@@        ASCII     @#@@@@          ASCII   @ @@@]          OFF       ASCIJT
)@@G@@I     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@HEXCHT    . @A@@@@I         DO        10 , * '0'JU
)@@G@@+I-1  @A@@@@I         DO        6 , * 'A'+I-1   @@@@@[@[@[@@.     @C@[@@JV
)@@G@@.         ...AND NOW FOR OUR BDITING FRIENDS... @[@[@@.     @ @[@@BHEXV$JW
)@@G@@*   B$        AHEXV$    @ @[@@BHEXF$*   B$        AHEXF$    @[@[@@.     JX
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     ___     AHEXF$    @[@[@@.     @#@@@@          ENJY
)@@G@@D     ___^W?9.D^W?/K@^Y2(?@^W4/K@^Y>C[@^W0:[D^W0/K@^Y>/K@^Y2%8K@@[(*D^W5JZ
)@@G@@/K@^Y(9!@^DO9(B@@@9(@OFL/K@^ZZ9!D^W?%8K@@[9.@^DO*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     KA
)@@G@@@C@@@@.         PROCS FOR SCHEDULER CALLING SEQUENCES @[@@@@.     @^@@@@KB
)@@G@@Q         PROC      1   @^@@@@P*        NAME      0   @^@@@@V*        NAKC
)@@G@@ME      1   @^@@@@INSERT*   NAME      2   @^@@@@REMOVE*   NAME      3   KD
)@@G@@@^@@@@PUT*      NAME      4   @^@@@@GET*      NAME      5   @^@@@@PMAY* KE
)@@G@@    NAME      6   @^@@[@PUSH*     NAME      7   @G@@@@          DO      KF
)@@G@@  Q(1)>0 , LA,14*(Q(1)<3) 12,Q(1,1),Q(1,2),Q(1,3)     @B@@@@          DOKG
)@@G@@        Q(0,0)=0 , LMJ 11,P   @B@@@@          DO        Q(0,0)=1 , LMJ 1KH
)@@G@@1,V   @C@@@@          DO        Q(0,0)=2 , LMJ 11,INSERT    @C@@@@      KI
)@@G@@    DO        Q(0,0)=3 , LMJ 11,REMOVE    @B@@@@          DO        Q(0,KJ
)@@G@@0)=4 , LMJ 15,PUT @B@@@@          DO        Q(0,0)=5 , LMJ 15,GET @B@@@@KK
)@@G@@          DO        Q(0,0)=6 , LMJ 11,PMAY@B@@[@          DO        Q(0,KL
)@@G@@0)=7 , LMJ 11,PUSH@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         FOKM
)@@G@@RK      <ADDRESS> @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@FORK* KN
)@@G@@    NAME      0   @G@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14*(P(1)<3) 13,PKO
)@@G@@(1,1),P(1,2),P(1,3)     @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=0 , LMJ 11,FORKKP
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      0,1 @^@@@@KQ
)@@G@@EXIT*     NAME      0   @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,EXIT  @#@@@@      KR
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         INITQ     <QUEUE ADDRESS> @[@@@@KS
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@INITQ*    NAME      0   @F@@@@KT
)@@G@@          DO        (P(1)>0)**(1-((P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=12))) , ;     @C@@@@KU
)@@G@@          LA,14*(P(1)<3) 12,P(1,1),P(1,2),P(1,3)@ @@@@          LMJ     KV
)@@G@@  11,INITQ  @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         INITPVQ KW
)@@G@@  <COUNT>,<P/V QUEUE ADDRESS> @D@@@@.         INITBB    <COUNT>,<BOUNDEDKX
)@@G@@ BUFFER ADDRESS>  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@@INITPVKY
)@@G@@Q*  NAME      0   @^@@@@INITBB*   NAME      1   @C@@@@          DO      KZ
)@@G@@  P(1)>0 , LA,14 13,P(1,1)    @F@@@@          DO        (P(1)>1)**(1-((PLA
)@@G@@(1)=2)**(P(1,2)=12))) , ;     @C@@@@          LA,14*(P(1)<4) 12,P(1,2),PLB
)@@G@@(1,3),P(1,4)@C@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=0 , LMJ 11,INITPVQ   @C@@@@LC
)@@G@@          DO        P(0,0)=1 , LMJ 11,INITBB    @#@@@@          END     LD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         QUEUE     [FIRST[,LAST]]  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@LE
)@@G@@P         PROC      1,QL@^@@@@QUEUE*    NAME      0   @^@@@@A(0)      EQLF
)@@G@@U       $   @C@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 ,A(0) EQU P(1,1).    @^@@@@LG
)@@G@@A(1)      EQU       A(0)@C@@@@          DO        P(1)>1 ,A(1) EQU P(1,2LH
)@@G@@)     @ @@@@          *         A(1),A(0) @B@@@@          DO        1-(TLI
)@@G@@SQ=0) , T$CELL 0  @A@@@@          DO        TSQ=0 , * 0     @#@@@@      LJ
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         PVQUEUE  N                    N LK
)@@G@@= INITIAL COUNT, >=0.   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@P         PROC      1,QPL     LL
)@@G@@@^@@@@PVQUEUE*  NAME      0   @G@@@@          DO        TSQ=0 , * $,$   LM
)@@G@@    QUEUE HEAD UNLESS TS QUEUING    @E@@@@          *         0,P(1,1)  LN
)@@G@@          COUNT, WORD 0 OR 1  @A@@@@          DO        TSQ=1 , TCELL$ 0LO
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@P         PROC      1,QL+2*QPLLP
)@@G@@@^@@@@BBUF*     NAME      0   @D@@@@          QUEUE     .               LQ
)@@G@@    DATA QUEUE    @E@@@@          PVQUEUE   0                   NOT-EMPTLR
)@@G@@Y QUEUE.    @E@@@@          PVQUEUE   P(1,1)              NOT-FULL QUEUELS
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         THE PROCEDURE LT
)@@G@@'SCHPROC' DEFINES THE FIELDS USED   @E@@@@.         BY THE SCHEDULER.  ALU
)@@G@@NY ELEMENT WHICH REFERENCES   @D@@@@.         THE PROCS 'QUEUE', 'PVQUEULV
)@@G@@E', OR 'BBUF' MUST@E@@@@.         CALL SCHPROC BEFORE THE FIRST SUCH REFLW
)@@G@@ERENCE.  THE@E@@@@.         TAG 'TSQ' DEFINES WHETHER THE SCHEDULER WILLLX
)@@G@@ USE  @E@@@@.         TEST AND SET QUEUEING FOR SYNCHRONISATION.  IF    LY
)@@G@@@D@@@@.         IT IS CHANGED, THE SCHEDULER ITSELF MUST BE @^@@@@.     LZ
)@@G@@    REASSEMBLED.  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          DEF     @E@@@@TSQ       EQMA
)@@G@@U       ;                   ONE IF TS QUEUING.  @^@@@@                  MB
)@@G@@  1   @D@@@@QHEAD     EQUF      1                   T/S CELL.     @E@@@@MC
)@@G@@QHL       EQUF      0,,2                QUEUE BACK LINK.    @E@@@@QFL   MD
)@@G@@    EQUF      0,,1                QUEUE FORWARD LINK. @D@@@@QN        EQME
)@@G@@UF      1-TSQ,,3            QUEUE COUNT.  @F@@@@QL        EQU       2   MF
)@@G@@                LENGTH OF QUEUE HEADER.   @F@@@@QPL       EQU       2   MG
)@@G@@                P/V QUEUE HEADER SIZE.    @^@@@@SCHDEF*   PROC      0   MH
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     ___COUNT>,<P/V QUEUE ADDRESS> @D@@@@.         INMI
)@@G@@ITBB    <COUNT>,<BOUNDED*[S@@@*SDFF*@C@@@@. AVAILABLE PREFIXES ARE G$ J$MJ
)@@G@@ M$ Q$ V$ W$ Z$   @]@@@@        DEF @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. KEYWORDS WHICH DMK
)@@G@@ETERMINE STRUCTURE OF THE HEADER LINE     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. NOTE THAT ML
)@@G@@THESE KEYWORDS ARE NEGATIVE TO AVOID CONFUSION  @F@@@@. WITH USER SUPPLIMM
)@@G@@ED REGISTER AND J-DESIGNATOR SPECIFICATIONS     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@IN    MN
)@@G@@  EQU    - 1@#@@@@IS      EQU    - 2@#@@@@THEN    EQU    - 3@#@@@@AND   MO
)@@G@@  EQU    - 4@#@@@@OR      EQU    - 5@#@@@@WHILE   EQU    - 6@#@@@@UNTIL MP
)@@G@@  EQU    - 7@H@@@@. NOTE: KEYWORDS VARY THRU LOOKFOR MUST BE IN ORDER, RMQ
)@@G@@ANGE TESTS ARE USED     @#@@@@VARY    EQU    - 8@#@@@@JGD     EQU    - 9MR
)@@G@@@^@@@@TLEM    EQU    - 10     @^@@@@JMGI    EQU    - 11     @^@@@@LOOKFOMS
)@@G@@R EQU    - 12     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@TO      EQU    - 13     @^@@@@BY    MT
)@@G@@  EQU    - 14     @^@@@@FOR     EQU    - 15     @^@@@@UP      EQU    - 1MU
)@@G@@6     @^@@@@DOWN    EQU    - 17     @^@@@@WHEN    EQU    - 18     @^@@@@MV
)@@G@@FROM    EQU    - 19     @^@@@@MASKED  EQU    - 20     @^@@@@SUBROUTINE EMW
)@@G@@QU - 21     @^@@@@MAINPROGRAM EQU - 22    @^@@@@CONTINGENCY EQU - 23    MX
)@@G@@@H@@@@COROUTINE EQU  - 24                   . UNDOCUMENTED AND SOON TO BMY
)@@G@@E REMOVED   @F@@@@CYCLIC    EQU       -24               . AND REPLACED WMZ
)@@G@@ITH THIS    @^@@@@POINTER EQU    - 25     @^@@@@SIGNAL  EQU    - 26     NA
)@@G@@@^@@@@STACK   EQU    - 27     @^@@@@SAVE    EQU    - 28     @^@@@@OFFSETNB
)@@G@@  EQU    - 29     @^@@@@CHANNEL EQU    - 30     @^@@@@STARTIO EQU    - 3NC
)@@G@@1     @^@@@@NOT       EQU       -32 @^@@@@NOSAVE    EQU       -33 @^@@@@ND
)@@G@@EXECSUB   EQU       -34 @^@@@@CALLING EQU         -35 @C@@@@/. TABLES FONE
)@@G@@R GENERATION OF TYPE 1 TESTS, FORM: @C@@@@.                 <AREG>,<KEYWNF
)@@G@@ORD>,<U-SPEC>     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. KEYWORDS-----   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@NG
)@@G@@EQ      EQU    1  @D@@@@NE      EQU    2                      . PREFERRENH
)@@G@@D     @F@@@@NEQ     EQU    NE                     . ALTERNATE (MAY BE RENI
)@@G@@MOVED)@#@@@@LT      EQU    3  @E@@@@GE      EQU    4                    NJ
)@@G@@  . PREFERRED KEYWORD   @F@@@@GEQ     EQU    GE                     . SUNK
)@@G@@PERCEDED BY THE ABOVE   @#@@@@GT      EQU    5  @E@@@@LE        EQU     NL
)@@G@@  6                 . THIS IS PREFERRED   @F@@@@LEQ       EQU       LE  NM
)@@G@@              . THIS HAS BEEN SUPERCEDED  @#@@@@SPANS   EQU    7  @#@@@@NN
)@@G@@NOSPAN  EQU    8  @#@@@@EVENP   EQU    9  @#@@@@ODDP    EQU    10 @#@@@@NO
)@@G@@DEQ     EQU    11 @D@@@@DNE     EQU    12                     . PREFERRENP
)@@G@@D     @F@@@@DNEQ    EQU    DNE                    . ALTERNATE (MAY BE RENQ
)@@G@@MOVED)@I@@@@AGE     EQU    13                     . PREFERRED: SPECIAL FNR
)@@G@@OR MASKED ALFA SEARC    @#@@@@AGEQ    EQU    AGE@#@@@@ALT     EQU    14 NS
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. WAITING STATUS=2 INDICATES  CONDITION AFTER TEST IS NT
)@@G@@ FALSE,TRUE @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$WS(1,EQ)        EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,NE)  NU
)@@G@@      EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,GT)        EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,LE)        EQU  3NV
)@@G@@@^@@@@G$WS(1,LT)        EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,GE)        EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1NW
)@@G@@,SPANS)     EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,NOSPAN)    EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,EVENP)     NX
)@@G@@EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,ODDP)      EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,DEQ)       EQU  2@^@@@@NY
)@@G@@G$WS(1,DNE)       EQU  3@^@@@@G$WS(1,AGE)       EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,ALT) NZ
)@@G@@      EQU  2@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. DEFINE INVERSE FUNCTIONS USED TO OPTIMIZOA
)@@G@@E     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@G$IV(1,EQ)        EQU  NE     @ @@@@G$IV(1,NE)  OB
)@@G@@      EQU  EQ     @ @@@@G$IV(1,GT)        EQU  LE     @ @@@@G$IV(1,LE)  OC
)@@G@@      EQU  GT     @ @@@@G$IV(1,LT)        EQU  GE     @ @@@@G$IV(1,GE)  OD
)@@G@@      EQU  LT     @ @@@@G$IV(1,SPANS)     EQU  NOSPAN @ @@@@G$IV(1,NOSPAOE
)@@G@@N)    EQU  SPANS  @ @@@@G$IV(1,EVENP)     EQU  ODDP   @ @@@@G$IV(1,ODDP)OF
)@@G@@      EQU  EVENP  @ @@@@G$IV(1,DEQ)       EQU  DNE    @ @@@@G$IV(1,DNE) OG
)@@G@@      EQU  DEQ    @ @@@@G$IV(1,AGE)       EQU  -1     @ @@@@G$IV(1,ALT) OH
)@@G@@      EQU  -1     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. DEFINE INSTRUCTION OPCODES TO BE UOI
)@@G@@SED IN CODE GENERATION  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FJ(1,EQ,1)      EQU  052    OJ
)@@G@@        . TEST EQUAL OPCODE   @C@@@@G$FJ(1,NE,1)      EQU  053          OK
)@@G@@  . TNE     @B@@@@G$FJ(1,GT,1)      EQU  055            . TG@C@@@@G$FJ(1OL
)@@G@@,GT,2)      EQU  053            . TNE     @B@@@@G$FJ(1,LE,1)      EQU  0OM
)@@G@@55            . TG@C@@@@G$FJ(1,LE,2)      EQU  053            . TNE     ON
)@@G@@@B@@@@G$FJ(1,LT,1)      EQU  055            . TG@C@@@@G$FJ(1,GE,1)      OO
)@@G@@EQU  054            . TLE     @B@@@@G$FJ(1,SPANS,1)   EQU  056          OP
)@@G@@  . TW@C@@@@G$FJ(1,NOSPAN,1)  EQU  057            . TNW     @C@@@@G$FJ(1OQ
)@@G@@,EVENP,1)   EQU  044            . TEP     @C@@@@G$FJ(1,ODDP,1)    EQU  0OR
)@@G@@45            . TOP     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. NOTE- DOUBLE TEST HAS A 2ND OS
)@@G@@ENTRY TO PREVENT OPTIMIZER    @E@@@@. FROM TRYING TO NEST IT.  THIS IS NOT
)@@G@@ECESSARY BECAUSE THERE  @D@@@@. IS NO DTNE INSTRUCTION, AND IF THE WAITIOU
)@@G@@NG VALUE    @E@@@@. OF THE TEST IS INVERTED BY THE OPTIMIZER (E.G. DEMOROV
)@@G@@GAN'S @E@@@@. THEOREM USED), THE NUMBER OF INSTRUCTIONS GENERATED WILL  OW
)@@G@@@#@@@@. BE DIFFERENT    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FJ(1,DEQ,1)     EQU  01637  OX
)@@G@@        . FJ FOR DTE INSTR    @F@@@@G$FJ(1,DEQ,2)     EQU  0            OY
)@@G@@  . DUMMY TO FOOL OPTIMIZER   @H@@@@G$FJ(1,DNE,1)     EQU  01637        OZ
)@@G@@  . SAME THING (BUT WAIT STATUS DIFFERENT)@F@@@@G$FJ(1,DNE,2)     EQU  0PA
)@@G@@              . DUMMY TO FOOL OPTIMIZER   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. FUDGED ENTPB
)@@G@@RIES FOR MASKED ALFABETIC SEARCH-- CODE GENERATOR WILL@D@@@@. SUBTRACT 0PC
)@@G@@52 FROM VALUES BELOW AND USE AS A J-FIELD @E@@@@. WE DON'T WORRY ABOUT IPD
)@@G@@NVERSION HERE SINCE THESE CAN ONLY  @E@@@@. APPEAR IN LOOKFOR FORMAT OF PE
)@@G@@A REPEAT STATEMENT, AND IT    @B@@@@. HAS ITS OWN SELF-PROTECTION MECHANPF
)@@G@@ISMS  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@G$FJ(1,AGE,1)     EQU  060            . GENERATEPG
)@@G@@S MASL@D@@@@G$FJ(1,ALT,1)     EQU  061            . GENERATES MASG@[@@@@PH

)@@G@@                    . PF'S : DBANK-LOCNCTR,DISPLAY-OCTAL-FLAG     @E@@@@TQ
)@@G@@STRUC$* NAME                          . NORMAL ENTRY POINT  @E@@@@ DO P(TR
)@@G@@1)>0 ,G$LCTR*(1) EQU P(1,1)     . SET DATA LOCN CTR   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@TS
)@@G@@. USAGE OF OVERALL COUNTER ARRAY G$CTR:   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.       1 = TT
)@@G@@COUNT OF TOTAL NO BLOX (ALL KINDS EXCEPT BEGIN) @A@@@@.       2 = GLOBALTU

)@@G@@NG DEPTH COUNTER  @D@@@@.       6 = LOGICAL FOR GLOBAL PASS: TRUE ON PASTX
)@@G@@S 1   @D@@@@.       7 = LOGICAL FOR GLOBAL PASS: TRUE ON PASS 2   @[@@@@TY
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@K DO     5 ,G$CTR*(K) EQU 0           . CLEAR COUNTERS@[@@@@TZ
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. NOW DEFINE SPECIAL THINGS DEPENDENT UPON WHICH ASSEMBLER PUA
)@@G@@ASS THIS IS @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$CTR*(6) EQU 1-G$CTR(6)            . SET UB
)@@G@@FLAG: ON IF ASSEMBLER PASS 1  @D@@@@G$CTR*(7) EQU      1-G$CTR(6)       UC
)@@G@@. ON IF PASS 2    @G@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , BRIEF                  . ON PASS UD
)@@G@@2, CLEAN UP THE LISTING @D@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , END                    . THUE
)@@G@@EN GET OUT  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. -------- PASS 1 ONLY BEYOND THIS POINT -UF
)@@G@@-------     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$AMPR*    EQU      &(5)=-2   UG
)@@G@@        . TRUE IF RELOCATION FUNC AVAILABLE     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO 1-UH
)@@G@@(P(0,1)='OLD PROGRAM') , G$JELLY . TRASH ILLEGAL MNEMONICS  @F@@@@      UI
)@@G@@    G$$CLD                      . DECLARE OUR 'CALL' PROC   @F@@@@      UJ
)@@G@@    G$RD$$D$  .                 . DECLARE THE READ$ PROCS   @[@@@@.     UK
)@@G@@@E@@@@FIXUP                                 . REMEMBER WHERE LC IS@I@@@@UL
)@@G@@           BRIEF                      . TRY SURPRESSING EXTRANEOUS OCTALUM

)@@G@@LER HAS BRIEF DIRECTIVE @F@@@@          RES       FIXUP-$           . MAUO

)@@G@@D FOR DUMMY PROCS @[@@@@.     @D@@@@P         PROC      *0,0            UQ

)@@G@@         END                          . END OF DUMMY INTERNAL PROC DEFN US
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@          END                         . END DEFN OF MAUT
)@@G@@STER MAGIC PROC   @ @@@@/. ***** DIAGNOSTICS *****    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@UU
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@. FIELDS IN ERROR MESSAGE FORM ARE: @C@@@@.    FIELD 1: TYPEUV
)@@G@@ OF CURRENTLY ACTIVE BLOCK    @E@@@@.             TYPES ARE 1=>BEGIN, 2=UW
)@@G@@>IF, 3=>CASE, 4=>REPEAT @A@@@@.          2: CURRENT NESTING DEPTH @F@@@@UX
)@@G@@.          3: MESSAGE CLASS (0=LOCN CTR, 1=SYNTAX, 2=STRUCTURE)   @^@@@@UY
)@@G@@.          4: ERROR TYPE@ @@@@.          5: ERROR SUBTYPE   @[@@@@.     UZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@. LOCATION COUNTER ERRORS (MESSAGE CLASS=0) ARE SIGNALLED WHEN    VA
)@@G@@@E@@@@. SOME CODE PREVIOUS TO THE POINT OF THE MESSAGE GENERATES  @F@@@@VB
)@@G@@. A DIFFERENT NUMBER OF INSTRUCTIONS ON ASSEMBLER PASSES ONE AND  @F@@@@VC
)@@G@@. TWO (ASSEMBLER D-FLAG). AT THE POINT OF DETECTION, STRUC$ WILL  @F@@@@VD
)@@G@@. ATTEMPT TO FORESTALL SPURIOUS ERRORS OF THIS TYPE IN THE CODE   @G@@@@VE
)@@G@@. WHICH FOLLOWS BY FORCING THE LOCATION COUNTER TO WHAT IT BELIEVES     VF
)@@G@@@F@@@@. THE CORRECT VALUE SHOULD BE. THE ERROR TYPE AND SUBTYPE FIELDS  VG
)@@G@@@F@@@@. ARE INTERNAL SERIAL NUMBERS, AND HAVE NO SPECIAL SIGNIFICANCE.  VH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. FOR SYNTAX ERRORS (MESSAGE CLASS=1), ERROR TYPES ANDVI
)@@G@@ SUBTYPES ARE:    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.    1,X => ERROR IN SPECIFICATION OVJ
)@@G@@F TEST@C@@@@.     ,01      UNRECOGNIZEABLE TYPE OF TEST     @B@@@@.     VK
)@@G@@,02      UNRECOGNIZEABLE KEYWORD    @B@@@@.    2,X => ERROR IN <VARY> SPVL
)@@G@@ECIFICATION @C@@@@.     ,01      OFFSET REQUIRES IMMEDIATE 'BY'   @E@@@@VM
)@@G@@.     ,02      LOOKFOR FORMAT REQUIRES 'BY' SPECIFICATION   @D@@@@.     VN
)@@G@@,03      REQUIRED FROM, TO, OR BY SPEC MISSING  @E@@@@.     ,04      LOOVO
)@@G@@P CONTROL VARIABLE PASSES THROUGH ZERO    @E@@@@.     ,05      SIGN OF BVP
)@@G@@Y CONFLICTS WITH SIGN OF TO-FROM    @F@@@@.     ,06      EXPLICIT SENSE VQ
)@@G@@(UP/DOWN) CONFLICTS WITH BY, TO-FROM@D@@@@.     ,07      REQUIRED 'BY' SVR
)@@G@@PECIFICATION NOT GIVEN  @C@@@@.     ,010     BAD KEYWORD FOLLOWING 'LOOKVS
)@@G@@FOR'  @ @@@@.    3,X => PARAMETER ERROR   @D@@@@.     ,01      CASEREGISVT
)@@G@@TER NOT OVERLAPPED (A0-A3)    @D@@@@.     ,02      REQUIRED REGISTER SPEVU
)@@G@@CIFICATION MISSING@D@@@@.     ,03      INCORRECT NUMBER OF FIELDS ON 'IFVV
)@@G@@'     @D@@@@.     ,04      MISSING 'WHEN' ON ESCAPE STATEMENT     @F@@@@VW
)@@G@@.     ,05      MINIMUM SPECIFIED CASE NOT ZERO (CALLING OPTION)   @F@@@@VX
)@@G@@.     ,06      ALL CASE VALUES NOT SPECIFIED (CALLING OPTION)     @[@@@@VY
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. FOR STRUCTURE ERRORS (MESSAGE CLASS=2) , TYPES AND SUBTYPEVZ
)@@G@@S ARE:@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.    1,X => NESTING ERROR     @F@@@@.     ,01   WA
)@@G@@   TOO MANY OR TOO FEW END STATMENTS IN PREVIOUS BLOCK@F@@@@.     ,02   WB
)@@G@@   MISSING END IN PREVIOUS BLOCK MAY CAUSE D-FLAGS    @E@@@@.     ,03   WC
)@@G@@   STATEMENT CANNOT APPEAR IN CURRENT BLOCK TYPE@F@@@@.              EITWD
)@@G@@HER THE END STATEMENT FOR THE PREVIOUS BLOCK OR @G@@@@.              THEWE
)@@G@@ START STATEMENT FOR THE CURRENT BLOCK IS MISSING     @D@@@@.    2,X => WF
)@@G@@INCONSISTENT LOGIC (STATEMENTS OR FIELDS) @G@@@@.     ,01      ESCAPE INWG
)@@G@@VALID IF BOTH WHILE/LOOKFOR AND UNTIL ARE GIVEN @E@@@@.     ,02      OTHWH
)@@G@@ERWISE STMNT MEANINGLESS, NO ESCAPE GIVEN @F@@@@.     ,03      ATEND UNRWI
)@@G@@EACHABLE, NO TESTS APPEARED ON REPEAT     @F@@@@.     ,05      NOFIND COWJ
)@@G@@DE ILLEGAL WITH CALLING OPTION (CASE)     @ @@@@.    3,X => MISCELLANEOUWK
)@@G@@S     @E@@@@.     ,01      ATTEMPT TO CHANGE LOCATION COUNTERS WITHIN   WL
)@@G@@@F@@@@.              A BLOCK. BLOCKS MUST BE WHOLLY CONTAINED WITHIN    WM
)@@G@@@F@@@@.              A SINGLE BANK. SWITCHING BETWEEN BANKS MUST BE     WN
)@@G@@@D@@@@.              ACCOMPLISHED VIA A SUBROUTINE CALL     @[@@@@.     WO
)@@G@@@#@@@@          DEF     @H@@@@G$ERFO    FORM      3,6,3,12,12     . A DIWP
)@@G@@STINCTIVE FORM FOR ERROR MESSAGES   @#@@@@P       PROC   *2 @[@@@@.     WQ
)@@G@@@^@@@@G$$GFL*   NAME      2   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. FORCE DEFINITION OF PRWR
)@@G@@OC NEEDED TO FORCE G-FLAGS    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          PROC    @#@@@@WS
)@@G@@G$$FRG**  NAME    @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     WT
)@@G@@@C@@@@. NOW G-FLAG GENERATOR ACTUALLY DOES ITS THING  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@WU
)@@G@@ GO G$$FRG          . LEAP TO OTHER PROC, WHICH LEAPS TO G$$DIA   @[@@@@WV
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$IFL*  NAME       3                 . THIS ENTWW
)@@G@@RY FOR TRULY INVALID INSTRUCTION    @H@@@@          RES       1         WX
)@@G@@        . WHICH ACTUALLY TAKES SPACE IN THE CODE@C@@@@ GO G$$DIA        WY

)@@G@@$DIA  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$$DFL*  NAME       0   @E@@@@G$DFLG****        XB

)@@G@@$             . THEN FORCE LC BACK INTO PHASE   @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @[@@@@XD
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@G$$TFL*  NAME       4                 . GENERATE A T-FLAG   XE
)@@G@@@A@@@@A       EQU    + (I$ 0,0,0,0,077,0) @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOW WE GENXF
)@@G@@ERATE THE MESSAGES. TO AVOID EXTRANEOUS D-FLAGS ON    @E@@@@. THE USER'SXG
)@@G@@ LISTING, NEGATIVE RES'S ARE USED TO INSURE THAT@F@@@@. THE MESSAGES DO XH
)@@G@@NOT OCCUPY ANY SPACE IN THE PROGRAM'S ADDRESS   @F@@@@. SPACE. TO INSUREXI
)@@G@@ THAT THE MESSAGE DOES NOT GO UNNOTICED, WE     @G@@@@. TRASH ON THE LASXJ
)@@G@@T WORD OF GENERATED USER CODE, MAKING IT AN IOPR.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@XK
)@@G@@. TO AVOID SURPRESSION IF BRIEF MODE IS ON, THE DIAGNOSTIC  @D@@@@. MESSXL
)@@G@@AGE SENTINAL WORD IS THE 1ST ONE GENERATED.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$DIAXM
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . DIAGNOSTIC PRINTOUT STARTS HERE @H@@@@XN
)@@G@@          RES       -1                . GET RID OF USER'S LAST INSTRUCTIXO
)@@G@@ON    @F@@@@K         EQU       1+(P(0,0)=0)      . SPEC TO FIND FLAGS IXP

)@@G@@          UNLIST  @F@@@@          G$$IFLAG                    . MARK THIXS

)@@G@@NTINAL AND IFLAG WORD   @H@@@@          +0                          . FOXU
)@@G@@RCE PROG TO IOPR IF ITS EXECUTED    @#@@@@          LIST    @E@@@@      XV
)@@G@@    END                         . OF DIAGNOSTIC PROCS @C@@@@/.    ******XW
)@@G@@** PROGRAM DEFINITION GROUP ********@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. ARRAY USAGE BY BXX
)@@G@@EGIN BLOCKS:@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    G$LABL(K,1) ENTRY POINT TO BLOCK (=PKXY

)@@G@@@E@@@@.             3) ADDR OF GENERATED REG SAVE AREA (IF ANY)   @C@@@@YA
