)@@G@@  2) NUMBER OF SAVED REGISTERS@C@@@@.             2,N) AXR$ VALUE OF N'TYD
)@@G@@H SAVED REG @C@@@@.             3) BLOCK TYPE (MAINPROG, ETC.)    @[@@@@YE
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.     YF
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               *       YG
)@@G@@    BEGIN             * @C@@@@.               *                         YH
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     YI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@           DEF    @H@@@@F          FUNC   YJ
)@@G@@                    . ----- UTILITY FUNC USED IN SORTING    @#@@@@G$$INCYK
)@@G@@*    NAME   @D@@@@III*(1)    EQU              III(1)+1  . BUMP COUNTER  YL
)@@G@@@E@@@@           END              III(1)    . RETURN NEW VALUE    @[@@@@YM
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *3 @]@@@@BEGIN*  NAME@H@@@@ DO 1-YN
)@@G@@(G$CTR(5)=0) , G$$GFL 1,1               . REQUIRE NESTING DEPTH ZERO    YO
)@@G@@@F@@@@M         EQU       1                 . FORCE NEW NESTING DEPTH   YP
)@@G@@@D@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU  M                      . THEN SAVE IT  @F@@@@ DO 1-YQ
)@@G@@(G$CTR(2)=0) , G$$GFL 1,2               . REQUIRE NO FLOAT  @[@@@@.     YR
)@@G@@@F@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SERIAL NUMBER   YS
)@@G@@@D@@@@G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @D@@@@G$TYPEYT
)@@G@@*(M) EQU      1                 . SET BLOCK TYPE@E@@@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU    YU
)@@G@@  K                 . SAVE SERIAL NUMBER  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@T         EQYV
)@@G@@U  P(1,1)+(P(1)=0)*MAINPROGRAM . GET PROG TYPE  @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU TYW
)@@G@@                     . AND REMEMBER IT    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. ALLOW 'NOSYX
)@@G@@AVE' TO DEFAULT TO SUBFIELD 2 @[@@@@.     @H@@@@NOSDEF    EQU       (T=SYY
)@@G@@UBROUTINE)**(P(1)=2)**(P(1,2)=NOSAVE) . NOSAVE DEFAULT@E@@@@ DO NOSDEF ,YZ
)@@G@@P(1,3) EQU NOSAVE         . FORCE THIRD FIELD   @D@@@@ DO NOSDEF ,P(1,2)ZA
)@@G@@ EQU 0              . CLEAR REGISTER@G@@@@ DO NOSDEF ,P(1)   EQU 3      ZB
)@@G@@        . NOW NOTE THERE ARE 3 SUBFIELDS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7)ZC
)@@G@@ , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,1)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)      ZD
)@@G@@              . SAVE ENTRY POINT TO BLOK  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          REZE
)@@G@@S       G$CTR(6)          . ALLOW ZERO AS A FLAG@E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU     ZF
)@@G@@  -G$CTR(7)         . SET GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO T=CYCLICZG
)@@G@@ , END                 . SINCE CYCLICS NEVER EXIT, WE'RE DONE     @G@@@@ZH
)@@G@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , +0D               . IF CONTING, GENERATE PACKET     ZI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.              HANDLE EXITS WHICH SIGNAL THE EXEC (MAIZJ
)@@G@@N/CONTINGENCY)    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@GI      EQU    (P(1,1)=SIGNAL)+2*(P(ZK
)@@G@@2,1)=SIGNAL)+3*(P(3,1)=SIGNAL)@F@@@@. SIGNAL XREG IS FLAG, IF NONE (<0),ZL
)@@G@@ THEN EXIT WILL BE 'NORMAL'   @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU (GI>0)*(P(1,2)+(P(1ZM
)@@G@@)<2)*A0)-(GI=0) . SET SIGNAL XREG   @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,4) EQU (T=CONTINGENCZN
)@@G@@Y)*G$LABL(K,1)-(T=SUBROUTINE) . DEFAULT   @C@@@@ DO (T=EXECSUB)**(P(1)=1ZO
)@@G@@) ,P*(1,2) EQU DISP     @G@@@@ DO T=EXECSUB ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU P(1,2) . JZP
)@@G@@UMPTARGET FOR EXEC ROUTINES   @G@@@@ DO GI>0 , DO P(GI)>1 ,G$LABL*(K,4) ZQ
)@@G@@EQU ;  UNLESS USER PROVIDED A USPEC @G@@@@        +      (I$ 0,P(GI,4),,ZR
)@@G@@P(GI,3),2*P(GI,*3)+P(GI,*2),P(GI,2) )     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.           ZS
)@@G@@   HANDLE REGISTER SAVE REQUESTS    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (T=SUBROUTINE)ZT
)@@G@@**(P(1,2)=0) ,P(1,2) EQU X11 . DEFAULT LINKREG TO X11 @H@@@@SII     EQU ZU
)@@G@@   ((P(1,1)=STACK)++(P(1,1)=SAVE))+; FIND REG SAVE CONTROL FIELD  @G@@@@ZV
)@@G@@2*((P(2,1)=STACK)++(P(2,1)=SAVE))+3*((P(3,1)=STACK)++(P(3,1)=SAVE))     ZW
)@@G@@@H@@@@SI      EQU    SII+((SII=0)**(T=SUBROUTINE)) . IF NONE**SUBROUTINEZX
)@@G@@, SET 1     @E@@@@ DO SI=0 ,  END                       . IF NONE, WE'REZY
)@@G@@ DONE @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ST      EQU    P(SI,1)                . ELSE GETZZ
)@@G@@ TYPE (SAVE/STACK/SUBROUTINE) @G@@@@NOLINK    EQU       P(1,3)=NOSAVE   AA
)@@G@@  . ON=> INHIBIT SAVE OF LINKREG    @G@@@@ DO NOLINK ,P(1,2) EQU -P(1,2)AB
)@@G@@        . IF NOT SAVING, JUST REMEMBER IT @G@@@@ DO NOLINK ,P(1) EQU +2 AC
)@@G@@              . AND FORCE THE NOSAVE SPEC AWAY  @H@@@@KLX     EQU    P(SAD
)@@G@@I)-2*(ST=STACK)     . INDEX OF LAST REG TO EXPLICITLY SAVE  @G@@@@I DO KAE
)@@G@@LX ,RSAV(P(SI,I+1)) EQU 1 . MARK ALL REGS REQUESTED EXPLICITLY    @H@@@@AF
)@@G@@III(1)     EQU      1       . INIT INCREMENTATION CTR: 1ST SUBFIELD WILLAG
)@@G@@ BE 2 @F@@@@I DO 128 , DO RSAV(I) ,P(SI,G$$INC(1)) EQU I . SORT EXPLICITAH
)@@G@@ REGS @H@@@@ DO KLX<P(SI) , DO 1-(P(SI,KLX+1)=POINTER) , G$$EFL 3,2 . REAI
)@@G@@QUIRE REG SPEC    @F@@@@SEX     EQU    1-(ST=SUBROUTINE)      . ON IF EXAJ
)@@G@@PLICIT SAVE GIVEN @H@@@@SLI     EQU    T=SUBROUTINE           . ON IF LIAK
)@@G@@NKREG IS TO BE REMEMBERED     @G@@@@ DO SEX**SLI ,P(SI,KLX+1) EQU P(1,2)AL
)@@G@@  . FORCE LINKREG INTO SAVE LIST    @G@@@@KLR     EQU    KLX+(SEX**SLI) AM
)@@G@@        . INDEX OF LAST REG TO REMEMBER   @H@@@@I DO     KLR-1 ,G$FLAG*(AN
)@@G@@K,2,I) EQU +P(SI,I+1) . REMEMBER WHATS BEING SAVED    @G@@@@KL        EQAO
)@@G@@U       KLR-NOLINK        . NUMBER TO ACTUALLY PUT IN CORE  @I@@@@I DO KAP
)@@G@@L-1 ,FNC(I) EQU 1+5*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+3*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)>A15) . SA, SX, SAQ
)@@G@@R     @G@@@@I DO KL-1 ,AFL(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-A0*(FNC(I)=1)-(R1-1)*(FNAR
)@@G@@C(I)=4)     @H@@@@I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)=1 ,FNC(I) EQU (FNC(I-1)<071)* ; AS
)@@G@@FOR SINGLE STORE A'S    @F@@@@  (070*(AFL(I+1)=(AFL(I)+1))+1) . DOUBLE SAT
)@@G@@TORE CONTIGUOUS AREGS   @G@@@@ DO ST=STACK , GO G$$B10              . IFAU
)@@G@@ STACKING, GO DO SPECIAL STUFF@G@@@@IC      EQU    &                    AV
)@@G@@  . PRESERVE USER'S LOCATION COUNTER@F@@@@$(G$LCTR(1))                  AW
)@@G@@        . AND ESTABLISH OUR OWN     @H@@@@ DO (&=IC)**(KL>1) , I$ 074,04AX
)@@G@@,,,,$+KL        . IF SAME, LEAP AROUND THE RES  @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) RES KAY
)@@G@@L-1                   . SET ASIDE SAVE SPACE    @E@@@@$(IC)             AZ
)@@G@@                    . RESTORE USER'S IC   @H@@@@I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)>0 BA
)@@G@@, I$ FNC(I),012*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LABL(K,3)+I-1 @G@@@@ DO 1 , END BB
)@@G@@                          . IF NOT STACKING, WE'RE DONE     @[@@@@.     BC
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$$B10  NAME                          . HANDLE STACKING HERE@F@@@@BD
)@@G@@OI      EQU    P(SI+1,1)=OFFSET       . ON IF OFFSET SPECIFIED    @H@@@@BE
)@@G@@AI      EQU    P(SI,*KLX+2)           . ON TO AUTO-INCREMENT STACK POINTBF
)@@G@@ER    @G@@@@OSV     EQU    + (I$ 0,OI*P(SI+1,3),0,P(SI,KLX+2),2*AI,OI*P(BG
)@@G@@SI+1,2))    @C@@@@I DO  KL-1 , S G$FLAG(K,2,I),OSV+(1-AI)*(I-1)   @F@@@@BH
)@@G@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU 0-OSV                  . REMEMBER OFFSET FLAGS   @]@@@@BI
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               **************BJ
)@@G@@***************** @C@@@@.               *                             * BK
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               *          ENDBEG             * @C@@@@.           BL
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               **************BM
)@@G@@***************** @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@BN
)@@G@@ENDBEG*  NAME     @G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET NESTBO
)@@G@@ING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @H@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GEBP
)@@G@@T OVERALL BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER     @F@@@@ DO 1-(M=1) , G$$GFL 1,1      BQ
)@@G@@     . BE SURE NESTING LEVEL IS OK  @D@@@@ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=1) , G$$GFL 1BR
)@@G@@,3 . AND BLOCK TYPE     @I@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       0                 . FOBS
)@@G@@RCE NESTING LEVEL FOR SUBSEQUENT CODE     @E@@@@ DO 1-(G$CTR(2)=-G$CTR(7BT
)@@G@@)) , G$$GFL 1,2 . DIAGNOSE BAD FLOAT@E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       0         BU
)@@G@@        . AND FORCE IT CORRECT@E@@@@T         EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)     BV
)@@G@@  . GET BEGIN BLOCK TYPE@[@@@@.     @E@@@@          RES       -G$CTR(6) BW
)@@G@@        . FIXUP FOR FLAGS     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,2)=$) BX
)@@G@@, G$$DFL G$LABL(K,2)    @D@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)                    . MARK ENDBY
)@@G@@ OF BLOCK   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO T=CYCLIC , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,1) . BZ
)@@G@@IF CYCLIC, LOOP BACK    @D@@@@ DO T=CYCLIC , END                 . AND TCA
)@@G@@HAT'S ALL   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. IF ANY REGS WERE SAVED, RESTORE THEM    CB
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,2)=0 , GO G$$X01 @H@@@@NRR     EQU    +G$CC
)@@G@@FLAG(K,2)              . GET NO OF REGISTERS REMEMBERED     @G@@@@LINK(1CD
)@@G@@)   EQU       G$FLAG(K,2,NRR)   . LINK IS ALWAYS THE LAST ONE     @H@@@@CE
)@@G@@NR        EQU       NRR-(LINK(1)<0)   . FUDGE IN CASE WE DIDN'T SAVE LINCF
)@@G@@K     @G@@@@ DO NRR>NR ,LINK(1) EQU -LINK(1)      . THEN GET REAL VALUE CG
)@@G@@OF LINK     @G@@@@I DO NR ,FNC(I) EQU 010+017*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+013*(G$CH
)@@G@@FLAG(K,2,I)>A15)  @G@@@@I DO NR ,AFL(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-A0*(FNC(I)=010CI
)@@G@@)-(R1-1)*(FNC(I)=023)   @H@@@@I DO NR , DO FNC(I)=010 ,FNC(I) EQU (FNC(ICJ
)@@G@@-1)<071)* ; FOR SINGLE LOAD A'S     @F@@@@  (061*(AFL(I+1)=(AFL(I)+1))+0CK
)@@G@@10) . DOUBLE LOAD CONTIGUOUS AREGS  @F@@@@SR      EQU    0-G$LABL(K,3)  CL
)@@G@@          . GET STACKREG/SAVE FLAG  @ @@@@ DO 1-(SR>0) ,I DO NR , ;     CM
)@@G@@@G@@@@  DO FNC(I)>0 , I$ FNC(I),013*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LABL(K,3)+I-CN
)@@G@@1     @F@@@@ DO 1-(SR>0) , GO G$$X01              . IF NOT STACKED, WE'RCO
)@@G@@E DONE@#@@@@. HANDLE STACKING @F@@@@INC     EQU    SR**0400000          CP
)@@G@@  . ISOLATE AUTO-INCREMENT BIT@F@@@@XSR     EQU    (017000000**SR)*/4   CQ
)@@G@@  . MOVE XREG INTO AREG FIELD @G@@@@ DO INC>0 , ANX,U 0,NR+((017000000**CR
)@@G@@SR)*/4) . BACK UP STACK POINTER     @F@@@@I DO     NR , L G$FLAG(K,2,I),CS
)@@G@@(SR**007777177777)+I-1 . AND UNSTACK@F@@@@G$$X01  NAME                  CT
)@@G@@        . END OF REG RESTORATION    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO T=SUBROUTINE ,CU
)@@G@@ I$ 074,04,,LINK(1),,0 . J 0,LINK   @B@@@@ DO T=EXECSUB , I$ 074,04,,,G$CV
)@@G@@LABL(K,4)   @B@@@@ DO (T=SUBROUTINE)++(T=EXECSUB) , END     @[@@@@.     CW
)@@G@@@B@@@@. PROCESS MAINPROGS AND CONTINGENCIES     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@XREG  CX
)@@G@@  EQU    G$FLAG(K,1)            . GET EXIT TYPE (NORMAL OR SIGNAL)@G@@@@CY
)@@G@@ DO XREG>0 , GO G$$X02                . IF EXCEPTION, GO PROCESS IT     CZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO T=MAINPROGRAM , ER 011            . NORMAL MAINPROGRAM EXIT ISDA
)@@G@@ EXIT$@E@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , SZ,H1 G$LABL(K,4) . CLEAR PACKET UPPER  DB
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . AND JUMP THRU PKT DC
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO 1 , END                           . THAT'S ALL FOR NORMAL EXITDD
)@@G@@S     @H@@@@G$$X02  NAME                          . HERE TO HANDLE EXITSDE
)@@G@@ WITH SIGNALLING  @F@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 051,H1,,,,G$LABL(K,4) . IDF
)@@G@@S UPPER (H1) ZERO @G@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . DG
)@@G@@YES, EXIT THRU PACKET   @G@@@@ DO 1-(G$LABL(K,4)<0) , I$ 027,,XREG,,,G$LDH
)@@G@@ABL(K,4) . LOAD FROM SIGNALLOC@F@@@@        I$     074,04,,XREG,,$+1    DI
)@@G@@  . JUMP INTO FOLLOWING TABLE @C@@@@        ER     011                  DJ
)@@G@@  . 0=EXIT$ @C@@@@        ER     040                    . 1=ERR$  @C@@@@DK
)@@G@@        ER     026                    . 2=EABT$ @C@@@@        ER     012DL
)@@G@@                    . 3=ABORT$@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     DM
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           DN
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *         SWITDO
)@@G@@CHTO            * @C@@@@.               *                             * DP
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@DQ
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@SWITCHTO*  NAME   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@DR
)@@G@@. NOTE: THIS FEATURE IS NO LONGER AVAILABLE BECAUSE OF@E@@@@. OPTIMIZATIDS
)@@G@@ON TECHNIQUES FOR THE OBJECT CODE. ANY BLOCK    @E@@@@. MUST BE WHOLLY GDT
)@@G@@ENERATED UNDER A SINGLE LOCATION COUNTER. @F@@@@. CONTINGENCY PROCESSINGDU
)@@G@@ IN A SEPERATE BANK MUST BE ACCOMPLISHED  @D@@@@. BY MEANS OF A SUBROUTIDV
)@@G@@NE CALL TO THE OTHER BANK.    @[@@@@.     @I@@@@          RES       1   DW
)@@G@@              . SPACE SO DIAGNOSTIC DOESN'T CREAM OLD US    @D@@@@      DX
)@@G@@    G$$GFL    3,1               . GIVE A WARNING@H@@@@          RES     DY
)@@G@@  -1                . ZAP THE IOPR SO THE PROGRAM WORKS     @G@@@@. NOTEDZ
)@@G@@ THAT WE SIMPLY IGNORE THE REQUEST FOR A LOCATION COUNTER CHANGE  @]@@@@EA
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               **************EB
)@@G@@***************** @C@@@@.               *                             * EC
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               *            CALL             * @C@@@@.           ED
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               **************EE
)@@G@@***************** @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          PROC      *0  EF
)@@G@@              . PROC TO DECLARE THE 'CALL' PROC @E@@@@. PREVENTS RLIB$ EEG
)@@G@@NTRY POINT CONFLICTS WITH COBOL'S 'CALL'  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@G$$CLD*   NAEH
)@@G@@ME                        .   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *2 @B@@@@EI
)@@G@@CALL*** NAME                          .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@XREG    EQU EJ
)@@G@@   P(0,1)+(P(0,1)=0)*X11  . DEFAULT LINKREG TO X11    @G@@@@K DO     P(2EK
)@@G@@) , SZ P(2,K)             . CLEAR ALT EXIT SENTINALS, IF ANY@E@@@@      EL
)@@G@@  I$     074,013,XREG,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) @G@@@@K DO     P(2EM
)@@G@@) , SX XREG,P(2,K)        . SET ALT EXIT SENTINALS, IF ANY  @H@@@@      EN
)@@G@@    END                         . END OF THE ACTUAL 'CALL' PROC DEFN    EO
)@@G@@@G@@@@          END                         . END OF PROC WHICH DEFINES EP
)@@G@@'CALL'@C@@@@/.           ******    IF   GROUP    *******    @[@@@@.     EQ
)@@G@@@ @@@@. USE OF LABELS AND FLAGS --  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.     ER
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,1) EXPLICIT NOT FLAG     @E@@@@.                2) SIDE EFFECES
)@@G@@T AND 'IF' TEST INVERSION FLAG@B@@@@.                3) IMPLIED LINEITEMET
)@@G@@ FLAG @D@@@@.                4) FLOAT ADJUSTMENT CAUSED BY 'ELSE' @F@@@@EU
)@@G@@.                5) FLOAT CAUSED BY OPTIMIZATION OF 'IF' TEST     @B@@@@EV
)@@G@@.                6) COMPLEX CONDITION FLAG@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.       G$LAEW
)@@G@@BL(K,1) START ADDR OF TESTS AT 'IF' @E@@@@.                2) START ADDREX
)@@G@@ OF USER CODE IN 'IF' BLOCK   @D@@@@.                3) END ADDR OF CODEEY
)@@G@@ IN 'IF' BLOCK    @D@@@@.                4) START ADDR OF CODE IN 'ELSE'EZ
)@@G@@ BLOCK@D@@@@.                5) TARGET ADDR FOR EXIT FROM BLOCK   @[@@@@FA
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.     FB
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               *       FC
)@@G@@     IF               * @C@@@@.               *                         FD
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     FE
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *6 @]@@@@IF*     NAME@[@@@@.     @H@@@@LOOF      EQFF
)@@G@@U       (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=LOOKFOR) . CHECK FOR TABLE SEARCH FORMAT@^@@@@FG
)@@G@@ DO LOOF , GO G$$I05    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. ANALYZE SYNTAX SO WE KNOW IFFH
)@@G@@ THIS IS LINEITEM OR A BLOCK  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@L       EQU    P-1@B@@@@FI
)@@G@@L1      EQU    (P(L)=1)**(P(L,1)=THEN)    @B@@@@L2      EQU    (P(L-1)=1FJ
)@@G@@)**(P(L-1,1)=THEN)@E@@@@FLT     EQU    L1*L+L2*(L-1)  . FIELD OF 'THEN' FK
)@@G@@OR ZERO     @E@@@@THF     EQU    FLT+(FLT=0)*P  . IF NOT GIVEN, ASSUME IFL
)@@G@@T     @F@@@@IFNOT     EQU       (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=NOT) . SET EXPLICIT NOFM
)@@G@@T FLAG@H@@@@ DO 1-((THF=(IFNOT+2))++(THF=(IFNOT+4))) , G$$EFL 3,3 . CHECFN
)@@G@@K NO OF FIELDS    @F@@@@CXF       EQU       THF=(4+IFNOT)     . SET COMPFO
)@@G@@LEX CONDITION FLAG@C@@@@ DO P<(THF+2) , GO G$$I05 . GO DO NORMAL FORMAT FP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. LINEITEM FORMAT DOES NOT UPDATE NESTING ARRAYS- GETSFQ
)@@G@@ SPECIAL HANDLING @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          G$$TST    1+IFNOT,CXF,IFNOFR
)@@G@@T . GENERATE THE TEST   @E@@@@          +P(THF+1,1)                 . THFS
)@@G@@EN THE LINEITEM   @A@@@@   DO 1 , END       . AND THEN QUIT @[@@@@.     FT
)@@G@@@B@@@@. PROCESS NORMAL (NOT LINEITEM) IF --     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I05FU
)@@G@@    NAME    @H@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUFV
)@@G@@ENCE NO FOR THIS BLOCK  @F@@@@G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . ANFW
)@@G@@D UPDATE BLOCK COUNTER  @G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       G$CTR(5)+1        . BUFX
)@@G@@MP CURRENT BLOCK NESTING LEVEL@G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        FY
)@@G@@  . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@@G$TYPE*(M)          EQU       FZ
)@@G@@        2 . SET CURRENT BLOCKTYPE TO IF   @H@@@@G$SEQN*(M)          EQU GA
)@@G@@              K . AND REMEMBER ITS SEQUENCE NUMBER    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@GB
)@@G@@. ADJUST ALL LABELS FOR FLOAT @[@@@@.     @D@@@@G$LABL*(K,1) EQU G$LABL(GC
)@@G@@K,1)+G$CTR(2) . GLOBAL FLOAT  @E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(GD
)@@G@@K,5) . APPLY 'IF' FLOAT @F@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) EQU G$LABL(K,N+1)+GGE
)@@G@@$CTR(2) . GLOBAL+IF     @F@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+3) EQU G$LABL(K,N+3)+GGF
)@@G@@$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,4)     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@  DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(KGG
)@@G@@,1)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)   @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)                 . REMEMGH
)@@G@@BER START ADDR FOR OPTIMIZATION     @H@@@@ DO LOOF , GO G$$I10          GI
)@@G@@        . LOOKFOR TESTS GET SPECIAL HANDLING    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@NOGEN GJ
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(7)*(G$LABL(K,5)=G$LABL(K,1)) . ON TO SURPRESS ALL   GK
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU G$CTR(4)+NOGEN           . KEEP G$$TST'S COUNTER IN GL
)@@G@@PHASE @A@@@@ DO NOGEN , END     . STOP IF NO MO @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAGGM
)@@G@@*(K,1) EQU IFNOT            . SAVE NOT FLAG FOR OPTIMIZER   @E@@@@G$FLAGGN
)@@G@@*(K,6) EQU CXF              . AND ALSO COMPLEX FLAG   @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6)GO
)@@G@@ , G$$SVA              . PASS 1: SAVE ARGS FOR RECALL AT ENDIF    @[@@@@GP
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@RVF       EQU       IFNOT--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL REVERSAGQ
)@@G@@L FLAG@F@@@@LIG       EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)     . SET IMPLIED LINEITEM FGR
)@@G@@LAG   @G@@@@ DO 1-LIG ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF G$LABL(K,4)  . GENERATEGS
)@@G@@ THE TEST   @H@@@@ DO LIG  ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF      . GENERATE LIGT
)@@G@@NE ITEM FORMAT TEST(S)  @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU SIDE(1)               . RGU
)@@G@@EMEMBER IF TEST HAS SIDE EFFECTS    @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)                  GV
)@@G@@. REMEMBER START OF USER CODE FOR OPTIMIZA@#@@@@ DO 1 , END .     @[@@@@GW
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. HANDLE 'LOOKFOR' TESTS, WHICH GENERATE 1100 SERIES SEARCH GX
)@@G@@INSTRUCTIONS@[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I10    NAME    @A@@@@ DO 1-(P(3,1)=VARYGY
)@@G@@) , G$$EFL 2,010 .@I@@@@VI        EQU       3                 . 'VARY' SGZ
)@@G@@PECIFICATION MUST FOLLOW 'LOOKFO    @E@@@@P(3,1)    EQU       LOOKFOR   HA
)@@G@@        . FORCE THE KEYWORD   @G@@@@KW(1)     EQU       LOOKFOR         HB
)@@G@@  . IN ALL PLACES ITS EXPECTED TO BE@G@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)                  HC
)@@G@@         . GUARANTEE NON-EMPTY 'IF' CLAUSE@H@@@@          G$$LAN        HD
)@@G@@              . ANALYZE SPECS, LOAD REGS IF NECESSARY @G@@@@          G$HE
)@@G@@$LGE    3,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,4),1 . GEN CODE FOR SEARCH   @F@@@@G$CTR*HF
)@@G@@(3) EQU G$CTR(3)+G$CTR(6)       . PRETEND WE SAVED THE ARGS @[@@@@.     HG
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ********HH
)@@G@@*********************** @C@@@@.               *                         HI
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               *           ELSE              * @C@@@@.     HJ
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               ********HK
)@@G@@*********************** @[@@@@.     @#@@@@        PROC   *0 @]@@@@ELSE* HL
)@@G@@  NAME@F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING HM
)@@G@@LEVEL @F@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GET SEQ NUM FOR THISHN
)@@G@@ BLOCK@F@@@@ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=2) , G$$GFL 1,3          . CATCH NESTING ERHO
)@@G@@RORS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,3)=$) , G$$DFL G$LHP
)@@G@@ABL(K,3) .  @B@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)     . MARK END OF 'IF' CLAUSE@F@@@@ DO G$HQ
)@@G@@LABL(K,2)=$ , END . EMPTY 'IF' => IGNORE ELSE COMPLETELY    @[@@@@.     HR
)@@G@@@G@@@@     DO G$FLAG(K,4)=0 , I$     074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,5) . LEAP TO ENDHS
)@@G@@I     @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,4) . SET ELSE FLOAT FOR CODEHT
)@@G@@ BELOW@D@@@@G$LABL*(K,4)          . MARK START OF 'ELSE' USER CODE@]@@@@HU
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               **************HV
)@@G@@***************** @C@@@@.               *                             * HW
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               *           ENDIF             * @C@@@@.           HX
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               **************HY
)@@G@@***************** @[@@@@.     @#@@@@        PROC   *0 @]@@@@ENDIF*  NAMEHZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL IA
)@@G@@@G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLIB
)@@G@@OCK   @F@@@@ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=2) , G$$GFL 1,3          . CATCH NESTING ERIC
)@@G@@RORS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,5)=$) , G$$DFL G$LID
)@@G@@ABL(K,5)    @D@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)                  . MARK END OF BLOCK     IE
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       M-1               . STEP NESTING BACK ONE LEVEIF
)@@G@@L     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. RESTORE GLOBAL FLOAT FOR FOLLOWING BLOX (EFFECIG
)@@G@@TIVE ON PASS 2 ONLY)    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(7)*(G$CTR(IH
)@@G@@2)-G$FLAG(K,5)-G$FLAG(K,4)) . @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RII
)@@G@@E DONE AT THIS POINT    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.   ***** PASS 1 ONLY BEYOND TIJ
)@@G@@HIS POINT *****   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$CTR*(3) EQU G$CTR(3)-1            IK
)@@G@@  . ADJUST ARGSAVE STACK POINTER    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. TABULATE FLOAT FIL
)@@G@@OR SURPRESSED ELSE, IF ANY    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,4) EQU -((G$LAIM
)@@G@@BL(K,3)>0)**(G$LABL(K,4)=$)) . 'ELSE' FLOAT     @G@@@@          RES     IN
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,4)     . APPLY ELSFLOAT FOR SUCCEEDING CODE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@IO
)@@G@@. CHECK FOR SURPRESSION OF EVERYTHING (NO CODE AND NO SIDE EFFECTS)     IP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO ($>G$LABL(K,2))++G$FLAG(K,2) , GO G$$I20 . IF NOT,IQ
)@@G@@ GO CHECK OPTIMIZATION  @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2) .IR
)@@G@@ TURN OFF 'IF'    @F@@@@          RES       G$LABL(K,1)-$   . ADJUST L.CIS
)@@G@@. APPROPRIATELY   @C@@@@  DO 1 , END        . AND TERMINATE GRACEFULLY  IT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. CHECK FOR POSSIBLE OPTIMIZATION OF THE INITIAL TEST IU
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I20    NAME    @E@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,4)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4IV
)@@G@@) . IF NO ELSE, PUT IT HERE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU G$LABL(IW
)@@G@@K,3)=G$LABL(K,2) . NO 'IF' CLAUSE =>INVERT@D@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU ($-G$LAIX
)@@G@@BL(K,2))=1 . IMPLIED LINEITEM @F@@@@ DO 1-(G$FLAG(K,2)++G$FLAG(K,3)) , EIY
)@@G@@ND . DONE IF NO OPTIMIZATION  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. WE'RE GOING TO OPTIMIZIZ
)@@G@@E THE JUMP WHEN WE GET BACK THERE ON PASS 2     @F@@@@. TO INSURE THAT LJA
)@@G@@ABELS BELOW THIS POINT ARE OK, WE MUST PERFORCE @E@@@@. DO A TRIAL GENERJB
)@@G@@ATION OF THE MODIFIED TEST SO WE KNOW     @G@@@@. HOW MANY INSTRUCTIONS JC
)@@G@@IT WILL TAKE WHEN WE GEN IT BACK AT THE TOP     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@KK    JD
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(3)+1        . GET ARGSAVE INDEX OF MATCHING 'IF'    JE
)@@G@@@F@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +G$ARGS(KK,I,J)    JF
)@@G@@@A@@@@IFNOT     EQU       G$FLAG(K,1)     @F@@@@CXF       EQU       G$FLJG
)@@G@@AG(K,6)   . RETRIEVE COMPLEX CONDN FLAG   @F@@@@RVF       EQU       IFNOJH
)@@G@@T--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL REVERSAL FLAG@E@@@@START                 . JI
)@@G@@REMEMBER WHERE BEGINNING OF TEST WAS@D@@@@ DO 1-G$FLAG(K,3) , G$$TST 1+IJJ
)@@G@@FNOT,CXF,RVF $+10 .     @D@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)   , G$$TST 1+IFNOT,CXF,RVFJK
)@@G@@      .     @H@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)-1        . RESTORE INTERNJL
)@@G@@AL CTR USED BY G$$TST   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOW SET ADDRESS ADJUSTMENT FJM
)@@G@@LAGS SO PASS 2 WILL GEN PROPER CODE @[@@@@.     @G@@@@SIZE      EQU     JN
)@@G@@  G$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1) . SIZE OF ORIGINAL TEST     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5)JO
)@@G@@ EQU $-START-SIZE       . COMPUTE PASS 2 FLOAT  @H@@@@          RES     JP
)@@G@@  -SIZE            . COMPENSATE L.C. FOR CODE WHICH FOLLOWS @]@@@@      JQ
)@@G@@  END @B@@@@/.          ******** CASE GROUP  *********@[@@@@.     @[@@@@JR
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@. ARRAY USAGE IS --     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       G$FLAG(K,1JS
)@@G@@) TOTAL NUMBER OF CASE VALUES GIVEN @G@@@@.         ...    2) RUNNING TAJT
)@@G@@LLY: NUMBER OF VALUES ON PREVIOUS CASE    @C@@@@.         ...    3) INHIJU
)@@G@@BIT/CALL OPTION FLAG    @E@@@@.         ...    4,X) VALUE OF X'TH SPECIFJV
)@@G@@IED CASEVALUE     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       G$LABL(K,1) START ADDR OF USJW
)@@G@@ER NOFIND CODE    @C@@@@.         ...    2) END ADDR OF USER NOFIND CODEJX
)@@G@@@D@@@@.         ...    3) ULTIMATE EXIT ADDR FROM BLOCK     @E@@@@.     JY
)@@G@@    ...    4,X) JUMPTARGET ADDR FOR X'TH CASEVALUE    @E@@@@.         ..JZ
)@@G@@.    5) RUNNING LABEL: LAST JUMP TO CLOSE A CASE@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     KA
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           KB
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *          CASKC
)@@G@@ENTRY           * @C@@@@.               *                             * KD
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @B@@@@KE
)@@G@@. SYNTAX--     CASENTRY <AXREG>    OR...  @D@@@@.              CASENTRY KF
)@@G@@CALLING(,<LINK>) NAME(,<TAG>) @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROCKG
)@@G@@   *2 @B@@@@CASENTRY*  NAME                       .   @F@@@@K         EQKH
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUENCE NUM    @D@@@@G$CTR*(1) EQKI
)@@G@@U       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTKJ
)@@G@@R(5)+1        . NESTING LEVEL FOR THIS BLOCK    @E@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU     KK
)@@G@@  M                 . UPDATE THAT, TOO    @G@@@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU      K   KL
)@@G@@              . REMEMBER BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER  @F@@@@G$TYPE*(M) EQU    KM
)@@G@@  3                 . SET BLOCK TYPE TO CASE    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABLKN
)@@G@@*(K,0) EQU    G$LABL(K,0)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY GLOBAL FLOAT     @E@@@@ DO G$KO
)@@G@@CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,0)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,0)    @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,0)KP
)@@G@@                          . MARK START IN CASE WE'LL INHIBIT@[@@@@.     KQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@CALOPT    EQU       P(1,1)=CALLING    . ON IF CALL OPTION SPECIFIEKR
)@@G@@D     @E@@@@          RES       CALOPT*G$CTR(6) . ACCOUNT FOR THE LMJ   KS
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C10    NAME    @F@@@@ DO 1-G$CTR(7) , GO G$$C40    KT
)@@G@@       . ON PASS 1, SKIP THIS STUFF @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. ***** PASS 2 ONLKU
)@@G@@Y-- GENERATE CHECKING AND THE JUMPTABLE   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@ DO 1-CALOPTKV
)@@G@@ , ; IF NOT A SUBROUTINE CALL BLOCK @F@@@@ DO (P(1,1)<A0)++(P(1,1)>A3) ,KW
)@@G@@ G$$EFL 3,1 . DIE IF NOT OVERLAP REG@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. COMPUTE CHARACTEKX
)@@G@@RISTICS OF THE TABLE    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NUMCA     EQU       +G$FLAG(K,KY
)@@G@@1)      . NUMBER OF CASES GIVEN     @H@@@@CMAX(1)   EQU       0400000000KZ
)@@G@@000     . INIT MAX TO SMALLEST POSSIBLE NUMBER  @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$LA
)@@G@@FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MAX    @H@@@@CMIN(1LB
)@@G@@)   EQU       0377777777777     . INIT MIN TO LARGEST POSSIBLE NUMBER   LC
)@@G@@@H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)<CMIN(1) ,CMIN(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) .LD
)@@G@@ GET MIN    @D@@@@OFF     EQU    1-CMIN(1)              . SET OFFSET    LE
)@@G@@@G@@@@JTSIZ   EQU    CMAX(1)+OFF            . SET TOT TABLE SIZE=RANGE OLF
)@@G@@F VAL @E@@@@JTL       EQU       JTSIZ-CALOPT*(G$FLAG(K,4,1)=CMAX(1))    LG
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO CALOPT , DO 1-(CMIN(1)=0) , G$$EFL 3,5 . MIN VAL NOT ZERO     LH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. APPLY FLOATS TO LABELS BELONGING TO THIS BLOCK, SET LI
)@@G@@GLOBAL FLOAT@[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU    G$LABL(K,3)+G$CTR(2) .LJ
)@@G@@ LAST LABEL GETS ONLY GLOBAL FLOAT  @H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+(LK
)@@G@@1-G$FLAG(K,3))*(4*(1-CALOPT)+JTL)  . SET FLOAT  @E@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,LL
)@@G@@N) EQU G$LABL(K,N)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY IT    @G@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3) , END   LM
)@@G@@              . IF OPTIMIZED AWAY, QUIT HERE    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPLN
)@@G@@UTE CROSS REFERENCES NEEDED TO GENERATE THE JUMP TABLE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@LO
)@@G@@NFA(1)    EQU  G$LABL(K,3-2*(G$LABL(K,2)>G$LABL(K,1))) . NOFIND ADDR    LP
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO CALOPT ,NFA(1) EQU -1             . DON'T ALLOW FOR CALL OPTIOLQ
)@@G@@N     @I@@@@N DO JTSIZ ,JT(N) EQU NFA(1)            . INITIALIZE ALL JUMLR
)@@G@@P TARGETS TO NOFIND     @G@@@@L DO NUMCA ,JT(G$FLAG(K,4,L)+OFF) EQU G$LALS
)@@G@@BL(K,4,L)+G$CTR(2) . SET ADDRS@F@@@@ DO CALOPT ,N DO JTSIZ , DO JT(N)<0 LT
)@@G@@, G$$EFL 3,6 . MISSING CASES  @G@@@@N DO JTSIZ , DO JT(N)=G$CTR(2) ,JT(NLU
)@@G@@) EQU G$LABL(K,3) . VACUOUS CASES   @F@@@@OTLAD     EQU       G$LABL(K,3LV
)@@G@@)+1     . FOR OPTIMIZED LAST CASE   @H@@@@N DO JTSIZ , DO JT(N)=OTLAD ,JLW
)@@G@@T(N) EQU G$LABL(K,3) . FIX REDUNDANT CLOSURES   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. GEN LX
)@@G@@CODE TO INSURE THAT XREG VALUE IS IN RANGE OF TABLE   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@LY
)@@G@@ DO CALOPT , GO G$$C30                . NOT FOR CALL OPTION @F@@@@      LZ
)@@G@@  I$     054,017,P(1,1)-A0,,3*(CMAX(1)<-1),CMAX(1)+1 . TLE,X@F@@@@      MA
)@@G@@  I$     054,017,P(1,1)-A0,,3*(CMIN(1)<0),CMIN(1) . TLE,XU  @F@@@@      MB
)@@G@@  I$     074,04,,,,NFA(1)         . J NOFIND (NOT IN TABLE) @E@@@@      MC
)@@G@@  I$     074,04,,P(1,1),,$+OFF  . JUMP THRU TABLE     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@MD
)@@G@@. NOW GENERATE THE ACTUAL JUMP TABLE ITSELF     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C30ME
)@@G@@    NAME    @G@@@@LINK      EQU       X11+(P(1)>1)*(P(1,2)-X11) . LINK RMF
)@@G@@EG, DEFAULT=X11   @H@@@@ DO CALOPT , I$ 074,013,LINK,P(2,2),2*P(2,*2)+P(MG
)@@G@@2,*1),P(2,1) . LMJ TO SUBRTN  @F@@@@N DO JTL , I$ 074,04,,,,JT(N)       MH
)@@G@@. LEAP TO THE CORRECT PLACE   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. ***** PASS 1 LEAPS DIRMI
)@@G@@ECTLY HERE  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C40    NAME    @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU -MJ
)@@G@@CALOPT              . REMEMBER CALL OPTION, IF ANY    @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)MK
)@@G@@                          . MARK START OF NOFIND CODE, IF ANY     @F@@@@ML
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU 0                    . NO CASE STMNTS SEEN YET   @G@@@@MM
)@@G@@G$LABL*(K,4,0)                        . INITIALIZE LOCAL OPTIMIZATION   MN
)@@G@@@I@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU 0                    . NO VALUES ON NON-EXISTENT MO
)@@G@@PREVIOUS CASE     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     MP
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           MQ
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *           CAMR
)@@G@@SE              * @C@@@@.               *                             * MS
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@MT
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @F@@@@CASE*   NAME                        MU
)@@G@@  . SPECS--  <VALUE-LIST>     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        MV
)@@G@@  . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)       MW
)@@G@@  . GET SEQUENCE NUM OF THIS BLOCK  @E@@@@ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=3) , G$$GFL 1MX
)@@G@@,3      . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)>0 , END             MY
)@@G@@    . DONE IF OPTIMIZED AWAY  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@JJ      EQU    +G$FLAG(KMZ
)@@G@@,1)           . GET # OF CASEVALS SO FAR IN THIS GRP  @G@@@@ DO JJ=0 ,G$NA
)@@G@@LABL*(K,2)                . MARK END OF USER NOFIND CODE    @B@@@@ DO (JNB
)@@G@@J>0)++(G$FLAG(K,3)>-1) , GO G$$C60 .@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. SPECIAL STUFF FONC
)@@G@@R 1ST CASE WITH CALLING OPTION@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO $>G$LABL(K,1) , G$$GND
)@@G@@FL 2,5 . NO NOFIND ALLOWED FOR CALL OPTION@D@@@@MAX(1)    EQU       P(1)NE
)@@G@@              . INITIALIZE MAX@F@@@@N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)>MAX(1) ,MAX(1)NF
)@@G@@ EQU P(1,N) . FIND MAX VALUE  @F@@@@IMAX(1)   EQU       1               NG
)@@G@@  . INITIALIZE POSN OF MAXVAL @F@@@@N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)=MAX(1) ,IMAX(1NH
)@@G@@) EQU N . FIND POSN OF MAXVAL @E@@@@MTEMP     EQU       P(1,1)          NI
)@@G@@  . TEMP SAVE 1ST VALUE @E@@@@P(1,1)    EQU       MAX(1)            . FONJ
)@@G@@RCE IT TO MAX     @G@@@@P(1,IMAX(1)) EQU    MTEMP             . EXCHANGENK
)@@G@@ WITH PREVIOUS VALUE    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. CLOSE PREVIOUS CASE   @[@@@@NL
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@G$$C60    NAME    @H@@@@REDUN     EQU       $=G$LABL(K,3)   NM
)@@G@@  . ON=> CLOSURE HERE WOULD BE REDUNDANT  @G@@@@GOTSOM EQU $>G$LABL(K,4,NN
)@@G@@JJ)           . ON IF PRECEDING CASE HAD CODE   @F@@@@ DO GOTSOM**(1-REDNO
)@@G@@UN) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,3) . CLOSE LAST CASE@H@@@@ DO GOTSOM ,G$LABLNP
)@@G@@*(K,5)              . MARK START USERCODE FOR THIS CASE     @F@@@@G$CTR*NQ
)@@G@@(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)-REDUN    . IF SURPRESSED, NOTE FLOAT @D@@@@N DO (NR
)@@G@@1-GOTSOM)*G$FLAG(K,2) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+1-N) EQU 0@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. TABUNS
)@@G@@LATE PARAMETERS FOR THE PRESENT CASE@[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU JNT
)@@G@@J+P(1)              . UPDATE CASEVAL COUNT@I@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU +P(1)  NU
)@@G@@              . REMEMBER HOW MANY TBL ENTRIES WE'RE USI     @F@@@@N DO  NV
)@@G@@   P(1) ,G$FLAG*(K,4,JJ+N) EQU +P(1,N) . SAVE CASE VALUE(S) @F@@@@ DO G$NW
)@@G@@CTR(7) , DO G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)>0 , ; IF NOT OPTIMIZED AWAY ...@H@@@@  DO 1NX
)@@G@@-((G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)+G$CTR(2))=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)+G$CTR(2)     NY
)@@G@@@G@@@@N DO     P(1) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+N)      . SET OUR OWN JUMPTARGET ADDNZ
)@@G@@RESSES@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.     OA
)@@G@@          ******************************* @C@@@@.               *       OB
)@@G@@                      * @C@@@@.               *          ENDCASE        OC
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.     OD
)@@G@@          ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@OE
)@@G@@P       PROC   *0 @#@@@@ENDCASE*  NAME    @G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTOF
)@@G@@R(5)          . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@@K         EQU     OG
)@@G@@  G$SEQN(M)         . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO 1-(G$TYPOH
)@@G@@E(M)=3) , G$$GFL 1,3      . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPOI
)@@G@@UTE TABLE SIZE SO WE KNOW HOW MUCH FLOAT TO APPLY     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@OJ
)@@G@@CALOPT    EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)<0     . SET IF CASENTRY WITH CALLING OPTOK
)@@G@@ION   @F@@@@NUMCA     EQU       +G$FLAG(K,1)      . NUMBER OF CASES GIVEOL
)@@G@@N     @H@@@@CMAX(1)   EQU       0400000000000     . INIT MAX TO SMALLESTOM
)@@G@@ POSSIBLE NUMBER  @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EON
)@@G@@QU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MAX    @H@@@@CMIN(1)   EQU       0377777777777   OO
)@@G@@  . INIT MIN TO LARGEST POSSIBLE NUMBER   @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(KOP
)@@G@@,4,L)<CMIN(1) ,CMIN(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MIN    @G@@@@JTS(1)   EQUOQ
)@@G@@    CMAX(1)-CMIN(1)+1      . SET TOT TABLE SIZE=RANGE OF VAL@E@@@@ DO G$OR
)@@G@@FLAG(K,3)<0 ,JTS(1) EQU JTS(1)-(CMAX(1)=G$FLAG(K,4,1))@[@@@@.     @F@@@@OS
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU    G$LABL(K,0)=$     . SET INHIBIT FLAG (NO CODE)@G@@@@OT
)@@G@@REDUN     EQU       G$LABL(K,5)=$ . ON => LAST CASE CLOSURE REDUNDANT   OU
)@@G@@@I@@@@FLOAT     EQU       (1-G$FLAG(K,3))*(4*(1-CALOPT)+JTS(1)-REDUN) . OV
)@@G@@FLOAT FOR TABL    @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) , RES FLOAT           . ON PASS 1, OW
)@@G@@APPLY TO LC @G@@@@ DO G$CTR(7)   ,G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(2)-FLOAT . ON 2, TOX
)@@G@@O GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,3)=$) OY
)@@G@@, G$$DFL G$LABL(K,3)    @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)                          . MAOZ
)@@G@@RK ULTIMATE EXIT POINT FROM BLOCK   @G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       M-1       PA
)@@G@@        . UPDATE GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@        END PB
)@@G@@@B@@@@/.       ********* REPEAT GROUP ********* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     PC
)@@G@@@E@@@@.    THE ARRAY G$FLAG(K,X) IS USED TO KEEP FLAGS THROUGOUT  @E@@@@PD
)@@G@@.    THE SCOPE OF THE REPEAT BLOCK. FOR EACH X, THE FLAG IS:@[@@@@.     PE
)@@G@@@F@@@@.       1      INDEX OF 'VARY' FIELD ON SOURCE 'REPEAT' IMAGE     PF
)@@G@@@F@@@@.       2      ON IF THERE IS <LOOP CTL> CODE WHICH MUST APPEAR   PG
)@@G@@@D@@@@.              AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE LOOP     @E@@@@.     PH
)@@G@@  3      INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD IN SOURCE 'REPEAT' IMAGE @F@@@@.       4   PI
)@@G@@   INDEX OF 'WHILE' FIELD ON SOURCE 'REPEAT IMAGE     @B@@@@.       5   PJ
)@@G@@   FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL @C@@@@.       6      INDEX OF 'UNTIL' ON SPK
)@@G@@OURCE IMAGE @B@@@@.       7      SURPRESS EVERYTHING FLAG   @A@@@@.     PL
)@@G@@  8      ON=> 'LOOKFOR' FORMAT@C@@@@.       9      ON=> BOTTOM OF LOOP CPM
)@@G@@HECKING DONE@E@@@@.       .      FLAGS USED TO CONTROL POSITIONING AND FPN
)@@G@@LOAT: @D@@@@.      10      ON=> ENTRY CONDITION IS JUMP TO WHILE  @B@@@@PO
)@@G@@.      11      ON => SURPRESS WHILE AT TOP@B@@@@.      12      ON=> INVEPP
)@@G@@RT ESCAPE TEST    @E@@@@.      13      ON=> CLOSE ESCAPE CLAUSE (WITH JUPQ
)@@G@@MP TO EXIT) @G@@@@.      14      ON=> CLOSE OTHERWISE/UNTIL CLAUSE (WITHPR
)@@G@@ JUMP TO LOOP)    @C@@@@.      15      ON=> SURPRESS WHILE AT BOTTOM    PS
)@@G@@@C@@@@.      16      FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRESSED AT TOP@B@@@@.      17   PT
)@@G@@   FLOAT FOR INVERTED ESCAPE  @D@@@@.      18      FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRPU
)@@G@@ESSED AT BOTTOM   @E@@@@.      19      ON=> CODE IN LOOP WILL APPEAR BELPV
)@@G@@OW ESCAPE   @C@@@@.      20      GLOBAL FLOAT AT ENTRY TO BLOCK   @E@@@@PW
)@@G@@.      21      1+FLOAT FOR INITIAL JUMP FALLTHRU (0=>NONE)  @[@@@@.     PX
)@@G@@@E@@@@.    THE ARRAY G$LABL(K,X) IS USED TO LABEL VARIOUS CONTROL @D@@@@PY
)@@G@@.    POINTS IN THE GENERATED CODE.  VALUES OF X ARE:  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PZ
)@@G@@.       1      LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP WHILE TEST     @D@@@@.       2   QA
)@@G@@   LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE    @F@@@@.       3      START USEQB
)@@G@@R-SPECIFIED REPEATED CODE (TOP OF LOOP)   @G@@@@.       4      LOCATION QC
)@@G@@OF CONDITION TEST AT ESCAPE (0=>NO ESCAPE STMNT)@D@@@@.       5      STAQD
)@@G@@RT USER-SPECIFIED ESCAPE CLAUSE     @D@@@@.       6      START USER-SPECQE
)@@G@@IFIED OTHERWISE CODE    @D@@@@.       7      LOCATION OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP QF
)@@G@@WHILE TEST  @D@@@@.       8      LOCATION OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE QG
)@@G@@@C@@@@.       9      START USER-SPECIFIED ATEND CODE  @C@@@@.      10   QH
)@@G@@   ULTIMATE BLOCK EXIT TARGET ADDR  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THE QI
)@@G@@FOLLOWING ARCANE RULES ARE FOLLOWED IN POSITIONING THE VARIOUS    @ @@@@QJ
)@@G@@. CODE GENERATED FOR A LOOP:  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. 1) <UNTIL> CODE ALWAYSQK
)@@G@@ APPEARS AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE LOOP     @F@@@@.            SO WEQL
)@@G@@ CAN AVOID JUMPING AROUND IT AT LOOP ENTRY.     @B@@@@. 2) <VARY>  CODE QM
)@@G@@MOVES AROUND AS FOLLOWS:@G@@@@.        A)  IF THE SENSE (UP/DOWN) IS KNOQN
)@@G@@WN, THEN THE CODE IS PLACED   @G@@@@.            ACCORDING TO THE PREFERQO
)@@G@@ENCE OF THE LOOP INSTRUCTION, E.G.  @D@@@@.            JGD AT THE BOTTOMQP
)@@G@@, SEARCHES AT THE TOP.  @G@@@@.        B)  IF THE SENSE IS UNKNOWN, THE QQ
)@@G@@CODE APPEARS AT BOTH TOP AND  @F@@@@.            BOTTOM, WITH THE BRANCHQR
)@@G@@ SENSE APPROPRIATELY INVERTED.@G@@@@.            IMMEDIATELY BEFORE THE QS
)@@G@@PRIMARY CODE (BOTTOM), A SIGN TEST  @G@@@@.            IS INSERTED WHICHQT
)@@G@@ DETERMINES WHICH OF THE TWO VARIATIONS   @ @@@@.            WILL BE EXEQU
)@@G@@CUTED.@G@@@@. 3) <WHILE> CODE ALSO MOVES AROUND. WE DEFINE A <WHILE> TESQV
)@@G@@T WHICH IS  @G@@@@.            PERFORMED IN A SINGLE INSTRUCTION WHICH HQW
)@@G@@AS AN INVERSE     @G@@@@.            (I.E. A CONDITIONAL JUMP) AS 'OPTIMQX
)@@G@@IZEABLE'. POSITIONING   @E@@@@.            THEN DEPENDS UPON OTHER CONDIQY
)@@G@@TIONS AS FOLLOWS- @G@@@@.            NORMAL POSITIONING IS AT THE BOTTOMQZ
)@@G@@, WITH A (ONE TIME) JUMP@H@@@@.            TO THE WHILE TEST INSERTED ATRA
)@@G@@ THE TOP. IF THERE IS AN ESCAPE     @G@@@@.            CONDITION WHICH WRB
)@@G@@OULD OTHERWISE FALL THROUGH, HOWEVER, THE @H@@@@.            JUMP AROUNDRC
)@@G@@ THE WHILE IS AVOIDED BY PUTTING IT AT THE TOP AND    @H@@@@.           RD
)@@G@@ INVERTING THE ESCAPE TEST ACCORDINGLY. IF THERE IS NO <VARY>     @G@@@@RE
)@@G@@.            CODE AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE LOOP, AND THE WHILE     RF
)@@G@@@G@@@@.            TEST IS OPTIMIZEABLE, THEN THE INITIAL JUMP TO THE WHRG
)@@G@@ILE   @G@@@@.            TEST IS REPLACED BY THE TEST ITSELF. IN THIS CARH
)@@G@@SE, THE     @G@@@@.            TEST WILL APPEAR AT BOTH THE TOP AND BOTTRI
)@@G@@OM OF THE LOOP.   @E@@@@. 4) ESCAPE  AN ESCAPE TEST CAN BE MODIFIED BOTHRJ
)@@G@@ BECAUSE OF @G@@@@.            THE ABOVE, OR BECAUSE THE CLAUSE IS EMPTYRK
)@@G@@. IF THE CODE     @F@@@@.            FOLLOWING THE TEST IS NOT IN THE LORL
)@@G@@OP (I.E. IS A NON-@F@@@@.            VACUOUS ESCAPE CLAUSE OR IS THE ENDRM
)@@G@@ OF THE LOOP),    @F@@@@.            THE ESCAPE TEST BRANCHES TO STAY INRN
)@@G@@ THE LOOP. IF     @G@@@@.            THE FOLLOWING CODE IS IN THE LOOP (RO
)@@G@@I.E. VACUOUS ESCAPE     @G@@@@.            AND NON-VACUOUS OTHERWISE), TRP
)@@G@@HEN THE SENSE IS REVERSED     @F@@@@.            SO THAT THE BRANCH CONDRQ
)@@G@@ITION GOES COMPLETELY OUT OF  @^@@@@.            THE BLOCK. @[@@@@.     RR
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           RS
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *           RERT
)@@G@@PEAT            * @C@@@@.               *                             * RU
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @#@@@@RV
)@@G@@P       PROC   *12@]@@@@REPEAT* NAME@[@@@@.     @E@@@@K         EQU     RW
)@@G@@  G$CTR(1)+1        . BUMP BLOCK COUNTER  @F@@@@G$CTR*(1) EQU       K   RX
)@@G@@              . SAVE UPDATED BLOCK COUNT  @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTRY
)@@G@@R(5)+1        . BUMP GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL @F@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       M   RZ
)@@G@@              . SAVE NEW NESTING LEVEL    @F@@@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU      K   SA
)@@G@@              . SAVE SEQ NO OF THIS BLOCK @F@@@@G$TYPE*(M) EQU      4   SB
)@@G@@              . SET BLOCK TYPE TO REPEAT  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. APPLY FLOASC
)@@G@@TS TO LABELS IN THIS BLOCK    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) , GO G$$R10SD
)@@G@@           . ON PASS 1, FLOAT MEANS NOTHING     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FLAGSE
)@@G@@*(K,20) EQU   G$CTR(2)          . SAVE INITIAL FLOAT  @H@@@@ESCF      EQSF
)@@G@@U       G$LABL(K,4)       . REMEMBER ENTRY VALUE OF ESCAPE FLAG   @H@@@@SG
)@@G@@FALLF     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,21)>0)*(1-G$FLAG(K,21)) . GET FALLTHRU FLOSH
)@@G@@AT    @H@@@@N DO 10 ,G$LABL*(K,N) EQU G$LABL(K,N)+G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) SI
)@@G@@. GLOBAL, JUMPENTR@I@@@@N DO 9 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) EQU G$LABL(K,N+1)+G$FLAG(SJ
)@@G@@K,16)+FALLF . SURPRESS TOP WHILE    @G@@@@N DO 6 ,G$LABL*(K,N+4) EQU G$LSK
)@@G@@ABL(K,N+4)+G$FLAG(K,17) . ESCAPE INVERSION@G@@@@N DO 5 ,G$LABL*(K,N+5) ESL
)@@G@@QU G$LABL(K,N+5)+G$FLAG(K,13) . ESCAPE CLOSURE  @I@@@@N DO 4 ,G$LABL*(K,SM
)@@G@@N+6) EQU G$LABL(K,N+6)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,5) . OTHER/UNTIL     @G@@@@SN
)@@G@@N DO 3 ,G$LABL*(K,N+7) EQU G$LABL(K,N+7)+G$FLAG(K,18) . BOTTOM WHILE    SO
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO ESCF=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU 0 . IF NO ESCAPE, RESTORE FLAG @[@@@@SP
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@. ***** SYNTAX ANALYSIS ***** @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@SQ
)@@G@@G$$R10    NAME    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@C(1)      EQU  1                    SR
)@@G@@  . INITIALIZE CURRENT FIELD COUNTER@G@@@@KW(1)     EQU  P(1,1)         SS
)@@G@@        . AND CURRENT LEADING KEYWORD     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.           ST
)@@G@@    EXAMINE 'WHILE' FIELD     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$$R50  NAME            SU
)@@G@@              . MARK START OF WHILE TEST  @G@@@@WI      EQU    KW(1)=WHISV
)@@G@@LE            . FIELD INDEX OF 'WHILE' OR ZERO  @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,4) EQU WSW
)@@G@@I                 . REMEMBER INDEX IN CASE DEFERRED   @C@@@@ DO WI=0 , GSX
)@@G@@O G$$R59 . IF NO 'WHILE', WE'RE DONE@C@@@@WYNOT     EQU       (P(2)=1)**SY
)@@G@@(P(2,1)=NOT) .    @H@@@@WC        EQU       ((P(3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNSZ
)@@G@@OT,1)=AND))**(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   @F@@@@C(1)    EQU    3+WYNOT+2*WC         TA
)@@G@@        . UPDATE FIELD POINTER@F@@@@KW(1)   EQU    P(C(1),1)            TB
)@@G@@  . KEYWORD FOR NEXT FIELD    @H@@@@G$$R59  NAME                        TC
)@@G@@  . END PROCESSING OF 'WHILE' CONDITION   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.       EXAMTD
)@@G@@INE <LOOP CTL> FIELD, LOADING REGS IF NECESSARY @D@@@@. NOTE: THE <LOOP TE
)@@G@@CONTROL> ANALYSIS SUBROUTINE G$$LAN @E@@@@. SETS THE FLAGS FI(X) USED BETF
)@@G@@LOW.  FOR THEIR DEFINITIONS,  @ @@@@. SEE THE CODE FOR G$$LAN     @[@@@@TG
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.       SEE IF THIS IS A HARDWARE SEARCH SPEC   @[@@@@.     TH
)@@G@@@I@@@@G$$R60  NAME                          . MARK START PROCESSING OF <TI
)@@G@@LOOP CNTRL> SP    @F@@@@ DO 1-(KW(1)=LOOKFOR) , GO G$$R61 . IF NOT LOOKFTJ
)@@G@@OR, GO TRY 'VARY' @I@@@@VI      EQU    C(1)+2                 . IN THIS TK
)@@G@@FMT, 'VARY' FOLLOWS LOOKFOR AND     @F@@@@ DO (P(VI,1)>VARY)++(P(VI,1)<LTL
)@@G@@OOKFOR) , G$$EFL 2,010 . CHECK IT   @G@@@@P(VI,1) EQU    LOOKFOR        TM
)@@G@@        . FORCE KEYWORD FOR USE BY G$$LAN @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,8) EQU 1      TN
)@@G@@           . SET FLAG ALLOWING UNCONDITIONAL ESCAPE   @A@@@@ GO G$$R62 .TO
)@@G@@ THEN GO PROCESS IT     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$$R61  NAME                  TP
)@@G@@        . TRY A NORMAL 'VARY' FIELD @G@@@@VI      EQU    C(1)*((KW(1)>(JTQ
)@@G@@MGI-1))**(KW(1)<(VARY+1))) . FIELD INDEX  @D@@@@ DO VI=0 , GO G$$R69 . STR
)@@G@@KIP THIS IF FIELD NOT GIVEN   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$R62  NAME@E@@@@      TS
)@@G@@  G$$LAN                . ANALYZE THE LOOP CTL FIELD  @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2)TT
)@@G@@ EQU FI(5)              . REMEMBER IF IT HAS DEFERRED CODE  @H@@@@G$FLAGTU
)@@G@@*(K,3) EQU FI(3)              . NOTE FIELD IN WHICH 'TO' SPEC APPEARS   TV
)@@G@@@H@@@@C(1)    EQU    FI(7)+1                . SET FIELD OF NEXT (I.E. UNTW
)@@G@@TIL) GROUP  @F@@@@KW(1)   EQU    P(C(1),1)              . AND ITS FUNCT TX
)@@G@@FLAG WORD   @]@@@@G$$R69  NAME@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU VI                 TY
)@@G@@. SAVE INDEX OF VARY FIELD, IF ANY  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.              SCATZ
)@@G@@N 'UNTIL' FIELD   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,6) EQU    C(1)*(KW(1)=UNTIUA
)@@G@@L). EXTERNALIZE SO WE KNOW IT WAS GIVEN   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     ***** UB
)@@G@@CODE GENERATION *****   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$R80  NAME@H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(KUC
)@@G@@,10) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,7) . ENTER WITH JUMP TO WHILE/VARY   @F@@@@UD
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) . APPLY FLOAT, IF ANY   @[@@@@UE
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)                 . MARK START OF WHILE TEST     UF
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO (WI>0)**(1-G$FLAG(K,11)) , G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,WYNOT G$LABL(K,9)UG
)@@G@@ . GEN IT   @D@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+((WI>0)**G$FLAG(K,11)) . UH
)@@G@@@F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,16) . AND APPLY THE FLOAT   UI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@. GENERATE LOOP <VARY> CODE, IF ANY @[@@@@.     @F@@@@UJ
)@@G@@G$LABL*(K,2)                  . MARK START OF 2NDARY LOOP CHECK   @C@@@@UK
)@@G@@ DO VI>0 , ; IF THERE IS LOOP VARIATION CODE    @G@@@@ DO (P(VI,1)=LOOKFUL
)@@G@@OR)++(1-(FI(5)=FI(6))) , ; AND SOME OR ALL IS HERE    @E@@@@        G$$LUM
)@@G@@GE VI,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,9),1 . GENERATE IT   @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,2)<$ UN
)@@G@@,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQU 0 . IF ANY, CAN'T FALL THRU  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. FINAUO
)@@G@@L CLEANUP   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          G$$SVA                      . SAUP
)@@G@@VE ARGS FOR LATER @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 0                 . CLEAR ENDCHUQ
)@@G@@ECK DONE FLAG     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,3)=$) , G$$DFL G$LUR
)@@G@@ABL(K,3)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)                  . MARK START OF USER'S CUS
)@@G@@ODE   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     UT
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           UU
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *           ESUV
)@@G@@CAPE            * @C@@@@.               *                             * UW
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@UX
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *4 @#@@@@ESCAPE*  NAME     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@UY
)@@G@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@UZ
)@@G@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   VA
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=4) , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTING ERRORS     @[@@@@VB
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,4)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,4)    VC
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$LABL*(K,4)                 . MARK START OF ESCAPE TEST    @[@@@@VD
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@TBOT      EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)>0     . ON => TEST AT LOGICAVE
)@@G@@L BOTTOM (UNTIL)  @H@@@@TTOP      EQU       (G$FLAG(K,1)>0)++(G$FLAG(K,4VF
)@@G@@)>0) . ON => TESTS AT LGL TOP @H@@@@ DO TTOP**TBOT , G$$GFL 2,1         VG
)@@G@@      . CAN'T HAVE CAKE AND EAT IT TOO    @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,8) EQU G$FLAG(VH
)@@G@@K,8)**(P(1)=0) . UNCONDITIONAL (LOOKFOR) FLAG   @G@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,8) , VI
)@@G@@I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,10) . UNCONDITIONAL => LEAP OUT @C@@@@ DO G$FLAG(KVJ
)@@G@@,8) , GO G$$E10 . THEN GO CLEAN UP  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO 1-(P(1,1)=WHENVK
)@@G@@) , G$$EFL 3,4 . SYNTAX ERROR IF NO 'WHEN'@F@@@@WHENOT    EQU       (P(2VL
)@@G@@)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT) . ON FOR NOT CONDITION @H@@@@CFLG    EQU    P>(3+WHENVM
)@@G@@OT)                    . ON FOR COMPOUND CONDITION    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@VN
)@@G@@. ON PASS 1, BOTH SENSES OF THE TEST ARE GENERATED, SO WE CAN     @F@@@@VO
)@@G@@. DETERMINE THE FLOAT TO USE IF REVERSAL OCCURS. ON PASS 2, ONLY  @A@@@@VP
)@@G@@. THE DESIRED SENSE IS GENERATED    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO G$CTR(6)++G$FLVQ
)@@G@@AG(K,12) , ; PASS 1 ALWAYS, PASS 2 IF REVERSED  @I@@@@    G$$TST 2+WHENOVR
)@@G@@T,CFLG,WHENOT G$LABL(K,1+5*G$FLAG(K,19)) . JUMP=> KEEP LOOPIN     @F@@@@VS
)@@G@@SIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(K,4)     . LENGTH OF REVERSED TEST   @E@@@@VT
)@@G@@          RES       -G$CTR(6)*SIZE . THEN RES TEST AWAY     @H@@@@G$CTR*VU
)@@G@@(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$CTR(7)+G$FLAG(K,7) . KEEP G$$TST CTR IN PHASE  VV
)@@G@@@I@@@@ DO 1-(G$FLAG(K,12)++G$FLAG(K,7)) , ; PASS1 ALWAYS, 2 IF NOT REVERVW
)@@G@@SED/SURPRESSED    @G@@@@    G$$TST 2+WHENOT,CFLG,1-WHENOT G$LABL(K,10) .VX
)@@G@@ JUMP=> EXIT FROM LOOP  @E@@@@WIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(K,4)     . SIVY
)@@G@@ZE OF 2ND TEST    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU    SIVZ
)@@G@@DE(1)           . PASS 1: SET SIDE EFFECT @H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTWA
)@@G@@R(2)+G$FLAG(K,17) . PASS2: APPLY FLOAT FOR ENCLOSED BL@E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,17WB
)@@G@@) EQU  SIZE-WIZE . PASS 1: GET FLOAT, 2=>NOISE  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$E10WC
)@@G@@    NAME    @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)                    . MARK START OF USER'SWD
)@@G@@ ESCAPE CODE@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.           WE
)@@G@@    ******************************* @C@@@@.               *             WF
)@@G@@                * @C@@@@.               *         OTHERWISE           * WG
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.           WH
)@@G@@    *           ATEND             * @C@@@@.               *             WI
)@@G@@                * @C@@@@.               *           ENDREP            * WJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.           WK
)@@G@@    ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@Y     WL
)@@G@@  PROC   *1 @^@@@@OTHERWISE* NAME     0   @^@@@@ATEND*    NAME      1   WM
)@@G@@@^@@@@ENDREP*   NAME      2   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTWN
)@@G@@R(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEWO
)@@G@@QN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO 1-(G$TYPE(M)=4WP
)@@G@@) , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTING ERRORS     @E@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,5)=0 ,G$LABWQ
)@@G@@L*(K,5) . FIXUP FOR MISSING ESCAPE  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. CLOSE DANGLING EWR
)@@G@@SCAPE, IF REQUIRED@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,13) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LAWS
)@@G@@BL(K,10) . PASS2: LEAP OUT    @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(WT
)@@G@@K,13) . APPLY CLOSURE FLOAT   @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,13) EQU   0               WU
)@@G@@  . REMEMBER WE'VE DONE THIS  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. **** OTHERWISE GETS OFWV
)@@G@@F THE TRAIN HERE ...    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO Y(0,0)>0 , GO G$$Z10      WW
)@@G@@        . IF ATEND OR ENDREP, KEEP MOVING @H@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,4)=0 , G$$GWX
)@@G@@FL 2,2            . OTHERWISE INVALID IF NO ESCAPE    @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7)WY
)@@G@@ , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,6)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,6) 1  @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,6)      WZ
)@@G@@            . MARK START OF 'OTHERWISE' CODE    @B@@@@ DO 1 , END       XA
)@@G@@  . THAT'S ALL FOLKS    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. **** ATEND/ENDREP LUMBER ONWXB
)@@G@@ARD...@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         CLOSE LOOP: GEN CTL CODE WHICH PREFERSXC
)@@G@@ PHYSICAL BOTTOM  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$Z10    NAME    @H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(KXD
)@@G@@,9) , GO G$$Z50          . IF ITS TUESDAY, THIS MUST BE ENDREP    @F@@@@XE
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 1                 . REMEMBER WE'VE BEEN HERE     @E@@@@XF
)@@G@@ DO G$LABL(K,6)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,6) . DEFAULT START OF OTHERWISE@G@@@@KK    XG
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(3)          . GET POINTER INTO ARGSAVE STACK  @H@@@@XH
)@@G@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +G$ARGS(KK,I,J) . GET ARGXI
)@@G@@S     @G@@@@G$CTR*(3) EQU       KK-1              . THEN MOVE STACK POINXJ
)@@G@@TER BACK    @I@@@@ DO (Y(0,0)=1)**(G$ARGS(KK)=0) , G$$GFL 2,3        . AXK
)@@G@@TEND UNREACHABLE IF NO ARG    @G@@@@LL      EQU    G$FLAG(K,2)          XL
)@@G@@. ON IF ANY <VARY> CODE WAS DEFERRED@H@@@@DFER      EQU       LL++(G$FLAXM
)@@G@@G(K,4)>0) . ON IF DEFFERED CODE OF ANY TYPE     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. HANDXN
)@@G@@LE UNTIL CONDITIONS. THEY CAN HAVE EITHER BRANCH SENSE:     @G@@@@.   A)XO
)@@G@@ IF WHILE/VARY CODE WILL FOLLOW, UNTIL SUCCESS LEAPS TO ATEND     @E@@@@XP
)@@G@@.   B) IF NOT (A), THEN UNTIL FAILURE LEAPS TO TOP OF LOOP  @[@@@@.     XQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@UNORG                                 . MARK ORIGIN OF UNTIL TESTSXR
)@@G@@, IF ANY    @G@@@@UN        EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)     . GET INDEX INTO PXS
)@@G@@ OF UNTIL SPECS   @B@@@@ DO UN=0 , GO G$$Z30                  .   @G@@@@XT
)@@G@@KILL      EQU       G$CTR(7)**G$FLAG(K,7) . ON IF SURPRESSING ALL CODE  XU
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,5) . APPLY UNTIL SURPRESS FLXV
)@@G@@OAT   @F@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+KILL     . COUNT SURPRESSED UNTXW
)@@G@@IL    @E@@@@ DO KILL , GO G$$Z30                   . AND FORGET THE RESTXX
)@@G@@@F@@@@UNN       EQU       (P(UN+1)=1)**(P(UN+1,1)=NOT) . SET NOT FLAG   XY
)@@G@@@I@@@@UNC       EQU       (P(UN+UNN+2)=1)**((P(UN+UNN+2,1)=OR)++(P(UN+UNXZ
)@@G@@N+2,1)=AND)) .    @D@@@@  G$$TST UN+UNN+1,UNC,DFER--UNN G$LABL(K,1+9*DFEYA
)@@G@@R)    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. CLOSE DANGLING OTHERWISE/UNTIL    @[@@@@.     YB
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$Z30    NAME    @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU    UNORG-$           . GEYC
)@@G@@T FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL  @E@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,14) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LAYD
)@@G@@BL(K,1) . JUMP TO TOP   @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,14) YE
)@@G@@. FLOAT FOLLOWING CODE  @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   0                 . REYF
)@@G@@MEMBER WE DID THIS@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. HANDLE WHILE CONDITIONS.  THESE CAYG
)@@G@@N BE SURPRESSED OR CAN BRANCH TWO   @F@@@@. WAYS; FORTUNATELY, THE BRANCYH
)@@G@@H SENSE IS KNOWN ON PASS 1 (LL):    @F@@@@.  A) IF <VARY> CODE FOLLOWS, YI
)@@G@@THEN WHILE FAILURE JUMPS TO ATEND   @D@@@@.  B) IF NOT (A), WHILE SUCCESYJ
)@@G@@S JUMPS TO TOP OF LOOP  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,7)                 .YK
)@@G@@ MARK START OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP WHILE @B@@@@. NOTE: IF WHILE EXISTS, ITS AYL
)@@G@@LWAYS SPEC 1@B@@@@WYNOT     EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT)@H@@@@WC    YM
)@@G@@    EQU       ((P(3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNOT,1)=AND))**(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   YN
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO (G$FLAG(K,4)>0)**(1-G$FLAG(K,15)) , ; IF EXISTS AND NOT SURPREYO
)@@G@@SSED- @D@@@@        G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,LL=WYNOT G$LABL(K,2+7*LL)   @F@@@@YP
)@@G@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$FLAG(K,15) . COUNT SURPRESSED WHILE@H@@@@YQ
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,18) . APPLY WHILE SURPRESSION FLOAYR
)@@G@@T     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. GENERATE <VARY> CODE  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABLYS
)@@G@@*(K,8)                 . MARK START OF BOTTOM OF LOOP VARY  @H@@@@ DO G$YT
)@@G@@CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++(G$FLAG(K,1)>0) . NOTE SIDE EFFEC YU
)@@G@@@D@@@@ DO LL , G$$LGE G$FLAG(K,1),G$FLAG(K,3) G$LABL(K,3)   @[@@@@.     YV
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++SIDE(1) . NOTE SIDE EFYW
)@@G@@FECTS @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,9)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,9) 2  YX
)@@G@@@F@@@@G$LABL*(K,9)                  . MARK START OF USER ATEND CODE     YY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. END PROCESSING OF LOOP TERMINATION CONDITIONS @[@@@@YZ
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@ DO Y(0,0)=1 , END  . ATEND STATEMENT FINISHES UP HERE@[@@@@ZA
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@. CLEANUP FOR ENDREP STATEMENT@[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$Z50    NAZB
)@@G@@ME    @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO 1-(G$LABL(K,10)=$) , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,10) 3ZC
)@@G@@@D@@@@G$LABL*(K,10)                  . SET BLOCK EXIT LABEL @E@@@@G$CTR*ZD
)@@G@@(2) EQU       G$FLAG(K,20)      . RESTORE GLOBAL FLOAT@G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQZE
)@@G@@U  M-1                    . DECREMENT GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL  @C@@@@ DO G$ZF
)@@G@@CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RE DONE HERE @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. ***** PASSZG
)@@G@@ 1 ONLY: DETERMINE POSITIONING AND OPTIMIZATIONS@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     ZH
)@@G@@@G@@@@. SET FLAGS INDICATING WHETHER USER PUT ANY CODE IN SPECIFIC CLAUSZI
)@@G@@ES    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ESCAPP    EQU       G$LABL(K,4)>0     . ON=>ESCAZJ
)@@G@@PE STMNT APPEARED @H@@@@RVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,3)=G$LABL(K,5-ESCAPZK
)@@G@@P) . ON=> NOTHING AFTER REPEAT@H@@@@EVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,5)=G$LAZL
)@@G@@BL(K,6) . ON=> USER ESCAPE CLAUSE VACUOUS @I@@@@UOVAC     EQU       G$LAZM
)@@G@@BL(K,6)=(G$LABL(K,7)+G$FLAG(K,5)) . ON=> NO USER 'OTHER     @I@@@@OVAC  ZN
)@@G@@    EQU       G$LABL(K,6)=G$LABL(K,7) . ON=> EMPTY OTHERWISE/UNTIL CLAUSZO
)@@G@@E     @H@@@@AVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,9)=G$LABL(K,10) . ON=> USER ATEZP
)@@G@@ND CLAUSE VACUOUS @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NOKILL    EQU       G$FLAG(K,7)++(1-ZQ
)@@G@@(RVAC**EVAC**UOVAC**AVAC)) .  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@VATBOT    EQU       G$FLZR
)@@G@@AG(K,2)       . ON=> SOME (OR ALL) <VARY> AT BOTTOM   @H@@@@LOOBOT    EQZS
)@@G@@U       VATBOT++(1-OVAC)  . ON=> SOME LOOP CODE WILL BE AT BOTTOM @H@@@@ZT
)@@G@@EFOLLO    EQU       LOOBOT++(1-AVAC)  . ON=> SOMETHING WILL FOLLOW ESCAPZU
)@@G@@E     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. COMPUTE OPTIMUM POSITIONING OF WHILE (CAN BE TZV
)@@G@@OP, BOTTOM, OR BOTH)    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@WHSPEC    EQU       G$FLAG(K,4ZW
)@@G@@)>0     . ON IF WHILE SPECIFICATION GIVEN @H@@@@WONET     EQU       1=(GZX
)@@G@@$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1)) . ON => WHILE IS ONE INST AT T@G@@@@WONEB     EQZY
)@@G@@U       1=(G$LABL(K,8)-G$LABL(K,7)) . ON => ONE INSTR AT BOT@[@@@@.     ZZ
)@@G@@@I@@@@WHIBOT    EQU       (EFOLLO++(1-ESCAPP))**NOKILL . ON=> IF WHILE, AA
)@@G@@ALLOW AT BOTTO    @I@@@@WHISBO    EQU       WHSPEC**WHIBOT    . ON => WHAB
)@@G@@ILE WILL REALLY APPEAR AT BOTTOM    @I@@@@WHITOP    EQU       ((WONET**WAC
)@@G@@ONEB**(1-VATBOT))++(1-WHIBOT))**NOKILL . 0N=>ALLOW    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@AD
)@@G@@. SET GLOBAL SURPRESS FLAGS AND FLOATS FOR WHILE OPTIMIZATION     @[@@@@AE
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,11) EQU   WHSPEC**(1-WHITOP) . ON => SURPRESS AT TAF
)@@G@@OP    @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,16) EQU   (G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2))*G$FLAG(K,11) .AG
)@@G@@ TOP SURPRESS FLOA@F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,15) EQU   WHSPEC**(1-WHIBOT) . ON=> SUAH
)@@G@@RPRESS AT BOTTOM  @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,18) EQU   (G$LABL(K,7)-G$LABL(K,8))*G$AI
)@@G@@FLAG(K,15) . BOT SURPRESS FLOA@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE VARIOUS FLAGS AJ
)@@G@@FOR ESCAPE OPTIMIZATION AND CLOSURE @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,19) EQU AK
)@@G@@  LOOBOT++WHISBO    . ON=>LOOP CODE FOLLOWS     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,12) EQU AL
)@@G@@  (1-(G$FLAG(K,19)**EVAC))**NOKILL . ON=>JUMP TO KEEP GOING @F@@@@G$FLAGAM
)@@G@@*(K,17) EQU   G$FLAG(K,17)*G$FLAG(K,12) . SET FLOAT TO USE  @F@@@@ DO 1-AN
)@@G@@NOKILL ,G$FLAG*(K,17) EQU ESCAPP*(G$LABL(K,4)-G$LABL(K,5)) .@H@@@@G$FLAGAO
)@@G@@*(K,13) EQU   NOKILL**ESCAPP**G$FLAG(K,12)**G$FLAG(K,19) . CLOSURE FLAG AP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SET FLAG FOR GENERATION OF JUMP TO WHILE/VARY AT TOPAQ
)@@G@@ (INITIAL ENTRY)  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU   (VATBOT++((1-WHIAR
)@@G@@TOP)**WHSPEC))**NOKILL . ON=> GEN ENTRY JUMP    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. FOR AS
)@@G@@IMMEDIATE JGD LOOPS WE WON'T JUMP. FOR NOW, WE WON'T CHECK FOR    @G@@@@AT
)@@G@@. PRESENCE OF WHILE AT TOP, BUT WILL TURN OFF THIS OPTIMIZATION IF THEREAU
)@@G@@@G@@@@. IS ANY WHILE AT ALL. IN ADDITION, ONLY JGD'S NOW SET THE OPTIMIZAV
)@@G@@ATION @G@@@@. FLAG, SO THERE WILL BE NO FLOATING. WHEN TLEM'S AND JMGI'SAW
)@@G@@ ARE DONE,  @G@@@@. SURPRESSION OF SOME REGISTER LOAD CODE WILL CAUSE FLAX
)@@G@@OAT WHICH WILL    @C@@@@. NEED TO BE COMPENSATED FOR AT THIS POINT.     AY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@CANFAL    EQU       (1-WHSPEC)**(G$FLAG(K,21)>0) . ON AZ
)@@G@@=> WE CAN FALL THRU     @H@@@@ DO CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU 0       . SOBA
)@@G@@ FORGET ABOUT JUMPING TO BOTTOM     @G@@@@ DO 1-CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQBB
)@@G@@U 0     . CLEAR FLAG IF WE CAN'T FALL THRU@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CLOSE OTHEBC
)@@G@@RWISE/UNTIL WITH JUMP IF NOT FOLLOWED BY TESTS WHICH DO IT  @[@@@@.     BD
)@@G@@@H@@@@UNTOP     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,6)>0)**(1-(VATBOT++WHSPEC)) . UNTIL BE
)@@G@@JUMPS TO TOP@H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   (1-((OVAC**ESCAPP)++WHISBO++VATBOTBF
)@@G@@++UNTOP))**NOKILL .     @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU G$FLAG(K,5)*(1-NOKILL) . BG
)@@G@@ADJUST UNTIL SURPRESSION FLOAT@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SET LC TO REFLECT WHATBH
)@@G@@ IT WILL BE ON PASS 2 BY APPLYING FLOATS TO IT  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAGBI
)@@G@@*(K,7) EQU    1-NOKILL          . SET FLAG TO KILL ALL CODE @H@@@@      BJ
)@@G@@    RES       G$FLAG(K,5)+G$FLAG(K,10)+G$FLAG(K,16)+G$FLAG(K,17)+ ;     BK
)@@G@@@E@@@@                    G$FLAG(K,13)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,18)  @]@@@@BL
)@@G@@        END @C@@@@/.         ******** EXEC REQUEST GROUP *********@[@@@@BM
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* BN
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.           BO
)@@G@@    *          -READ-$            * @C@@@@.               *             BP
)@@G@@                * @C@@@@.               ******************************* BQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@          PROC      *0                PROCBR
)@@G@@ TO DEFINE 'READ$', ETC.@^@@@@G$RD$$D$* NAME      0   @#@@@@P       PROCBS
)@@G@@   *1 @^@@@@READ$***  NAME   015    @^@@@@READA$***  NAME  042    @^@@@@BT
)@@G@@TREAD$***  NAME  0102   @^@@@@AREAD$***  NAME  0166   @^@@@@AREADA$***  BU
)@@G@@NAME 0167   @^@@@@ATREAD$***  NAME 0170   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (P(0,0)=BV
)@@G@@015)++(P(0,0)=0166) , GO G$$D20 . NO PKT IF READ$,AREAD$    @G@@@@PKTOFFBW
)@@G@@  EQU    (P(0,0)=0102)++(P(0,0)=0170) . OFFSET FOR TREAD$ PACKETS @G@@@@BX
)@@G@@ DO P(1)=0 , GO G$$D10                . IF PKT ADDR NOT GIVEN, GO KLUDGEBY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GENERATE CODE FOR CASE WHERE PACKET ADDR EXPLICITLY BZ
)@@G@@GIVEN---    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@        LA,U   A0,$+5                 . GECA
)@@G@@T EOF ADDR (SKIP AFTER READ$) @H@@@@        I$     06,H1,A0,P(1,2),P(1,*CB
)@@G@@1),P(1,1)+PKTOFF . STASH IN PACKET (FIELD @G@@@@        I$     026,U,A0,CC
)@@G@@P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM PKT ADR   @E@@@@ GO G$$D99        CD
)@@G@@                    . GO GENERATE THE READ@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. IF PACKET CE
)@@G@@ADDR CAN VARY AT XQT TIME, WE MUST FARBLE A BIT @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$D10CF
)@@G@@  NAME@G@@@@        LXI,U  A0,0,A1                . TEMP SAVE A1 LOWER ICG
)@@G@@N A0 UPPER  @F@@@@        LXM,U  A1,$+7                 . GET ADDR OF EOCH
)@@G@@F RETURN    @E@@@@        SA,H1  A1,PKTOFF,A0           . EOF ADDR TO PACI
)@@G@@CKET  @G@@@@        LSSC   A0,18                  . ALIGN OLD A1 LOWER ICJ
)@@G@@N A0 LOWER  @E@@@@        LXM,U  A1,0,A0                . RESTORE A1 LOWCK
)@@G@@ER    @E@@@@        SSL    A0,18                  . REALIGN PACKET ADDR CL
)@@G@@@E@@@@ GO G$$D99                            . THEN GO DO THE ER   @[@@@@CM
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@. GENERATE CALL FOR IO FUNCTS WHICH DO NOT USE PACKETS@[@@@@CN
)@@G@@.     @]@@@@G$$D20  NAME@G@@@@        LXI,U  A0,$+(P(1)>0)+3        . SECO
)@@G@@T EOF TO SKIP AFTER READ$     @H@@@@ DO P(1)>0 ,         I$     026,U,A0CP
)@@G@@,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM BUF@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$D99  NAMECQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@        ER     P(0,0)                 . DO THE FUNC   @E@@@@      CR
)@@G@@  I$     074,04,,,,$+2          . NORMAL EXIT HERE    @G@@@@        AA,UCS
)@@G@@   A0,0400000             . IF EOF, SET LOWORDER SIGN BIT   @]@@@@      CT
)@@G@@  END @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@/.   ****** UTILITIES FOCU
)@@G@@R CONDITION TESTING *******   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ******************CV
)@@G@@**************************************    @F@@@@.     *                 CW
)@@G@@                                     *    @F@@@@.     *       G$$CAN : ACX
)@@G@@NALYZE A SIMPLE CONDITION FIELD      *    @F@@@@.     *                 CY
)@@G@@                                     *    @F@@@@.     ******************CZ
)@@G@@**************************************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@DA
)@@G@@. DEFINE ARRAYS FOR OPTIMIZATION OF TYPE 1 TESTS ON REGISTERS INTO TYPE DB
)@@G@@3     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          DEF     @F@@@@G$ALTT(NE)  EQU     NONZDC
)@@G@@              . NOT EQUAL ZERO IS NONZERO @E@@@@G$ALTT(EQ)  EQU     ZERODD
)@@G@@              . EQUAL ZERO IS ZERO  @ @@@@G$ALTT(DNE) EQU     DNONZ     DE
)@@G@@@ @@@@G$ALTT(DEQ) EQU     DZERO     @F@@@@G$ALTT(LT)  EQU     NEG       DF
)@@G@@        . LESS THAN ZERO IS NEGATIVE@G@@@@G$ALTT(GE)  EQU     POS       DG
)@@G@@        . GTR OR EQUAL ZERO IS POSITIVE   @#@@@@Z       PROC   *1 @#@@@@DH
)@@G@@G$$CAN*  NAME     @H@@@@I       EQU    Z(1,1)                 . GET INDEDI
)@@G@@X TO FIELD BEING ANALYZED     @F@@@@K       EQU    Z(1,2)               DJ
)@@G@@  . GET ITS ORDER IN THE TEST @ @@@@. DETERMINE TYPE OF CONDITION @ @@@@DK
)@@G@@ DO P(I,2)>0  ,N(1) EQU 1     @ @@@@ DO P(I,2)=IN ,N(1) EQU 2     @A@@@@DL
)@@G@@ DO P(I,2)=IS ,N(1) EQU 3+2*(P(I)=4)@ @@@@ DO P(I)=1    ,N(1) EQU 4     DM
)@@G@@@ @@@@ DO P(I,1)=CHANNEL ,N(1) EQU 6@F@@@@ DO N(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,1       DN
)@@G@@        . E-FLAG IF UNKNOWN TYPE    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. TRY TO CHANGE TEDO
)@@G@@ST TO A MORE OPTIMAL ONE THAN SPECIFIED   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO (N(1)=2)DP
)@@G@@**G$AMPR , GO G$$A10      . REG STATUS NEEDS RELOCATION FUNC &(X) @G@@@@DQ
)@@G@@ DO (N(1)>1)++(P(I,5)<016) , GO G$$A30 . VALUE TESTS NEED IMMEDIATES    DR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. IMMEDIATE LE OR GT CAN BE ALTERED TO LT OR GE...    DS
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@FUDGE     EQU       (LT-LE)*(P(I,2)=LE)+(GE-GT)*(P(I,2DT
)@@G@@)=GT) @D@@@@P**(I,2) EQU        P(I,2)+FUDGE      . ADJUST KEYWORD@F@@@@DU
)@@G@@P**(I,3) EQU        P(I,3)+1-(FUDGE=0) . ADJUST IMMEDIATE VALUE   @F@@@@DV
)@@G@@ DO (1-((P(I,3)=0)**(P(I,4)=0)))++(G$ALTT(P(I,2))=0) , GO G$$A30 .@[@@@@DW
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. REGISTER TESTS AGAINST IMMEDIATE ZEROES CAN BECOME CONDITIDX
)@@G@@ONAL JUMPS  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. BE CAREFUL NOT TO OVEROPTIMIZE IMMEDIATEDY
)@@G@@S     @F@@@@ DO 1-G$AMPR , GO G$$A30 . CANNOT OPTIMIZE WITHOUT & FUNCTIODZ
)@@G@@N     @E@@@@ DO 1-(&(P(I,3))=-2) , GO G$$A30 . ZERO MUST BE ABSOLUTE    EA
)@@G@@@F@@@@P**(I,3)  EQU       G$ALTT(P(I,2))    . GET ALTERNATE KEYWORD     EB
)@@G@@@H@@@@P**(I)    EQU       3                 . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNEC
)@@G@@E AWAY ,,U) @C@@@@ GO G$$A20          . GO FINISH UP THE FARBLING @[@@@@ED
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. TYPE 2 CONDITION TESTS ON A-REGS CAN BECOME CONDITIONAL JUEE
)@@G@@MPS, TOO.   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$A10    NAME    @I@@@@REG       EQU     EF
)@@G@@  P(I,3)            . GET REG FROM  <KEYWORD>,IN,<REG> FORMAT     @G@@@@EG
)@@G@@ DO (REG<A0)++(REG>A15) , GO G$$A30   . MAKE SURE ITS WITHIN AREG RANGE EH
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO 1-(&(REG)=-2) , GO G$$A30         . AND AN ABSOLUTE VALUE     EI
)@@G@@@H@@@@P**(I,3)  EQU       P(I,1)            . FORCE CONDITION KEYWORD INEJ
)@@G@@TO SPEC3    @F@@@@P**(I,1)  EQU       REG               . THEN MOVE REG EK
)@@G@@INTO SPEC1  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$A20    NAME                        . FIEL
)@@G@@NISH FUDGING  <AREG>,IS,<KEYWORD> TEST    @E@@@@P**(I,2)  EQU       IS  EM
)@@G@@              . CRAM IN THE KEYWORD @G@@@@N(1)      EQU       3         EN
)@@G@@        . AND MARK THIS AS A TYPE 3 TEST  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$A30    NAEO
)@@G@@ME    @F@@@@J(1)    EQU    P(I,G$KSF(N(1)))       . GET FUNC KEYWORD VALEP
)@@G@@UE    @H@@@@ DO DTH ,J(1) EQU G$IV(N(1),J(1))     . FLIP IF DEMORGAN'S TEQ
)@@G@@HEOREM IN EFFECT  @F@@@@ DO J(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,2               . E-FLAG IER
)@@G@@F UNKNOWN KEYWORD @F@@@@NI$*(K) EQU    G$FJ(N(1),J(1))        . NO OF INES
)@@G@@STRS GENERATED    @D@@@@WA$*(K) EQU    G$WS(N(1),J(1))        . WAITING ET
)@@G@@STATUS@G@@@@KE$*(K) EQU    J(1)                   . EXTERNALIZE FUNC KEYEU
)@@G@@WORD VAL    @F@@@@TP$*(K) EQU    N(1)                   . EXTERNALIZE TYEV
)@@G@@PE OF TEST  @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@EW
)@@G@@.     ********************************************************    @F@@@@EX
)@@G@@.     *                                                      *    @F@@@@EY
)@@G@@.     *  G$$COD : GENERATE CODE FOR A SIMPLE CONDITION TEST  *    @F@@@@EZ
)@@G@@.     *                                                      *    @F@@@@FA
)@@G@@.     ********************************************************    @[@@@@FB
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@Q       PROC   *2 @I@@@@G$$COD*  NAME           FC
)@@G@@              . PF'S: FIELD-INDEX,TEST-INDEX,WAIT-VAL FA    @F@@@@I     FD
)@@G@@  EQU    Q(1,1)                 . GET FIELD WE'RE SCANNING  @F@@@@NN    FE
)@@G@@  EQU    Q(1,2)                 . GET DECODED DATA INDEX    @E@@@@N     FF
)@@G@@  EQU    TP$(NN)                . GET CONDITION TYPE  @E@@@@. COMPUTE FIFG
)@@G@@ELDS WHICH ARE INDEPENDENT OF FUNCTION/CONDITION@I@@@@CGISF   EQU    G$FFH
)@@G@@CF(N)=0             . SET FLAG IF G$FJ=FUNC CODE (ELSE ITS J-S    @H@@@@FI
)@@G@@AAA     EQU    0+(G$ASF(N)>0)*(P(I,G$ASF(N))-A0) . WATCH OUT FOR -0!!!!!FJ
)@@G@@!     @ @@@@EXREG   EQU    CGISF*P(I,4)   @B@@@@HI      EQU    CGISF*(2*FK
)@@G@@P(I,*4)+P(I,*3))  @C@@@@EWE     EQU    CGISF*P(I,3)+(1-CGISF)*Q(2,1)    FL
)@@G@@@G@@@@SIDE**(1) EQU SIDE(1)++(N=5)++(HI>0)  . ON IF TEST HAS SIDE EFFECTFM
)@@G@@S     @E@@@@. NOW GET FIELDS WHICH DEPEND UPON THE SPECIFIED CONDITION  FN
)@@G@@@E@@@@JI(1)   EQU    KE$(NN)                . GET KEYWORD FUNCTION@F@@@@FO
)@@G@@JI(2)   EQU    G$IV(N,JI(1))          . AND KEYWORD OF THE INVERSE@F@@@@FP
)@@G@@WOK     EQU    Q(1,3)=G$WS(N,JI(1))   . ON IF WAITING STATUS OK   @H@@@@FQ
)@@G@@ DO G$FJ(N,JI(1),1)>077 , GO G$$C01   . CHECK FOR ASYMMETRIC INSTRUCTIONFR
)@@G@@S     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. PROCESS SYMMETRIC TESTS (FOR WHICH AN INVERSE FS
)@@G@@MACHINE INSTR EXISTS)   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@JIU     EQU    JI(2-WOK)      FT
)@@G@@        . GET INDEX OF OPCODE WE'LL USE   @G@@@@NUMINS  EQU    G$FJ(N,JIFU
)@@G@@U)            . GET NO OF INSTRS TO GENERATE    @H@@@@XTIM      EQU     FV
)@@G@@CGISF**(N<3)**(HI=0)**(P(I,5)>015) . IMMEDIATE EXTENSION    @E@@@@K DO  FW
)@@G@@   NUMINS ,FUN(K) EQU G$FCF(N)+CGISF*G$FJ(N,JIU,K)    @F@@@@K DO     NUMFX
)@@G@@INS ,JAY(K) EQU CGISF*P(I,5)+(1-CGISF)*G$FJ(N,JIU,K)  @I@@@@K DO     NUMFY
)@@G@@INS*(1-XTIM) , I$ FUN(K),JAY(K),AAA,EXREG,HI,EWE . GENERATE THE INST    FZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@K DO     NUMINS*XTIM , G$$IMU FUN(K),JAY(K),AAA,EXREG,EWE . IMMEDIGA
)@@G@@ATES  @G@@@@REVER**(1) EQU (G$FJ(N,JI(1))*G$FJ(N,JI(2)))=1 . SET REVERSIGB
)@@G@@BLE FLAG    @G@@@@ DO 1-(REVER(1)++WOK) , I$ 074,04,,,,$+2 . WATCHOUT FOGC
)@@G@@R NON-REVERSIBLES @H@@@@ DO 1 , END                           . FOR STANGD
)@@G@@DARD INSTRS, ITS ALL OVER HERE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. PROCESS ASYMMETRIC INSGE
)@@G@@TRS (FOR WHICH NO SINGLE INVERSE EXISTS)  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$C01  NAMEGF
)@@G@@@F@@@@FUN     EQU    G$FJ(N,JI(1),1)        . GET FUNCT-JDESIG VALUE    GG
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO FUN=01637 , GO G$$C02             . TEST FOR DTE INSTR  @D@@@@GH
)@@G@@. IF NOT A DTE, THEN INSTRUCTION IS A JUMP OF SORTS   @B@@@@. (EITHER DJGI
)@@G@@Z OR AN I/O CHANNEL TEST)     @H@@@@AREG    EQU    AAA+A0*(FUN>01700)   GJ
)@@G@@  . FOR CHANNEL INSTRS, USE GIVEN AVALUE  @C@@@@        G$$FFJ FUN,AREG,GK
)@@G@@,,WOK*EWE+(WOK=0)*($+2) @ @@@@ DO WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,EWE  @]@@@@ DO 1 GL
)@@G@@, END @B@@@@. HERE WE HANDLE THE DOUBLE TEST EQUAL -  @]@@@@G$$C02  NAMEGM
)@@G@@@A@@@@        G$$FFJ FUN,AAA,EXREG,HI,EWE @ @@@@ DO WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,GN
)@@G@@,$+2  @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************GO
)@@G@@********************************************    @F@@@@.     *           GP
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     *  G$$TST : GQ
)@@G@@DRIVER FOR SIMPLE AND COMPOUND COND TESTS  *    @F@@@@.     *           GR
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     ************GS
)@@G@@********************************************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     GT
)@@G@@@#@@@@R       PROC   *2 @H@@@@G$$TST*  NAME                         . PFGU
)@@G@@'S: FIELD-IN-P,COMPOUND-FLAG,INVERT @I@@@@                              GV
)@@G@@. IF NO JUMP-EXIT GIVEN, G$TLBL(TTL)+1 IS USED (LINE I@H@@@@TTL     EQU GW
)@@G@@   G$CTR(4)+1             . COUNT THIS REFERENCE TO THIS PROCEDURE@F@@@@GX
)@@G@@ORIG                                  . REMEMBER WHERE WE STARTED @G@@@@GY
