)@@G@@UTILITIES FOR GENERATION OF LOOP CONTROLS ******@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     KK
)@@G@@@F@@@@. SELECTION OF THE INSTRUCTION TO BE USED TO CONTROL THE LOOP IS: KL
)@@G@@@E@@@@.    1) JGD    IF LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS -1, OR   @E@@@@KM
)@@G@@.              LOOP IS FOR A SPECIFIED NUMBER OF TIMES.     @E@@@@.    2KN
)@@G@@) JMGI   IF LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS NOT -1.  @D@@@@.    3) TLEMKO
)@@G@@   IF LOOP TERMINATES AT OTHER THAN ZERO. @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. POSITIONINKP
)@@G@@G OF THE LOOP CONTROL INSTRUCTION IS:     @A@@@@.    1) JGD    ALWAYS ATKQ
)@@G@@ THE BOTTOM @F@@@@.    2) JMGI   AT BOTTOM (SO JUMP DESTINATION CONTINUEKR
)@@G@@S IN THE    @F@@@@.              LOOP), IF INCREMENT NEGATIVE (LOOP SENSKS
)@@G@@E DOWN),    @E@@@@.              I.E. VALUES OF LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE ARKT
)@@G@@E >0 .@A@@@@.              AT TOP OTHERWISE     @F@@@@.    3) TLEM   AT KU
)@@G@@BOTTOM (SO SKIP CAUSES EXIT FROM LOOP) WHEN     @E@@@@.              INCKV
)@@G@@REMENT IS POSITIVE (LOOP SENSE UP), I.E.  @F@@@@.              TERMINATIKW
)@@G@@ON CONDITION IS APPROACHED FROM BELOW.    @F@@@@.              BECAUSE OKX
)@@G@@F LACK OF SIGN EXTENSION, THIS HOLDS RE-  @F@@@@.              GARDLESS KY
)@@G@@OF THE SIGN OF THE LOOP VARIABLE ITSELF.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE: IF TKZ
)@@G@@HE SIGN OF THE INCREMENT IS UNKNOWN (JMGI/TLEM), THE CODE   @G@@@@. TO VLA
)@@G@@ARY THE LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE WILL BE DUPLICATED AT BOTH TOP AND  @F@@@@LB
)@@G@@. BOTTOM, WITH AN EXECUTE-TIME TEST (SIGN JUMP) AT THE BOTTOM TO  @A@@@@LC
)@@G@@. DETERMINE WHICH IS TO BE USED.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. TO ENFORCE THE RLD
)@@G@@EQUIREMENT THAT THE LOOP CONTROL REGISTER CONTAIN     @F@@@@. THE FROM/TLE
)@@G@@O VALUES ON THE FIRST AND LAST TIMES THROUGH THE LOOP,@D@@@@. TLEM TESTSLF
)@@G@@ AT THE TOP ARE SURROUNDED BY AX AND ANX  @F@@@@. OF THE INCREMENT. IN TLG
)@@G@@HE GENERAL CASE, THERE IS NO WAY TO AVOID @G@@@@. THIS. IN THE FUTURE, WLH
)@@G@@E WILL ALLOW THE USER TO SURPRESS IT, AND/OR    @G@@@@. IN THE CASE WHERLI
)@@G@@E THE CONTROL FIELDS ARE IMMEDIATE, GENERATE SLIGHTLY @C@@@@. DIFFERENT LJ
)@@G@@CODE WHICH WILL MAKE IT UNNECESSARY.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************LK
)@@G@@********************************************    @F@@@@.     *           LL
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     *   G$$LAN :LM
)@@G@@ ANALYZE A <LOOP CONTROL> SPECIFICATION    *    @F@@@@.     *           LN
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     ************LO
)@@G@@********************************************    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.    FLP
)@@G@@LAGS SET BY THIS SUBROUTINE ARE USED BY CALLING ROUTINE (REPEAT)  @^@@@@LQ
)@@G@@.    THEIR MEANINGS ARE:@D@@@@.       FI(1)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FOR' SPELR
)@@G@@CIFICATION  @C@@@@.       FI(2)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FROM' SPEC    @G@@@@LS
)@@G@@.       FI(3)  INDEX OF 'TO' SPEC ('VARY'), OR 'MASKED' SPEC ('LOOKFOR')LT
)@@G@@@G@@@@.       FI(4)  INDEX OF 'BY' SPEC. NOTE THAT IF USER DIDN'T GIVE OLU
)@@G@@NE,   @C@@@@.              WE FORCE IT BY STORING IN P(X,Y) @G@@@@.     LV
)@@G@@  FI(5)  ON IF ANY LOOP CONTROL CODE IS TO APPEAR AT THE PHYSICAL @B@@@@LW
)@@G@@.              BOTTOM OF THE LOOP CODE    @F@@@@.       FI(6)  ON IF SENLX
)@@G@@SE OF LOOP CTL VARIABLE (UP\DOWN) IS KNOWN@D@@@@.              ('VARY'),LY
)@@G@@ OR OFFSET VALUE ('LOOKFOR')  @F@@@@.       FI(7)  INDEX IN P OF LAST FILZ
)@@G@@ELD SCANNED BY THIS ROUTINE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE ARRAYS IM(K) AND IMA
)@@G@@V(K) ARE USED INTERNALLY FOR THE ANALYZED @H@@@@. PARAMETERS OF THE LOOPMB
)@@G@@ SPECIFICATION. IM IS ON IF THE VALUE IS IMMEDIATE,   @G@@@@. AND IV IS MC
)@@G@@THE VALUE ITSELF. K=1,2,3,4=> FORVAL, FROMVAL, TOVAL, BYVAL.@[@@@@.     MD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@        PROC   *0                     . NOTE: ONE-PASSME
)@@G@@ PROC FLAG REQUIRED     @#@@@@G$$LAN*  NAME     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@W(1)  MF
)@@G@@  EQU    KW(1)                  . GET KEYWORD WHICH DESCRIBES FIELD     MG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@.       ***** BREAK DOWN SOURCE IMAGE, SET DEFAULTS **MH
)@@G@@***   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. SCAN ALL FIELDS FOR DEFINING KEYWORDS   @[@@@@MI
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@K3      EQU    MASKED*(W(1)=LOOKFOR)+TO*(1-(W(1)=LOOKFOR))  MJ
)@@G@@@G@@@@FI*(1)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FOR)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FOR)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=FMK
)@@G@@OR)   @G@@@@FI*(2)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FROM)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FROM)+3*(P(VML
)@@G@@I+3,1)=FROM)@D@@@@FI*(3)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=K3)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=K3)+;   MM
)@@G@@@B@@@@        3*(P(VI+3,1)=K3)+4*(P(VI+4,1)=K3) @F@@@@FI*(4)  EQU    VI+MN
)@@G@@(P(VI+1,1)=BY)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=BY)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=BY)@G@@@@FI*(7)  EQU    FI(MO
)@@G@@4)                  . INITIALIZE LAST FIELD POINTER   @H@@@@I DO     3 ,MP
)@@G@@ DO FI(I)>FI(7) ,FI*(7) EQU FI(I) . FIND LAST FIELD USER GAVE US  @I@@@@MQ
)@@G@@LF(1)   EQU    0+P                    . SET INDEX OF LAST FIELD + 1 IN CMR
)@@G@@ASE OF D    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. DEFAULT A MISSING 'TO' SPECIFICATION TO MS
)@@G@@ZERO  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (K3=MASKED)++(FI(3)>VI) , GO G$$L01 . IF 'TOMT
)@@G@@' EXPLICIT, SKIP THIS   @H@@@@FI*(3)  EQU    LF(1)                  . FOMU
)@@G@@RCE IT INTO THE NEXT AVAIL SUBFIELD @E@@@@P*(FI(3),1) EQU TO            MV
)@@G@@        . SET ITS KEYWORD     @F@@@@P*(FI(3),4) EQU XU                  MW
)@@G@@  . MAKE IT AN IMMEDIATE ZERO @G@@@@LF(1)   EQU    LF(1)+1              MX
)@@G@@  . BUMP NEXT USABLE FIELD POINTER  @G@@@@G$$L01  NAME                  MY
)@@G@@        . END OF DEFAULT FOR 'TO' FIELD   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. 'BY' FIELDMZ
)@@G@@ (IF GIVEN) IS VARIABLE LENGTH. FORCE TO FIXED FORMAT @C@@@@. BY MOVING NA
)@@G@@UP/DOWN/OFFSET TO THE FIFTH SUBFIELD@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO FI(4)=VI , GO NB
)@@G@@G$$L02              . IF 'BY' OMITTED, SKIP THIS@E@@@@ DO P(FI(4),4)=U ,NC
)@@G@@P*(FI(4),4) EQU XU . FORCE SIGN EXTENSION @F@@@@NB      EQU    0+P(FI(4)ND
)@@G@@)             . NO OF SPECS IN 'BY' FIELD @E@@@@ DO (P(FI(4),NB)>0)++(NBNE
)@@G@@=5) , GO G$$L02 . NOTHING TO ADJUST @G@@@@P*(FI(4),5) EQU P(FI(4),NB)   NF
)@@G@@        . FORCE UP DOWN OFFSET TO FIELD 5 @F@@@@P*(FI(4),NB) EQU 0      NG
)@@G@@              . AND RESET WHEREVER IT WAS @H@@@@G$$L02  NAME            NH
)@@G@@              . END KEYWORD FARBLING FOR 'BY' FIELD   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@NI
)@@G@@. PUT ALL FIELDS IN STANDARD FORM TO HANDLE EQUF'S    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@NJ
)@@G@@I DO     4 , DO FI(I)>VI ,UV(I) EQU ; COMBINE ALL FIELDS    @G@@@@ +(I$ NK
)@@G@@0,P(FI(I),4),0,P(FI(I),3),2*P(FI(I),*3)+P(FI(I),*2),P(FI(I),2))   @[@@@@NL
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE:  THE CODE BELOW WILL GENERATE (USUALLY) SPURIOUS R-FNM
)@@G@@LAGS IF     @F@@@@. THE FIELDS BEING EXAMINED ARE EXTERNAL (I.E. U-FLAGGNN
)@@G@@ED) EVEN    @F@@@@. THOUGH WE ARE STRIPPING OFF FIELDS WHICH HAVE NO RELNO
)@@G@@OCATION (THE@E@@@@. X AND J FIELDS), AND EVEN THOUGH THE PORTION OF UV WNP
)@@G@@HICH  @F@@@@. MAY CARRY RELOCATION (THE U-FIELD) IS NOT MASKED AT THE PONQ
)@@G@@INT   @A@@@@. OF ITS USE. <EXPLETIVE DELETED>   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@I DO  NR
)@@G@@   4 , DO P(FI(I),2)>0777777 ; IF THE USER EQUF'D THE SYMBOL@E@@@@      NS
)@@G@@  ,IM(I) EQU (07017000000**(G$NOFO UV(I)))=07000000000@F@@@@I DO     4 ,NT
)@@G@@ DO P(FI(I),2)<01000000 ; IF HE DIDN'T EQUF IT ..     @H@@@@        ,IM(NU
)@@G@@I) EQU (P(FI(I),3)=0)**(016=(P(FI(I),4)**016)) . CHECK FOR EXPLICI@E@@@@NV
)@@G@@I DO     4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)<01000000) ; IF NOT EQUF'D@F@@@@      NW
)@@G@@  ,IV(I) EQU P(FI(I),2)         . USE THE VALUE HE GAVE     @F@@@@I DO  NX
)@@G@@   4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)>0777777) ; BUT IF HE EQUF'D IT @G@@@@      NY
)@@G@@  ,IV(I) EQU + (G$NOFO UV(I)**G$UMSK) . PRAY ITS NOT EXTERNAL     @H@@@@NZ
)@@G@@I DO     4 , DO IV(I)>0377777 ,IV(I) EQU IV(I)++0777777000000 . SIGN EXTOA
)@@G@@END   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DEFAULT A MISSING 'BY' SPECIFICATIOB
)@@G@@ON TO +-1, DEPENDING UPON     @F@@@@. THE SIGN OF TO-FROM, AND/OR THE USOC
)@@G@@ER'S UP/DOWN/OFFSET SPEC.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO FI(4)>VIOD
)@@G@@ , GO G$$L03              . SKIP THIS IF USER GAVE THIS FIELD     @F@@@@OE
)@@G@@FI*(4)  EQU    LF(1)                  . REMEMBER WHERE ITS GOING  @H@@@@OF
)@@G@@ DO 1-((W(1)=VARY)++(W(1)=LOOKFOR)) , GO G$$L03 . SKIP FOR SPECIFIC LOOPOG
)@@G@@ TYPE @F@@@@IV(4)   EQU    1                      . INITIAL ASSUMPTION IOH
)@@G@@S +1  @G@@@@ DO (1-(W(1)=LOOKFOR))**IM(2)**IM(3)  ; UNLESS WE KNOW TO-FROI
)@@G@@OM VALUES   @F@@@@        ,IV(4) EQU 1-2*(IV(2)>IV(3))  . THEN USE SIGN OJ
)@@G@@OF DIFF     @F@@@@P*(FI(4),2) EQU     IV(4)             . SAVE FOR USE BOK
)@@G@@Y GENERATOR @D@@@@P*(FI(4),4) EQU XU  . MAKE SURE HE KNOWS ITS IMMEDIATEOL
)@@G@@@E@@@@UV(4)   EQUF   IV(4),,XU              . MARK IT AS IMMEDIATE@G@@@@OM
)@@G@@IM(4)   EQU    1                      . AND TURN ON THE IMMEDIATE FLAG  ON
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$$L03  NAME                          . END DEFAULT PROCESSING OF OO
)@@G@@'BY'  @G@@@@ DO P(FI(4),5)=0 ,P*(FI(4),5) EQU P(VI,3) . SET USER'S SIGN,OP
)@@G@@ IF ANY     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO 1-(W(1)=LOOKFOR) , GO G$$LOQ
)@@G@@30      . IF NOT LOOKFOR, GO DO VARY@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     OR
)@@G@@  ***** PROCESS 'LOOKFOR' LOOP (I.E. SEARCH, MASKED SEARCH) ***** @[@@@@OS
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@FI*(5)  EQU    0                      . FLAG NO CODE APPEARSOT
)@@G@@ AT THE BOTTOM    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. LOAD MASK AND REPEAT REGISTERS    OU
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (FI(3)>VI)**(P(FI(3))>1) , I$ 023,,2,,,UV(3) . LOAOV
)@@G@@D MASK REG (R2)   @F@@@@ DO FI(1)>VI , I$ 023,,1,,,UV(1)      . AND REPEOW
)@@G@@AT COUNT (R1)     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. INITIALIZE REG USED AS TABLE INDEXOX
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO (P(FI(4),5)=OFFSET)**(1-IM(4)) , G$$EFL 2,1 . OFFSOY
)@@G@@ET NEEDS IMMEDIATE BY   @F@@@@OFV     EQU    IM(4)*(P(FI(4),5)=OFFSET)*IOZ
)@@G@@V(4) . SET OFFSET VALUE @H@@@@FI*(6)  EQU    OFV                    . ANPA
)@@G@@D SAVE FOR USE BY CODE GENERATOR    @E@@@@ DO FI(2)=VI , END            PB
)@@G@@        . IF NO 'FROM', QUIT  @H@@@@ DO FI(4)=VI , G$$EFL 2,2           PC
)@@G@@      . REQUIRE THAT A 'BY' SPEC APPEARED @H@@@@ DO IM(2)**IM(4) , GO G$PD
)@@G@@$L21          . IF BOTH IMMEDIATE, GO USE CONSTANT    @D@@@@        I$  PE
)@@G@@   027,,P(VI,2),,,UV(2)   . LX XN,FROM    @F@@@@ DO OFV=0 , I$ 046,,P(VIPF
)@@G@@,2),,,UV(4)   . IF NO OFFSET, LXI XN,BY   @C@@@@ DO OFV=0 , END         PG
)@@G@@              . AND QUIT@G@@@@ DO P(VI,2)>X11 , AH P(VI,2),(+OFV,-OFV) .PH
)@@G@@ IF OVERLAPPED, ADD OFFSET IN @H@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , ANX,U P(VI,2),OFV  PI
)@@G@@  . IF NONOVERLAPPED, USE BRUTE FORCE     @B@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , LXI,U PPJ
)@@G@@(VI,2),OFV    .   @D@@@@ DO 1 , END                           . THEN GETPK
)@@G@@ OUT  @I@@@@G$$L21  NAME                          . COME HERE IF FROM ANPL
)@@G@@D BY BOTH IMMEDIATE     @G@@@@        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,(+IV(4),IV(2PM
)@@G@@)-OFV) . LOAD XREG FROM CONS  @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     PN
)@@G@@  ****** PROCESS 'VARY' (NORMAL LOOP) SPECIFICATION *****   @[@@@@.     PO
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$$L30  NAME                          . MARK START OF VARY CHECKINPP
)@@G@@G     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.       IF LOOP INSTR SPEC GENERIC, CHOOSE THE MPQ
)@@G@@ACHINE INSTR@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO 1-(W(1)=VARY) , GO G$$L40 . SKIP IF USPR
)@@G@@ER TOLD US THE INSTR    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$L31  NAME                  PS
)@@G@@        . FORCE OPCODE IF ITS NOT KNOWN   @G@@@@ DO FI(1)>VI , GO G$$L34PT
)@@G@@              . IF 'FOR', ASSUME JGD IMMEDIATELY@G@@@@ DO 1-(IM(2)**IM(3PU
)@@G@@)**IM(4)) , GO G$$L35 . NO FUDGE IF ALL NOT KNOWN     @D@@@@ DO 1-((IV(2PV
)@@G@@)>0)**(IV(3)=0)**(IV(4)=-1)) , GO G$$L35  @G@@@@FI*(1)  EQU    FI(2)    PW
)@@G@@              . PUT 'FOR' IN P WHERE 'FROM' WAS @F@@@@FI*(2)  EQU    VI PX
)@@G@@                    . AND INVALIDATE THE 'FROM' @G@@@@IV(1)   EQU    IV(PY
)@@G@@2)+1                . FORVAL IS ONE MORE THAN FROMVAL @G@@@@IM(1)   EQU PZ
)@@G@@   1                      . TURN ON IMMEDIATE 'FOR' FLAG    @D@@@@UV(1) QA
)@@G@@  EQUF   IV(1),,XU              . AND SET U-SPEC@D@@@@G$$L34  NAME      QB
)@@G@@                    . SET OPCODE JGD@G@@@@W(1)    EQU    0+JGD          QC
)@@G@@        . ADD ZERO TO OVERRIDE OPCODE EQU @G@@@@ GO G$$L39              QD
)@@G@@              . THEN GO GLOBALIZE THE OPCODE    @F@@@@.                 QE
)@@G@@            OP CAN'T BE JGD, MUST BE TLEM\JMGI  @]@@@@G$$L35  NAME@G@@@@QF
)@@G@@ DO (FI(2)=VI)++(FI(3)=VI)++(FI(4)=VI) , G$$EFL 2,3 . REQUIRE ALL SPECS QG
)@@G@@@D@@@@W(1)    EQU    0+TLEM                 . ASSUME TLEM   @F@@@@ DO IMQH
)@@G@@(3)**(IV(3)=0) ,W(1) EQU 0+JMGI . UNLESS TO IMMEDIATE ZERO  @[@@@@.     QI
)@@G@@@I@@@@G$$L39  NAME                          . END DETERMINATION OF INSTRQJ
)@@G@@ SPECIFICATION    @F@@@@P*(VI,1) EQU   W(1)                   . FORCE OPQK
)@@G@@CODE SPEC FIELD   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.        SET LOOP SENSE AND FLAG IF QL
)@@G@@CODE AT BOTTOM OF LOOP REQUIRED     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$L40  NAME@F@@@@QM
)@@G@@ DO 1-(W(1)=JGD) , GO G$$L41          . IF NOT JGD, WE MUST FARBLE@F@@@@QN
)@@G@@FI*(6)  EQU    1                      . ELSE MARK SENSE KNOWN     @I@@@@QO
)@@G@@FI*(5)  EQU    1                      . SET FLAG THAT CODE WILL APPEAR AQP
)@@G@@T BOTTOM    @D@@@@ GO G$$L49                            . AND WE'RE DONEQQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. COMPUTE SIGN/SENSE FOR JMGI, TLEM LOOPS, AND CHECK TQR
)@@G@@ERMINATION  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L41  NAME                          . NOQS
)@@G@@T JGD, DETERMINE SENSE THE HARD WAY @H@@@@USS     EQU    (P(FI(4),5)=UP)QT
)@@G@@-(P(FI(4),5)=DOWN) . SET USER SUPPLIED SIGN     @D@@@@BYS     EQU    IM(QU
)@@G@@4)*(1-2*(IV(4)<0))  . SIGN FROM 'BY'@F@@@@FTS     EQU    (IM(2)**IM(3))*QV
)@@G@@(1-2*(IV(2)>IV(3))) . FROMTO SIGN   @G@@@@ DO (FTS*BYS)=-1 , G$$EFL 2,5 QW
)@@G@@            . N.G. IF SIGNS DON'T AGREE   @E@@@@MYS     EQU    FTS+BYS  QX
)@@G@@              . GET MY OWN SIGN FLAG@F@@@@ DO (MYS*USS)=-1 , G$$EFL 2,6 QY
)@@G@@            . BETTER AGREE WITH HIS @F@@@@SIGN    EQU    MYS+USS        QZ
)@@G@@        . GET THE SIGN WE'LL USE    @F@@@@FI*(6)  EQU    1-(SIGN=0)     RA
)@@G@@        . ON IF WE KNOW LOOP SENSE  @H@@@@P*(VI,3) EQU   SIGN           RB
)@@G@@        . REMEMBER FOR BOTTOM OF LOOP USAGE     @G@@@@FI*(5) EQU (SIGN=0RC
)@@G@@)++((W(1)=TLEM)**(SIGN>0))++((W(1)=JMGI)**(SIGN<0))   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@RD
)@@G@@. WATCH OUT FOR AX/ANX: TERMINATION CONDITION MAY NOT PASS THRU ZERO    RE
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO (W(1)=TLEM)**IM(2)**IM(3)**IM(4) , ; IF TLEM AND IRF
)@@G@@MMEDIATE    @F@@@@ DO (IV(2)*(IV(3)+IV(4)))<0 , G$$EFL 2,4 . LOOP PASSESRG
)@@G@@ THRU ZERO  @I@@@@G$$L49  NAME                          . END OF SENSE ARH
)@@G@@ND PREFERENCE DETERMINATIO    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. GENERATE REGISTER INITRI
)@@G@@IAL LOAD CODE, IF ANY   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@IMOP      EQU       G$FLAG(K,2RJ
)@@G@@1)>0    . IMMEDIATE OPTIMIZE FLAG (ZERO ON PASS 1)    @H@@@@ DO FI(1)=VIRK
)@@G@@ , GO G$$L51              . IF 'FOR' NOT GIVEN, GO DO FROM/BY     @G@@@@RL
)@@G@@RR      EQU    027*(P(VI,2)<A4)+023*(P(VI,2)>(R1-1)) . OPCODE IF X/R REGRM
)@@G@@@B@@@@RA      EQU    077**(0+P(VI,2)-(RR=0)*A0) @G@@@@        I$     RR+RN
)@@G@@010*(RR=0),,RA,,,UV(1)-IMOP . LOAD COUNT REGISTER     @G@@@@G$FLAG**(K,2RO
)@@G@@1) EQU IM(1)              . SET IMMEDIATE OPTIMIZATION FLAG @F@@@@ DO 1 RP
)@@G@@, END                           . END OF REG LOAD GENERATION@[@@@@.     RQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@G$$L51  NAME                          . HERE TO LOAD REG USING FRORR
)@@G@@M/BY SPECS  @G@@@@ DO FI(2)=VI , END                    . NO LOAD IF 'FRRS
)@@G@@OM' FIELD ABSENT  @G@@@@ DO FI(4)=VI , G$$EFL 2,7                 . ERRORT
)@@G@@R IF 'FROM' BUT NO 'BY' @H@@@@ DO IM(4) , GO G$$L52                 . IFRU
)@@G@@ 'BY' IMMEDIATE, GO USE AS A LITERAL@E@@@@        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,RV
)@@G@@UV(2)   . LX WITH FROMVAL     @H@@@@        I$     025,,P(VI,2),,,UV(4) RW
)@@G@@  . ANX STEP TO COMPENSATE FOR INCR AT TOP@G@@@@        I$     046,,P(VIRX
)@@G@@,2),,,UV(4)   . LXI STEP TO SET UP INCREMENT    @F@@@@ DO 1 , END       RY
)@@G@@                    . END OF REG INITIALIZATION @I@@@@G$$L52  NAME      RZ
)@@G@@                    . IF 'BY' IMMEDIATE, LITERALS CAN BE USED-    @F@@@@SA
)@@G@@        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,(+IV(4),0+IV(2)*IM(2)-IV(4)) . LX   @D@@@@SB
)@@G@@ DO IM(2)=0 , I$ 024,,P(VI,2),,,UV(2) . AX FROMVAL    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@SC
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************SD
)@@G@@********************************    @F@@@@.     *                       SE
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     *   G$$LGE : GENERATE COSF
)@@G@@DE FOR <LOOP CONTROL> FIELDS   *    @F@@@@.     *                       SG
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     ************************SH
)@@G@@********************************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @I@@@@Q     SI
)@@G@@  PROC   *2                     . PF'S: 'VARY','TO','BY'  JUMPTARG,TOP/BSJ
)@@G@@OT    @#@@@@G$$LGE*  NAME     @G@@@@VI      EQU    Q(1,1)               SK
)@@G@@  . INDEX IN P OF VARY SPEC FIELD   @E@@@@TI      EQU    Q(1,2)         SL
)@@G@@        . INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD @E@@@@BI      EQU    Q(1,3)               SM
)@@G@@  . INDEX OF 'BY' FIELD @E@@@@F       EQU    P(VI,1)                . FUSN
)@@G@@NCTION REQUESTED  @H@@@@ATTOP     EQU       Q(2,2)            . ON IF BESO
)@@G@@ING CALLED AT TOP OF LOOP     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO F=LOOKFOR , GO G$$L8SP
)@@G@@0             . SPECIAL HANDLING FOR SEARCHING  @F@@@@ DO F=JGD , G$$FJASQ
)@@G@@ 070,P(VI,2),,,Q(2,1) . JUMP TO KEEP LOOPING    @G@@@@ DO F=JGD , END   SR
)@@G@@                    . FOR JGD, THAT'S ALL THERE IS    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@SS
)@@G@@. TLEM/JMGI ---   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@JMF     EQU    F=JMGI               ST
)@@G@@  . TRUE IF FUNC IS JMGI@G@@@@OLAP    EQU    P(VI,2)>X11            . ONSU
)@@G@@ IF LOOP CTL REG IS OVERLAPPED@G@@@@SENU    EQU    (P(VI,3)=0)**(ATTOP=0SV
)@@G@@) . ON AT BOTTOM AND UNKNOWN SENSE  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO SENU**(1-OLAP)SW
)@@G@@ , I$ 060+JMF,,,,,P(VI,2) . TP(TLEM) TN(JMGI) ON REG  @G@@@@ DO SENU , ISX
)@@G@@$ 074,04-OLAP*(JMF+1),OLAP*P(VI,2),,,G$LABL(K,2) . J JN JP  @[@@@@.     SY
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO JMF , GO G$$L70 . JMGI LOOPS ARE SIMPLE     @H@@@@TUHI      EQSZ
)@@G@@U       3*(P(TI,2)<0)+2*P(TI,*3)+P(TI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON  @D@@@@TA
)@@G@@TU      EQU    + (I$ 0,P(TI,4),,P(TI,3),TUHI,P(TI,2)) @H@@@@BUHI      EQTB
)@@G@@U       3*(P(BI,2)<0)+2*P(BI,*3)+P(BI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON  @D@@@@TC
)@@G@@BU      EQU    + (I$ 0,P(BI,4),,P(BI,3),BUHI,P(BI,2)) @F@@@@ DO ATTOP , TD
)@@G@@I$ 074,06,0,P(VI,2),2,0   . AT TOP AX INCR WITH A NOP @E@@@@          I$TE
)@@G@@        047,,P(VI,2),,,TU . TLEM ON 'TO' FIELD  @B@@@@        I$     074TF
)@@G@@,04,,,,Q(2,1) . JUMP    @G@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 025,,P(VI,2),,,BU      . UNTG
)@@G@@DO FUDGE WITH ANX OF INCR     @E@@@@ DO 1 , END                         TH
)@@G@@  . THAT'S ALL FOR TLEM @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. HANDLE JMGI LOOPS (WHICH TERTI
)@@G@@MINATE AT ZERO)   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$L70    NAME    @F@@@@ DO ATTOP , TJ
)@@G@@I$ 051,017,0,P(VI,2),,0 . TNZ REG (LAST TIME CHECK)   @B@@@@ DO ATTOP , TK
)@@G@@I$ 074,04,,,,Q(2,1)       .   @C@@@@        I$     074,012,P(VI,2),,,Q(2TL
)@@G@@,1) . JMGI  @#@@@@ DO 1 , END .     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. HANDLE SEARCH/MATM
)@@G@@SKED SEARCH. NOTE: SINCE THIS IS ALWAYS CALLED  @E@@@@. AT THE PHYSICAL TN
)@@G@@TOP OF THE LOOP BY REPEAT, THE VALUES OF  @B@@@@. THE ARRAY FI(N) ARE ALTO
)@@G@@WAYS AVAILABLE    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$L80  NAME@H@@@@IC      EQU    VI-TP
)@@G@@1                   . INDEX IN P OF CONDITION TEST FIELD    @H@@@@KWD   TQ
)@@G@@  EQU    P(IC,2)                . GET KEYWORD FROM CONDITION SPEC FIELD TR
)@@G@@@F@@@@MSF     EQU    FI(3)>VI               . ON IF SEARCH IS MASKED    TS
)@@G@@@G@@@@FUN     EQU    G$FJ(1,KWD,1)+010*(1-MSF)-052*MSF . MODIFY TO A SEATT
)@@G@@RCH   @G@@@@ DO   MSF , I$ 071,FUN,P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+P(IC,*3),P(IC,3)TU
)@@G@@+FI(6) . MS-@H@@@@ DO 1-MSF , I$ FUN,P(IC,5),P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+P(IC,*TV
)@@G@@3),P(IC,3)+FI(6) . S-   @E@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,Q(2,1)  . AT NOFITW
)@@G@@ND,  JUMP TO ATEND@[@@@@.     @]@@@@        END @ @@@@/. *** MISCELLANEOTX
)@@G@@US UTILITIES@[@@@@.     @H@@@@. PROCS TO CONSERVE TABLE SPACE BY SAVING TY
)@@G@@ARGUMENTS IN RE-USABLE ARRAY SPACE  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          PROC    TZ
)@@G@@  *0  @I@@@@G$$SVA* NAME                          . SAVE ARRAY P IN STANUA
)@@G@@DARD ARGUMENT ARRAY     @F@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(3)+1        . BUUB
)@@G@@MP ARG PUSHDOWN LEVEL   @D@@@@G$CTR**(3) EQU K                      . SAUC
)@@G@@VE THE LEVEL@^@@@@G$ARGS**(K) EQU +P-1    @A@@@@N DO P-1 ,G$ARGS**(K,N) UD
)@@G@@EQU +0+P(N) @C@@@@N DO P-1 ,M DO P(N) ,G$ARGS**(K,N,M) EQU +P(N,M)@#@@@@UE
)@@G@@          END     @D@@@@/. TURN ASSEMBLER MNEMONICS FOR JUMP INSTRS INTOUF
)@@G@@ TRASH@[@@@@.     @#@@@@Q         PROC    @H@@@@G$JELLY* NAME           UG
)@@G@@              . TURN THE WORLD INTO A QUIVVERING MASS @[@@@@.     @D@@@@UH
)@@G@@. THE ROLE OF THIS PROC IS MERELY TO GET THE PROC     @D@@@@. WHICH FOLLUI
)@@G@@OWS THIS DEFINED AT THE PROGRAM LEVEL     @E@@@@. IT CANNOT HAVE ITS OWNUJ
)@@G@@ ENTRY POINTS OR ELSE THE ASSEMBLER @D@@@@. WOULD BE DESTROYED FOR NON-SUK
)@@G@@TRUCTURED ASSEMBLIES.   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@P       PROC   *1,1           UL
)@@G@@        . A SEPERATE PROC TO AVOID NAMING CONFLICT    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@UM
)@@G@@. JGD AND JMGI ARE SPECIAL CASES, ALLOWED IF ONLY DOING ARITHMETIC@[@@@@UN
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@JGD***  NAME   - 1@#@@@@NEXTI   EQU    $+1@H@@@@COUNT   EQU UO
)@@G@@   (P(1,2)=NEXTI)**(P(1)<3)**(P(1,*2)=0) . ON IF ONLY COUNTING    @B@@@@UP
)@@G@@ DO 1-COUNT , G$$IFL                  .   @E@@@@        G$$FJA 070,P(1,1UQ
)@@G@@),P(1,3),2*P(1,*3)+P(1,*2),P(1,2)   @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @F@@@@UR
)@@G@@JMGI*** NAME   012                    . JMGI IS A SPECIAL CASE--  @#@@@@US
)@@G@@NEXTI   EQU    $+1@H@@@@COUNT   EQU    (P(1,2)=NEXTI)**(P(1)<3)**(P(1,*2UT
)@@G@@)=0) . ON IF ONLY COUNTING    @^@@@@ DO 1-COUNT , G$$IFL    @F@@@@      UU
)@@G@@  I$     074,P(0,0),P(1,1),P(1,3),2*P(1,*3)+P(1,*2),P(1,2)  @]@@@@ DO 1 UV
)@@G@@, END @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. ALL REMAINING INSTRUCTIONS WHICH CAN CAUSE CONUW
)@@G@@TROL XFER ARE 'INOPERATIVE'   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@TEP***  NAME   044      UX
)@@G@@              . TESTS   @#@@@@TOP***  NAME   045@#@@@@TLEM*** NAME   047UY
)@@G@@@#@@@@TNGM*** NAME   047@#@@@@TZ***   NAME   050@#@@@@TNZ***  NAME   051UZ
)@@G@@@#@@@@TE***   NAME   052@#@@@@TNE***  NAME   053@#@@@@TLE***  NAME   054VA
)@@G@@@#@@@@TNG***  NAME   054@#@@@@TG***   NAME   055@#@@@@TW***   NAME   056VB
)@@G@@@#@@@@TNW***  NAME   057@#@@@@TP***   NAME   060@#@@@@TN***   NAME   061VC
)@@G@@@C@@@@SE***   NAME   062                    . SEARCHES@#@@@@SNE***  NAMEVD
)@@G@@   063@#@@@@SLE***  NAME   064@#@@@@SNG***  NAME   064@#@@@@SG***   NAMEVE
)@@G@@   065@#@@@@SW***   NAME   066@#@@@@SNW***  NAME   067@H@@@@MSE***  NAMEVF
)@@G@@   000                    . DOUBLE PRECISION AND MASKED SEARCH    @#@@@@VG
)@@G@@MSNE*** NAME   001@#@@@@MSLE*** NAME   002@#@@@@MSNG*** NAME   002@#@@@@VH
)@@G@@MSG***  NAME   003@#@@@@MSW***  NAME   004@#@@@@MSNW*** NAME   005@#@@@@VI
)@@G@@MASL*** NAME   006@#@@@@MASG*** NAME   007@#@@@@DJZ***  NAME   016@#@@@@VJ
)@@G@@DTE***  NAME   017@H@@@@JPS***  NAME   002                    . OTHER INVK
)@@G@@STRS WITH FORCED J-FIELDS     @#@@@@JNS***  NAME   003@F@@@@J***    NAMEVL
)@@G@@   004                    . JUMPS WITH FORCED A-FIELDS@#@@@@HJ***   NAMEVM

)@@G@@              . FUNCT=072     @F@@@@JZ***   NAME   000                  VQ
)@@G@@  . JUMPS WITH NORMAL A-FIELDS@#@@@@JNZ***  NAME   001@#@@@@JP***   NAMEVR

)@@G@@ MASK @#@@@@JK***   NAME   004@#@@@@HJK***  NAME   005@D@@@@JIC***  NAMEVU

)@@G@@JFC***  NAME   012@E@@@@        G$$IFL                        . GENERATEVW
)@@G@@ I-FLAG     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. PUMPKINIZE ILLEGAL ER VX
)@@G@@INDICES     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@READ$**   EQU  01234567 @^@@@@READA$**  EQVY
)@@G@@U  01234567 @^@@@@TREAD$**  EQU  01234567 @^@@@@AREAD$**  EQU  01234567 VZ

)@@G@@        END                           . END OF SILLYPUTTY PROC    @D@@@@WD
)@@G@@/. THINGS TO ADD IN THE FUTURE-- (NOTES TO MYSELF)-   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@WE
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.      ENDBEG    SPAWNING AT,<LABEL> WITH IOXI$ (AND MAKE IOWF
)@@G@@XI N.G.)    @G@@@@.                   SINCE IOXI IS ANOTHER WAY OF TERMIWG
)@@G@@NATING AN ACTIVITY@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.      SPAWN AT,<LABEL> NAME,<NAME-SWH
)@@G@@TASH> @G@@@@.                      FORK$ TO AN ACTIVITY AND ACQUIRE A NAWI
)@@G@@ME FOR IT   @G@@@@.                      NOTE THAT NAME IS OWNED BY SPAWWJ
)@@G@@NNER, NOT SPAWNEE @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.      DEFINITIONS OF 'CRITICAL' BLOWK
)@@G@@CKS, BOUNDED BY TS, CTS ON DATA     @E@@@@.      AND/OR IMPLEMENTATION OWL
)@@G@@F P/V OR TS QUEUEING USAGE    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. FINISH FALWM
)@@G@@LTHRU OPTIMIZATION FOR JMGI/TLEM LOOPS    @C@@@@. FLAG AND SURPRESS CODEWN
)@@G@@ FOR 0 EXECUTION LOOPS  @C@@@@. FLAG AND SURPRESS CODE FOR IMPOSSIBLE TEWO
)@@G@@STS   @F@@@@. DO DOUBLE LINEITEM IF-ELSE: TEST/INST1/NOTEST/INST2, IF ANWP
)@@G@@D     @E@@@@.   ONLY IF NO SIDE EFFECTS AND INST1 DOES NOT ALTER CONTEXTWQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@. CASENTRY CALLING: NORMAL 1,X11 AND 1 INSTR 0,X11 SHOULD SKIP    WR
)@@G@@@D@@@@. DO SPARSE CASES WITH TESTS INSTEAD OF JUMPTABLES    @E@@@@. DO SWS
)@@G@@AVE/LOAD AREGS AT BEGIN.ENDBEG USING DL,DS IF POSSIBLE@B@@@@. OPTIMIZE JWT
)@@G@@UMPS ACROSS BLOCK BOUNDARIES  @F@@@@          PROC                      WU
)@@G@@  . THIS IS A CHARLIE MCCARTHY@E@@@@          END                       WV
)@@G@@  . AND A MORTIMER SNERD___S WITH FORCED J-FIELDS     @#@@@@JNS***  NAMEWW
)@@G@@   003@F@@@@J***    NAME   004                  *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@].     WX
)@@G@@@A@@@].         SCHEDULING PRIMITIVES     @[@@@].     @F@@@].           WY
)@@G@@                            JOHN WALKER   APRIL 1972  @[@@@].     @#@@@]WZ
)@@G@@          AXR$    @#@@@]          DEFUNCT$@^@@@]          LIT$      1   XA
)@@G@@@#@@@]          SCHDEF  @[@@@].     @F@@@].         THE FOLLOWING PARAMEXB
)@@G@@TERS CONFIGURE THE SCHEDULER BY     @F@@@].         SELECTING THOSE ROUTXC
)@@G@@INES WHICH ARE NEEDED BY THE USER.  @[@@@].     @F@@@]PMAYN     EQU     XD
)@@G@@  ;                   ONE IF 'PMAY' IS NEEDED   @^@@@]                  XE
)@@G@@  1   @[@@@].     @G@@@]IRN       EQU       ;                   ONE IF IXF
)@@G@@NSERT / REMOVE NEEDED   @^@@@]                    1   @[@@[A.     @E@@[AXG
)@@G@@PUSHN     EQU       ;                   ONE IF PUSH NEEDED  @^@@[A      XH
)@@G@@              1   @[@@@].     @F@@@]BBN       EQU       ;               XI
)@@G@@    ONE IF PUT / GET NEEDED   @^@@@]                    1   @[@@@].     XJ
)@@G@@@F@@@]FEN       EQU       ;                   ONE IF FORK / EXIT NEEDED XK
)@@G@@@^@^@]                    1   @^@@@^                    0   @[@@@].     XL
)@@G@@@H@@@]ACTN      EQU       ;                   ONE IF ACTIVITY NAMING IN XM
)@@G@@TSQ MODE    @^@@@]                    1   @[@@@].     @G@@@].         THXN
)@@G@@E PARAMETER 'DYNQ' SHOULD BE SET NONZERO IF THE SUBROUTINE  @G@@@].     XO
)@@G@@    'INITQ' IS NEEDED TO DYNAMICALLY INITIALISE AN INSERT / REMOVE@#@@@]XP
)@@G@@.         QUEUE.  @[@@@].     @F@@@]DYNQ      EQU       ;               XQ
)@@G@@    ONE TO GENERATE INITQ     @^@@@]                    1   @[@@@].     XR
)@@G@@@G@@@].         THE PARAMETER 'DYNPVQ' SHOULD BE SET NONZERO IF THE SUBRXS
)@@G@@OUTINE@G@@@].         'INITPVQ' IS NEEDED TO DYNAMICALLY INITIALISE A P/XT
)@@G@@V QUEUE.    @[@@@].     @F@@@]DYNPVQ    EQU       ;                   ONXU
)@@G@@E TO GENERATE INITPVQ   @^@@@]                    1   @[@@@].     @G@@@]XV
)@@G@@.         THE PARAMETER 'DYNBB' SHOULD BE SET NONZERO IF THE SUBROUTINE XW
)@@G@@@G@@@].         'INITBB' IS NEEDED TO DYNAMICALLY INITIALISE A BOUNDED BXX
)@@G@@UFFER.@G@@@].         SETTING THIS PARAMETER NONZERO ALSO CAUSES THE GENXY
)@@G@@ERATION     @G@@@].         OF 'INITQ' AND 'INITPVQ' REGARDLESS OF THE VXZ
)@@G@@ALUE OF THE TAGS  @A@@@].         'DYNQ' AND 'DYNPVQ' ABOVE.@[@@@].     YA
)@@G@@@H@@@]DYNBB     EQU       ;                   ONE TO GENERATE INITBB, INYB
)@@G@@ITQ, INITPVQ@^@@@]                    1   @[@@@].     @^@^@]            YC
)@@G@@        1   @[@@@].     @A@@@]ACTNAM    EQU       ACTN++(TSQ=0)   @[@@@]YD
)@@G@@.     @^@@@].         DATA FORMATS  @[@@@].     @[@@@].     @ @@@]      YE
)@@G@@    ON         TSQ=0    @[@@@].     @A@@@].         ACTIVITY SWITCHLIST YF
)@@G@@ENTRY @[@@@].     @D@@@]PHNAME    EQUF      QL-1                ACTIVITYYG
)@@G@@ NAME @E@@@]PHL       EQU       QL                  ACTIVITY SWL LENGTH YH
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @ @@@]          OFF       TSQ=0     @[@@@#.     @B@@@#.     YI
)@@G@@    CLEAR TEST AND SET INSTRUCTION  @[@@@#.     @^@@@#P         PROC    YJ
)@@G@@  *1  @^@@@#CTS*      NAME      0   @C@@@#          DO        TSQ=0 , SZYK
)@@G@@,S1 P(1,1),P(1,2) @C@@@#          DO        TSQ , C$TS P(1,1),P(1,2)    YL
)@@G@@@#@@@#          END     @[@@@]/.    @[@@@].     @ @@@].         P AND V YM
)@@G@@FUNCTIONS   @[@@@].     @[@@@].     @ @@@].         DIJKSTRA P FUNCTION YN
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @[@@@].     @ @@@].         LA,U      A0,<QUEUE>@ @@@].     YO
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,P     @D@@@].         <RETURN>                      A2YP
)@@G@@ DESTROYED  @[@@@].     @D@@@]P*        TS        QHEAD,A0            LOYQ
)@@G@@CK THE QUEUE@E@@@]          LX        A2,QN,A0            LOAD QUEUE COUYR
)@@G@@NT    @E@@@]          ANX,U     A2,1                BACK UP THE COUNT   YS
)@@G@@@G@@@]          SX        A2,QN,A0            REPLACE THE COUNT IN THE QYT
)@@G@@UEUE  @G@@@]          TN        A2                  DO WE NEED TO DEACTIYU
)@@G@@VATE HIM ?  @F@@@]          J         PDONE               NO.  SKIP DEACYV
)@@G@@TIVATION    @ @@@]          ON        TSQ=0     @F@@@]          LX      YW
)@@G@@  A2,QHL,A0           LOAD BACK LINK OF QUEUE   @G@@@]          SX      YX
)@@G@@  A2,QHL,X4           PUT INTO BACK LINK OF ACTIVITY  @G@@@]          SXYY
)@@G@@        X4,QFL,A2           CHAIN ACTIVITY TO LAST ACTIVITY @F@@@]      YZ
)@@G@@    SA        A0,QFL,X4           CHAIN HEAD TO NEW ACTIVITY@H@@@]      ZA
)@@G@@    SX        X4,QHL,A0           MAKE THE NEW ACTIVITY LAST ON QUEUE   ZB
)@@G@@@G@@@]          CTS       QHEAD,A0            RELEASE PROTECTION ON QUEUZC
)@@G@@E HEAD@E@@@]          DACT$     .                   DEACTIVATE PROCESS  ZD
)@@G@@@#@@@]          OFF     @^@@@]          ON        TSQ @D@@@]          C$ZE
)@@G@@TSQ     QHEAD,A0            WAIT FOR C$TSA@#@@@]          OFF     @F@@@]ZF
)@@G@@          J         0,X11               RETURN AFTER ACTIVATION   @[@@@]ZG
)@@G@@.     @E@@@]PDONE     CTS       QHEAD,A0            UNLOCK THE QUEUE    ZH
)@@G@@@C@@@]          J         0,X11               RETURN  @[@@@].     @[@@@]ZI
)@@G@@.     @ @@@].         DIJKSTRA V FUNCTION @[@@@].     @ @@@].         LAZJ
)@@G@@,U      A0,<QUEUE>@ @@@].         LMJ       X11,V     @G@@@].         <RZK
)@@G@@ETURN>                      A2 DESTROYED; A3 IFF NOT TSQ.   @[@@@].     ZL
)@@G@@@E@@@]V*        TS        QHEAD,A0            LOCK THE QUEUE HEAD @E@@@]ZM
)@@G@@          LX        A2,QN,A0            LOAD QUEUE COUNT    @D@@@]      ZN
)@@G@@    AX,U      A2,1                COUNT IT UP   @E@@@]          SX      ZO
)@@G@@  A2,QN,A0            UPDATE QUEUE COUNT  @E@@@]          ANX,U     A2,1ZP
)@@G@@                BACK UP THE COUNT   @G@@@]          TN        A2        ZQ
)@@G@@          DID WE WAKE UP AN ACTIVITY ?    @E@@@]          J         VDONZR
)@@G@@E               NO.  SKIP THIS STUFF@ @@@]          ON        TSQ=0     ZS
)@@G@@@F@@@]          LX        A2,QFL,A0           GET FIRST WAITING PROCESS ZT
)@@G@@@F@@@]          LX        A3,QFL,A2           GET NEXT WAITING PROCESS  ZU
)@@G@@@E@@@]          SX        A3,QFL,A0           CHAIN NEXT TO HEAD  @G@@@]ZV
)@@G@@          SA        A0,QHL,A3           POINT NEW FIRST ONE TO HEAD     ZW
)@@G@@@C@@@]          SA        A0,A3               SAVE A0 @F@@@]          LAZX
)@@G@@        A0,PHNAME,A2        LOAD PROCESS HEADER NAME  @E@@@]          ACZY
)@@G@@T$      .                   ACTIVATE THE PROCESS@D@@@]          LA      ZZ
)@@G@@  A0,A3               RESTORE NAME  @#@@@]          OFF     @^@@@]      AA
)@@G@@    ON        TSQ @F@@@]          C$TSA     QHEAD,A0            ACTIVATEAB
)@@G@@ THE FIRST ONE.   @C@@@]          J         0,X11               RETURN. AC
)@@G@@@#@@@]          OFF     @E@@@]VDONE     CTS       QHEAD,A0            UNAD
)@@G@@LOCK THE QUEUE    @C@@@]          J         0,X11               RETURN  AE
)@@G@@@[@@@]/.    @[@@@].     @A@@@].         CONDITIONAL P FUNCTION    @[@@@]AF
)@@G@@.     @ @@@].         LA,U      A0,<QUEUE>@ @@@].         LMJ       X11,AG
)@@G@@PMAY  @F@@@].         <FAILED RETURN>                (YOU DON'T GO TO SLAH
)@@G@@EEP)  @ @@@].         <NORMAL RETURN>     @[@@@].     @ @@@]          ONAI
)@@G@@        PMAYN     @D@@@]PMAY$*    TS        QHEAD,A0            LOCK THEAJ
)@@G@@ QUEUE@D@@@]          LX        A2,QN,A0            LOAD THE COUNT@D@@@]AK
)@@G@@          ANX,U     A2,1                COUNT IT DOWN @F@@@]          TPAL
)@@G@@        A2                  IS IT POSITIVE OR ZERO ?  @D@@@]          J AM
)@@G@@        PMAYF               NO.  IT FAILED@G@@@]          SX        A2,QAN
)@@G@@N,A0            STORE OUT DECREMENTED COUNT     @E@@@]          CTS     AO
)@@G@@  QHEAD,A0            UNLOCK THE QUEUE    @F@@@]          J         1,X1AP
)@@G@@1               RETURN TO NORMAL RETURN   @[@@@].     @E@@@]PMAYF     CTAQ
)@@G@@S       QHEAD,A0            UNLOCK THE QUEUE    @E@@@]          J       AR
)@@G@@  0,X11               TAKE FAILED RETURN  @ @@@]          OFF       PMAYAS
)@@G@@N     @[@@@]/.    @[@@@].     @B@@@].         QUEUE MANIPULATION PRIMITIAT
)@@G@@VES   @[@@@].     @^@@@].         QUEUE INSERT  @[@@@].     @ @@@].     AU
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,<QUEUE>@ @@@].         LA,U      A1,<DATA> @ @@@].     AV
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,INSERT@D@@@].         <RETURN>                      A2AW
)@@G@@ DESTROYED  @[@@@].     @ @@@]          ON        IRN++BBN  @D@@@]INSERTAX
)@@G@@*   TS        QHEAD,A0            LOCK THE QUEUE@F@@@]          LX      AY
)@@G@@  A2,QHL,A0           A2 = LAST BUFFER ON QUEUE @F@@@]          SX      AZ
)@@G@@  A2,QHL,A1           POINT NEW ONE TO LAST     @G@@@]          SA      BA
)@@G@@  A1,QFL,A2           SET FORWARD LINK OF LAST ONE    @F@@@]          SABB
)@@G@@        A0,QFL,A1           POINT NEW ONE TO HEAD     @F@@@]          SABC
)@@G@@        A1,QHL,A0           POINT HEAD TO NEW ONE     @E@@@]          CTBD
)@@G@@S       QHEAD,A0            UNLOCK THE QUEUE    @C@@@]          J       BE
)@@G@@  0,X11               RETURN  @[@@@].     @[@@@].     @^@@@].         QUBF
)@@G@@EUE REMOVE  @[@@@].     @ @@@].         LA,U      A0,<QUEUE>@ @@@].     BG
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,REMOVE@D@@@].         <RETURN>                      A1BH
)@@G@@ = DATA     @D@@@].                                       A2 DESTROYED  BI
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @D@@@]REMOVE*   TS        QHEAD,A0            LOCK THE QUEUEBJ
)@@G@@@G@@@]          LA        A1,QFL,A0           LOAD FIRST ALLOCATED PACKEBK
)@@G@@T     @E@@@]          LX        A2,QFL,A1           GET NEXT BUFFER     BL
)@@G@@@E@@@]          SX        A2,QFL,A0           POINT HEAD TO IT    @F@@@]BM
)@@G@@          SA        A0,QHL,A2           POINT IT BACK TO HEAD     @E@@@]BN
)@@G@@          CTS       QHEAD,A0            UNLOCK THE HEAD     @C@@@]      BO
)@@G@@    J         0,X11               RETURN  @ @@@]          OFF       IRN+BP
)@@G@@+BBN  @[@@[A.     @[@@[A.     @B@@[A.         QUEUE PUSH (INSERT AT HEADBQ
)@@G@@)     @[@@[A.     @ @@[A.         LA,U      A0,<QUEUE>@ @@[A.         LABR
)@@G@@,U      A1,<DATA> @ @@[A.         LMJ       X11,PUSH  @D@@[A.         <RBS
)@@G@@ETURN>                      A2 DESTROYED  @[@@[A.     @ @@[A          ONBT
)@@G@@        PUSHN     @E@@[APUSH*     TS        QHEAD,A0            LOCK QUEBU
)@@G@@UE LINKS    @G@@[A          LX        A2,QFL,A0           LOAD LINK TO FBV
)@@G@@IRST DATA ITEM    @G@@[A          SX        A2,QFL,A1           ATTACH FBW
)@@G@@ORWARD CHAIN TO NEW ITEM@G@@[A          SA        A1,QHL,A2           POBX
)@@G@@INT BACKPOINTER TO NEW ITEM   @H@@[A          SA        A0,QHL,A1       BY
)@@G@@    SET BACKPOINTER OF NEW ITEM TO HEAD   @G@@[A          SA        A1,QBZ
)@@G@@FL,A0           MAKE NEW ITEM FIRST ON QUEUE    @E@@[A          CTS     CA
)@@G@@  QHEAD,A0            UNLOCK QUEUE LINKS  @E@@[A          J         0,X1CB
)@@G@@1               RETURN TO CALLER    @ @@[A          OFF       PUSHN     CC
)@@G@@@[@@@]/.    @[@@@].     @A@@@].         BOUNDED BUFFER OPERATIONS @[@@@]CD
)@@G@@.     @A@@@].         PUT ONTO BOUNDED BUFFER   @[@@@].     @B@@@].     CE
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,<BOUNDED BUFFER>   @ @@@].         LA,U      A1,<DATA> CF
)@@G@@@ @@@].         LMJ       A3,PUT    @E@@@].         <RETURN>            CG
)@@G@@          X11, A2 DESTROYED   @[@@@].     @^@@@]          ON        BBN CH
)@@G@@@F@@@]PUT*      AA,U      A0,QL*2             POINT TO 'QUEUE NOT FULL' CI
)@@G@@@D@@@]          LXI       X11,A3              SAVE RETURN.  @E@@@]      CJ
)@@G@@    P         .                   P 'QUEUE NOT FULL'  @E@@@]          ANCK
)@@G@@A,U     A0,QL*2             POINT TO DATA QUEUE @F@@@]          INSERT  CL
)@@G@@  .                   INSERT DATUM ON QUEUE     @F@@@]          AA,U    CM
)@@G@@  A0,QL               POINT TO QUEUE NOT EMPTY  @E@@@]          V       CN
)@@G@@  .                   V 'QUEUE NOT EMPTY' @F@@@]          ANA,U     A0,QCO
)@@G@@L               POINT BACK TO BEGINNING   @E@@@]          L         A3,XCP
)@@G@@11              RETURN IN UPPER(A3) @F@@@]          SSL       A3,18     CQ
)@@G@@          PUT IT SOMEWHERE USEFUL.  @C@@@]          J         0,A3      CR
)@@G@@          RETURN  @[@@@].     @A@@@].         BOUNDED BUFFER ITEM GET   CS
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @B@@@].         LA,U      A0,<BOUNDED BUFFER>   @ @@@].     CT
)@@G@@    LMJ       A3,GET    @D@@@].         <RETURN>                      A1CU
)@@G@@ = <DATA>   @E@@@].                                       X11, A2 DESTROCV
)@@G@@YED   @[@@@].     @F@@@]GET*      AA,U      A0,QL               POINT TOCW
)@@G@@ QUEUE NOT EMPTY  @D@@@]          LXI       X11,A3              SAVE RETCX
)@@G@@URN.  @E@@@]          P         .                   P 'QUEUE NOT EMPTY' CY
)@@G@@@F@@@]          ANA,U     A0,QL               BACK UP TO DATA QUEUE     CZ
)@@G@@@G@@@]          REMOVE    .                   REMOVE THE ITEM FROM THE QDA
)@@G@@UEUE  @F@@@]          AA,U      A0,QL*2             POINT TO QUEUE NOT FDB
)@@G@@ULL   @E@@@]          V         .                   V 'QUEUE NOT FULL'  DC
)@@G@@@H@@@]          ANA,U     A0,QL*2             BACK UP TO HEAD OF BOUNDEDDD
)@@G@@ BUFFER     @F@@@]          L         A3,X11              RETURN IS IN IDE
)@@G@@NCREMENT.   @D@@@]          SSL       A3,18               MOVE IT DOWN. DF
)@@G@@@C@@@]          J         0,A3                RETURN  @^@@@]          OFDG
)@@G@@F       BBN @[@@@]/.    @[@@@].     @A@@@].         CREATE / DESTROY ACTDH
)@@G@@IVITY @[@@@].     @A@@@].         CREATE A NEW ACTIVITY     @[@@@].     DI
)@@G@@@A@@@].         LA,U      A1,<ENTRY POINT>@ @@@].         LMJ       X11,DJ
)@@G@@FORK  @[@@@].     @^@@@]          ON        FEN @E@@@]FORK*     FORK$   DK
)@@G@@  FSETUP,1            GET A NEW ACTIVITY  @C@@@]          J         0,X1DL
)@@G@@1               RETURN  @[@@@].     @]@@@]FSETUP    . @ @@@]          ONDM
)@@G@@        TSQ=0     @F@@@]          BGET      PHL                 ALLOCATEDN
)@@G@@ A PROCESS HEADER.@G@@@]          LX,U      X4,,A0              LOAD RUNDO
)@@G@@NING SWITCHLIST POINTER @ @@@]          OFF       TSQ=0     @ @@@]      DP
)@@G@@    ON        ACTNAM    @I@@@]          LA,U      A0,,A1              USDQ
)@@G@@E ENTRY ADDRESS AS USER ACTIVITY NAME     @G@@@]          NAME$     .   DR
)@@G@@                ATTACH A NAME TO THE ACTIVITY   @ @@@]          ON      DS
)@@G@@  TSQ=0     @F@@@]          SA        A0,PHNAME,X4        SET ACTIVITY NDT
)@@G@@AME IN SWL  @ @@@]          OFF       TSQ=0     @ @@@]          OFF     DU
)@@G@@  ACTNAM    @E@@@]          J         0,A1                ENTER NEW ACTIDV
)@@G@@VITY  @[@@@].     @ @@@].         TERMINATE ACTIVITY  @[@@@].     @D@@@]DW
)@@G@@.         THE SWITCHLIST IS RELEASED BY THIS ROUTINE  @[@@@].     @[@@@]DX
)@@G@@EXIT*.@ @@@]          ON        TSQ=0     @F@@@]          BRELP     X4  DY
)@@G@@                RELEASE THE SWITCH LIST.  @#@@@]          OFF     @C@@@]DZ
)@@G@@          EXIT$     .                   BYE !   @[@@@].     @^@@@]      EA
)@@G@@    OFF       FEN @[@@@]/.    @[@@@].     @B@@@].         DYNAMIC QUEUE EB
)@@G@@INITIALISATION    @[@@@].     @[@@@].     @C@@@].         INITIALISE AN EC
)@@G@@INSERT / REMOVE QUEUE   @[@@@].     @ @ @].         LA,U      A1,<QUEUE>ED
)@@G@@@ @@@ .         LA,U      A0,<QUEUE>@ @@@].         LMJ       X11,INITQ EE
)@@G@@@D@ @].         <RETURN>                      A0 DESTROYED  @D@@@ .     EF
)@@G@@    <RETURN>                      A1 DESTROYED  @[@@@].     @A@@@]      EG
)@@G@@    ON        DYNQ++DYNBB     @G@ @]INITQ*    SA        A1,QFL,A1       EH
)@@G@@    POINT FORWARD LINK TO QUEUE     @G@@@ INITQ*    SA        A0,QFL,A0 EI
)@@G@@          POINT FORWARD LINK TO QUEUE     @F@ @]          SA        A1,QEJ
)@@G@@HL,A1           POINT BACK LINK TO QUEUE  @F@@@           SA        A0,QEK
)@@G@@HL,A0           POINT BACK LINK TO QUEUE  @ @@@]          ON        TSQ=EL
)@@G@@0     @G@ @]          SZ        QHEAD,A1            CLEAR TEST AND SET OEM
)@@G@@N QUEUE HEAD@G@@@           SZ        QHEAD,A0            CLEAR TEST ANDEN
)@@G@@ SET ON QUEUE HEAD@ @@@]          OFF       TSQ=0     @^@@@]          ONEO
)@@G@@        TSQ @F@#@]          LA        A0,(T$CELL )        LOAD A TEST ANEP
)@@G@@D SET CELL  @F@ @#          LA        A0,(T$CELL 0)       LOAD A TEST ANEQ
)@@G@@D SET CELL  @F@@@           LA        A1,(T$CELL 0)       LOAD A TEST ANER
)@@G@@D SET CELL  @F@ @]          SA        A0,QHEAD,A1         INITIALISE THEES
)@@G@@ QUEUE HEAD @F@@@           SA        A1,QHEAD,A0         INITIALISE THEET
)@@G@@ QUEUE HEAD @^@@@]          OFF       TSQ @E@@@]          J         0,X1EU
)@@G@@1               RETURN TO CALLER    @A@@@]          OFF       DYNQ++DYNBEV
)@@G@@B     @[@@@].     @[@@@].     @A@@@].         INITIALISE A P/V QUEUE    EW
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @ @ @].         LA,U      A0,<COUNT>@ @@@ .         LA,U    EX
)@@G@@  A1,<COUNT>@ @ @].         LA,U      A1,<QUEUE>@ @@@ .         LA,U    EY
)@@G@@  A0,<QUEUE>@A@@@].         LMJ       X11,INITPVQ     @#@@@].         <REZ
)@@G@@ETURN>@[@@@].     @A@@@]          ON        DYNPVQ++DYNBB   @E@ @]INITPVFA
)@@G@@Q*  SA        A0,QN,A1            SET COUNT IN QUEUE  @E@@@ INITPVQ*  SAFB
)@@G@@        A1,QN,A0            SET COUNT IN QUEUE  @ @@@]          ON      FC
)@@G@@  TSQ=0     @E@ @]          SZ,H1     QHEAD,A1            CLEAR TEST ANDFD
)@@G@@ SET  @E@@@           SZ,H1     QHEAD,A0            CLEAR TEST AND SET  FE
)@@G@@@F@ @]          SA        A1,QFL,A1           LINK FORWARD LINK TO QUEUEFF
)@@G@@@F@@@           SA        A0,QFL,A0           LINK FORWARD LINK TO QUEUEFG
)@@G@@@F@ @]          SA        A1,QHL,A1           LINK BACK LINK TO QUEUE   FH
)@@G@@@F@@@           SA        A0,QHL,A0           LINK BACK LINK TO QUEUE   FI
)@@G@@@ @@@]          OFF       TSQ=0     @^@@@]          ON        TSQ @F@#@]FJ
)@@G@@          LA        A0,(T$CELL )        LOAD A TEST AND SET CELL  @F@ @#FK
)@@G@@          LA        A0,(T$CELL 0)       LOAD A TEST AND SET CELL  @F@@@ FL
)@@G@@          LA        A1,(T$CELL 0)       LOAD A TEST AND SET CELL  @F@ @]FM
)@@G@@          SA        A0,QHEAD,A1         SET CELL IN QUEUE HEAD    @F@@@ FN
)@@G@@          SA        A1,QHEAD,A0         SET CELL IN QUEUE HEAD    @F@ @]FO
)@@G@@          LA        A0,QN,A1            RELOAD ORIGINAL COUNT     @F@@@ FP
)@@G@@          LA        A1,QN,A0            RELOAD ORIGINAL COUNT     @^@@@]FQ
)@@G@@          OFF       TSQ @E@@@]          J         0,X11               REFR
)@@G@@TURN TO CALLER    @A@@@]          OFF       DYNPVQ++DYNBB   @[@@@].     FS
)@@G@@@[@@@].     @B@@@].         INITIALISE A BOUNDED BUFFER     @[@@@].     FT
)@@G@@@F@ @].         LA,U      A0,<COUNT>          COUNT FOR NOT FULL QUEUE  FU
)@@G@@@F@@@ .         LA,U      A1,<COUNT>          COUNT FOR NOT FULL QUEUE  FV
)@@G@@@A@ @].         LA,U      A1,<BUFFER>     @A@@@ .         LA,U      A0,<FW
)@@G@@BUFFER>     @ @@@].         LMJ       X11,INITBB@F@ @].         <RETURN>FX
)@@G@@                      H1(X11), A0 DESTROYED     @F@@@ .         <RETURN>FY
)@@G@@                      H1(X11), A1 DESTROYED     @[@@@].     @ @@@]      FZ
)@@G@@    ON        DYNBB     @F@@@]INITBB*   LXI,U     X11,,X11            SAGA
)@@G@@VE ORIGINAL CALL ADDRESS@F@ @]          AA,U      A1,QL+QPL           ADGB
)@@G@@VANCE TO NOT FULL QUEUE @F@@@           AA,U      A0,QL+QPL           ADGC
)@@G@@VANCE TO NOT FULL QUEUE @H@^@]          LMJ       X11,INITPVQ         INGD
)@@G@@ITIALISE THE NOT FULL P/V QUEUE     @H@@@^          INITPVQ   .         GE
)@@G@@          INITIALISE THE NOT FULL P/V QUEUE     @G@ @]          ANA,U   GF
)@@G@@  A1,QPL              BACK UP TO THE NOT EMPTY QUEUE  @G@@@           ANGG
)@@G@@A,U     A0,QPL              BACK UP TO THE NOT EMPTY QUEUE  @G@ @]      GH
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0                  CLEAR COUNT FOR NOT EMPTY QUEUE @G@@@ GI
)@@G@@          LA,U      A1                  CLEAR COUNT FOR NOT EMPTY QUEUE GJ
)@@G@@@H@^@]          LMJ       X11,INITPVQ         INITIALISE THE NOT EMPTY PGK
)@@G@@/V QUEUE    @H@@@^          INITPVQ   .                   INITIALISE THEGL
)@@G@@ NOT EMPTY P/V QUEUE    @H@ @]          ANA,U     A1,QL               BAGM
)@@G@@CK UP TO DATA QUEUE AT BEGINNING    @H@@@           ANA,U     A0,QL     GN
)@@G@@          BACK UP TO DATA QUEUE AT BEGINNING    @F@@@]          LXM,U   GO
)@@G@@  X11                 CLEAR MODIFIER OF X11     @G@@@]          NOP     GP
)@@G@@  0,,*X11             RESTORE ORIGINAL CALL ADDRESS   @G@@@]          J GQ
)@@G@@        INITQ               GO INITIALISE THE DATA QUEUE    @ @@@]      GR
)@@G@@    OFF       DYNBB     @#@@@]          END     ___1,QHL,A1           LIGS
)@@G@@NK BACK LINK TO QUEUE   @F@@@           SA        A0,QHL,A0           LIGT
