)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @E@@@@.                 LC
)@@G@@           BUFFER ALLOCATION ROUTINES     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.           LD
)@@G@@          JULY 1972                     JOHN WALKER   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@LE
)@@G@@.                 THIS  ELEMENT CONSISTS OF ROUTINES TO ALLOCATE AND RELLF
)@@G@@EASE  @H@@@@.         VARIABLE  LENGTH BUFFERS.  BUFFERS ARE ALLOCATED FLG
)@@G@@ROM AND RETURNED  @H@@@@.         TO  A FREE SPACE POOL.  THIS SPACE MAYLH
)@@G@@ EXPAND AND CONTRACT DYNAMI-  @#@@@@.         CALLY.  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@LI
)@@G@@.         TO ALLOCATE A BUFFER:     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.                 LJ
)@@G@@LA,U      A0,<LENGTH REQUIRED>@A@@@@.                 LMJ       X11,BGETLK
)@@G@@@ @@@@.                 <RETURN>    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         UPON  RELL
)@@G@@TURN,  A0  CONTAINS  THE  ADDRESS OF THE FIRST WORD OF THE  @#@@@@.     LM
)@@G@@    BUFFER. @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         TO RELEASE A BUFFER:@[@@@@.     LN
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                 LA,U      A0,<ADDRESS OF BUFFER>    @A@@@@.     LO
)@@G@@            LMJ       X11,BREL@ @@@@.                 <RETURN>    @[@@@@LP
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@.         BOTH  ROUTINES  DESTROY  ONLY THE REGISTERS X11 ANLQ
)@@G@@D A0, AND MAY BE  @H@@@@.         CALLED  BY  ACTIVITIES RUNNING IN THE LR
)@@G@@MINOR SET OF REGISTERS.  THE  @H@@@@.         ROUTINES  ARE  QUARTER  WOLS
)@@G@@RD INSENSITIVE, AND MAY BE CALLED SIMUL-  @H@@@@.         TANEOUSLY  BY LT
)@@G@@MULTI-ACTIVITY PROGRAMS OR INCORPORATED INTO A REEN-  @ @@@@.         TRLU
)@@G@@ANT PROCESSOR.    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 THE  ABOVE  IS SUFLV
)@@G@@FICIENT INFORMATION TO INTELLIGENTLY USE  @H@@@@.         THE  BUFFER  ALW
)@@G@@LLOCATION PACKAGE.  THOSE OF YOU WHOSE BLOOD COURSES  @H@@@@.         ATLX
)@@G@@ THE THOUGHT OF THE UNKNOWN ARE NOW INVITED DOWN THE RABBIT HOLE  @H@@@@LY
)@@G@@.         TO LEARN HOW THIS THING OPERATES AND HOW TO CONFIGURE IT OPTIMLZ
)@@G@@ALLY  @ @@@@.         FOR AN APPLICATION. @[@@@@/.    @H@@@@.           MA
)@@G@@      EACH  BUFFER  IS PRECEDED BY TWO WORDS OF CONTROL INFORMA-  @G@@@@MB
)@@G@@.         TION.  THIS INFORMATION CONSISTS OF FOUR HALF WORD ITEMS:     MC
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                 SIZE      SIZE  OF THIS BUFFER INCLUMD
)@@G@@DING CONTROL@F@@@@.                           WORDS.   THIS FIELD IS NEGME
)@@G@@ATIVE IF THE@C@@@@.                           BUFFER IS IN USE.   @[@@@@MF
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@.                 HL        LINK  TO  PREVIOUS  BLOCK IN CORMG
)@@G@@E.  IF@F@@@@.                           ZERO, THE PREVIOUS BLOCK IS IN UMH
)@@G@@SE.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                 FL        LINK TO NEXT FREE BUMI
)@@G@@FFER (USED ONLY IF@C@@@@.                           BUFFER IS FREE).    MJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                 BL - ARQ  IF  BUFFER  IS  FREE, LINKMK
)@@G@@ TO PREVIOUS@F@@@@.                           FREE BUFFER (BL), IF BUFFEML
)@@G@@R IS IN USE,@F@@@@.                           ADDRESS  OF  REQUESTOR  OFMM
)@@G@@  THE BUFFER@A@@@@.                           (ARQ).  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@MN
)@@G@@.                 AT  THE  TAG HEAD IS THE HEAD OF THE LIST OF FREE BUFFMO
)@@G@@ERS.  @H@@@@.         THE LENGTH FIELD OF THE HEAD IS SET TO -1 TO PREVEMP
)@@G@@NT ALLOCATION OF  @^@@@@.         THE HEAD.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.     MQ
)@@G@@            THE  ROUTINE  BGET  ALLOCATES  BUFFERS  BY THE 'FIRST FIT'  MR
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         METHOD,  AS  FOLLOWS:   STARTING  AT  HEAD,  IT  LINKS TMS
)@@G@@HROUGH THE  @H@@@@.         BUFFERS  UNTIL  IT  FINDS ONE LARGE ENOUGH TMT
)@@G@@O SATISFY THE REQUEST.  @H@@@@.         HAVING FOUND ONE, IT DETERMINES MU
)@@G@@HOW MUCH UNUSED SPACE WILL BE LEFT  @H@@@@.         OVER  ONCE  THE  REQMV
)@@G@@UESTED  SPACE IS GIVEN TO THE USER.  IF ENOUGH  @H@@@@.         SPACE REMW
)@@G@@MAINS TO FORM ANOTHER FREE BLOCK, IT REDUCES THE LENGTH OF  @H@@@@.     MX
)@@G@@    THE  FREE BLOCK BY THE LENGTH TO BE ALLOCATED, CONSTRUCTS A BUFFER  MY
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         FROM  THE  END  OF  THE  FREE  BLOCK, AND PASSES THAT TOMZ
)@@G@@ THE USER.  @H@@@@.         OTHERWISE,  THE  ENTIRE  FREE  BLOCK IS UNCHNA
)@@G@@AINED AND GIVEN TO THE  @H@@@@.         USER.  THE HEAD LINK OF THE NEXTNB
)@@G@@ BLOCK IS CLEARED TO INDICATE THAT  @B@@@@.         THE BLOCK HAS BEEN ANC
)@@G@@LLOCATED.   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 THE ROUTINE BREL RETURNSND
)@@G@@ A BUFFER TO THE FREE POOL, POSSI-  @H@@@@.         BLY  RECOMBINING  ITNE
)@@G@@  WITH  CONTIGUOUS  BLOCKS TO FORM LARGER FREE  @H@@@@.         BLOCKS. NF
)@@G@@  IF  BOTH  THE PRECEDING AND FOLLOWING BLOCKS OF A BUFFER  @H@@@@.     NG
)@@G@@    ARE  IN  USE,  THE  BUFFER BEING RELEASED IS SIMPLY CHAINED TO THE  NH
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         LIST  OF FREE BUFFERS.  IF THE PRECEDING BLOCK IS FREE, NI
)@@G@@THE BUFFER  @H@@@@.         BEING  RETURNED  IS  APPENDED  TO  THE  PRECNJ
)@@G@@EDING BUFFER, WHICH IS  @H@@@@.         ALREADY  ON  THE  FREE  LIST.   NK
)@@G@@AT  THIS POINT, THE NEXT BUFFER IS  @H@@@@.         EXAMINED.   IF  IT  NL
)@@G@@IS  FREE, IT IS REMOVED FROM THE FREE LIST AND  @D@@@@.         ABSORBEDNM
)@@G@@ INTO THE BUFFER BEING RELEASED.    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 NN
)@@G@@IF  THE  EQU  EXPINC IS NONZERO, CODE WILL BE GENERATED TO  @H@@@@.     NO
)@@G@@    DYNAMICALLY  EXPAND THE BUFFER POOL WHEN SPACE IS EXHAUSTED.  THIS  NP
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         CODE,  STARTING AT THE TAG MT, ACQUIRES ENOUGH CORE TO SNQ
)@@G@@ATISFY THE  @H@@@@.         REQUEST  (OR AT LEAST EXPINC WORDS), AND CONNR
)@@G@@STRUCTS A LARGE BUFFER  @H@@@@.         OF  IT.   AN 'IMPENETRABLE BARRINS
)@@G@@ER' ONE WORD LONG IS PLACED AT THE  @H@@@@.         END  OF  THE  BUFFERNT
)@@G@@.   THIS  BARRIER CONTAINS THE NEGATIVE OF THE  @H@@@@.         BLOCK  LNU
)@@G@@ENGTH IN THE SIZE FIELD TO STOP RECOMBINATION.  THE END OF  @H@@@@.     NV
)@@G@@    CORE  POINTER,  LASTD, IS UPDATED.  THE NEW BUFFER IS THEN CHAINED  NW
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         TO THE FREE LIST, AND THE USER REQUEST IS THEN RETRIED. NX
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 THE  EQU  LCORE CONTROLS WHETHER EXPNY
)@@G@@ANSION BLOCKS ACQUIRED  @H@@@@.         BY  THE  ABOVE  MECHANISM  WILL NZ
)@@G@@BE RELEASED WHEN TOTALLY FREE.  IN  @H@@@@.         GENERAL,  THIS  MECHOA
)@@G@@ANISM IS USEFUL ONLY TO PROGRAMS WITH LONG RUN  @H@@@@.         TIMES,  OB
)@@G@@LARGE  SIZE VARIATIONS, AND A TRUE NESTING OF REQUESTS AND  @H@@@@.     OC
)@@G@@    RELEASES.   THE  CODE, WHICH STARTS AT THE TAG BRL5, CHECKS WHEN A  OD
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         BUFFER  IS  RELEASED  TO SEE IF IT EXTENDS TO THE END OFOE
)@@G@@ CORE.  IF  @H@@@@.         SO,  THE ROUTINE STARTING AT BRL3 IS INVOKEDOF
)@@G@@ TO DETERMINE FROM THE  @H@@@@.         SIZE  FIELD  AND  THE BARRIER WOOG
)@@G@@RD WHETHER THE ENTIRE BLOCK IS NOW  @H@@@@.         FREE.   IF  IT  IS, OH
)@@G@@ THE BLOCK IS UNCHAINED FROM THE FREE LIST AND  @H@@@@.         RELEASEDOI
)@@G@@  VIA LCORE$.  IF OTHER EXPANSION BLOCKS ARE PRESENT, THEY  @C@@@@.     OJ
)@@G@@    ARE EXAMINED FOR POSSIBLE RELEASE.    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.           OK
)@@G@@      BUFFERS ARE INITIALLY ALLOCATED FROM A POOL ASSEMBLED INTO  @H@@@@OL
)@@G@@.         THE  ELEMENT.   THE  SIZE OF THIS INITIAL RESERVE IS DETERMINEOM
)@@G@@D BY  @H@@@@.         THE  EQU  BSIZE.   THE  INTERNAL  BUFFER  STARTS AON
)@@G@@T THE TAG BIBUF,  @H@@@@.         IMMEDIATELY  BEFORE  THE  HEAD PACKET.OO
)@@G@@  THE FIRST WORD OF THE HEAD  @H@@@@.         SERVES  AS THE BARRIER WOROP
)@@G@@D FOR THE INTERNAL BUFFER.  BSIZE MAY BE  @H@@@@.         ZERO, IN WHICHOQ
)@@G@@ CASE THE INITIAL RESERVE WILL NOT BE GENERATED, AND  @H@@@@.         THOR
)@@G@@E  HEAD  WILL  BE  CHAINED  TO  ITSELF.  IN THIS CASE, THE FIRST  @F@@@@OS
)@@G@@.         REQUEST MADE UPON BGET WILL ALLOCATE AN EXPANSION BLOCK.@[@@@@OT
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@.                 THE   ROUTINE   MUST   PROTECT  ITS  DATA OU
)@@G@@ FOR  USE  IN  A  @H@@@@.         MULTI-ACTIVITY  ENVIRONMENT.  THE PROCOV
)@@G@@S P AND V ARE USED TO INVOKE  @H@@@@.         AND  RELEASE  PROTECTION, OW
)@@G@@ RESPECTIVELY.   THE  EQU TSQ DETERMINES  @H@@@@.         WHETHER  NORMAOX
)@@G@@L  TEST  AND  SET  SYNCHRONISATION  OR  TEST AND SET  @H@@@@.         QUOY
)@@G@@EUEING  WILL BE USED FOR DATA PROTECTION.  TEST AND SET QUEUEING  @H@@@@OZ
)@@G@@.         MUST  BE  USED IF BGET AND BREL ARE TO BE CALLED SIMULTANEOUSLPA
)@@G@@Y BY  @H@@@@.         REAL-TIME  AND  REGULAR (BATCH OR DEMAND) ACTIVITIPB
)@@G@@ES.  THE PROGRAM  @H@@@@.         MUST  EXECUTE AN ER TSQRG$ BEFORE AMY PC
)@@G@@REFERENCE TO BGET, IF TSQ IS  @C@@@@.         THE SELECTED SYNCHRONISATIPD
)@@G@@ON METHOD.  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 THE  REST  OF THE EQU'S PE
)@@G@@CONTROL ERROR CHECKING AND DIAGNO-  @H@@@@.         SIS.  MAXSIZ ESTABLIPF
)@@G@@SHES A BOUND ON THE LARGEST BUFFER REQUEST, TO  @H@@@@.         TRAP  WIPG
)@@G@@LD  CALLS.   ADDITIONALLY, IF MAXSIZ IS SUFFICIENTLY SMALL  @H@@@@.     PH
)@@G@@    THAT EXPINC WILL ALWAYS BE ENOUGH EXPANSION CORE TO SATISFY A USER  PI
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         REQUEST,  TWO  INSTRUCTIONS  WILL  BE  REMOVED  FROM THEPJ
)@@G@@ EXPANSION  @#@@@@.         ROUTINE.@[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 PK
)@@G@@TRACE  TURNS  ON  CODE  WHICH LOGS EXPANSIONS AND CONTRAC-  @H@@@@.     PL
)@@G@@    TIONS,  AND  DEFINES  AN  EXTERNAL  TAG  BTRACE.  IF BTRACE IS SET  PM
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         NON-ZERO,  ALL  BGET AND BREL CALLS WILL BE LOGGED UPON PN
)@@G@@OCCURENCE.  @D@@@@.         THIS IS USEFUL IN TRACKING DOWN ERRORS.     PO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 IF  STATS  IS  SET  TO  1,  STATISTIPP
)@@G@@CS WILL BE KEPT ON THE  @H@@@@.         NUMBER OF BGET AND BREL CALLS, TPQ
)@@G@@HE TOTAL SPACE IN USE AT ANY TIME,  @H@@@@.         AND  THE  MAXIMUM SPPR
)@@G@@ACE IN USE SO FAR.  THIS INFORMATION, STARTING  @H@@@@.         AT  THE PS
)@@G@@ TAG  BSTATW,  MAY  BE ACCESSED BY THE USER PROGRAM (WHICH  @H@@@@.     PT
)@@G@@    SHOULD  SET  THE  LOCK FIRST), OR MAY BE EDITED AND PRINTED BY THE  PU
)@@G@@@#@@@@.         CALL:   @B@@@@.                 LMJ       X11,BSTATP    PV
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         THE SUBROUTINE BSTATP IS GENERATED ONLY IF STATS IS SET PW
)@@G@@TO 1. @[@@@@.     @I@@@@.                   IF HOPE IS SET TO 1 AND EXPIPX
)@@G@@NC IS ZERO, UNSATISFIED REQUESTS    @H@@@@.         ARE QUEUED INSTEAD OPY
)@@G@@F BOMBING THE EXECUTION. (OBVIOUSLY AN ACTIVITY @G@@@@.         COULD GOPZ
)@@G@@ TO SLEEP PERMANENTLY, SO USE THIS WITH CAUTION.)     @E@@@@.         EVQA
)@@G@@ERY SUCCEEDING CALL ON BREL WILL EVENTUALLY     @G@@@@.         CAUSE REQB
)@@G@@ACTIVATION OF ALL QUEUED ACTIVITIES, WHICH WILL FLIP  @F@@@@.         BEQC
)@@G@@TWEEN TWO QUEUES, SO THAT EVERYONE GETS A CHANCE AT   @H@@@@.         NEQD
)@@G@@WLY FREED SPACE. PART OF THIS MECHANISM INVOLVES REACTIVATIONS    @^@@@@QE
)@@G@@.         BY BGET CALLS.@G@@@@.         IF STATISTICS ARE KEPT, MAXUSE IQF
)@@G@@S THE MAX OF (SPACE IN USE    @H@@@@.         + SIZE OF AN UNSATISFIED RQG
)@@G@@EQUEST) AND MAY BE LESS THAN THE TOTAL    @G@@@@.         SPACE WHICH WOQH
)@@G@@ULD HAVE BEEN USED IF ALL REQUESTS HAD BEEN     @^@@@@.         SATISFIAQI
)@@G@@BLE.  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.                 IF ANY ERROR IS DETECTED BY BGQJ
)@@G@@ET OR BREL, THE ACTION TAKEN  @H@@@@.         DEPENDS ON THE SETTING OF QK
)@@G@@ERRLEV.  FIVE SETTINGS, DESCRIBED BEFORE  @H@@@@.         THE  VARIABLE,QL
)@@G@@  ACCOMODATE PROGRAMS ACROSS THE SPECTRUM FROM THOSE  @D@@@@.         ABQM
)@@G@@OVE SUSPICION TO THOSE BENEATH CONTEMPT.  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.           QN
)@@G@@      THE CORE ALLOCATION ALGORITHM USED HEREIN IS AN ADAPTATION  @H@@@@QO
)@@G@@.         OF  THE  MECHANISM  USED  IN  THE  ALGOL COMPILER DESIGNED AT QP
)@@G@@CASE  @H@@@@.         WESTERN  RESERVE  UNIVERSITY.   THE OCTAL EDITOR SQQ
)@@G@@UBROUTINE IN THE  @H@@@@.         MANNER  OF  EXEC  II WAS ADAPTED FROM QR
)@@G@@A ROUTINE BY DEREK ZAVE (NOT  @C@@@@.         THE FAMOUS 12 INSTRUCTION QS
)@@G@@EDITOR).    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         TO  ASSEMBLE  THIS  ROUTINE, THEQT
)@@G@@ WALKER ER PROCS MUST BE AVAILABLE  @ @@@@.         (ELEMENT ERPROCS).  QU
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         THE FOLLQV
)@@G@@OWING PARAMETERISE THIS VERSION OF BGET   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@QW
)@@G@@.         ERRLEV DETERMINES THE AMOUNT OF ERROR DIAGNOSIS AND     @F@@@@QX
)@@G@@.         CHECKING TO BE PERFORMED BY BGET AND BREL.  THE HIGHER  @F@@@@QY
)@@G@@.         THE VALUE, THE HIGHER THE QUALITY OF ERROR DIAGNOSIS.   @A@@@@QZ
)@@G@@.         PERMITTED VALUES ARE:     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.                 RA
)@@G@@  0     NO ERROR CHECKING AT ALL    @E@@@@.                   1     EABTRB
)@@G@@$ IF AN ERROR IS DETECTED     @E@@@@.                   2     EABT$ WITHRC
)@@G@@ CODES IN REGISTERS     @E@@@@.                              A0 = +(ERRORD
)@@G@@R CODE,USER A0)   @D@@@@.                              X11 = CALL ADDRESRE
)@@G@@S     @D@@@@.                   3     ERROR NUMBER, X11, A0 EDITED@E@@@@RF
)@@G@@.                   4     ERROR MESSAGE, X11, A0 EDITED     @[@@@@.     RG
)@@G@@@^@@@@ERRLEV    EQU       ;   @^@@@@                    4   @[@@@@.     RH
)@@G@@@B@@@@.         EXPANSION INCREMENT IN WORDS    @C@@@@.         IF ZERO,RI
)@@G@@ EXPANSION IS NOT PERMITTED   @F@@@@.         THIS IS THE ACTUAL AMOUNT RJ
)@@G@@OF SPACE, INCLUDING CONTROL   @F@@@@.         WORDS, TO BE ALLOCATED.  TRK
)@@G@@HE MAXIMUM BUFFER THAT CAN    @E@@@@.         CARVED OUT OF THIS SPACE IRL
)@@G@@S NCWIU WORDS SMALLER.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@EXPINC    EQU       ;   @^@@@@RM
)@@G@@                    512 @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         MAXIMUM REQUEST SIZERN
)@@G@@ (NO MAXIMUM IF ZERO)   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@MAXSIZ    EQU       ;   @^@@@@RO
)@@G@@                    0   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         SHOULD LCORE$ BE USERP
)@@G@@D TO RELEASE EXPANSION BLOCKS ?     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@LCORE     EQU     RQ
)@@G@@  ;   @^@@@@                    1   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         IF MANUARR
)@@G@@L IS SET NONZERO, SPACE ALLOCATED VIA MCORE$ WILL NOT @G@@@@.         BERS
)@@G@@ RELEASED WHEN POSSIBLE VIA BREL, BUT WILL BE KEPT IN THE   @H@@@@.     RT
)@@G@@    AVAILABLE SPACE POOL UNTIL A CALL ON BRELC IS MADE.  AT THAT TIME,  RU
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         ANY ELIGIBLE SPACE WILL BE RELEASED.  THIS PREVENTS MCORRV
)@@G@@E/LCORE     @H@@@@.         TOGGLING (WITH ATTENDANT I/O RUNDOWN) IN PRORW
)@@G@@GRAMS ALLOCATING AND    @A@@@@.         RELEASING MANY BUFFERS.   @[@@@@RX
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@MANUAL    EQU       ;   @^@@@@                    0   @[@@@@RY
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.         INITIAL RESERVE SIZE (MAY BE ZERO)    @[@@@@.     RZ
)@@G@@@^@@@@BSIZE     EQU       ;   @^@@@@                    0   @[@@@@.     SA
)@@G@@@D@@@@.         SET TO 1 TO ENABLE TRACING OF OPERATIONS    @[@@@@.     SB
)@@G@@@^@@@@TRACE     EQU       ;   @^@@@@                    1   @[@@@@.     SC
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         STATS CONTROLS THE KEEPING OF STATISTICS ON BREL USAGE. SD
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         IF SET TO 1, THE ROUTINE KEEPS TRACK OF THE NUMBER OF   SE
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         ALLOCATE AND RELEASE CALLS, AND CODE IS GENERATED FOR   SF
)@@G@@@F@@@@.         THE SUBROUTINE 'BSTAT', WHICH EDITS THE INFORMATION     SG
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         WHEN CALLED BY THE USER.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@STATS     EQSH
)@@G@@U       ;   @^@@@@                    1   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         TSSI
)@@G@@Q IS ONE IF TEST AND SET QUEUEING IS TO BE THE  @C@@@@.         METHOD OSJ
)@@G@@F CRITICAL SECTION LOCKING.   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@TSQ       EQU       ;   SK
)@@G@@@^@@@@                    0   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         HOSL
)@@G@@PE IS ONE IF, IN THE ABSENCE OF MCORE$ (EXPINC=0),    @E@@@@.         ANSM
)@@G@@ ACTIVITY FINDING NOT ENOUGH CORE IS TO QUEUE   @F@@@@.         ITSELF ISN
)@@G@@N THE HOPE THAT SOMEONE WILL RELEASE SOME CORE. @^@@@@HOPE      EQU     SO
)@@G@@  ;   @^@@@@                    1   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.     SP
)@@G@@    DERIVATIVE VARIABLES FROM CONFIGURATION     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.     SQ
)@@G@@    THIS COMPUTED VARIABLE DETERMINES WHETHER   @B@@@@.         'EXPINC'SR
)@@G@@ IS ALWAYS ENOUGH CORE. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@BOUNDED   EQU       (MAXSIZ=0)SS
)@@G@@++((MAXSIZ+NCWIU+1)>EXPINC)   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         THIS COMPUTED ST
)@@G@@VARIABLE TELLS WHETHER  @C@@@@.         WE WILL USE LCORE$ TO RELEASE COSU
)@@G@@RE    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@CORREL    EQU       (EXPINC>0)**(LCORE>0) @[@@@@SV
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         MANREL IS NONZERO IF MANUAL RELEASE IS DESIRED ANDSW
)@@G@@ NEEDED     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@MANREL    EQU       CORREL**(MANUAL>0)    SX
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         THIS COMPUTED VARIABLE CONTROLS ERROR CHECKISY
)@@G@@NG CODE     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@CHECK     EQU       ERRLEV>0  @[@@@@.     SZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         THIS COMPUTED VARIABLE DETERMINES WHETHER THE CODE@E@@@@TA
)@@G@@.         FOR THE INTERNAL OCTAL EDITOR SHOULD BE GENERATED.@[@@@@.     TB
)@@G@@@C@@@@EDITOR    EQU       TRACE++(ERRLEV>2)++STATS    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@TC
)@@G@@.         WAIT IS NON-ZERO IF CODE FOR WAITING FOR SPACE IS NEEDED.     TD
)@@G@@@A@@@@WAIT      EQU       HOPE**(EXPINC=0)@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         CHTE
)@@G@@ECK VALIDITY OF PARAMETERS    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@          DO        (BSITF
)@@G@@ZE=0)**(EXPINC=0) , I FLAG INDICATES NO CORE POSSIBLE @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@TG
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@.         PROCS   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          AXR$    @#@@@@TH
)@@G@@          DEFUNCT$@^@@@@          LIT$      2   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@P     TI
)@@G@@    PROC      1,1                 TO GENERATE ERROR CALL    @^@@@@KABONGTJ
)@@G@@*   NAME      0   @A@@@@          DO        ERRLEV<2 , EABT$@E@@@@      TK
)@@G@@    DO        ERRLEV>1 , I$ 072,010,P(1,1),,,KABTRAP  @#@@@@          ENTL
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@E$        PROC      1,2 @^@@@@E$BO*     NAME    TM
)@@G@@  0   @ @@@@B         EQU       E$(1,1)-1 @ @@@@Y         FORM      6,12TN
)@@G@@,18   @C@@@@          DO        E$(0,0)=0 , SLJ    EBO$     @C@@@@      TO
)@@G@@    Y         E$(1,3),B-B/6*6,E$(1,2)+B/6 @#@@@@          END     @[@@@@TP
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@P*        PROC      1                   INVOKE CRITICAL SECTTQ
)@@G@@ION   @D@@@@          TS        P(1,1)              SET THE LOCK  @#@@@@TR
)@@G@@          END     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@V*        PROC      1               TS
)@@G@@    RELEASE CRITICAL SECTION  @B@@@@          DO        TSQ=0 , SZ,S1 V(TT
)@@G@@1,1)  @B@@@@          DO        TSQ>0 , CTS$  V(1,1)  @#@@@@          ENTU
)@@G@@D     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@P         PROC      0,1                 CRITICALTV
)@@G@@ SECTION LOCK     @^@@@@SEMA4*    NAME      0   @A@@@@          DO      TW
)@@G@@  TSQ=0 , * 0     @A@@@@          DO        TSQ>0 , TCELL$  @#@@@@      TX
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         BUFFER FORMAT EQUATETY
)@@G@@S     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@HL        EQUF      0,,H1               POINTER TZ
)@@G@@TO PREVIOUS BLOCK @G@@@@.                                       ZERO MEAUA
)@@G@@NS PREVIOUS BLOCK IN USE@[@@@@.     @H@@@@SIZE      EQUF      0,,XH2    UB
)@@G@@          SIZE OF BLOCK INCLUDING CONTROL WORDS @G@@@@.                 UC
)@@G@@                      NEGATIVE MEANS BLOCK IS IN USE  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@UD
)@@G@@FBL       EQUF      1                   LINK WORD     @G@@@@FL        EQUE
)@@G@@UF      FBL,,H1             FORWARD LINK TO NEXT FREE BLOCK @H@@@@BL    UF
)@@G@@    EQUF      FBL,,H2             BACKWARD LINK TO PREVIOUS FREE BLOCK  UG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @H@@@@ARQ       EQUF      1,,H2               ADDRESS OF REQUH
)@@G@@UEST OF BLOCK IF IN USE @[@@@@.     @H@@@@NCWIU     EQU       2         UI
)@@G@@          NUMBER OF CONTROL WORDS IF IN USE     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@MIN   UJ
)@@G@@    EQU       NCWIU+1             MINIMUM SIZE BUFFER TO KEEP     @[@@@@UK
)@@G@@/.    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         DATA AREA     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@      UL
)@@G@@    ON        BSIZE>0   @ @@@@BIBUF     *         0,BSIZE   @ @@@@      UM
)@@G@@    *         HEAD,HEAD @A@@@@          RES       BSIZE-NCWIU     @ @@@@UN
)@@G@@          OFF       BSIZE>0   @A@@@@          DO        BSIZE=0 ,BIBUF. UO
)@@G@@@C@@@@HEAD      *         BIBUF,-1            HL,SIZE @G@@@@          * UP
)@@G@@        BIBUF,BIBUF         INITIALLY ONE BIG (?) BLOCK     @[@@@@.     UQ
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        STATS     @]@@@@BSTATW*   . @E@@@@GETCALL   * UR
)@@G@@        0                   NUMBER OF BGET CALLS@E@@@@RELCALL   *       US
)@@G@@  0                   NUMBER OF BREL CALLS@D@@@@INUSE     EQUF      $,,HUT
)@@G@@1               WORDS IN USE  @F@@@@MAXUSE    EQUF      $,,XH2          UU
)@@G@@    -(MAX WORDS USED SO FAR)  @^@@@@          *         0,0 @ @@@@      UV
)@@G@@    OFF       STATS     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          ON        WAIT@G@@@@UW
)@@G@@WAITC     *         0                   # TIMES ANYONE HAD TO WAIT.     UX
)@@G@@@^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@[@@@@.     @F@@@@CRIT      SEMA4     .   UY
)@@G@@                CRITICAL SECTION LOCK     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ONUZ
)@@G@@        EXPINC>0  @E@@@@LASTD     EQUF      $,,H1               NEXT USAVA
)@@G@@BLE ADDRESS @F@@@@SVLEN     EQUF      $,,XH2              SAVE FOR BUFFEVB
)@@G@@R LENGTH    @A@@@@SNAPR     *         LASTD$+1,$-$    @ @@@@          OFVC
)@@G@@F       EXPINC>0  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@SVA1      RES       2               VD
)@@G@@    SAVE A1, A2   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         REQUEST CORE BVE
)@@G@@LOCK  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         LA,U      A0,<LENGTH>     VF
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         LMJ       X11,BGET  @E@@@@.         <RETURN>            VG
)@@G@@          A0 = BUFFER ADDRESS @[@@@@.     @[@@@@$(1). @G@@@@BGET*     P VH
)@@G@@        CRIT                INVOKE CRITICAL SECTION LOCK    @A@@@@      VI
)@@G@@    ON        TRACE++WAIT     @C@@@@          SA        A0,TSAVE        VJ
)@@G@@    SAVE A0 @A@@@@          OFF       TRACE++WAIT     @ @@@@          ONVK
)@@G@@        TRACE     @F@@@@          TNZ       BTRACE              IS TRACEVL
)@@G@@ OUTPUT DESIRED ? @E@@@@          J         BGTTF               NO.  SKIVM
)@@G@@P EDITING   @D@@@@          E$BO      38,T$BGET,12        EDIT PARAMETERVN
)@@G@@@E@@@@          LA,U      A0,,X11             GET RETURN ADDRESS  @D@@@@VO
)@@G@@          ANA,U     A0,1                BACK IT UP    @E@@@@          E$VP
)@@G@@BO      6,T$BGET,6          EDIT INTO TRACE LINE@E@@@@          PRINT$  VQ
)@@G@@  T$BGET,T$LBGET      PRINT THE TRACE     @D@@@@          LA        A0,TVR
)@@G@@SAVE            RELOAD A0     @]@@@@BGTTF     . @ @@@@          OFF     VS
)@@G@@  TRACE     @D@@@@          DS        A1,SVA1             SAVE A1, A2   VT
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ON        STATS     @F@@@@          LA        A1,GETCALLVU
)@@G@@          LOAD NUMBER OF BGET CALLS @D@@@@          AA,U      A1,1      VV
)@@G@@          INCREMENT IT  @G@@@@          SA        A1,GETCALL          UPVW
)@@G@@DATE CALLS ON BGET SO FAR     @ @@@@          OFF       STATS     @B@@@@VX
)@@G@@          ON        CHECK**(MAXSIZ>0)     @G@@@@          TG,U      A0,MVY
)@@G@@AXSIZ           IS USER REQUEST WITHIN RANGE ?  @E@@@@          KABONG  VZ
)@@G@@  1                   NO.  ERROR CODE 1   @B@@@@          OFF       CHECWA
)@@G@@K**(MAXSIZ>0)     @G@@@@          LNA,U     A0,NCWIU,A0         A0 = -(AWB
)@@G@@CTUAL LENGTH NEEDED)    @G@@@@BGET0     LA,U      A2,HEAD             POWC
)@@G@@INT TO HEAD OF FREE BLOCKS    @E@@@@BGET1     LA        A2,FL,A2        WD
)@@G@@    LINK TO NEXT BLOCK  @G@@@@          TNE,U     A2,HEAD             DOWE
)@@G@@ES THAT BRING US BACK HOME ?  @ @@@@          ON        EXPINC>0  @I@@@@WF
)@@G@@          J         MT                  YES.  NEED MORE CORE TO SATISFY WG
)@@G@@REQUEST     @ @@@@          OFF       EXPINC>0  @ @@@@          ON      WH
)@@G@@  EXPINC=0  @ @@@@          ON        WAIT=0    @F@@@@          KABONG  WI
)@@G@@  4                   NO MORE CORE.  FATAL ERROR@ @@@@          OFF     WJ
)@@G@@  WAIT=0    @^@@@@          ON        WAIT@F@@@@          J         QUYRWK
)@@G@@SELF            NO MORE CORE. WAIT FOR IT.@^@@@@          OFF       WAITWL
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       EXPINC=0  @F@@@@          AU        A0,SIZE,A2WM
)@@G@@          IS THIS BLOCK BIG ENOUGH ?@F@@@@          JN        A1,BGET1  WN
)@@G@@          NO.  LOOK AT NEXT ONE     @F@@@@          TLE,U     A1,MIN    WO
)@@G@@          CAN WE SPLIT THIS BLOCK ? @G@@@@          J         BGET3     WP
)@@G@@          NO.  JUST REMOVE THE WHOLE THING@G@@@@.                       WQ
)@@G@@                OTHERWISE, TAKE THE SECOND PART @I@@@@.                 WR
)@@G@@                      AND LEAVE THE FIRST PART ON THE FREELIST    @F@@@@WS
)@@G@@          SA        A1,SIZE,A2          UPDATE SIZE REMAINING     @H@@@@WT
)@@G@@          AA,U      A1,,A2              POINT TO PART TO BE GIVEN TO USEWU
)@@G@@R     @G@@@@          SA        A2,HL,A1            POINT BACK TO PREVIOWV
)@@G@@US BUFFER   @F@@@@BGET2     SA        A0,SIZE,A1          STORE SIZE, MAWW
)@@G@@RKING IN USE@G@@@@          ANU,XU    A1,,A0              COMPUTE NEXT BWX
)@@G@@UFFER ADDRESS     @F@@@@          SZ        HL,A2               MARK THIWY
)@@G@@S BUFFER IN USE   @F@@@@          SX        X11,ARQ,A1          SAVE REQWZ
)@@G@@UESTOR'S ADDRESS  @ @@@@          ON        STATS     @E@@@@          LAXA
)@@G@@        A2,A1               SAVE BUFFER ADDRESS.@G@@@@          ANU     XB
)@@G@@  A0,INUSE            A1 = -(TOTAL WORDS ALLOCATED)   @E@@@@          SNXC
)@@G@@A       A1,INUSE            UPDATE INUSE COUNT  @F@@@@          TLE     XD
)@@G@@  A1,MAXUSE           IS IT A NEW HIGH (LOW)    @E@@@@          SA      XE
)@@G@@  A1,MAXUSE           YES.  UPDATE MAX USE@E@@@@          LA        A1,AXF
)@@G@@2               RESTORE ADDRESS.    @ @@@@          OFF       STATS     XG
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,U      A0,NCWIU,A1         PASS BACK ADDRESS TO USER XH
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ON        WAIT@E@@@@          SA        A0,TSAVE        XI
)@@G@@    SAVE THE ANSWER.    @F@@@@          LMJ       A2,QUF              STXJ
)@@G@@ART UP WAITING REQUESTS.@E@@@@          LA        A0,TSAVE            REXK
)@@G@@STORE ANSWER.     @^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@E@@@@          DL      XL
)@@G@@  A1,SVA1             RESTORE REGISTERS   @ @@@@          ON        TRACXM
)@@G@@E     @E@@@@          TNZ       BTRACE              TRACING REQUESTS ?  XN
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         BGTTF1              NO.  SKIP THIS@C@@@@      XO
)@@G@@    SA        A0,TSAVE            SAVE A0 @F@@@@          E$BO      38,TXP
)@@G@@$BGET1,12       EDIT ADDRESS RETURNED     @E@@@@          PRINT$    T$BGXQ
)@@G@@ET1,T$LBGET1    PRINT TRACE LINE    @D@@@@          LA        A0,TSAVE  XR
)@@G@@          RELOAD A0     @]@@@@BGTTF1    . @ @@@@          OFF       TRACXS
)@@G@@E     @F@@@@          V         CRIT                CLEAR CRITICAL SECTIXT
)@@G@@ON    @F@@@@          J         0,X11               RETURN TO CALLING SEXU
)@@G@@QUENCE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@BGET3     LA        A0,FL,A2            LOAD FORXV
)@@G@@WARD LINK IN BLOCK@E@@@@          LA        A1,BL,A2            LOAD BACXW
)@@G@@KWARD LINK  @G@@@@          SA        A0,FL,A1            PUT FORWARD LIXX
)@@G@@NK IN LAST BLOCK  @G@@@@          SA        A1,BL,A0            PUT BACKXY
)@@G@@WARD LINK IN NEXT BLOCK @F@@@@          LNA       A0,SIZE,A2          LOXZ
)@@G@@AD -(ACTUAL BLOCK SIZE) @F@@@@          LA,U      A1,,A2              GEYA
)@@G@@T BUFFER ADDRESS IN A1  @F@@@@          J         BGET2               JOYB
)@@G@@IN RETURN TO USER CODE  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         QUEUE ACTIVITY TO WAYC
)@@G@@IT FOR SPACE AVAILABLILITY.   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          ON        WAITYD
)@@G@@@]@@@@QUYRSELF.   @ @@@@          ON        STATS     @G@@@@          ANYE
)@@G@@U       A0,INUSE            A1 = -(TOTAL WORDS ALLOCATED)   @F@@@@      YF
)@@G@@    TLE       A1,MAXUSE           IS IT A NEW HIGH (LOW)    @E@@@@      YG
)@@G@@    SA        A1,MAXUSE           YES.  UPDATE MAX USE@ @@@@          OFYH
)@@G@@F       STATS     @F@@@@          LA        A0,WAITC            COUNT OFYI
)@@G@@ PREVIOUS WAITS.  @D@@@@          AA,U      A0,1                INCREMENYJ
)@@G@@T IT. @D@@@@          SA        A0,WAITC            PUT BACK.     @F@@@@YK
)@@G@@          LMJ       A2,QUF              START A WAITING ACTIVITY. @G@@@@YL
)@@G@@          LA        A1,QCOUNT,A0        COUNT OF STUFF IN NEW QUEUE.    YM
)@@G@@@C@@@@          AA,U      A1,1                BUMP IT.@C@@@@          SAYN
)@@G@@        A1,QCOUNT,A0        SAVE IT.@D@@@@          DL        A1,SVA1   YO
)@@G@@          RESTORE A1-A2.@E@@@@          TE,U      A0,QUEUE0           IFYP
)@@G@@ GOING TO QUEUE 1,@D@@@@          J         QUY1                GO THEREYQ
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@          LA        A0,TSAVE            RESTORE A0.   @E@@@@YR
)@@G@@          V         CRIT                OPEN CRITICAL CODE. @C@@@@      YS
)@@G@@    CTSQ$     QUEUE0              WAIT.   @C@@@@          J         BGETYT
)@@G@@                GO.     @D@@@@QUY1      LA        A0,TSAVE            REYU
)@@G@@STORE A0.   @E@@@@          V         CRIT                OPEN CRITICAL YV
)@@G@@CODE. @C@@@@          CTSQ$     QUEUE1              WAIT.   @C@@@@      YW
)@@G@@    J         BGET                GO ON.  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@YX
)@@G@@QUF       LA        A0,QFROM            QUEUE THAT THEY'RE COMING FROM. YY
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A1,QCOUNT,A0        COUNT OF THINGS IN IT.    YZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          JZ        A1,QUF1             IF NONE, NOTHING TO DO.   ZA
)@@G@@@D@@@@          ANA,U     A1,1                REDUCE COUNT. @D@@@@      ZB
)@@G@@    SA        A1,QCOUNT,A0        PUT IT BACK.  @E@@@@          CTSA$   ZC
)@@G@@  0,A0                START SOMEBODY.     @[@@@@QUF1. @F@@@@          LAZD
)@@G@@        A0,QTO              POINT TO THE OTHER QUEUE. @C@@@@          J ZE
)@@G@@        0,A2                RETURN. @^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@[@@@@ZF
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@.         ACQUIRE AN EXPANSION BLOCK@[@@@@.     @ @@@@      ZG
)@@G@@    ON        EXPINC>0  @]@@@@MT        . @F@@@@          SA        A0,SZH
)@@G@@VLEN            SAVE USER LENGTH REQUEST  @ @@@@          ON        BOUNZI
)@@G@@DED   @G@@@@          LMA       A0,A0               LOAD POSITIVE LENGTHZJ
)@@G@@ REQUESTED  @H@@@@          TLE,U     A0,EXPINC           IS USER REQUESZK
)@@G@@T > EXPANSION SIZE ?    @ @@@@          OFF       BOUNDED   @G@@@@      ZL
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,EXPINC           LOAD SIZE OF EXPANSION BLOCK    @ @@@@ZM
)@@G@@          ON        TRACE     @E@@@@          TNZ       BTRACE          ZN
)@@G@@    TRACE REQUESTS ?    @E@@@@          J         MTTRC               NOZO
)@@G@@.  SKIP LOGGING   @D@@@@          E$BO      16,T$RQST,6         LOG REQUZP
)@@G@@EST   @E@@@@          SA        A0,TSAVE            SAVE A0 OVER TRACE  ZQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          PRINT$    T$RQST,T$LRQST      PRINT THE MESSAGE   @D@@@@ZR
)@@G@@          LA        A0,TSAVE            RELOAD A0     @]@@@@MTTRC     . ZS
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       TRACE     @F@@@@          LNA,U     A2,,A0    ZT
)@@G@@          LOAD -(BUFFER LENGTH)     @H@@@@          LXI,U     A2        ZU
)@@G@@          CLEAR H1 OF A2, FORMING END BARRIER   @G@@@@          AU      ZV
)@@G@@  A0,LASTD            COMPUTE HIGHEST ADDRESS NEEDED  @D@@@@          DSZW
)@@G@@C       A0,36               SWAP A0, A1   @F@@@@          LXI,U     A0,0ZX
)@@G@@200000          EXPAND FOR ENTIRE PROGRAM @E@@@@          MCORE$    .   ZY
)@@G@@                OBTAIN THE CORE     @G@@@@          SA        A2,,A0    ZZ
)@@G@@          PUT AT END OF EXPANSION BLOCK   @G@@@@          AA,U      A0,1AA
)@@G@@                COMPUTE NEXT WORD TO REQUEST    @F@@@@          SA      AB
)@@G@@  A0,LASTD            UPDATE END-OF-CORE WORD   @G@@@@          ANA,U   AC
)@@G@@  A0,1,A1             A0 = START OF NEW BUFFER AREA   @G@@@@          SAAD
)@@G@@        A1,SIZE,A0          SAVE SIZE OF BUFFER IN BUFFER   @G@@@@      AE
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,HEAD             GET ADDRESS OF HEAD OF CHAIN    @G@@@@AF
)@@G@@          SA        A1,BL,A0            SET UP BACK LINK OF NEW BUFFER  AG
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A1,HEAD+FL          GET FIRST BUFFER IN CHAIN AH
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A1,FL,A0            LINK TO NEW ONE     @F@@@@AI
)@@G@@          SA        A0,BL,A1            POINT OLD ONE TO THIS ONE @F@@@@AJ
)@@G@@          SZ        HL,A0               DON'T ALLOW RECOMBINATION @F@@@@AK
)@@G@@          SA        A0,HEAD+FL          CHAIN THIS ONE TO THE HEAD@F@@@@AL
)@@G@@          LA        A0,SVLEN            RELOAD LENGTH OF BUFFER   @C@@@@AM
)@@G@@          J         BGET0               CONTINUE@ @@@@          OFF     AN
)@@G@@  EXPINC>0  @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         RELEASE CORE BLOCK  AO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         LA,U      A0,<ADDRESS>    @ @@@@.         LMAP
)@@G@@J       X11,BREL  @E@@@@.         <RETURN>                      X11, A0 AQ
)@@G@@DESTROYED   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@BREL*     ANA,U     A0,NCWIU            POAR
)@@G@@INT TO ACTUAL BUFFER START    @E@@@@          LXI,U     X11,,X11        AS
)@@G@@    SAVE RETURN POINT   @F@@@@          P         CRIT                INAT
)@@G@@VOKE CRITICAL SECTION   @ @@@@          ON        TRACE     @E@@@@      AU
)@@G@@    TNZ       BTRACE              TRACING REQUESTS ?  @F@@@@          J AV
)@@G@@        BRLTF               NO.  SKIP THIS EDITING    @C@@@@          SAAW
)@@G@@        A0,TSAVE            SAVE A0 @E@@@@          AA,U      A0,NCWIU  AX
)@@G@@          COMPUTE USER ADDRESS@E@@@@          E$BO      38,T$BREL,12    AY
)@@G@@    EDIT ADDRESS PASSED @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,,X11             GEAZ
)@@G@@T RETURN ADDRESS  @D@@@@          ANA,U     A0,1                BACK IT BA
)@@G@@UP    @F@@@@          E$BO      6,T$BREL,6          EDIT IT INTO THE TRABB
)@@G@@CE    @D@@@@          PRINT$    T$BREL,T$LBREL      PRINT TRACE   @D@@@@BC
)@@G@@          LA        A0,TSAVE            RELOAD A0     @]@@@@BRLTF     . BD
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       TRACE     @D@@@@          DS        A1,SVA1   BE
)@@G@@          SAVE A1, A2   @ @@@@          ON        CHECK     @D@@@@      BF
)@@G@@    TN        SIZE,A0             IS IT IN USE ?@H@@@@          KABONG  BG
)@@G@@  2                   NO.  RELEASE OF UNALLOCATED BUFFER    @ @@@@      BH
)@@G@@    OFF       CHECK     @ @@@@          ON        STATS     @F@@@@      BI
)@@G@@    LA        A1,RELCALL          LOAD NUMBER OF BREL CALLS @D@@@@      BJ
)@@G@@    AA,U      A1,1                INCREMENT IT  @F@@@@          SA      BK
)@@G@@  A1,RELCALL          UPDATE TOTAL BREL CALLS   @G@@@@          LA      BL
)@@G@@  A1,INUSE            LOAD NUMBER OF WORDS IN USE     @E@@@@          AABM
)@@G@@        A1,SIZE,A0          COMPUTE NEW TOTAL   @E@@@@          SA      BN
)@@G@@  A1,INUSE            UPDATE THE TOTAL    @ @@@@          OFF       STATBO
)@@G@@S     @F@@@@          LA        A2,HL,A0            IS PREVIOUS BLOCK INBP
)@@G@@ USE ?@G@@@@          JNZ       A2,BRL1             NO.  A2 POINTS TO PRBQ
)@@G@@EVIOUS BLOCK@F@@@@.                                       CHAIN TO AVAILBR
)@@G@@ABLE LIST   @E@@@@          LA,U      A2,HEAD             GET HEAD OF CHBS
)@@G@@AIN   @F@@@@          SA        A2,BL,A0            CHAIN NEW BLOCK TO HBT
)@@G@@EAD   @E@@@@          LA        A2,HEAD+FL          GET FIRST AVAILABLE BU
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A2,FL,A0            CHAIN TO THIS BLOCK @F@@@@BV
)@@G@@          SA        A0,HEAD+FL          THIS BUFFER IS NOW FIRST  @I@@@@BW
)@@G@@          SA        A0,BL,A2            MAKE OLD FIRST BUFFER POINT TO TBX
)@@G@@HIS ONE     @H@@@@          LA,U      A2,,A0              LOAD ADDRESS OBY
)@@G@@F BLOCK BEING RETURNED  @E@@@@BRL1      ANU       A0,SIZE,A0          POBZ
)@@G@@INT TO NEXT BLOCK @ @@@@          ON        CHECK     @F@@@@          TZCA
)@@G@@        HL,A1               IS BLOCK MARKED IN USE ?  @F@@@@          KACB
)@@G@@BONG    3                   YES.  BAD NEXT BUFFER LINK@ @@@@          OFCC
)@@G@@F       CHECK     @F@@@@          TP        SIZE,A1             IS NEXT CD
)@@G@@BLOCK AVAILABLE ? @F@@@@          J         BRL2                NO.  CANCE
)@@G@@NOT COMBINE IT    @G@@@@.                                       REMOVE NCF
)@@G@@EXT BLOCK FROM FREE LIST@G@@@@          LXM       X11,FL,A1           GECG
)@@G@@T FORWARD LINK OF NEXT BLOCK  @E@@@@          LA        A0,BL,A1        CH
)@@G@@    ...AND BACKWARD LINK@H@@@@          SX        X11,FL,A0           UPCI
)@@G@@DATE FORWARD LINK OF PREVIOUS BUFFER@H@@@@          SA        A0,BL,X11 CJ
)@@G@@          UPDATE BACKWARD LINK OF NEXT BUFFER   @G@@@@          AA      CK
)@@G@@  A1,SIZE,A1          POINT TO NEXT BLOCK IN CORE     @E@@@@BRL2      SACL
)@@G@@        A2,HL,A1            POINT NEXT BLOCK    @E@@@@          ANA,U   CM
)@@G@@  A1,,A2              COMPUTE TOTAL LENGTH@G@@@@          SA        A1,SCN
)@@G@@IZE,A2          STORE SIZE, MARKING AVAILABLE   @B@@@@          ON      CO
)@@G@@  CORREL**(MANREL=0)    @E@@@@BRL5      AA,U      A1,1,A2             A1CP
)@@G@@ = END OF BUFFER+1@F@@@@          TNE       A1,LASTD            IS THIS CQ
)@@G@@THE END OF CORE ? @H@@@@          J         BRL3                YES.  THCR
)@@G@@INK ABOUT LCORE$ POSSIBILITIES@B@@@@          OFF       CORREL**(MANREL=CS
)@@G@@0)    @[@@@@BRL4. @^@@@@          ON        WAIT@E@@@@          LA      CT
)@@G@@  A0,QTF              QUEUE POINTERS.     @E@@@@          TNZ       QCOUCU
)@@G@@NT,A0           IF FROM-QUEUE EMPTY,@D@@@@          SSC       A0,18     CV
)@@G@@          SWITCH THEM.  @ @@@@          SA        A0,QTF    @F@@@@      CW
)@@G@@    LMJ       A2,QUF              START WAITING ACTIVITIES. @^@@@@      CX
)@@G@@    OFF       WAIT@D@@@@          DL        A1,SVA1             RESTORE CY
)@@G@@A1-A2.@E@@@@          V         CRIT                OPEN CRITICAL CODE. CZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A0,X11              GET BACK RETURN POINT     DA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SSL       A0,18               MOVE RETURN TO MODIFIER   DB
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         0,A0                RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@DC
)@@G@@.         RELEASE FREE EXPANSION BLOCKS   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ONDD
)@@G@@        CORREL    @G@@@@BRL3      ANA,U     A1,1                POINT TODE
)@@G@@ FINAL (BARRIER) WORD   @E@@@@          LMA,XH2   A0,,A1              LODF
)@@G@@AD SIZE SENTINEL  @F@@@@          TE        A0,SIZE,A2          IS THE WDG
)@@G@@HOLE BLOCK FREE ? @E@@@@          J         BRL4                NO.  SKIDH
)@@G@@P THIS STUFF@ @@@@          ON        TRACE     @E@@@@          TNZ     DI
)@@G@@  BTRACE              TRACING REQUESTS ?  @F@@@@          J         BRL3DJ
)@@G@@T               NO.  SKIP LCORE LOGGING   @E@@@@          E$BO      15,TDK
)@@G@@$RTRN,6         EDIT WORDS RELEASED @F@@@@          PRINT$    T$RTRN,T$LDL
)@@G@@RTRN      PRINT LOGGING MESSAGE     @]@@@@BRL3T     . @ @@@@          OFDM
)@@G@@F       TRACE     @F@@@@.                                       UNCHAIN DN
)@@G@@FROM FREE LIST    @G@@@@          LA        A0,FL,A2            LOAD POIDO
)@@G@@NTER TO NEXT BUFFER     @G@@@@          LX        A1,BL,A2            LODP
)@@G@@AD POINTER TO LAST BUFFER     @E@@@@          SA        A0,FL,A1        DQ
)@@G@@    CHAIN NEXT TO LAST  @E@@@@          SX        A1,BL,A0            CHDR
)@@G@@AIN LAST TO NEXT  @F@@@@          SA        A2,LASTD            UPDATE NDS
)@@G@@EXT FREE WORD     @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,,A2              LOAD TOPDT
)@@G@@ OF CORE    @G@@@@          ANA,U     A0,1                PARAMETER IS HDU
)@@G@@IGHEST WORD NEEDED@G@@@@          LXI,U     A0,0200000          SET FOR DV
)@@G@@PROGRAM-WIDE RELEASE    @E@@@@          LCORE$    .                   REDW
)@@G@@LEASE UNUSED CORE @F@@@@          LXI,U     A0                  CLEAR PRDX
)@@G@@OGRAM-WIDE FLAG   @F@@@@          TLE,U     A0,LASTD$+1         ARE WE SDY
)@@G@@TILL EXPANDED ?   @C@@@@          J         BRL4                RETURN  DZ
)@@G@@@H@@@@          LA,XH2    A1,,A0              YES.  LOAD LENGTH FROM THIEA
)@@G@@S BARRIER   @G@@@@          AU,U      A1,,A0              A2 = ADDRESS OEB
)@@G@@F LAST BUFFER HEAD@F@@@@          LA        A1,SIZE,A2          LOAD SIZEC
)@@G@@E OF THAT BUFFER  @H@@@@          JN        A1,BRL4             DONE WITED
)@@G@@H CONTRACTION OF THIS ONE BUSY@ @@@@          ON        MANREL    @H@@@@EE
)@@G@@          AA,U      A1,1,A2             COMPUTE END OF BUFFER + 1 ADDRESEF
)@@G@@S     @I@@@@          TNE       A1,LASTD            DOES THIS BUFFER ABUEG
)@@G@@T THE END OF MEMORY?    @F@@@@          J         BRL3                YEEH
)@@G@@S.  INVESTIGATE LCORE$  @G@@@@          J         BRL4                NOEI
)@@G@@.  NO FURTHER RELEASE POSSIBLE@ @@@@          OFF       MANREL    @ @@@@EJ
)@@G@@          ON        MANREL=0  @F@@@@          J         BRL5            EK
)@@G@@    CHECK FOR FURTHER RELEASES@ @@@@          OFF       MANREL=0  @ @@@@EL
)@@G@@          OFF       CORREL    @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         REEM
)@@G@@LEASE ANY AVAILABLE EXPANSION BUFFERS     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         LMEN
)@@G@@J       X11,BRELC @E@@@@.         <RETURN>                      X11, A0 EO
)@@G@@DESTROYED   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         IF THE CONFIGURATION TAGS MANUALEP
)@@G@@ AND LCORE ARE SET, THIS CODE WILL  @G@@@@.         BE ENABLED TO PERMITEQ
)@@G@@ THE RELEASE OF EXPANSION BLOCKS AT ANY   @C@@@@.         TIME DESIRED BER
)@@G@@Y THE CALLING PROGRAM.  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON        MANREL    ES
)@@G@@@E@@@@BRELC*    LXI,U     X11,,X11            SAVE ENTRY ADDRESS  @G@@@@ET
)@@G@@          P         CRIT                INVOKE CRITICAL SECTION LOCK    EU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DS        A1,SVA1             SAVE A1, A2   @G@@@@      EV
)@@G@@    LA        A1,LASTD            LOAD LAST ALLOCATED ADDRESS + 1 @G@@@@EW
)@@G@@          TLE,U     A1,LASTD$+1         ARE WE EXPANDED CURRENTLY ?     EX
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         BRL4                NO.  DON'T NEED TO RELEASEEY
)@@G@@@H@@@@          LA,U      A2,HEAD             LOAD ADDRESS OF BUFFER CHAEZ
)@@G@@IN HEAD     @G@@@@BRC1      LA        A2,FL,A2            CHAIN TO NEXT FA
)@@G@@AVAILABLE BUFFER  @F@@@@          TNE,U     A2,HEAD             END OF CFB
)@@G@@HAIN AND NO FIND ?@G@@@@          J         BRL4                YES.  REFC
)@@G@@TURN HAVING DONE NOTHING@F@@@@          LA        A1,SIZE,A2          LOFD
)@@G@@AD SIZE OF THIS BUFFER  @G@@@@          JN        A1,BRC1             IGFE
)@@G@@NORE IT IF IT'S ALLOCATED     @H@@@@          AA,U      A1,1,A2         FF
)@@G@@    COMPUTE FIRST WORD AFTER THIS BUFFER  @G@@@@          TE        A1,LFG
)@@G@@ASTD            IS IT LAST WORD ALLOCATED ?     @H@@@@          J       FH
)@@G@@  BRC1                NO.  THIS BUFFER DOES NOT ADJOIN END  @H@@@@      FI
)@@G@@    J         BRL3                YES.  THIS BUFFER IS AT END AND AVAIL FJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                                       GO ENTER RELEASE CODE     FK
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       MANREL    @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.     FL
)@@G@@    STATISTICS EDITOR   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         LMJ       X11,BSTATPFM
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         <RETURN>                      NO REGISTERS CHANGED@[@@@@FN
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@          ON        STATS     @E@@@@BSTATP*   P         CRITFO
)@@G@@                SET CRITICAL SECTION@C@@@@          SA        A0,SVA1   FP
)@@G@@          SAVE A0 @F@@@@          LA        A0,GETCALL          LOAD NUMFQ
)@@G@@BER OF BGET CALLS @E@@@@          E$BO      8,STATMS,8          EDIT INTFR
)@@G@@O MESSAGE   @F@@@@          LA        A0,RELCALL          GET NUMBER OF FS
)@@G@@REL CALLS   @G@@@@          E$BO      29,STATMS,8         AND PUT IT INTFT
)@@G@@O THE MESSAGE     @G@@@@          LA        A0,INUSE            LOAD NUMFU
)@@G@@BER OF WORDS IN USE     @E@@@@          E$BO      48,STATMS,6         EDFV
)@@G@@IT WORDS IN USE   @F@@@@          LNA       A0,MAXUSE           LOAD MAXFW
)@@G@@IMUM WORDS IN USE @D@@@@          E$BO      89,STATMS,6         EDIT THAFX
)@@G@@T     @^@@@@          ON        WAIT@F@@@@          LA        A0,WAITC  FY
)@@G@@          LOAD NUMBER OF DELAYS.    @C@@@@          E$BO      97,STATMS,FZ
)@@G@@6         EDIT IT.@^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@G@@@@          PRINT$  GA
)@@G@@  STATMS,STATMSL      PRINT THE CURRENT STATISTICS    @E@@@@          LAGB
)@@G@@        A0,SVA1             LOAD UP USER'S A0   @F@@@@          V       GC
)@@G@@  CRIT                CLEAR CRITICAL SECTION    @D@@@@          J       GD
)@@G@@  0,X11               RETURN TO CALL@ @@@@          OFF       STATS     GE
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         ERROR AND TRACE HANDLER   @[@@@@GF
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@          ON        ERRLEV>1  @E@@@@KABTRAP   LMJ       A2,$GG
)@@G@@+1              SAVE ADDRESS TRAPPED@F@@@@          ANA,U     A2,1      GH
)@@G@@          BACK UP TO EX INSTRUCTION @E@@@@          LA,H1     A2,,A2    GI
)@@G@@          RECOVER ERROR CODE  @D@@@@          LSSL      A2,18+10        GJ
)@@G@@    SHIFT OFF F, J@F@@@@          SSL       A2,18+10+4          SHIFT OFGK
)@@G@@F X, RIGHT JUSTIFY@F@@@@          LXI,U     A0,,A2              SAVE ERRGL
)@@G@@OR CODE FOR USER  @F@@@@          TE,U      A2,2                ERROR DEGM
)@@G@@TECTED FROM BREL ?@D@@@@          TNE,U     A2,3                ...BREL GN
)@@G@@?     @H@@@@          J         KABNG1              YES.  MUST CONVERT XGO
)@@G@@11 TO USER RETURN @ @@@@          ON        EXPINC=0  @G@@@@          TNGP
)@@G@@E,U     A2,4                WAS IT NO MORE CORE ERROR ?     @H@@@@      GQ
)@@G@@    LNA,XU    A0,NCWIU,A0         YES.  CONVERT A0 TO USER PARAMETER    GR
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LXI,U     A0,,A2              RESTORE ERROR CODE IN H1  GS
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       EXPINC=0  @]@@@@KABNG2    . @ @@@@          ONGT
)@@G@@        ERRLEV>2  @G@@@@          E$BO      41,REGM,6           EDIT A0 GU
)@@G@@CONTENTS INTO MESSAGE   @E@@@@          LXM,U     A0,,X11             GEGV
)@@G@@T RETURN ADDRESS  @F@@@@          E$BO      22,REGM,6           EDIT IT GW
)@@G@@INTO THE MESSAGE  @F@@@@          SSL       A0,18               RIGHT JUGX
)@@G@@STIFY ERROR NUMBER@ @@@@          OFF       ERRLEV>2  @ @@@@          ONGY
)@@G@@        ERRLEV=3  @E@@@@          E$BO      15,ERCM,3           EDIT ERRGZ
)@@G@@OR NUMBER   @ @@@@          OFF       ERRLEV=3  @ @@@@          ON      HA
)@@G@@  ERRLEV=4  @E@@@@          PRINT$P   ERRMT-1,A0          PRINT THE MESSHB
)@@G@@AGE   @ @@@@          OFF       ERRLEV=4  @ @@@@          ON        ERRLHC
)@@G@@EV>2  @F@@@@          PRINT$    DIAGM,DIAGL         PRINT REGISTER CONTEHD
)@@G@@NTS   @ @@@@          OFF       ERRLEV>2  @D@@@@          EABT$     .   HE
)@@G@@                TERMINATE RUN @[@@@@.     @C@@@@KABNG1    SX        X11,HF
)@@G@@ERRTMP          SAVE X11@F@@@@          LX,H1     X11,ERRTMP          REHG
)@@G@@LOAD RETURN ADDRESS     @F@@@@          J         KABNG2              REHH
)@@G@@TURN TO ERROR ROUTINE   @ @@@@          OFF       ERRLEV>1  @[@@@@.     HI
)@@G@@@[@@@@$(2). @ @@@@          ON        ERRLEV>2  @]@@@@DIAGM     . @ @@@@HJ
)@@G@@          ON        ERRLEV=3  @ @@@@ERCM      'ERROR CODE: 999'   @ @@@@HK
)@@G@@          OFF       ERRLEV=3  @D@@@@REGM      'RETURN ADDRESS: 999999  PHL
)@@G@@ARAMETER: 999999' @ @@@@DIAGL     EQU       $-DIAGM   @ @@@@          OFHM
)@@G@@F       ERRLEV>2  @ @@@@          ON        ERRLEV=4  @D@@@@ERRM1     'SHN
)@@G@@IZE REQUESTED EXCEEDS MAXIMUM BUFFER SIZE'@ @@@@ERRL1     EQU       $-ERHO
)@@G@@RM1   @F@@@@ERRM2     'ADDRESS PASSED TO BREL IS NOT AN ALLOCATED BUFFERHP
)@@G@@'     @ @@@@ERRL2     EQU       $-ERRM2   @E@@@@ERRM3     'BREL ERROR:  HQ
)@@G@@NEXT BUFFER BACKPOINTER IS BAD.'    @ @@@@ERRL3     EQU       $-ERRM3   HR
)@@G@@@C@@@@ERRM4     'INSUFFICIENT CORE TO SATISFY REQUEST'@ @@@@ERRL4     EQHS
)@@G@@U       $-ERRM4   @ @@@@PF        FORM      12,6,18   @]@@@@ERRMT     . HT
)@@G@@@A@@@@          PF        1,ERRL1,ERRM1   @A@@@@          PF        1,ERHU
)@@G@@RL2,ERRM2   @A@@@@          PF        1,ERRL3,ERRM3   @A@@@@          PFHV
)@@G@@        1,ERRL4,ERRM4   @ @@@@          OFF       ERRLEV=4  @ @@@@      HW
)@@G@@    ON        ERRLEV>1  @^@@@@ERRTMP    RES       1   @ @@@@          OFHX
)@@G@@F       ERRLEV>1  @A@@@@          ON        TRACE++WAIT     @E@@@@TSAVE HY

)@@G@@****  @D@@@@T$BGET    '999999  LMJ  X11,BGET  A0=999999999999'    @C@@@@IC
)@@G@@T$LBGET   EQU                           $-T$BGET@D@@@@T$BGET1   '      BID

)@@G@@9999999'    @C@@@@T$LBREL   EQU                           $-T$BREL@ @@@@IG
)@@G@@          ON        EXPINC>0  @C@@@@T$RQST    'REQUESTED 999999 WORDS VIIH
)@@G@@A MCORE$.'  @ @@@@T$LRQST   EQU       $-T$RQST  @ @@@@          OFF     II

)@@G@@D 999999 WORDS VIA LCORE$.'   @ @@@@T$LRTRN   EQU       $-T$RTRN  @ @@@@IK
)@@G@@          OFF       CORREL    @ @@@@          OFF       TRACE     @[@@@@IL
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@          ON        WAIT@^@@@@QUEUE0    TCELL$    .   @D@@@@IM
)@@G@@          RES       1                   FOR COUNT.    @^@@@@QUEUE1    TCIN
)@@G@@ELL$    .   @ @@@@QCOUNT    EQUF      $-QUEUE1  @D@@@@          RES     IO
)@@G@@  1                   FOR COUNT.    @A@@@@QTF       *         QUEUE0,QUEIP
)@@G@@UE1   @ @@@@QTO       EQUF      QTF,,H1   @ @@@@QFROM     EQUF      QTF,IQ
)@@G@@,H2   @^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON      IR
)@@G@@  STATS     @]@@@@STATMS    . @D@@@@          '99999999 BGET CALLS, 9999IS
)@@G@@9999 BREL CALLS, '@E@@@@          '999999 WORDS IN USE, MAXIMUM USE SO FIT
)@@G@@AR: 999999.'@^@@@@          ON        WAIT@ @@@@          '        WAITSIU
)@@G@@.'    @^@@@@          OFF       WAIT@ @@@@STATMSL   EQU       $-STATMS  IV
)@@G@@@ @@@@          OFF       STATS     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         OCTAL EDIW
)@@G@@ITOR FOR TRACE AND ERROR MESSAGES   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@          ON      IX
)@@G@@  EDITOR    @^@@@@EBO$      I$        .   @F@@@@          J         $(1)IY
)@@G@@                ENTER REENTRANT IBANK     @ @@@@$(1)      DS        A0,SIZ
)@@G@@A0    @ @@@@          DS        A2,SA2    @ @@@@          SR        R1,VJA
)@@G@@R1    @ @@@@          SR        R2,VR2    @ @@@@          LA,H1     A2,*JB
)@@G@@EBO$  @ @@@@          AND,U     A2,077    @^@@@@          LA,U      A2,0JC
)@@G@@@ @@@@          AA,H2     A2,*EBO$  @F@@@@          LXI,U     A2,-1     JD
)@@G@@          SET UP WORD INCREMENT     @F@@@@          LXI,U     A3,-1     JE
)@@G@@          SET UP CHARACTER INCREMENT@F@@@@          LR,U      R2,-7     JF
)@@G@@          INITIALISE MASK FOR MLU   @ @@@@          LR,S1     R1,*EBO$  JG
)@@G@@@^@@@@          J         EBO2@ @@@@EBO1      MLU,U     A0,'0'    @ @@@@JH

)@@G@@    LA,H2     A2,EBO$             LOAD PARAMETER ADDRESS    @F@@@@      JK
)@@G@@    AA,U      A2,1                POINT TO NEXT INSTRUCTION @F@@@@      JL
)@@G@@    SA,H2     A2,EBO$             SET UP FOR INDIRECT RETURN@ @@@@      JM

)@@G@@    LR        R2,VR2    @C@@@@          J         *EBO$               REJO

)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@B@@@@.         STORE SIXTH WORD ASCII CHARACTER@@@@@@@ @@@[LY
)@@G@@          ON        SIXBIT    @G@@@@ASCHR$*   STORE     TSQ,A0          LZ

)@@G@@          RETURN  @ @@@[          OFF       SIXBIT    @@@@@@@@@@@@@ @@@@MB
)@@G@@.         STORE FIELDATA WORDS@@@@@@@C@@@@AFD1$*    LA,U      A3,5      MC
)@@G@@          ONE WORD@C@@@@          J         EFD1                SKIP    MD
)@@G@@@D@@@@AFD2$*    LA,U      A3,11               TWO WORDS     @G@@@@EFD1  ME
)@@G@@    DSC       A0,66               POSITION THE NEXT CHARACTER     @E@@@@MF
)@@G@@          AND,U     A1,1*/6-1           ISOLATE IT IN A2    @E@@@@      MG
)@@G@@    TE,U      A2,' '              IS IT A BLANK ?     @E@@@@          TNMH
)@@G@@E,U     A2,'@'              OR A MASTERSPACE ?  @D@@@@          J       MI
)@@G@@  EFD1A               YES. SKIP IT  @G@@@@          LA        A2,TFQ,A2 MJ
)@@G@@          TRANSLATE FIELDATA TO ASCII     @D@@@@          TE,U      A2,NMK
)@@G@@ULL             IS IT A NULL ?@D@@@@          STORE     .               ML
)@@G@@    NO. STORE IT  @D@@@@EFD1A     JGD       A3,EFD1             LOOP ON MM
)@@G@@A3    @C@@@@          J         0,X11               RETURN  @C@@@@AFD3$*MN
)@@G@@    LA,U      A3,5                ONE WORD@^@@@@          J         EFD2MO
)@@G@@@D@@@@AFD4$*    LA,U      A3,11               TWO WORDS     @G@@@@EFD2  MP
)@@G@@    DSC       A0,66               POSITION THE NEXT CHARACTER     @E@@@@MQ
)@@G@@          AND,U     A1,1*/6-1           ISOLATE IT IN A2    @E@@@@      MR
)@@G@@    JZ        A2,EFD2A            SKIP MASTERSPACES   @E@@@@          LAMS
)@@G@@        A2,TFQ,A2           TRANSLATE TO ASCII  @D@@@@          TE,U    MT
)@@G@@  A2,NULL             IS IT A NULL  @D@@@@          STORE     .         MU
)@@G@@          NO. STORE IT  @D@@@@EFD2A     JGD       A3,EFD2             LOMV
)@@G@@OP ON A3    @C@@@@          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@]MW
)@@G@@@D@@@].         EDIT FIELDATA IGNORING ONLY TRAILING SPACES @@@@@]@F@@@]MX
)@@G@@AFD5$*    LA        A1,('      ')       TURN INTO DOUBLE WORD     @F@@@]MY
)@@G@@AFD6$*    LA,U      A3,11               INITIALISE SHIFT COUNT    @G@@@]MZ
)@@G@@          SX        X11,RET             SAVE RETURN POINT TO CALLER     NA
)@@G@@@G@@@]          LX,U      X11,0               CLEAR SHIFT COUNT TO RE-ADNB
)@@G@@JUST  @F@@@]AFD3      AND,U     A1,1*/6-1           MASK OUT LAST CHARACNC
)@@G@@TER   @F@@@]          TE,U      A2,' '              IS IT A TRAILING SPAND
)@@G@@CE ?  @H@@@]          J         AFD4                NO.  DONE ELIMINATINNE
)@@G@@G TRAILING SPACES @G@@@]          AX,U      X11,6               UPDATE CNF
)@@G@@OUNT OF TOTAL SHIFT     @F@@@]          DSL       A0,6                DING
)@@G@@SCARD TRAILING SPACE    @F@@@]          JGD       A3,AFD3             MONH
)@@G@@RE CHARACTERS TO TEST ? @F@@@]          LX        X11,RET             NONI
)@@G@@.  LOAD RETURN POINT    @G@@@]          J         0,X11               RENJ
)@@G@@TURN.  INPUT WAS ALL SPACES   @[@@@].     @H@@@]AFD4      LDSL      A0,,NK
)@@G@@X11             RESTORE LEFT-JUSTIFICATION OF DATA    @G@@@]          LXNL
)@@G@@        X11,RET             LOAD RETURN POINT TO CALLER     @G@@@]AFD5  NM
)@@G@@    DSC       A0,72-6             MOVE NEXT CHARACTER TO LOW A1   @E@@@]NN
)@@G@@          AND,U     A1,1*/6-1           ISOLATE IT IN A2    @G@@@]      NO
)@@G@@    STORE     TFQ,A2              TRANSLATE TO ASCII AND STORE    @F@@@]NP
)@@G@@          JGD       A3,AFD5             LOOP STORING CHARACTERS   @E@@@]NQ
)@@G@@          J         0,X11               RETURN TO CALLER    @@@@@@@@@@@@NR
)@@G@@@B@@@@.         STORE SIXTH WORD ASCII (6 BITS) @@@@@@@ @@@[          ONNS
)@@G@@        SIXBIT    @C@@@@ASW1$*    LA,U      A3,5                ONE WORDNT
)@@G@@@^@@@@          J         ASW1@D@@@@ASW2$*    LA,U      A3,11           NU
)@@G@@    TWO WORDS     @F@@@@ASW1      DSC       A0,72-6             POSITIONNV
)@@G@@ NEXT CHARACTER   @D@@@@          AND,U     A1,1*/6-1           6 BITS INW
)@@G@@N A2  @F@@@@          LA        A2,TSQ,A2           TRANSLATE SIXTH TO QNX
)@@G@@UARTER@F@@@@          TE,U      A2,BLANK            SKIP BLANKS AND NULLNY
)@@G@@S     @ @@@@          TNE,U     A2,NULL   @^@@@@          J         ASW2NZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          STORE     .                   STORE CHARACTER     @C@@@@OA
)@@G@@ASW2      JGD       A3,ASW1             REPEAT  @C@@@@          J       OB
)@@G@@  0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@@@C@@@@ASW3$*    LA,U      A3,5      OC
)@@G@@          ONE WORD@^@@@@          J         ASW3@D@@@@ASW4$*    LA,U    OD
)@@G@@  A3,11               TWO WORDS     @F@@@@ASW3      DSC       A0,72-6   OE
)@@G@@          POSITION NEXT CHARACTER   @D@@@@          AND,U     A1,1*/6-1 OF
)@@G@@          6 BITS IN A2  @F@@@@          LA        A2,TSQ,A2           TROG
)@@G@@ANSLATE SIXTH TO QUARTER@D@@@@          TE,U      A2,NULL             SKOH
)@@G@@IP NULLS    @E@@@@          STORE     .                   STORE CHARACTEOI
)@@G@@R     @C@@@@          JGD       A3,ASW3             REPEAT  @C@@@@      OJ
)@@G@@    J         0,X11               RETURN  @ @@@[          OFF       SIXBOK
)@@G@@IT    @@@@@@@@@@@@@C@@@@.         COPY A STRING WITH OR WITHOUT PACKING OL
)@@G@@@@@@@@@E@@@@AFCOP$*   LA,U      A3,0,A1             A3 = CHARACTER COUNTOM
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DSL       A0,18               POSITION CHARACTER INDEX  ON
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SSL       A1,18               POSITION WORD INDEX @E@@@@OO
)@@G@@          LXI,U     A0,1                SET UP INCREMENTS   @^@@@@      OP
)@@G@@    LXI,U     A1,1@D@@@@          J         ECOPY2              JUMP INTOQ
)@@G@@O LOOP@D@@@@ECOPY1    EX        EDITL,*A0           GET CHARACTER @G@@@@OR
)@@G@@          STORE     TFQ,A2              TRANSLATE AND STORE CHARACTER   OS
)@@G@@@C@@@@ECOPY2    JGD       A3,ECOPY1           REPEAT  @C@@@@          J OT
)@@G@@        0,X11               RETURN  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@AFPAC$*   LA,U    OU
)@@G@@  A3,0,A1             A3 = CHARACTER COUNT@F@@@@          DSL       A0,1OV
)@@G@@8               POSITON CHARACTER INDEX   @E@@@@          SSL       A1,1OW
)@@G@@8               POSITION WORD INDEX @E@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1      OX
)@@G@@          SET UP INCREMENTS   @^@@@@          LXI,U     A1,1@D@@@@      OY
)@@G@@    J         EPACK3              JUMP INTO LOOP@D@@@@EPACK1    EX      OZ
)@@G@@  EDITL,*A0           GET CHARACTER @D@@@@          TNE,U     A2,' '    PA
)@@G@@          IS IT A BLANK?@C@@@@          J         EPACK4              YEPB
)@@G@@S     @E@@@@EPACK2    JZ        A2,EPACK3           SKIP MASTERSPACES   PC
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA        A2,TFQ,A2           TRANSLATE FIELDATA TO ASCIPD
)@@G@@I     @D@@@@          TE,U      A2,NULL             IS IT A NULL ?@D@@@@PE
)@@G@@          STORE     .                   NO. STORE IT  @C@@@@EPACK3    JGPF
)@@G@@D       A3,EPACK1           REPEAT  @C@@@@          J         0,X11     PG
)@@G@@          RETURN  @G@@@@EPACK4    LA        A2,TFQ,A2           TRANSLATPH
)@@G@@E FIELDATA TO ASCII     @E@@@@          STORE     .                   STPI
)@@G@@ORE THE BLANK     @C@@@@          JGD       A3,EPACK5           CONTINUEPJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@          J         0,X11     @E@@@@EPACK5    EX        EDITL,*A0 PK
)@@G@@          GET A CHARACTER     @D@@@@          TE,U      A2,' '          PL
)@@G@@    IS IT A BLANK?@F@@@@          J         EPACK2              NO. BACKPM
)@@G@@ TO MAIN LOOP     @D@@@@          JGD       A3,EPACK5           YES. IGNPN
)@@G@@ORE IT@C@@@@          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@@@A@@@@PO
)@@G@@.         GENERALIZED MESSAGE EDITOR@@@@@@@F@@@@AFMSR$*   LXI,U     X11,PP
)@@G@@0               INDICATE SAVE POINTER     @G@@@@          LA        A0,CPQ
)@@G@@IM              RESTORE THE CHARACTER INDEX     @F@@@@          LA      PR
)@@G@@  A1,WIM              RESTORE THE WORD INDEX    @C@@@@          J       PS
)@@G@@  EMSG1               BYPASS  @E@@@@AFMS1$*   LXI,U     X11,-1          PT
)@@G@@    INDICATE NO SAVE    @ @@@@          J         EMSG0     @F@@@@AFMSG$PU
)@@G@@*   LXI,U     X11,0               INDICATE SAVE POINTER     @G@@@@EMSG0 PV
)@@G@@    DSL       A0,18               POSITION THE CHARACTER INDEX    @F@@@@PW
)@@G@@          SSL       A1,18               POSITION THE WORD INDEX   @F@@@@PX
)@@G@@EMSG1     LXI,U     A0,1                SET UP THE INCREMENTS     @^@@@@PY
)@@G@@          LXI,U     A1,1@F@@@@EMSG2     EX        EDITL,*A0           GEPZ
)@@G@@T THE NEXT CHARACTER    @G@@@#          LA        A2,TFQ,A2           TRQA
)@@G@@ANSLATE CHARACTER TO ASCII    @E@@@@          TNE       A2,EMSGC        QB
)@@G@@    IS IT THE SIGNAL ?  @C@@@@          J         EMSG3               YEQC
)@@G@@S     @E@#@@          STORE     TFQ,A2              TRANSLATE AND STORE QD
)@@G@@@E@@@#          STORE     .                   TRANSLATE AND STORE @C@@@@QE
)@@G@@          J         EMSG2               LOOP    @C@@@@EMSG3     TP      QF
)@@G@@  X11                 SAVE IT?@B@@@@          J         0,X11           QG
)@@G@@    NO@F@@@@          SA        A0,CIM              SAVE THE CHARACTER IQH
)@@G@@NDEX  @E@@@@          SA        A1,WIM              SAVE THE WORD INDEX QI
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@@@^@@@@.     QJ
)@@G@@    LOAD VECTOR   @@@@@@@ @@@@EDITL     LA,S1     A2,,A1    @ @@@@      QK
)@@G@@    LA,S2     A2,,A1    @ @@@@          LA,S3     A2,,A1    @ @@@@      QL
)@@G@@    LA,S4     A2,,A1    @ @@@@          LA,S5     A2,,A1    @D@@@@      QM
)@@G@@    LMJ       A0,$+1              BREAK OUT     @F@@@@          LA,S6   QN
)@@G@@  A2,,*A1             LOAD THE LAST CHARACTER   @E@@@@          SA,H2   QO
)@@G@@  A0,RETURN           SET UP THE RETURN   @G@@@@          LXM,U     A0,0QP
)@@G@@                INITIALIZE THE CHARACTER INDEX  @C@@@@          J       QQ
)@@G@@  *RETURN             GET BACK@@@^@@@ @^@@.         GENERAL FORM EDITOR QR
)@@G@@@@@^@@@D@^@@AFI$*     LA        A1,(A$FW 6,4,4,4,2,16) I$ FORM    @@@^@@QS
)@@G@@@ @^@@AFORM$*   LA        A3,A0     @ @^@@          LA        A0,A1     QT
)@@G@@@E@^@@          JN        A0,EF2              JUMP IF 36 BIT FORM @G@^@@QU
)@@G@@          JNZ       A0,EF1              JUMP IF THERE IS A FORM WORD    QV
)@@G@@@E@^@@          LA        A0,(1*/35)          EDIT A 36 BIT GROUP @^@^@@QW
)@@G@@          J         EF2 @E@^@@EF1       LSC       A0,A0               FIQX
)@@G@@ND THE FIRST BIT  @G@^@@          LSSL      A0,1                GET RID QY
)@@G@@OF UPPER PART OF FORM   @H@^@@          LSSL      A3,1,A1             GEQZ
)@@G@@T RID OF UPPER PART OF THE WORD     @E@^@@EF2       ANA       A0,(1*/35)RA
)@@G@@          REMOVE THE UPPER BIT@E@^@@          LSC       A1,A0           RB
)@@G@@    FIND THE SECOND BIT @E@^@@          LDSL      A0,36+1             CORC
)@@G@@MPLETE THE SHIFT  @D@^@@          SSL       A0,0,A2             MOVE IT RD
)@@G@@BACK  @E@^@@          OR,U      A0,1                PUT A BIT AT THE ENDRE
)@@G@@@ @^@@          DL        A0,A1     @@@^@@@H@^@@EF3       AA,U      A1,1RF
)@@G@@                COMPUTE NUMBER OF BITS FOR FIRST SHIFT@F@^@@          MSRG
)@@G@@I       A1,(0252525252525)  COMPUTE MOD(A1-1,3)+1     @ @^@@          SSRH
)@@G@@L       A1,34     @ @^@@          SSL       A2,36     @F@^@@          LDRI
)@@G@@SL      A2,0,A1             SHIFT 1, 2, OR 3 BITS     @@@^@@@E@^@@EF4   RJ
)@@G@@    STORE     TFQ+'0',A2          STORE OCTAL DIGIT   @H@^@@          JNRK
)@@G@@S       A0,EF5              NEGATIVE FORM WORD IS END OF GROUP    @ @^@@RL
)@@G@@          JNS       A0,EF5    @ @^@@          JNS       A0,EF5    @ @^@@RM
)@@G@@          SSL       A2,36     @^@^@@          LDSL      A2,3@F@^@@      RN
)@@G@@    J         EF4                 CONTINUE WITH THIS GROUP  @@@^@@@E@^@@RO
)@@G@@EF5       SSL       A0,1                SHIFT FORM WORD BACK@E@^@@      RP
)@@G@@    JZ        A0,0,X11            EXIT IF NO MORE BITS@D@^@@          STRQ
)@@G@@ORE,U   BLANK               STORE A BLANK @E@^@@          LSC       A0,ARR
)@@G@@0               FIND THE NEXT BIT   @E@^@@          LSSL      A0,1      RS
)@@G@@          COMPLETE THE SHIFT  @D@^@@          SSL       A0,0,A1         RT
)@@G@@    MOVE IT BACK  @F@^@@          J         EF3                 REPEAT FRU
)@@G@@OR NEXT GROUP     @@@^@@@C@^@@AFH$*     LA        A1,(A$FW 18,18)     HARV
)@@G@@LVES  @ @^@@          J         AFORM$    @@@^@@@[@@@@/     @@@@@@@@@@@@RW
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         TRANSLATION TABLES  @@@@@@@^@@@@C*        PROC      1,1 RX
)@@G@@@ @@@@F         FORM      9,9,6,12  @B@@@@          F         C(1,2),C(1RY
)@@G@@,3),C(1,4),0@#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@@@@@@@D@@@@.         Q1:     RZ
)@@G@@  FIELDATA TO QUARTER WORD ASCII    @E@@@@.         Q2:       SIXTH WORDSA
)@@G@@ ASCII TO QUARTER WORD ASCII  @C@@@@.         S4:       SIXTH WORD ASCIISB

)@@G@@    C         051,LP7,RP7,')' @A@@@@          C         052,PC7,AST7,'*'TC

)@@G@@SH7,'/'     @@@@@@@A@@@@          C         060,A07,A07,'0' @A@@@@      TG
)@@G@@    C         061,A17,A17,'1' @A@@@@          C         062,A27,A27,'2' TH
)@@G@@@A@@@@          C         063,A37,A37,'3' @A@@@@          C         064,TI
)@@G@@A47,A47,'4' @A@@@@          C         065,A57,A57,'5' @A@@@@          C TJ
)@@G@@        066,A67,A67,'6' @A@@@@          C         067,A77,A77,'7' @@@@@@TK

)@@G@@A97,A97,'9' @B@@@@          C         072,APT7,CLN7,':'     @B@@@@      TM
)@@G@@    C         073,SEMI7,SEMI7,';'   @B@@@@          C         074,SLSH7,TN
)@@G@@LTN7,'<'    @A@@@@          C         075,PR7,EQ7,'=' @B@@@@          C TO
)@@G@@        076,QUTS7,GTN7,'>'    @B@@@@          C         077,0137,QUST7,'TP
)@@G@@?'    @@@@@@@@@@@@@#@@@@          END     ___   *[@@@@*SDFF*@@@@@@@@@@@@TQ
)@@G@@@A@]@@.         ADIT$ EDITTING PACKAGE    @A@@@].         ADIT$ EDITING TR
)@@G@@PACKAGE     @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@#@@@@          AXR$    @#@@@@          A$TS
)@@G@@DEF   @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@B@@@@.         COPY A QUARTER WORD ASCII STRINGTT
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@]@@@@AQCOP$*     @E@@@@ACOPY$*   LA,U      A3,0,A1         TU
)@@G@@    A3 = CHARACTER COUNT@F@@@@          DSL       A0,18               POTV
)@@G@@SITION CHARACTER INDEX  @E@@@@          SSL       A1,18               POTW
)@@G@@SITION WORD INDEX @E@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1                SET UP ITX
)@@G@@NCREMENTS   @^@@@@          LXI,U     A1,1@D@@@@          J         AQCOTY
)@@G@@P2              ENTER THE LOOP@D@@@@AQCOP1    EX        ADITL,*A0       TZ
)@@G@@    GET CHARACTER @ @@@[          ON        PARSTRIP  @E@@@@          LSUA
)@@G@@SL      A2,36-7             STRIP OFF PARITY    @ @@@@          SSL     UB
)@@G@@  A2,36-7   @ @@@[          OFF       PARSTRIP  @D@@@@          PARITY  UC
)@@G@@  .                   INSERT PARITY @E@@@@          STORE     .         UD
)@@G@@          STORE CHARACTER     @C@@@@AQCOP2    JGD       A3,AQCOP1       UE
)@@G@@    REPEAT  @C@@@@          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@@UF
)@@G@@@@@@@@@]@@@@AQPAC$*     @E@@@@APACK$*   LA,U      A3,0,A1             A3UG
)@@G@@ = CHARACTER COUNT@F@@@@          DSL       A0,18               POSITIONUH
)@@G@@ CHARACTER INDEX  @E@@@@          SSL       A1,18               POSITIONUI
)@@G@@ WORD INDEX @D@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1                SET INCREMENTSUJ
)@@G@@@^@@@@          LXI,U     A1,1@E@@@@          J         AQPAC3          UK
)@@G@@    JUMP INTO THE LOOP  @E@@@@AQPAC1    EX        ADITL,*A0           GEUL
)@@G@@T NEXT CHARACTER  @ @@@[          ON        PARSTRIP  @E@@@@          LSUM
)@@G@@SL      A2,36-7             STRIP OFF PARITY    @ @@@@          SSL     UN
)@@G@@  A2,36-7   @ @@@[          OFF       PARSTRIP  @D@@@@          PARITY  UO
)@@G@@  .                   INSERT PARITY @D@@@@          TNE,U     A2,BLANK  UP
)@@G@@          IS IT A BLANK?@C@@@@          J         AQPAC4              YEUQ
)@@G@@S     @D@@@@AQPAC2    TE,U      A2,NULL             IS IT A NULL? @D@@@@UR
)@@G@@          STORE     .                   NO. STORE IT  @C@@@@AQPAC3    JGUS
)@@G@@D       A3,AQPAC1           REPEAT  @C@@@@          J         0,X11     UT
)@@G@@          EXIT    @E@@@@AQPAC4    STORE     .                   STORE THUU
)@@G@@E BLANK     @C@@@@          JGD       A3,AQPAC5           CONTINUE@C@@@@UV
)@@G@@          J         0,X11               RETURN  @E@@@@AQPAC5    EX      UW
)@@G@@  ADITL,*A0           GET NEXT CHARACTER  @ @@@[          ON        PARSUX
)@@G@@TRIP  @E@@@@          LSSL      A2,36-7             STRIP OFF PARITY    UY
)@@G@@@ @@@@          SSL       A2,36-7   @ @@@[          OFF       PARSTRIP  UZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          PARITY    .                   INSERT PARITY @E@@@@      VA
)@@G@@    TE,U      A2,BLANK            IS IT ANOTHER BLANK?@F@@@@          J VB
)@@G@@        AQPAC2              NO. BACK TO MAIN LOOP     @D@@@@          JGVC
)@@G@@D       A3,AQPAC5           YES. IGNORE IT@C@@@@          J         0,X1VD
)@@G@@1               RETURN  @@@@@@@A@[@@.         GENERLIZED MESSAGE EDITOR VE
)@@G@@@A@@@[.         GENERALIZED MESSAGE EDITOR@@@@@@@H@[@@AQMSGR$*  . THIS TVF
)@@G@@AG WAS A MISTAKE, BUT NOW WE'VE GOTO TO KEEP IT AROUND...   @H@#@[AQMSGRVG
)@@G@@$*  . THIS TAG WAS A MISTAKE, BUT NOW WE'VE GOTTA TO KEEP IT AROUND...  VH
)@@G@@@A@#@@AQMSR$*   . THIS IS THE PROPER TAG  @]@@@#AQMSR$*   . @F@@@@AMSGR$VI
)@@G@@*   LXI,U     X11,0               INDICATE SAVE POINTER     @G@@@@      VJ
)@@G@@    LA        A0,CIM              RESTORE THE CHARACTER INDEX     @F@@@@VK
)@@G@@          LA        A1,WIM              RESTORE THE WORD INDEX    @C@@@@VL
)@@G@@          J         AMSG1               BYPASS  @]@@@@AQMS1$*     @E@@@@VM
)@@G@@AMSG1$*   LXI,U     X11,-1              INDICATE NO SAVE    @ @@@@      VN
)@@G@@    J         AMSG0     @]@@@@AQMSG$*     @F@@@@AMSG$*    LXI,U     X11,VO
)@@G@@0               INDICATE SAVE POINTER     @G@@@@AMSG0     DSL       A0,1VP
)@@G@@8               POSITION THE CHARACTER INDEX    @F@@@@          SSL     VQ
)@@G@@  A1,18               POSITION THE WORD INDEX   @F@@@@AMSG1     LXI,U   VR
)@@G@@  A0,1                SET UP THE INCREMENTS     @^@@@@          LXI,U   VS
)@@G@@  A1,1@F@@@@AMSG2     EX        ADITL,*A0           GET THE NEXT CHARACTVT
)@@G@@ER    @E@@@@          TNE       A2,EMSGC            IS IT THE SIGNAL?   VU
)@@G@@@C@@@@          J         AMSG3               YES     @ @@@[          ONVV
)@@G@@        PARSTRIP  @E@@@@          LSSL      A2,36-7             STRIP OFVW
)@@G@@F PARITY    @ @@@@          SSL       A2,36-7   @ @@@[          OFF     VX
)@@G@@  PARSTRIP  @D@@@@          PARITY    .                   INSERT PARITY VY
)@@G@@@E@@@@          STORE     .                   STORE CHARACTER     @C@@@@VZ
)@@G@@          J         AMSG2               LOOP    @D@@@@AMSG3     TP      WA
)@@G@@  X11                 SAVE POSITION?@B@@@@          J         0,X11     WB
)@@G@@          NO@F@@@@          SA        A0,CIM              SAVE THE CHARAWC
)@@G@@CTER INDEX  @E@@@@          SA        A1,WIM              SAVE THE WORD WD
)@@G@@INDEX @C@@@@          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@@@@@@@@WE
)@@G@@@^@@@@.         LOAD VECTOR   @@@@@@@ @@@@ADITL     LA,Q1     A2,0,A1   WF
)@@G@@@ @@@@          LA,Q2     A2,0,A1   @ @@@@          LA,Q3     A2,0,A1   WG
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LMJ       A0,$+1              BREAK OUT     @F@@@@      WH
)@@G@@    LA,Q4     A2,0,*A1            LOAD THE LAST CHARACTER   @E@@@@      WI
)@@G@@    SA,H2     A0,RETURN           SET UP THE RETURN   @G@@@@          LXWJ
)@@G@@M,U     A0,0                INITIALIZE THE CHARACTER INDEX  @C@@@@      WK
)@@G@@    J         *RETURN             GO BACK @@@@@@@ @@@@.         GENERAL WL
)@@G@@FORM EDITOR @@@@@@@D@@@@AFI$*     LA        A1,(A$FW 6,4,4,4,2,16) I$ FOWM
)@@G@@RM    @@@@@@@ @@@@AFORM$*   LA        A3,A0     @ @@@@          LA      WN
)@@G@@  A0,A1     @E@@@@          JN        A0,EF2              JUMP IF 36 BITWO
)@@G@@ FORM @G@@@@          JNZ       A0,EF1              JUMP IF THERE IS A FWP
)@@G@@ORM WORD    @E@@@@          LA        A0,(1*/35)          EDIT A 36 BIT WQ
)@@G@@GROUP @^@@@@          J         EF2 @E@@@@EF1       LSC       A0,A0     WR
)@@G@@          FIND THE FIRST BIT  @G@@@@          LSSL      A0,1            WS
)@@G@@    GET RID OF UPPER PART OF FORM   @H@@@@          LSSL      A3,1,A1   WT
)@@G@@          GET RID OF UPPER PART OF THE WORD     @E@@@@EF2       ANA     WU
)@@G@@  A0,(1*/35)          REMOVE THE UPPER BIT@E@@@@          LSC       A1,AWV
)@@G@@0               FIND THE SECOND BIT @E@@@@          LDSL      A0,36+1   WW
)@@G@@          COMPLETE THE SHIFT  @D@@@@          SSL       A0,0,A2         WX
)@@G@@    MOVE IT BACK  @E@@@@          OR,U      A0,1                PUT A BIWY
)@@G@@T AT THE END@ @@@@          DL        A0,A1     @@@@@@@H@@@@EF3       AAWZ
)@@G@@,U      A1,1                COMPUTE NUMBER OF BITS FOR FIRST SHIFT@F@@@@XA
)@@G@@          MSI       A1,(0252525252525)  COMPUTE MOD(A1-1,3)+1     @ @@@@XB
)@@G@@          SSL       A1,34     @ @@@@          SSL       A2,36     @F@@@@XC
)@@G@@          LDSL      A2,0,A1             SHIFT 1, 2, OR 3 BITS     @@@@@@XD
)@@G@@@E@@@^EF4       AA,U      A2,ZER              FORM ASCII DIGIT    @F@@@^XE
)@@G@@          PARITY    .                   GET PARITY ON CHARACTER   @D@@@^XF
)@@G@@          STORE     .                   STORE IN IMAGE@H@@@@          JNXG
)@@G@@S       A0,EF5              NEGATIVE FORM WORD IS END OF GROUP    @ @@@@XH
)@@G@@          JNS       A0,EF5    @ @@@@          JNS       A0,EF5    @ @@@@XI
)@@G@@          SSL       A2,36     @^@@@@          LDSL      A2,3@F@@@@      XJ
)@@G@@    J         EF4                 CONTINUE WITH THIS GROUP  @@@@@@@E@@@@XK
)@@G@@EF5       SSL       A0,1                SHIFT FORM WORD BACK@E@@@@      XL
)@@G@@    JZ        A0,0,X11            EXIT IF NO MORE BITS@D@@@@          STXM
)@@G@@ORE,U   BLANK               STORE A BLANK @E@@@@          LSC       A0,AXN
)@@G@@0               FIND THE NEXT BIT   @E@@@@          LSSL      A0,1      XO
)@@G@@          COMPLETE THE SHIFT  @D@@@@          SSL       A0,0,A1         XP
)@@G@@    MOVE IT BACK  @F@@@@          J         EF3                 REPEAT FXQ
)@@G@@OR NEXT GROUP     @@@@@@@C@@@@AFH$*     LA        A1,(A$FW 18,18)     HAXR
)@@G@@LVES  @ @@@@          J         AFORM$    @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@#@@@@      XS
)@@G@@    END     ___ RETURN  @E@@@@AQPAC5    EX        ADITL,*A0           GEXT
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@@HDG,N@#@@@@@DOC,Q EDIT$/DOC  @E@@@@@HDG,P EXTENDED EDXU
