)@@G@@  SAME AS APACK$. @[@A@#.     @F@A@#.         AFCOP$ -  SAME AS ACOPY$ EJO
)@@G@@XCEPT THE INPUT STRING IS     @ @A@#.                   FIELDATA. @[@A@#JP
)@@G@@.     @F@A@#.         AFPAC$ -  SAME AS APACK$ EXCEPT THE INPUT STRING IJQ
)@@G@@S     @ @A@#.                   FIELDATA. @[@A@#.     @E@A@#.         AMJR
)@@G@@SG$  -  COPIES THE CHARACTERS STARTING AT A0    @E@A@#.                 JS
)@@G@@  INTO THE IMAGE. THIS PROCESS STOPS WHEN @E@A@#.                   THE JT
)@@G@@CHARACTER IN Q1 OF THE THIRD WORD OF@E@A@#.                   THE PACKETJU
)@@G@@ IS FOUND. THE POINTER TO THIS@E@A@#.                   STRING IS SAVED JV
)@@G@@IN THE PACKET AND RETURN@B@A@#.                   IS MADE TO THE USER.  JW
)@@G@@@[@A@#.     @A@A@#.         AQMSG$ -  SAME AS AMSG$.  @[@A@#.     @E@A@#JX
)@@G@@.         AFMSG$ -  SAME AS AMSG$ EXCEPT THE INPUT STRING IS@ @A@#.     JY
)@@G@@              FIELDATA. @[@A@#.     @F@A@#.         AMSG1$ -  SAME AS AMJZ
)@@G@@SG$ EXCEPT THE POINTER IS NOT SAVED.@[@A@#.     @A@A@#.         AQMS1$ -KA
)@@G@@  SAME AS AMSG1$. @[@A@#.     @F@A@#.         AFMS1$ -  SAME AS AMSG1$ EKB
)@@G@@XCEPT THE INPUT STRING IS     @ @A@#.                   FIELDATA. @[@A@#KC
)@@G@@.     @E@A@#.         AMSGR$ -  THIS ROUTINE PERFORMS THE SAME OPERATIONKD
)@@G@@@F@A@#.                   AS AMSG$ EXCEPT THAT THE POINTER TO THE INPUT KE
)@@G@@@F@A@#.                   STRING IS TAKEN FROM THE PACKET. WITH THESE   KF
)@@G@@@F@A@#.                   TWO ROUTINES IT IS POSSIBLE TO COPY A STRING  KG
)@@G@@@F@A@#.                   INTO THE IMAGE AND OCCASIONALLY INTERRUPT THISKH
)@@G@@@F@A@#.                   PROCESS TO PERFORM OTHER EDITING FUNCTIONS    KI
)@@G@@@F@A@#.                   AT CERTAIN SELECTED POINTS IN THE STRING.     KJ
)@@G@@@[@A@#.     @A@A@#.         AQMSR$ -  SAME AS AMSGR$  @[@A@#.     @E@A@#KK
)@@G@@.         AFMSR$ -  SAME AS AMSGR$ EXCEPT THE INPUT STRING  @ @A@#.     KL
)@@G@@              FIELDATA. @[@A@#.     @E@A@#.         AOCTV$ -  EDITS A0 TKM
)@@G@@O OCTAL. THE NUMBER OF DIGITS @F@A@#.                   GENERATED WILL DKN
)@@G@@EPEND ON THE LOGICAL MAGNITUDE@F@A@#.                   OF A0. IF A0 IS KO
)@@G@@LOGICALLY GREATER THAN 7 A    @B@A@#.                   LEADING ZERO IS KP
)@@G@@ADDED.@[@A@#.     @F@A@#.         AOCTF$ -  EDITS A0 TO A1 OCTAL DIGITS.KQ
)@@G@@ LEADING ZEROS    @B@A@#.                   ARE NOT SUPRESSED.    @[@A@#KR
)@@G@@.     @F@A@#.         ADECV$ -  EDITS A0 TO A DECIMAL NUMBER. A LEADING KS
)@@G@@'-'   @F@A@#.                   IS ADDED IF A0 IS NEGATIVE. THE NUMBER OKT
)@@G@@F     @F@A@#.                   CHARACTERS GENERATED IS A FUNCTION OF THKU
)@@G@@E     @C@A@#.                   SIGN AND MAGNITUDE OF A0.   @[@A@#.     KV
)@@G@@@F@A@#.         ADECF$ -  EDITS A0 TO A DECIMAL NUMBER RIGHT JUSTIFIED  KW
)@@G@@@F@A@#.                   IN A FIELD OF A1 CHARACTERS. A LEADING '-'    KX
)@@G@@@F@A@#.                   IS ADDED IF A0 IS NEGATIVE. THE RESULT WILL   KY
)@@G@@@F@A@#.                   OVERFLOW THE FIELD TO THE RIGHT IF IT DOES    KZ
)@@G@@@E@A@#.                   NOT FIT IN THE SPECIFIED FIELD SIZE.    @[@A@#LA
)@@G@@.     @G@A@#.         ADECZ$ -  SAME AS ADECF$ EXCEPT LEADING ZEROS ARE LB
)@@G@@EDITED.     @[@A@#.     @F@A@#.         AFORM$ -  EDITS A0 TO A GENERAL LC
)@@G@@FORM (GROUPS OF OCTAL   @E@A@#.                   DIGITS SEPARATED BY SPLD
)@@G@@ACES) SPECIFIED   @F@A@#.                   BY THE FORM WORD IN A1.  EACLE
)@@G@@H BIT IN THE FORM @F@A@#.                   WORD DETERMINES THE LEFT BOULF
)@@G@@NDARY OF A GROUP. @F@A@#.                   IF THE 1*/35 BIT IS 0 THE FILG
)@@G@@RST GROUP WILL    @F@A@#.                   NOT BE EDITED.  IF THE FORM LH
)@@G@@WORD IS ZERO ALL  @E@A@#.                   36 BITS WILL BE EDITED IN ONLI
)@@G@@E GROUP.    @[@A@#.     @F@A@#.         AFI$   -  EDITS A0 INTO THE I$ FLJ
)@@G@@ORM (6,4,4,4,2,16).     @[@A@#.     @D@A@#.         AFH$   -  EDITS A0 ILK
)@@G@@NTO 2 18 BIT GROUPS.    @[@@@#.     @@@@@#@A@@@#.         INITIAL ENTRY LL
)@@G@@TO EDIT MODE@@@@@#@G@@@#ADIT$*    SX        PX,SAVE1-PKT,A0     SAVE THELM
)@@G@@ NON-VOLATILE REGISTERS @A@@@#          SX        CX,SAVE2-PKT,A0 @A@@@#LN
)@@G@@          SX        WX,SAVE3-PKT,A0 @F@@@#          TP,T1     $         LO
)@@G@@          IS QUARTER-WORD MODE ON ? @F@@@#          J         ADNQWM$   LP
)@@G@@          NO.  ABORT THE CALLER     @F@@@#          LXM,U     PX,,A0    LQ
)@@G@@          SET UP THE PACKET ADDRESS @E@@@#          LR        R1,IL     LR
)@@G@@          R1 = IMAGE LENGTH   @F@@@#          LX        CX,(1,0)        LS
)@@G@@    SET UP THE CHARACTER INDEX@F@@@#          LX        WX,ILOC         LT
)@@G@@    SET UP THE WORD INDEX     @^@@@#          LXI,U     WX,1@D@@@#      LU
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,(BLANKS)         BLANK THE LINE@ @@@#          BT      LV
)@@G@@  WX,,*A0   @F@@@#          LXM       WX,ILOC             INITIALIZE THELW
)@@G@@ WORD INDEX @C@@@#          SZ,S3     RETURN              FUDGE   @C@@@#LX
)@@G@@          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@#@E@@@#.         RELY
)@@G@@-ENTRY TO EDIT MODE AND ZERO COLUMN POINTER     @@@@@#@E@@@#ADITZ$*   SZLZ
)@@G@@        CIX-PKT,A0          RESET COLUMN POINTER@ @@@#          SZ      MA
)@@G@@  WIX-PKT,A0@@@@@#@A@@@#.         RE-ENTRY TO EDIT MODE     @@@@@#@G@@@#MB
)@@G@@ADITR$*   SX        PX,SAVE1-PKT,A0     SAVE THE NON-VOLATILE REGISTERS MC
)@@G@@@A@@@#          SX        CX,SAVE2-PKT,A0 @A@@@#          SX        WX,SMD
)@@G@@AVE3-PKT,A0 @F@@@#          TP,T1     $                   IS QUARTER-WORME
)@@G@@D MODE ON ? @F@@@#          J         ADNQWM$             NO.  ABORT THEMF
)@@G@@ CALLER     @F@@@#          LXM,U     PX,,A0              SET UP THE PACMG
)@@G@@KET ADDRESS @G@@@#          LXI,U     CX,1                RESTORE THE CHMH
)@@G@@ARACTER INDEX     @ @@@#          LXM       CX,CIX    @F@@@#          LXMI
)@@G@@I,U     WX,1                RESTORE THE WORD INDEX    @ @@@#          LXMJ
)@@G@@M       WX,WIX    @ @@@#          AX        WX,ILOC   @C@@@#          J MK
)@@G@@        0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@#@ @@@#.         EXIT FROM EDITML
)@@G@@ MODE @@@@@#@F@@@#ADITX$*   SX        CX,CIX              SAVE THE CHARAMM
)@@G@@CTER INDEX  @E@@@#          ANX       WX,ILOC             SAVE THE WORD MN
)@@G@@INDEX @ @@@#          SX        WX,WIX    @E@@@#          LA,U      A0,PMO
)@@G@@KT              A0 = PACKET LOCATION@H@@@#          LXM       PX,SAVE1  MP
)@@G@@          RESTORE THE NON-VOLATILE REGISTERS    @A@@@#          LX      MQ
)@@G@@  CX,SAVE2-PKT,A0 @A@@@#          LX        WX,SAVE3-PKT,A0 @C@@@#      MR
)@@G@@    J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@#@@@@@#@^@@@#.         STMS
)@@G@@ORE VECTOR  @@@@@#@ @@@#ADIT$T*   SA,Q1     A2,WI     @ @@@#          SAMT
)@@G@@,Q2     A2,WI     @ @@@#          SA,Q3     A2,WI     @D@@@#          LMMU
)@@G@@J       CX,ET1              BREAK OUT     @@@@@#@B@@@#          DO      MV
)@@G@@  4 , LMJ A2,ADARR$     @@@@@#@F@@@#ET1       SA,Q4     A2,,*WX         MW
)@@G@@    STORE THE LAST CHARACTER  @D@@@#AT$*      SX,H2     CX,RETURN       MX
)@@G@@    SET UP RETURN @F@@@#          LXM,U     CX,,A2              SAVE THEMY
)@@G@@ CHARACTER IN A2  @F@@@#          LA,U      A2,0,WX             IS NEXT MZ
)@@G@@STORE IN IMAGE?   @ @@@#          TLE       A2,ILOC   @^@@@#          J NA
)@@G@@        ET2 @ @@@#          ANA       A2,IL     @ @@@#          TG      NB
)@@G@@  A2,ILOC   @^@@@#          J         ET2 @F@@@#          L,U       A2,,NC
)@@G@@CX              RESTORE THE CHARACTER     @G@@@#          LXM,U     CX,0ND
)@@G@@                INITIALIZE THE CHARACTER INDEX  @ @@@#          J       NE
)@@G@@  *RETURN   @F@@@#ET2       L,U       A2,,CX              RESTORE THE CHNF
)@@G@@ARACTER     @B@@@#          LXM,U     CX,4                NO@^@@@#      NG
)@@G@@    ANX,U     WX,1@ @@@#          J         *RETURN   @@@@@#@ @@@#.     NH
)@@G@@    STORE A CHARACTER   @@@@@#@]@@@#AQCHR$*     @]@@@#ACHAR$*     @ @@@#NI
)@@G@@          ON        PARSTRIP  @E@@@#          LSSL      A0,36-7         NJ
)@@G@@    STRIP OFF PARITY    @ @@@#          SSL       A0,36-7   @ @@@#      NK
)@@G@@    OFF       PARSTRIP  @D@@@#          PARITY    A0                  INNL
)@@G@@SERT PARITY @E@@@#          STORE     A0                  STORE CHARACTENM
)@@G@@R     @C@@@#          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@#@A@@@#NN
)@@G@@.         POSITION TO A FIXED COLUMN@@@@@#@D@@@#ACOL$*    DSL       A0,2NO
)@@G@@                DIVIDE BY 4   @ @@@#          SSL       A1,36-2   @F@@@#NP
)@@G@@          AA        A0,ILOC             GET THE WORD LOCATION     @F@@@#NQ
)@@G@@          LXM,U     CX,,A1              SET UP THE CHARACTER INDEX@F@@@#NR
)@@G@@          LXM,U     WX,,A0              SET UP THE WORD INDEX     @E@@@#NS
)@@G@@          ANU       A0,IL               IS IT IN IMAGE?     @ @@@#      NT
)@@G@@    TLE       A1,ILOC   @ @@@#          TLE       A0,ILOC   @B@@@#      NU
)@@G@@    J         ECOL                NO@ @@@#          J         0,X11     NV
)@@G@@@@@@@#@D@@@#ECOL      AX,U      CX,4                OUT OF IMAGE  @^@@@#NW
)@@G@@          ANX,U     WX,1@C@@@#          J         0,X11               RENX
)@@G@@TURN  @@@@@#@^@@@#.         SKIP AN AREA  @@@@@#@F@@@#ASKIP$*   AA,U    NY
)@@G@@  A0,CI               ADD THE CHARACTER INDEX   @E@@@#          LA,U    NZ
)@@G@@  A1,WI               A1 = WORD INDEX     @E@@@#          ANA       A1,IOA
)@@G@@LOC             MAKE IT RELATIVE    @G@@@#          LSSL      A1,2      OB
)@@G@@          GET THE NUMBER OF CHARACTERS    @E@@@#          AA,U      A0,,OC
)@@G@@A1              A0 = COLUMN NUMBER  @D@@@#          J         ACOL$     OD
)@@G@@          FINISH UP     @@@@@#@A@@@#.         COMPUTE THE COLUMN NUMBER OE
)@@G@@@@@@@#@E@@@#ACOLN$*   LA,U      A0,WI               A0 = WORD INDEX     OF
)@@G@@@E@@@#          ANA       A0,ILOC             MAKE IT RELATIVE    @G@@@#OG
)@@G@@          LSSL      A0,2                GET THE NUMBER OF CHARACTERS    OH
)@@G@@@F@@@#          AA,U      A0,CI               ADD THE CHARACTER INDEX   OI
)@@G@@@C@@@#          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@#@D@@@#.     OJ
)@@G@@    CLEAR BUFFER TO SPACES AND RESET TO COLUMN 0@@@@@#@E@@@#ACLEAR$*  LROK
)@@G@@        R1,IL               R1 = IMAGE LENGTH   @E@@@#          LXM     OL
)@@G@@  WX,ILOC             SET UP WORD INDEX   @D@@@#          LA,U      A0,(OM
)@@G@@BLANKS)         BLANK THE LINE@ @@@#          BT        WX,,*A0   @E@@@#ON
)@@G@@          LXM,U     CX,0                RESET TO COLUMN 0   @ @@@#      OO
)@@G@@    LXM       WX,ILOC   @C@@@#          J         0,X11               REOP
)@@G@@TURN  @@@@@#@@@@@#@C@@@#.         STORE QUARTER WORD ASCII (7 OR 8 BITS)OQ
)@@G@@@@@@@#@C@@@#AQW1$*    LA,U      A3,3                ONE WORD@^@@@#      OR
)@@G@@    J         AQW1@D@@@#AQW2$*    LA,U      A3,7                TWO WORDOS
)@@G@@S     @F@@@#AQW1      DSC       A0,72-9             POSITION NEXT CHARACOT
)@@G@@TER   @ @@@#          ON        PARSTRIP  @D@@@#          AND,U     A1,1OU
)@@G@@*/7-1           7 BITS IN A2  @ @@@#          OFF       PARSTRIP  @ @@@#OV
)@@G@@          ON        PARSTRIP=0@D@@@#          AND,U     A1,1*/8-1       OW
)@@G@@    8 BITS TO A2  @ @@@#          OFF       PARSTRIP=0@D@@@#          PAOX
)@@G@@RITY    .                   COMPUTE PARITY@F@@@#          TE,U      A2,BOY
)@@G@@LANK            SKIP BLANKS AND NULLS     @ @@@#          TNE,U     A2,NOZ
)@@G@@ULL   @^@@@#          J         AQW2@E@@@#          STORE     .         PA
)@@G@@          STORE CHARACTER     @C@@@#AQW2      JGD       A3,AQW1         PB
)@@G@@    REPEAT  @C@@@#          J         0,X11               RETURN  @C@@@#PC
)@@G@@AQW3$*    LA,U      A3,3                ONE WORD@^@@@#          J       PD
)@@G@@  AQW3@D@@@#AQW4$*    LA,U      A3,7                TWO WORDS     @F@@@#PE
)@@G@@AQW3      DSC       A0,72-9             POSITION NEXT CHARACTER   @D@@@#PF
)@@G@@          AND,U     A1,1*/7-1           7 BITS IN A2  @D@@@#          PAPG
)@@G@@RITY    .                   COMPUTE PARITY@D@@@#          TE,U      A2,NPH
)@@G@@ULL             SKIP NULLS    @E@@@#          STORE     .               PI
)@@G@@    STORE CHARACTER     @C@@@#          JGD       A3,AQW3             REPJ
)@@G@@PEAT  @C@@@#          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@#@@@@@#PK
)@@G@@@A@@@#.         VARIABLE LENGTH OCTAL EDIT@@@@@#@C@@@#AOCTV$*   LA,U    PL
)@@G@@  A3,0                A3 = 0  @F@@@#          DSL       A0,3            PM
)@@G@@    SHIFT OFF LOW-ORDER DIGIT @F@@@#          JZ        A0,EOCTV2       PN
)@@G@@    ONLY ONE DIGIT - BYPASS   @C@@@#EOCTV1    AA,U      A3,1            PO
)@@G@@    ADD 1   @F@@@#          DSL       A0,3                SHIFT OFF THE PP
)@@G@@NEXT DIGIT  @E@@@#          JNZ       A0,EOCTV1           MORE TO GO - LPQ
)@@G@@OOP   @E@@@#          STORE,U   ZER                 STORE A LEADING ZEROPR
)@@G@@@C@@@#EOCTV2    LA,U      A2,0                CLEAR A2@F@@@#          LDPS
)@@G@@SC      A1,3                POSITION THE NEXT DIGIT   @D@@@#          AAPT
)@@G@@,U      A2,ZER              MAKE IT ASCII @E@@@#          PARITY    .   PU
)@@G@@                COMPUTE ITS PARITY  @C@@@#          STORE     .         PV
)@@G@@          STORE IT@D@@@#          JGD       A3,EOCTV2           LOOP ON PW
)@@G@@A3    @C@@@#          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@#@A@@@#PX
)@@G@@.         FIXED LENGTH OCTAL EDIT   @@@@@#@C@@@#AOCTF$*   LA,U      A3,,PY
)@@G@@A1              A3 = A1 @F@@@#          MSI,U     A1,3                COPZ
)@@G@@MPUTE THE NUMBER OF BITS@D@@@#          DSL       A0,,A1              SHQA
)@@G@@IFT THEM OFF@D@@@#          ANA,U     A3,1                DECREMENT A3  QB
)@@G@@@D@@@#          J         EOCTV2              FINISH UP     @@@@@#@@@@@#QC
)@@G@@@C@@@#.         FIXED AND VARIABLE LENGTH DECIMAL EDIT@@@@@#@]@@@#ADCFZ$QD
)@@G@@*   . @E@@@#ADECZ$*   LXI,U     X11,ZER             EDIT LEADING ZEROS  QE
)@@G@@@ @@@#          J         EDECF0    @F@@@#ADECV$*   LA,U      A1,0      QF
)@@G@@          SIZE DEPENDS ON VALUE     @E@@@#ADECF$*   LXI,U     X11,BLANK QG
)@@G@@          EDIT LEADING BLANKS @E@@@#EDECF0    LR,U      R1,0,A1         QH
)@@G@@    R1 = FIELD SIZE     @C@@@#          LA,U      A3,0                A3QI
)@@G@@ = 0  @D@@@#EDECF1    DSA       A0,36               SET UP DIVIDE @D@@@#QJ
)@@G@@          DI,U      A0,10               DIVIDE BY 10  @D@@@#          LMQK
)@@G@@A,XU    A1,,A1              GET THE DIGIT @D@@@#          LDSL      A2,6QL
)@@G@@                MAKE ROOM     @D@@@#          AA,U      A3,ZER,A1       QM
)@@G@@    THROW IT IN   @D@@@#          JGD       R1,$+1              DECREMENQN
)@@G@@T R1  @D@@@#          JNZ       A0,EDECF1           MORE TO GO    @E@@@#QO
)@@G@@          JP        A0,EDECF2           IT WAS POSITIVE     @D@@@#      QP
)@@G@@    LDSL      A2,6                MAKE ROOM     @E@@@#          AA,U    QQ
)@@G@@  A3,MINUS            THROW IN THE SIGN   @D@@@#          JGD       R1,$QR
)@@G@@+1              DECREMENT R1  @D@@@#EDECF2    DL        A0,A2           QS
)@@G@@    A0,A1 = A2,A3 @E@@@#          LA        A3,X11              GET FILLQT
)@@G@@ CHARACTER  @ @@@#          SSL       A3,18     @C@@@#          J       QU
)@@G@@  EDECF5              SKIP    @E@@@#EDECF4    STORE     A3              QV
)@@G@@    STORE FILL CHARACTER@D@@@#EDECF5    JGD       R1,EDECF4           LOQW
)@@G@@OP ON R1    @E@@@#EDECF3    AND,U     A1,1*/6-1           A2 = NEXT CHARQX
)@@G@@ACTER @E@@@#          PARITY    .                   COMPUTE ITS PARITY  QY
)@@G@@@C@@@#          STORE     .                   STORE IT@D@@@#          DSQZ
)@@G@@L       A0,6                MOVE DOWN ONE @D@@@#          JNZ       A1,ERA
)@@G@@DECF3           MORE TO GO    @C@@@#          J         0,X11           RB
)@@G@@    RETURN  @@@@@#@@@@@#@ @@@#.         IMAGE OVERRUN ERROR @@@@@#@D@@@#RC
)@@G@@ADARR$*   SA        A0,SNPKT+2          SAVE USER A0  @H@@@#          PRRD
)@@G@@INT$    ERRM,ERRML          PRINT IMAGE OVERRUN ERROR MESSAGE     @^@@@#RE
)@@G@@          TNZ       RET @^@@@#          J         ERR1@ @@@#          LXRF
)@@G@@        X11,RET   @^@@@#          SZ        RET @E@@@#ERR1      SX,H2   RG
)@@G@@  PX,SNPKT+1          SET UP SNAP PACKET  @E@@@#          SNAP$P    SNPKRH
)@@G@@T               DUMP THE PACKET     @^@@@#          LA,U      A0,0@ @@@#RI
)@@G@@          J         ACOL$     @@@@@#@B@@@#.         QUARTER WORD MODE NORJ
)@@G@@T SET ERROR @@@@@#@E@@@#ADNQWM$*  PRINT$    QWERM,QWERL,2       PRINT ERRK
)@@G@@ROR MESSAGE @E@@@#          EABT$     .                   ABORT THE PROGRL
)@@G@@RAM   @@@@@#@B@@@#SNPKT     SNAP$PKT,'XAR' $-$,12,'A$PKT'   @@@@@#@@@@@#RM
)@@G@@@H@@@#ERRM      '*****  ADIT$: ATTEMPT TO STORE OR LOAD OUTSIDE OF IMAGERN
)@@G@@  *****'    @ @@@#ERRML     EQU       $-ERRM    @@@@@#@E@@@#QWERM     '*RO
)@@G@@****  ADIT$: QUARTER WORD MODE REQUIRED *****'  @ @@@#QWERL     EQU     RP
)@@G@@  $-QWERM   @@@@@#@#@@@#          END     ___RACTER   @ @@@#          ONRQ
)@@G@@        PARSTRIP  @D@@@#          AND,U     A1,1*/7-1           7 BITS IRR
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@@@@@@@@@@@@@A@@@@.         ADIT$ EDITING PACKAGE     @@@@@@RS
)@@G@@@D@@@@.         MONOCASE TO UPPER/LOWER CASE TRANSLATOR     @@@@@@@F@]@[RT
)@@G@@$$$$$ >> TEXT MOVED FROM HERE TO Z$F.A BY RJEND COMMAND << $$$$$  @G@@@]RU
)@@G@@.         THIS EXTENSION  OF  THE  ADIT$  PACKAGE  PERMITS  CONVENIENT  RV
)@@G@@@G@@@].         SPECIFICATION  OF UPPER/LOWER CASE OUTPUT THROUGH THE USRW
)@@G@@E OF  @G@@@].         A FORCE  CHARACTER  IN  MONOCASE  QUARTER-WORD  INRX
)@@G@@PUT.   THE  @G@@@].         ROUTINES  IN  THIS  ELEMENT  FUNCTION IDENTIRY
)@@G@@CALLY TO AQMSG$,  @G@@@].         AQMSR$, AND AQMS1$, EXCEPT THAT  ALL  RZ
)@@G@@ALPHABETIC  CHARACTERS  @G@@@].         ARE TRANSLATED TO LOWER CASE UNLSA
)@@G@@ESS PRECEDED BY A SHARP SIGN  @G@@@].         (#).  THE SHARP SIGN ACTS SB
)@@G@@ALSO AS A FORCE CHARACTER, AND MAY  @G@@@].         BE USED TO FORCE ITSSC
)@@G@@ELF OR THE AMSG$ STOP CHARACTER INTO THE  @^@@@].         OUTPUT STRING.SD
)@@G@@@F@[@@.         THIS EXTENSION OF THE ADIT$ PACKAGE PERMITS CONVENIENT  SE
)@@G@@@F@[@@.         SPECIFICATION OF UPPER/LOWER CASE OUTPUT THROUGH THE USESF
)@@G@@@G@[@@.         OF A FORCE CHARACTER IN MONOCASE QUARTER-WORD INPUT.  THSG
)@@G@@E     @F@[@@.         ROUTINES IN THIS ELEMENT FUNCTION IDENTICALLY TO ASH
)@@G@@QMSG$,@G@[@@.         AQMSR$, AND AQMS1$, EXCEPT THAT ALL ALPHABETIC CHASI
)@@G@@RACTERS     @F@[@@.         ARE TRANSLATED TO LOWER CASE UNLESS PRECEDEDSJ
)@@G@@ BY A SHARP @G@[@@.         SIGN (#).  THE SHARP SIGN ACTS ALSO AS A FORSK
)@@G@@CE CHARACTER,     @G@[@@.         AND MAY BE USED TO FORCE ITSELF OR THESL
)@@G@@ AMSG$ STOP CHARACTER   @A@[@@.         INTO THE OUTPUT STRING.   @[@@@@SM
)@@G@@.     @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@#@@@@          AXR$    @#@@@@          A$DEF   SN
)@@G@@@#@@@@          ASCII   @@@@@@@F@@@@ALMSR$*   LXI,U     X11,0           SO
)@@G@@    INDICATE SAVE POINTER     @G@@@@          LA        A0,CIM          SP
)@@G@@    RESTORE THE CHARACTER INDEX     @F@@@@          LA        A1,WIM    SQ
)@@G@@          RESTORE THE WORD INDEX    @C@@@@          J         AMSG1     SR

)@@G@@        A0,,X11             RETURN IF A0 = 0    @ @^@#          ON      BZ
)@@G@@  ASCII     @I@^@#          J         ACOL$               POSITION TO THCA
)@@G@@E PROPER COLUMN AND RETURN    @I@@@^          J         ICOL$           CB
)@@G@@    POSITION TO THE PROPER COLUMN AND RETURN    @ @^@#          OFF     CC
)@@G@@  ASCII     @ @^@#          ON        1-ASCII   @I@^@#          J       CD
)@@G@@  ECOL$               POSITION TO THE PROPER COLUMN AND RETURN    @ @^@#CE
)@@G@@          OFF       1-ASCII   @@@@@#@^@@@#.         EDIT NICELY   @@@@@#CF
)@@G@@@ @@@#          ON        ASCII     @]@@@#AFLN1$*   . @ @@@#          OFCG
)@@G@@F       ASCII     @ @@@#          ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@#EFLN1$*   . CH
)@@G@@@ @@@#          OFF       1-ASCII   @F@@@#          LMJ       A3,ENTER1 CI
)@@G@@          SINGLE PRECISION ENTRANCE @@@@@#@ @@@#          ON        ASCICJ
)@@G@@I     @]@@@#AFLN2$*   . @ @@@#          OFF       ASCII     @ @@@#      CK
)@@G@@    ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@#EFLN2$*   . @ @@@#          OFF       1-ASCL
)@@G@@CII   @F@@@#          LMJ       A3,ENTER2           DOUBLE PRECISION ENTCM
)@@G@@RANCE @E@@@#          LA        A0,SCALE            A0 = POWER OF TEN   CN
)@@G@@@ @@@#          LNA       A1,NDF    @D@@@#          TLE       A0,NDF    CO
)@@G@@          IS IT NICE    @ @@@#          TLE       A0,A1     @F@@@#      CP
)@@G@@    J         EFLS1               NO, USE SCIENTIFIC FORMAT @G@@@#      CQ
)@@G@@    AA,U      A0,1                A0 = NUMBER OF LEADING DIGITS   @G@@@#CR
)@@G@@          JP        A0,LN4A             SKIP IF ABS(NUMBER) GEQ 0.1     CS
)@@G@@@H@@@#          LMA       A0,A0               A0 = NUMBER OF EXTRA ZEROSCT
)@@G@@ NEEDED     @E@@@#          TG,U      A0,18               IS NUMBER TOO CU
)@@G@@SMALL?@C@@@#          J         EFLS1               YES     @ @@@#      CV
)@@G@@    DL        A1,VALUE  @E@@@#          TLE,U     A0,9                MOCW
)@@G@@RE THAN 9 ZEROS?  @B@@@#          J         LN4                 NO@^@@@#CX
)@@G@@          ANA,U     A0,9@ @@@#          DSL       A1,36     @ @@@#LN4   CY
)@@G@@    DSL       A2,36     @D@@@#          DS        A2,VALUE            STCZ
)@@G@@ORE A2,A3   @D@@@#          DSL       A1,36               SET UP DIVIDE DA
)@@G@@@H@@@#          DI        A1,PTENI,A0         DIVIDE BY THE CORRECT POWEDB
)@@G@@R OF TEN    @E@@@#          MI        A2,PTENI9           ADJUST THE REMDC
)@@G@@AINDER@E@@@#          DA        A2,VALUE            ADD THE SECOND WORD DD
)@@G@@@H@@@#          DI        A2,PTENI,A0         DIVIDE BY THE CORRECT POWEDE
)@@G@@R OF TEN    @E@@@#          DS        A1,VALUE            STORE THE NEW DF
)@@G@@VALUE @C@@@#          LA,U      A0,0                FUDGE   @C@@@#LN4A  DG
)@@G@@    SA        A0,NDP              STORE IT@G@@@#          LA        A1,NDH
)@@G@@DF              A1 = NUMBER OF DIGITS EDITED    @G@@@#          ANA     DI
)@@G@@  A0,A1               A0 = -NUMBER OF LEADING DIGITS  @C@@@#          SMDJ
)@@G@@A       A0,NDF              SAVE IT @G@@@#          TG,U      A1,9      DK
)@@G@@          LESS THAN 9 DIGITS TO BE EDITED?@B@@@#          J         LN  DL
)@@G@@                NO@^@@@#          ANA,U     A1,9@ @@@#          LMA     DM
)@@G@@  A1,A1     @F@@@#          LA        A2,VALUE            GET RID OF EVEDN
)@@G@@RYTHING ELSE@ @@@#          DSL       A2,36     @A@@@#          DI      DO
)@@G@@  A2,PTENI,A1     @A@@@#          MSI       A2,PTENI,A1     @ @@@#      DP
)@@G@@    SA        A2,VALUE  @ @@@#          SZ        VALUE+1   @^@@@#      DQ
)@@G@@    J         LN0 @G@@@#LN        TG,U      A1,18               LESS THADR
)@@G@@N 18 DIGITS TO BE EDITED@B@@@#          J         LN0                 NODS
)@@G@@@ @@@#          ANA,U     A1,18     @ @@@#          LMA       A1,A1     DT
)@@G@@@F@@@#          LA        A2,VALUE+1          GET RID OF EVERYTHING ELSEDU
)@@G@@@ @@@#          DSL       A2,36     @A@@@#          DI        A2,PTENI,ADV
)@@G@@1     @A@@@#          MSI       A2,PTENI,A1     @ @@@#          SA      DW
)@@G@@  A2,VALUE+1@ @@@#LN0       LMJ       A1,FILLA  @D@@@#          LA,U    DX
)@@G@@  A2,CMINUS           STORE SIGN    @^@@@#          TZ        SIGN@^@@@#DY
)@@G@@          STORE     .   @F@@@#          LR        R1,NDP              R1DZ
)@@G@@ = DIGITS BEFORE DP     @E@@@#          LA        A1,VALUE            A1EA
)@@G@@ = FIRST 9 DIGITS @^@@@#          LA,U      A3,9@D@@@#LN1       JGD     EB
)@@G@@  R1,LN1A             LOOP ON R1    @C@@@#          J         LN2       EC
)@@G@@          EDIT DP @D@@@#LN1A      JGD       A3,LN1B             LOOP ON ED
)@@G@@A3    @E@@@#          LA        A1,VALUE+1          A1 = NEXT 9 DIGITS  EE
)@@G@@@C@@@#          SZ        VALUE+1             ZERO IT @^@@@#          LAEF
)@@G@@,U      A3,8@^@@@#LN1B      LA,U      A0,0@E@@@#          DI        A0,PEG
)@@G@@TENI,A3         GET THE NEXT DIGIT  @H@@@#          LA,U      A2,CZERO,AEH
)@@G@@0         TRANSLATE TO OUTPUT CHARACTER SET     @ @^@#          ON      EI
)@@G@@  ASCII     @^@@@#          PARITY    .   @ @^@#          OFF       ASCIEJ
)@@G@@I     @^@@@#          STORE     .   @^@@@#          J         LN1 @E@@@#EK
)@@G@@LN2       JNZ       A1,LN2A             IS ANYTHING LEFT?   @ @@@#      EL
)@@G@@    TNZ       VALUE+1   @F@@@#          J         EFLG1               NOEM
)@@G@@. QUIT WHILE WERE AHEAD @E@@@#LN2A      STORE,U   CPERIOD             STEN
)@@G@@ORE DECIMAL POINT @E@@@#          LR        R1,NDF              R1 = DIGEO
)@@G@@ITS AFTER DP@D@@@#LN3       JGD       R1,LN3B             LOOP ON R1    EP
)@@G@@@ @@@#          J         EFLG1     @D@@@#LN3B      JGD       A3,LN3C   EQ
)@@G@@          LOOP ON A3    @E@@@#          LA        A1,VALUE+1          A1ER
)@@G@@ = NEXT 9 DIGITS  @C@@@#          SZ        VALUE+1             ZERO IT ES
)@@G@@@^@@@#          LA,U      A3,8@^@@@#LN3C      LA,U      A0,0@E@@@#      ET
)@@G@@    DI        A0,PTENI,A3         GET THE NEXT DIGIT  @H@@@#          LAEU
)@@G@@,U      A2,CZERO,A0         TRANSLATE TO OUTPUT CHARACTER SET     @ @^@#EV
)@@G@@          ON        ASCII     @^@@@#          PARITY    .   @ @^@#      EW
)@@G@@    OFF       ASCII     @^@@@#          STORE     .   @E@@@#          JNEX
)@@G@@Z       A1,LN3              IS ANYTHING LEFT?   @ @@@#          TZ      EY
)@@G@@  VALUE+1   @^@@@#          J         LN3 @F@@@#          J         EFLGEZ
)@@G@@1               NO. QUIT WHILE WE'RE AHEAD@@@@@#@ @@@#.         FIXED POFA
)@@G@@INT FORMAT  @@@@@#@ @@@#          ON        ASCII     @]@@@#AFLF1$*   . FB
)@@G@@@ @@@#          OFF       ASCII     @ @@@#          ON        1-ASCII   FC
)@@G@@@]@@@#EFLF1$*   . @ @@@#          OFF       1-ASCII   @F@@@#          LMFD
)@@G@@J       A3,ENTER1           SINGLE PRECISION ENTRANCE @@@@@#@ @@@#      FE
)@@G@@    ON        ASCII     @]@@@#AFLF2$*   . @ @@@#          OFF       ASCIFF
)@@G@@I     @ @@@#          ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@#EFLF2$*   . @ @@@#      FG
)@@G@@    OFF       1-ASCII   @F@@@#          LMJ       A3,ENTER2           DOFH
)@@G@@UBLE PRECISION ENTRANCE @G@@@#          LMA       A0,SCALE            A0FI
)@@G@@ = MAGNITUDE OF THE SCALE     @F@@@#          TN        SCALE           FJ
)@@G@@    IS THE SCALE NEGATIVE ?   @B@@@#          J         EFLF3           FK
)@@G@@    NO@D@@@#          DL        A1,VALUE            A1,A2 = VALUE @E@@@#FL
)@@G@@EFLF1     TLE,U     A0,9                MORE THAN 8 PLACES ?@B@@@#      FM
)@@G@@    J         EFLF2               NO@E@@@#          DSL       A1,36     FN
)@@G@@          YES, SHIFT ONE WORD @D@@@#          ANA,U     A0,9            FO
)@@G@@    DECREMENT A0  @D@@@#          J         EFLF1               TRY AGAIFP
)@@G@@N     @D@@@#EFLF2     DSL       A2,36               ZERO FILL A2  @D@@@#FQ
)@@G@@          DS        A2,VALUE            STORE A2,A3   @D@@@#          DSFR
)@@G@@L       A1,36               SET UP DIVIDE @H@@@#          DI        A1,PFS
)@@G@@TENI,A0         DIVIDE BY THE CORRECT POWER OF TEN    @E@@@#          MIFT
)@@G@@        A2,PTENI9           ADJUST THE REMAINDER@E@@@#          DA      FU
)@@G@@  A2,VALUE            ADD THE SECOND WORD @H@@@#          DI        A2,PFV
)@@G@@TENI,A0         DIVIDE BY THE CORRECT POWER OF TEN    @E@@@#          DSFW
)@@G@@        A1,VALUE            STORE THE NEW VALUE @C@@@#          LA,U    FX
)@@G@@  A0,0                FUDGE   @F@@@#EFLF3     AA,U      A0,1            FY
)@@G@@    A0 = LEADING DIGIT COUNT  @C@@@#          SA        A0,NDP          FZ
)@@G@@    STORE IT@G@@@#          AA,U      A0,1                ADD ONE FOR THGA
)@@G@@E DECIMAL POINT   @F@@@#          AA        A0,NDF              ADD THE GB
)@@G@@TRAILING DIGITS   @F@@@#          AA        A0,SIGN             ADD THE GC
)@@G@@LENGTH OF THE SIGN@C@@@#          LA        A3,FCOL             A3 = X  GD
)@@G@@@F@@@#          ANA,U     A3,,A0              A3 = NUMBER OF BLANKS     GE
)@@G@@@C@@@#          J         EFLF5               SKIP    @D@@@#EFLF4     STGF
)@@G@@ORE,U   CBLANK              STORE BLANK   @D@@@#EFLF5     JGD       A3,EGG
)@@G@@FLF4            LOOP ON A3    @E@@@#          LMJ       X11,EMANT       GH
)@@G@@    EDIT THE MANTISSA   @C@@@#          J         EFLS2               REGI
)@@G@@TURN  @@@@@#@@@@@#@^@@@#.         BLANK FILL    @@@@@#@F@@@#FILL      LAGJ
)@@G@@        A2,NDP              A2 = LEADING DIGIT COUNT  @G@@@#          AAGK
)@@G@@        A2,NDF              ADD THE TRAILING DIGIT COUNT    @C@@@#      GL
)@@G@@    AA,U      A2,4                ADD 4   @E@@@#          TN        X11 GM
)@@G@@                DOUBLE PRECISION ?  @C@@@#          AA,U      A2,1      GN
)@@G@@          YES     @E@@@#          AA        A2,SIGN             ADD THE GO
)@@G@@SIGN LENGTH @E@@@#          TP        X11                 SINGLE PRECISIGP
)@@G@@ON ?  @G@@@#          LA        A3,SPC              YES, A3 = SEPARATINGGQ
)@@G@@ CHARACTER  @E@@@#          TN        X11                 DOUBLE PRECISIGR
)@@G@@ON ?  @G@@@#          LA        A3,DPC              YES, A3 = SEPARATINGGS
)@@G@@ CHARACTER  @E@@@#          TZ        A3                  IS A3 NONZERO GT
)@@G@@?     @D@@@#          AA,U      A2,1                YES, ADD 1    @E@@@#GU
)@@G@@FILL0     LA        A3,FCOL             A3 = FIELD SIZE     @C@@@#      GV
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,0                A0 = 0  @E@@@#          TLE,U     A3,,GW
)@@G@@A2              PLENTY OF ROOM ?    @B@@@#          J         FILL1     GX
)@@G@@          NO@ @^@#          ON        ASCII     @F@^@#          A$COLN  GY
)@@G@@                      YES, GET THE COLUMN NUMBER@F@@@^          LMJ     GZ
)@@G@@  X11,ICOLN$          YES, GET THE COLUMN NUMBER@ @^@#          OFF     HA
)@@G@@  ASCII     @ @^@#          ON        1-ASCII   @F@^@#          E$COLN  HB
)@@G@@  .                   YES, GET THE COLUMN NUMBER@ @^@#          OFF     HC
)@@G@@  1-ASCII   @E@@@#          AA,U      A0,,A3              ADD THE FIELD HD
)@@G@@SIZE  @F@@@#FILL1     SA        A0,FCOL             STORE THE FINAL COLUHE
)@@G@@MN    @F@@@#          ANA,U     A3,,A2              A3 = NUMBER OF BLANKHF
)@@G@@S     @C@@@#          J         FILL3               SKIP    @D@@@#FILL2 HG
)@@G@@    STORE,U   CBLANK              STORE A SPACE @C@@@#FILL3     JGD     HH
)@@G@@  A3,FILL2            LOOP    @C@@@#          J         0,A1            HI
)@@G@@    RETURN  @E@@@#FILLA     LA        A2,NDP              LEADING DIGIT HJ
)@@G@@COUNT @E@@@#          AA        A2,NDF              TRAILING DIGIT COUNTHK
)@@G@@@D@@@#          AA,U      A2,1                DECIMAL POINT @C@@@#      HL
)@@G@@    AA        A2,SIGN             SIGN    @ @@@#          J         FILLHM
)@@G@@0     @@@@@#@^@@@#.         EDIT THE SCALE@@@@@#@E@@@#ESC       TN      HN
)@@G@@  X11                 DOUBLE PRECISION ?  @G@@@#          LA        A2,DHO
)@@G@@PC              YES, A2 = SEPARATING CHARACTER  @E@@@#          TP      HP
)@@G@@  X11                 SINGLE PRECISION ?  @G@@@#          LA        A2,SHQ
)@@G@@PC              YES, A2 = SEPARATING CHARACTER  @E@@@#          TZ      HR
)@@G@@  A2                  WAS THERE ONE ?     @D@@@#          STORE     .   HS
)@@G@@                YES, STORE IT @D@@@#          LA        A0,SCALE        HT
)@@G@@    A0 = SCALE    @D@@@#          AA,U      A0,1                ADJUST IHU
)@@G@@T     @ @@@#          ANA       A0,NDP    @F@@@#          TZ        ZEROHV
)@@G@@                FLOATING POINT ZERO ?     @E@@@#          LA,U      A0,0HW
)@@G@@                YES, SPECIAL CASE   @C@@@#          LA,U      A2,CMINUS HX
)@@G@@          A2 = '-'@F@@@#          TN        A0                  IS THE SHY
)@@G@@CALE NEGATIVE ?   @D@@@#          LA,U      A2,CPLUS            NO, A2 =HZ
)@@G@@ '+'  @E@@@#          STORE     .                   STORE THE CHARACTER IA
)@@G@@@E@@@#          LMA,XU    A0,,A0              GET THE MAGNITUDE   @F@@@#IB
)@@G@@          TNZ       FCOL                ARE WE SHORT OF ROOM ?    @ @^@#IC
)@@G@@          ON        ASCII     @G@^@#          J         ADECV$          ID
)@@G@@    YES, PACK THE CHARACTERISTIC    @G@@@^          J         IDECV$    IE
)@@G@@          YES, PACK THE CHARACTERISTIC    @ @^@#          OFF       ASCIIF
)@@G@@I     @ @^@#          ON        1-ASCII   @G@^@#          J         EDECIG
)@@G@@V$              YES, PACK THE CHARACTERISTIC    @ @^@#          OFF     IH
)@@G@@  1-ASCII   @F@@@#          L         A3,A0               FOR THE UPCOMIII
)@@G@@NG DIVIDE   @F@@@#          L,U       A1,1                ASSUME TWO DIGIJ
)@@G@@IT EXPONENT @E@@@#          TN        X11                 IS IT TWO DIGIIK
)@@G@@T ?   @D@@@#          L,U       A1,2                NOPE   THREE  @G@@@#IL
)@@G@@ESC1      SSL       A2,36               SHIFT AND CLEAR FOR THE DIVIDE  IM
)@@G@@@E@@@#          DI        A2,PTENI,A1         GET A POWER OF TEN  @H@@@#IN
)@@G@@          AA,U      A2,CZERO            TRANSLATE TO OUTPUT CHARACTER SEIO
)@@G@@T     @ @^@#          ON        ASCII     @^@@@#          PARITY    .   IP
)@@G@@@ @^@#          OFF       ASCII     @^@@@#          STORE     .   @E@@@#IQ
)@@G@@          JGD       A1,ESC1             LOOP UNTIL ALL DONE @ @@@#      IR
)@@G@@    J         0,X11     @@@@@#@ @@@#.         EDIT THE MANTISSA   @@@@@#IS
)@@G@@@C@@@#EMANT     LA,U      A2,CMINUS           A2 = '-'@D@@@#          TZIT
)@@G@@        SIGN                LEADING '-' ? @C@@@#          STORE     .   IU
)@@G@@                YES     @G@@@#          LR        R1,NDP              R1IV
)@@G@@ = DIGITS BEFORE DECIMAL POINT@E@@@#          LA        A1,VALUE        IW
)@@G@@    A1 = FIRST 9 DIGITS @C@@@#          LA,U      A3,9                A3IX
)@@G@@ = 9  @D@@@#EMANT1    JGD       R1,EMANT2           LOOP ON R1    @F@@@#IY
)@@G@@          J         EMANT4              PUT OUT THE DECIMAL POINT @D@@@#IZ
)@@G@@EMANT2    JGD       A3,EMANT3           LOOP ON A3    @E@@@#          LAJA
)@@G@@        A1,VALUE+1          A1 = NEXT 9 DIGITS  @D@@@#          SZ      JB
)@@G@@  VALUE+1             ZERO THEM     @C@@@#          LA,U      A3,8      JC
)@@G@@          A3 = 8  @D@@@#EMANT3    LA,U      A0,0                SET UP DJD
)@@G@@IVIDE @E@@@#          DI        A0,PTENI,A3         GET THE NEXT DIGIT  JE
)@@G@@@H@@@#          LA,U      A2,CZERO,A0         TRANSLATE TO OUTPUT CHARACJF
)@@G@@TER SET     @ @^@#          ON        ASCII     @^@@@#          PARITY  JG
)@@G@@  .   @ @^@#          OFF       ASCII     @^@@@#          STORE     .   JH
)@@G@@@C@@@#          J         EMANT1              LOOP    @E@@@#EMANT4    STJI
)@@G@@ORE,U   CPERIOD             STORE DECIMAL POINT @G@@@#          LR      JJ
)@@G@@  R1,NDF              R1 = DIGITS BEHIND DECIMAL POINT@D@@@#EMANT5    JGJK
)@@G@@D       R1,EMANT6           LOOP ON R1    @D@@@#          J         0,X1JL
)@@G@@1               DONE - RETURN @D@@@#EMANT6    JGD       A3,EMANT7       JM
)@@G@@    LOOP ON A3    @E@@@#          LA        A1,VALUE+1          A1 = NEXJN
)@@G@@T 9 DIGITS  @C@@@#          SZ        VALUE+1             ZERO IT @C@@@#JO
)@@G@@          LA,U      A3,8                A3 = 8  @D@@@#EMANT7    LA,U    JP
)@@G@@  A0,0                SET UP DIVIDE @E@@@#          DI        A0,PTENI,AJQ
)@@G@@3         GET THE NEXT DIGIT  @H@@@#          LA,U      A2,CZERO,A0     JR
)@@G@@    TRANSLATE TO OUTPUT CHARACTER SET     @ @^@#          ON        ASCIJS
)@@G@@I     @^@@@#          PARITY    .   @ @^@#          OFF       ASCII     JT
)@@G@@@^@@@#          STORE     .   @C@@@#          J         EMANT5          JU
)@@G@@    LOOP    @@@@@#@@@@@#@^@@@#.         SET UP ENTRY  @@@@@#@F@@@#ENTER1JV
)@@G@@    LXI,U     X11,-1              INDICATE SINGLE PRECISION @G@@@#      JW
)@@G@@    FEL       A1,A1               EXPAND A1 TO DOUBLE PRECISION   @F@@@#JX
)@@G@@          AA,U      A3,1                ADJUST THE RETURN POINT   @^@@@#JY
)@@G@@          J         $+2 @F@@@#ENTER2    LXI,U     X11,0               INJZ
)@@G@@DICATE DOUBLE PRECISION @F@@@#          SX        X11,RET             SAKA
)@@G@@VE THE RETURN POINT     @C@@@#          SA        A0,NDF              SAKB
)@@G@@VE Y  @C@@@#          SSL       A0,6                A0 = X  @C@@@#      KC
)@@G@@    SA        A0,FCOL             SAVE X  @F@@@#          LXM,U     X11,KD
)@@G@@,A3             SET UP GSC RETURN POINT   @E@@@#.         J         GSC KE
)@@G@@                DECOMPOSE THE NUMBER@@@@@#@@@@@#@C@@@#.         DECOMPOSKF
)@@G@@E A FLOATING POINT NUMBER     @@@@@#@E@@@#GSC       SZ        SIGN      KG
)@@G@@          CLEAR THE SIGN FLAG @G@@@#          SZ        ZERO            KH
)@@G@@    CLEAR THE UNNORMALIZED FLAG     @C@@@#          LA,U      A0,1      KI
)@@G@@          A0 = 1  @E@@@#          TOP       A1,(1*/35+1*/23)    IS IT NOKJ
)@@G@@RMALIZED ?  @B@@@#          J         GSC6                NO@F@@@#      KK
)@@G@@    TP        A1                  IS THE NUMBER POSITIVE ?  @F@@@#      KL
)@@G@@    SA        A0,SIGN             NO, INDICATE NEGATIVE     @E@@@#      KM
)@@G@@    DLM       A2,A1               A2,A3 = MAGNITUDE   @D@@@#          DSKN
)@@G@@        A2,VALUE            SAVE THE VALUE@E@@@#          LA,U      A0,0KO
)@@G@@                A0 = INITIAL SCALE  @D@@@#          DAN       A2,PTEN0  KP
)@@G@@          SUBTRACT 1.0  @E@@@#          JP        A2,GSC1             NOKQ
)@@G@@T SMALLER THAN 1.0@D@@@#          DL        A2,VALUE            A2,A3 = KR
)@@G@@VALUE @C@@@#          DFD       A2,PTEN37           FUDGE   @D@@@#      KS
)@@G@@    DS        A2,VALUE            STORE IT BACK @D@@@#          LA,XU   KT
)@@G@@  A0,-307             A0 = NEW SCALE@C@@@#GSC1      LR,U      R1,9      KU
)@@G@@          R1 = 9  @G@@@#          LA        A1,(-2,18)          A1 = INDKV
)@@G@@EX TO THE POWERS OF TEN @D@@@#GSC2      DL        A2,VALUE            A2KW
)@@G@@,A3 = VALUE @F@@@#          SLE       A2,PTENP-2,*A1      LOOK FOR THE PKX
)@@G@@OWER OF TEN @C@@@#          J         GSC3                DONE    @E@@@#KY
)@@G@@          DAN       A2,PTENP,A1         IS IT SMALLER ?     @B@@@#      KZ
)@@G@@    JN        A2,GSC2             NO@D@@@#          LA,U      A2,,A1    LA
)@@G@@          A2 = INDEX    @E@@@#          SSL       A2,1                A2LB
)@@G@@ = POWER OF TWO   @C@@@#          LA,U      A3,1                A3 = 1  LC
)@@G@@@E@@@#          LSSL      A3,,A2              BUILD THE INCREMENT @E@@@#LD
)@@G@@          AA,U      A0,,A3              UPDATE THE SCALE    @D@@@#      LE
)@@G@@    DL        A2,VALUE            A2,A3 = VALUE @D@@@#          DFD     LF
)@@G@@  A2,PTENP,A1         ADJUST IT     @C@@@#          DS        A2,VALUE  LG
)@@G@@          STORE IT@D@@@#          J         GSC2+1              TRY AGAILH
)@@G@@N     @G@@@#GSC3      DFD       A2,PTEN17           MAKE A2,A3 AN 18 DIGLI
)@@G@@IT INTEGER  @D@@@#          TNZ       FPR                 ROUNDING ?    LJ
)@@G@@@B@@@#          J         GSC4                NO@E@@@#          TP      LK
)@@G@@  X11                 SINGLE PRECISION ?  @C@@@#          DFA       A2,PLL
)@@G@@HALF1           YES     @E@@@#          TN        X11                 DOLM
)@@G@@UBLE PRECISION ?  @C@@@#          DFA       A2,PHALF            YES     LN
)@@G@@@D@@@#GSC4      DS        A2,VALUE            SAVE THE VALUE@E@@@#      LO
)@@G@@    DAN       A2,PTEN18           SUBTRACT 10**18     @E@@@#          JNLP
)@@G@@        A2,GSC5             NO ADJUSTMENT NEEDED@E@@@#          AA,U    LQ
)@@G@@  A0,1                INCREMENT THE SCALE @F@@@#          DL        A2,VLR
)@@G@@ALUE            DIVIDE THE VALUE BY 10    @ @@@#          DFD       A2,PLS
)@@G@@TENP  @E@@@#          DS        A2,VALUE            STORE THE VALUE     LT
)@@G@@@E@@@#GSC5      SA        A0,SCALE            STORE THE SCALE     @E@@@#LU
)@@G@@          DFU       A0,VALUE            UNPACK THE VALUE    @G@@@#      LV
)@@G@@    ANA,U     A0,02000+60         GET THE NEGATIVE SHIFT COUNT    @E@@@#LW
)@@G@@          LMA,XU    A0,,A0              GET THE MAGNITUDE   @E@@@#      LX
)@@G@@    DSL       A1,,A0              GET THE MANTISSA    @D@@@#          DILY
)@@G@@        A1,PTENI9           SPLIT IT UP   @C@@@#          DS        A1,VLZ
)@@G@@ALUE            STORE IT@C@@@#          J         0,X11               REMA
)@@G@@TURN  @F@@@#GSC6      SA        A0,ZERO             INDICATE A ZERO VALUMB
)@@G@@E     @E@@@#          SZ        SCALE               CLEAR THE SCALE     MC
)@@G@@@E@@@#          SZ        VALUE               CLEAR THE VALUE     @ @@@#MD
)@@G@@          SZ        VALUE+1   @C@@@#          J         0,X11           ME
)@@G@@    RETURN  @@@@@#@@@@@#@A@@@#.         INTEGER POWERS OF TEN     @@@@@#MF

)@@G@@ED FLAG     @C@@@#          LA,U      A0,1                A0 = 1  @E@@@#NF
)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@^@@@LASCII     EQU       1   @@@@@L@@@@@L@@@@@L@A@@@L.     NG
)@@G@@    ADIT$ EDITING PACKAGE     @@@@@L@@@@@L@@@@@L@A@@@L.         BASIC SCNH
)@@G@@ANNING SUBROUTINES@@@@@L@@@@@L@G@@@L.                                   NI
)@@G@@    JOHN WALKER   SEPTEMBER 1977    @F@@@L.                             NJ
)@@G@@          BASED ON EDIT$S, CONCEIVED@F@@@L.                             NK
)@@G@@          INDEPENDENTLY BY DAVE REAM@G@@@L.                             NL
)@@G@@          AND JOHN WALKER, IMPLEMENTED    @D@@@L.                       NM
)@@G@@                BY DAVE REAM. @@@@@L@@@@@L@[@@@L.     @F@@@L.         ADNN
)@@G@@IT$S  IS  A COLLECTION OF SCANNING ROUTINES WHICH     @F@@@L.         ALNO
)@@G@@LOWS THE USER TO EASILY DECOMPOSE COMPLEX STRINGS     @F@@@L.         OFNP
)@@G@@ FIELDATA CHARACTERS. ITS SISTER ELEMENT, ADIT$U,     @C@@@L.         CONQ
)@@G@@NTAINS THE FLOATING POINT ROUTINES. @[@@@L.     @F@@@L.         THESE RONR
)@@G@@UTINES  FOLLOW  ALL  OF  THE  NORMAL  ADIT$     @F@@@L.         CONVENTINS
)@@G@@ONS AS FAR AS REGISTER USAGE, PACKET FORMAT     @F@@@L.         AND CALLNT
)@@G@@ING SEQUENCES ARE CONCERNED.  IN  ADDITION,     @E@@@L.         THE SCANNU
)@@G@@NING PACKAGE RETURNS THE FOLLOWING VALUES:@[@@@L.     @F@@@L.           NV
)@@G@@        A1 (AND A0 FOR DP)  CONTAIN  THE  SCANNED     @#@@@L.         VANW
)@@G@@LUE.  @[@@@L.     @F@@@L.                   A2 CONTAINS THE NEXT CHARACTNX
)@@G@@ER (OR -0  IF     @B@@@L.         THERE IS NO NEXT CHARACTER).    @[@@@LNY
)@@G@@.     @F@@@L.                   A2 CONTAINS -1 IF YOU REQUESTED  SCANNINNZ
)@@G@@G     @D@@@L.         WHICH WENT BEYOND THE END OF THE IMAGE.     @[@@@LOA
)@@G@@.     @G@@@L.         THIS ELEMENT IS USED TO GENERATE  BOTH  THE  ASCIIOB
)@@G@@  SCANNING  @G@@@L.         ROUTINES  AND THE FIELDATA ELEMENT EDIT$S.  OC
)@@G@@THE OPERATION OF  @G@@@L.         THE FIELDATA AND ASCII ROUTINES ARE IDOD
)@@G@@ENTICAL EXCEPT FOR THE  @G@@@L.         CHARACTER   CODE  SCANNED  AND  OE
)@@G@@THE  PACKET  USED.   IN  THE  @G@@@L.         FOLLOWING DISCUSSIONS, THEOF
)@@G@@ CHARACTER 'J' WILL STAND FOR  'U'  @G@@@L.         FOR   THE  FIELDATA OG
)@@G@@VERSION AND 'C' FOR THE ASCII VERSION OF  @^@@@L.         THE ELEMENT.  OH
)@@G@@@[@@@L.     @A@@@L.         EACH ROUTINE IS CALLED BY:@[@@@L.     @B@@@LOI
)@@G@@.                   LMJ X11,<ROUTINE>     @[@@@L.     @B@@@L.         ANOJ
)@@G@@D RETURNS FOLLOWING THE CALL. @[@@@L.     @[@@@L.     @ @@@L.        ROUOK
)@@G@@TINE DESCRIPTIONS:@ @@@L.        -------- ----------- @[@@@L.     @F@N@MOL
)@@G@@$$$$$ >> TEXT MOVED FROM HERE TO Z$F.A BY RJEND COMMAND << $$$$$  @G@@@NOM
)@@G@@.         JPOS1$ -  POSITIONS THE POINTER BEFORE THE  NEXT  OCCURRENCE  ON
)@@G@@@C@@@N.                   OF THE CHARACTER IN A0.     @[@@@N.     @G@@@NOO
)@@G@@.         JPOS2$ -  POSITIONS THE POINTER AFTER THE NEXT OCCURRENCE OF  OP
)@@G@@@B@@@N.                   THE CHARACTER IN A0.  @[@@@N.     @G@@@N.     OQ
)@@G@@    JPOS3$ -  POSITIONS THE POINTER BEFORE THE  FIRST  NON-BLANK  @ @@@NOR
)@@G@@.                   CHARACTER.@[@@@N.     @F@@@N.         JPOS4$ -  LOADOS
)@@G@@ THE FIRST NON-BLANK CHARACTER INTO A0.   @[@@@N.     @C@@@N.         JCOT
)@@G@@HAR$ -  LOAD THE NEXT CHARACTER.    @[@@@N.     @G@@@N.         JLOOK$ -OU
)@@G@@  LOOK AT THE NEXT CHAR W/O TOUCHING THE POINTER.     @E@M@L.         JPOV
)@@G@@OS1$ -  POSITIONS THE POINTER BEFORE THE NEXT   @D@M@L.                 OW
)@@G@@  OCCURRENCE OF THE CHARACTER IN A0 @[@M@L.     @E@M@L.         JPOS2$ -OX
)@@G@@  POSITIONS THE POINTER AFTER THE NEXT    @D@M@L.                   OCCUOY
)@@G@@RRENCE OF THE CHARACTER IN A0 @[@M@L.     @E@M@L.         JPOS3$ -  POSIOZ
)@@G@@TIONS THE POINTER BEFORE THE FIRST  @B@M@L.                   NON- BLANKPA
)@@G@@ CHARACTER  @[@M@L.     @F@M@L.         JPOS4$ -  LOAD THE FIRST NON-BLAPB
)@@G@@NK CHARACTER INTO A0    @[@M@L.     @C@M@L.         JCHAR$ -  LOAD THE NPC
)@@G@@EXT CHARACTER     @[@M@L.     @F@M@L.         JLOOK$ -  LOOK AT THE NEXTPD
)@@G@@ CHAR W/O TOUCHING THE POINTER@[@N@L.     @[@@@N.     @G@@@L.           PE
)@@G@@   THE FOLLOWING NUMERICAL ROUTINES  WILL  IGNORE  LEADING  @G@@@L.     PF
)@@G@@    SPACES;  IF THE NUMBER IS DETERMINED TO BE DOUBLE PRECISION,  @G@@@LPG
)@@G@@.         THEN TWO SEQUENTIAL REGISTERS WILL BE USED,  OTHERWISE,  THE  PH
)@@G@@@E@@@L.         NUMBER WILL BE LOADED IN THE SECOND REGISTER.     @[@@@LPI
)@@G@@.     @F@M@L$$$$$ >> TEXT MOVED FROM HERE TO Z$F.A BY RJEND COMMAND << $PJ
)@@G@@$$$$  @G@@@M.         JI$    -  SCAN  AN  INTEGER;  IF  A   LEADING   ZEPK
)@@G@@RO(S)   IS  @G@@@M.                   ENCOUNTERED,  THE NUMBER IS REGARDPL
)@@G@@ED AS OCTAL ELSE  @ @@@M.                   DECIMAL.  @[@@@M.     @E@@@MPM
)@@G@@.         JDI$   -  FORCE SCANNING OF A DECIMAL INTEGER.    @[@@@M.     PN
)@@G@@@E@@@M.         JOI$   -  FORCE SCANNING OF AN OCTAL INTEGER.     @[@@@OPO
)@@G@@.     @F@P@O$$$$$ >> TEXT MOVED FROM HERE TO Z$F.A BY RJEND COMMAND << $PP
)@@G@@$$$$  @G@@@P.         JHI$   -  SCAN  A  HEXADECIMAL  INTEGER.   THE  LEPQ
)@@G@@TTERS  'A'  @G@@@P.                   THROUGH 'F' REPRESENT THE DIGITS WPR
)@@G@@ITH VALUES OF 10  @G@@@P.                   TO 15 DECIMAL.  THE ASCII VEPS
)@@G@@RSION  ACCEPTS  EITHER  @C@@@P.                   UPPER OR LOWER CASE LEPT
)@@G@@TTERS.@[@@@L.     @@@@@L@#@@@L          AXR$    @@@@@L@ @@@L          ONPU
)@@G@@        ASCII     @#@@@L          A$DEF   @#@@@L          C$DEF   @ @@@LPV
)@@G@@          OFF       ASCII     @@@@@L@ @@@L          ON        1-ASCII   PW
)@@G@@@#@@@L          E$DEF   @#@@@L          U$DEF   @ @@@L          OFF     PX
)@@G@@  1-ASCII   @@@@@L@@@@@L@ @@@L.         CONSTANT CHARACTERS @@@@@L@ @@@LPY
)@@G@@          ON        ASCII     @@@@@L@ @@@LCBLANK    EQU       BLANK     PZ
)@@G@@@^@@@LCZERO     EQU       ZER @^@@@LCPLUS     EQU       PLUS@ @@@LCMINUSQA
)@@G@@    EQU       MINUS     @ @@@PCLTRA     EQU       LETTERA   @@@@@L@ @@@LQB
)@@G@@          OFF       ASCII     @@@@@L@ @@@L          ON        1-ASCII   QC
)@@G@@@@@@@L@^@@@LCBLANK    EQU       ' ' @^@@@LCZERO     EQU       '0' @^@@@LQD
)@@G@@CPLUS     EQU       '+' @^@@@LCMINUS    EQU       '-' @^@@@PCLTRA     EQQE
)@@G@@U       'A' @@@@@L@ @@@L          OFF       1-ASCII   @[@@@L/.    @[@@@LQF
)@@G@@.     @ @@@L.         LOAD A CHARACTER    @[@@@L.     @ @@@L.         LMQG
)@@G@@J       X11,JCHAR$@E@@@L.         <RETURN>                      A0 = <CHQH
)@@G@@ARACTER>    @[@@@L.     @ @@@L          ON        ASCII     @]@@@LCCHAR$QI
)@@G@@*   . @ @@@L          OFF       ASCII     @ @@@L          ON        1-ASQJ
)@@G@@CII   @]@@@LUCHAR$*   . @ @@@L          OFF       1-ASCII   @F@@@L      QK
)@@G@@    SX        X11,RET             SAVE RETURN FOR ERRORS    @E@@@L      QL
)@@G@@    EX        LOAD                LOAD NEXT CHARACTER @F@@@L          SAQM
)@@G@@        A2,A0               RETURN TO CALLER IN A0    @F@@@L          EXQN
)@@G@@        LOOK                PROVIDE LOOK-AHEAD IN A2  @E@@@L          J QO
)@@G@@        0,X11               RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@L.     @[@@@L.     QP
)@@G@@@B@@@L.         LOOK AHEAD AT NEXT CHARACTER    @[@@@L.     @ @@@L.     QQ
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,JLOOK$@E@@@L.         <RETURN>                      A0QR
)@@G@@ = <CHARACTER>    @F@@@L.                                       A0<0 IF QS
)@@G@@OFF END OF IMAGE  @[@@@L.     @ @@@L          ON        ASCII     @]@@@LQT
)@@G@@CLOOK$*   . @ @@@L          OFF       ASCII     @ @@@L          ON      QU
)@@G@@  1-ASCII   @]@@@LULOOK$*   . @ @@@L          OFF       1-ASCII   @G@@@LQV
)@@G@@          SX        X11,RET             SAVE RETURN POINT IN PACKET     QW
)@@G@@@F@@@L          EX        LOOK                LOOK FOR NEXT CHARACTER   QX
)@@G@@@E@@@L          LA        A0,A2               PASS BACK IN A0     @E@@@LQY
)@@G@@          J         0,X11               RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@L/.    QZ
)@@G@@@[@@@L.     @F@@@L.         POSITION BEFORE NEXT OCCURRENCE OF SPECIFIEDRA
)@@G@@ CHARACTER  @[@@@L.     @A@@@L.         LA,U      A0,<CHARACTER>  @ @@@LRB
)@@G@@.         LMJ       X11,JPOS1$@#@@@L.         <RETURN>@[@@@L.     @ @@@LRC
)@@G@@          ON        ASCII     @]@@@LCPOS1$*   . @ @@@L          OFF     RD
)@@G@@  ASCII     @ @@@L          ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@LUPOS1$*   . @ @@@LRE
)@@G@@          OFF       1-ASCII   @F@@@L          LXI,U     X11,0           RF
)@@G@@    SET STOP BEFORE CHARACTER @E@@@L          J         CPOS1           RG
)@@G@@    ENTER COMMON CODE   @[@@@L.     @[@@@L.     @F@@@L.         POSITIONRH
)@@G@@ AFTER NEXT OCCURRENCE OF SPECIFIED CHARACTER   @[@@@L.     @A@@@L.     RI
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,<CHARACTER>  @ @@@L.         LMJ       X11,JPOS2$@#@@@LRJ
)@@G@@.         <RETURN>@[@@@L.     @ @@@L          ON        ASCII     @]@@@LRK
)@@G@@CPOS2$*   . @ @@@L          OFF       ASCII     @ @@@L          ON      RL
)@@G@@  1-ASCII   @]@@@LUPOS2$*   . @ @@@L          OFF       1-ASCII   @F@@@LRM
)@@G@@          LXI,XU    X11,-1              LOAD POSITION AFTER FLAG  @G@@@LRN
)@@G@@CPOS1     SX        X11,RET             SAVE RETURN POINT FOR ERROR     RO
)@@G@@@[@@@L.     @F@@@LCPOS2L    EX        LOOK                LOOK AT NEXT CRP
)@@G@@HARACTER    @G@@@L          TNE       A2,A0               IS IT THE DESIRQ
)@@G@@RED CHARACTER ?   @E@@@L          J         CFIN                YES.  RERR
)@@G@@TURN TO USER@G@@@L          EX        LOAD                NO.  LOAD, ADVRS
)@@G@@ANCING TO NEXT    @F@@@L          J         CPOS2L              LOOP UNTRT
)@@G@@IL CHARACTER FOUND@[@@@L.     @[@@@L.     @D@@@L.         POSITION BEFORRU
)@@G@@E NEXT NON-BLANK CHARACTER    @[@@@L.     @ @@@L.         LMJ       X11,RV
)@@G@@JPOS3$@#@@@L.         <RETURN>@[@@@L.     @ @@@L          ON        ASCIRW
)@@G@@I     @]@@@LCPOS3$*   . @ @@@L          OFF       ASCII     @ @@@L      RX
)@@G@@    ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@LUPOS3$*   . @ @@@L          OFF       1-ASRY
)@@G@@CII   @G@@@L          LXI,U     X11,0               SET TO STOP BEFORE CRZ
)@@G@@HARACTER    @E@@@L          J         CPOS3               ENTER COMMON CSA
)@@G@@ODE   @[@@@L.     @[@@@L.     @B@@@L.         LOAD NEXT NON-BLANK CHARACSB
)@@G@@TER   @[@@@L.     @ @@@L.         LMJ       X11,JPOS4$@E@@@L.         <RSC
)@@G@@ETURN>                      A0 = <CHARACTER>    @[@@@L.     @ @@@L      SD
)@@G@@    ON        ASCII     @]@@@LCPOS4$*   . @ @@@L          OFF       ASCISE
)@@G@@I     @ @@@L          ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@LUPOS4$*   . @ @@@L      SF
)@@G@@    OFF       1-ASCII   @G@@@L          LXI,XU    X11,-1              LOSG
)@@G@@AD FLAG TO PICK UP CHARACTER  @G@@@LCPOS3     SX        X11,RET         SH
)@@G@@    SAVE RETURN POINT FOR ERRORS    @[@@@L.     @E@@@LCPOS4L    EX      SI
)@@G@@  LOOK                LOAD NEXT CHARACTER @E@@@L          TE,U      A2,CSJ
)@@G@@BLANK           IS IT A SPACE ?     @F@@@L          J         CFIN      SK
)@@G@@          NO.  THAT'S THE TERMINATOR@F@@@L          EX        LOAD      SL
)@@G@@          YES.  LOAD AND SKIP IT    @F@@@L          J         CPOS4L    SM
)@@G@@          LOOK AT NEXT CHARACTER    @[@@@L.     @[@@@L.     @C@@@L.     SN
)@@G@@    COMMON EXIT FROM POSITIONING ROUTINES @[@@@L.     @G@@@LCFIN      LASO
)@@G@@        A0,A2               LOAD CHARACTER WE STOPPED ON    @G@@@L      SP
)@@G@@    TN        X11                 LOAD THE TERMINATING CHARACTER ?@F@@@LSQ
)@@G@@          J         0,X11               NO.  JUST STOP BEFORE IT  @[@@@LSR
)@@G@@.     @F@@@LCFINX     EX        LOAD                LOAD TERMINATING DELSS
)@@G@@IMITER@F@@@L          LA        A0,A2               RETURN TO CALLER IN ST
)@@G@@A0    @G@@@L          EX        LOOK                LOOK AHEAD TO NEXT CSU
)@@G@@HARACTER    @E@@@L          J         0,X11               RETURN TO CALLSV
)@@G@@ER    @[@@@L/.    @[@@@L.     @B@@@L.         SCAN A VARIABLE LENGTH INTSW
)@@G@@EGER  @[@@@L.     @ @@@L.         LMJ       X11,JI$   @F@@@L.         <RSX
)@@G@@ETURN>                      A0,A1 = <INTEGER SCANNED> @[@@@L.     @G@@@LSY
)@@G@@.         IF THE NUMBER HAS A LEADING ZERO, IT WILL BE INTERPRETED AS   SZ
)@@G@@@E@@@L.         OCTAL.  OTHERWISE, IT WILL BE SCANNED AS DECIMAL. @[@@@LTA
)@@G@@.     @ @@@L          ON        ASCII     @]@@@LCI$*      . @ @@@L      TB
)@@G@@    OFF       ASCII     @ @@@L          ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@LUI$*  TC
)@@G@@    . @ @@@L          OFF       1-ASCII   @E@@@L          SX        X11,TD
)@@G@@RET             SAVE RETURN POINT   @E@@@L          LMJ       X11,JSIGN$TE
)@@G@@          SCAN (OPTIONAL) SIGN@F@@@L          LA,U      A3,0            TF
)@@G@@    CLEAR DIGITS SCANNED COUNT@G@@@L          EX        LOOK            TG
)@@G@@    LOOK AT CHARACTER AFTER SIGN    @F@@@L          TNE,U     A2,CZERO  TH
)@@G@@          LEADING ZERO ON NUMBER ?  @F@@@L          J         COI       TI
)@@G@@          YES.  SCAN OCTAL INTEGER  @F@@@L          J         CDI       TJ
)@@G@@          NO.  SCAN DECIMAL INTEGER @[@@@L.     @[@@@L.     @C@@@L.     TK
)@@G@@    SCAN A VARIABLE LENGTH DECIMAL INTEGER@[@@@L.     @ @@@L.         LMTL
)@@G@@J       X11,JDI$  @F@@@L.         <RETURN>                      A1 = <INTM
)@@G@@TEGER SCANNED>    @[@@@L.     @ @@@L          ON        ASCII     @]@@@LTN
)@@G@@CDI$*     . @ @@@L          OFF       ASCII     @ @@@L          ON      TO
)@@G@@  1-ASCII   @]@@@LUDI$*     . @ @@@L          OFF       1-ASCII   @E@@@LTP
)@@G@@          SX        X11,RET             SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @F@@@L      TQ
)@@G@@    LA,U      A3,0                CLEAR DIGITS SCANNED COUNT@F@@@L      TR
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,JSIGN$          SCAN AND PROCESS THE SIGN @F@@@LCDI   TS
)@@G@@    EX        LOOK                LOOK AT NEXT CHARACTER    @E@@@L      TT
)@@G@@    TG,U      A2,CZERO            IS IT NUMERIC ?     @G@@@L          TGTU
)@@G@@,U      A2,CZERO+10         ...AND VALID DECIMAL DIGIT ?    @H@@@L      TV
)@@G@@    J         JFINI$              NO.  THIS IS TERMINATING DELIMITER    TW
)@@G@@@E@@@L          EX        LOAD                LOAD NEXT CHARACTER @E@@@LTX
)@@G@@          ANA,U     A2,CZERO            CONVERT TO BINARY   @E@@@L      TY
)@@G@@    MSI,U     A1,10               SCALE RESULT SO FAR @E@@@L          AATZ
)@@G@@        A1,A2               ADD IN LATEST DIGIT @F@@@L          AA,U    UA
)@@G@@  A3,1                INCREMENT DIGITS SCANNED  @G@@@L          J       UB
)@@G@@  CDI                 CONTINUE SCANNING TO DELIMETER  @[@@@L.     @[@@@LUC
)@@G@@.     @C@@@L.         SCAN A VARIABLE LENGTH OCTAL INTEGER  @[@@@L.     UD
)@@G@@@ @@@L.         LMJ       X11,JOI$  @F@@@L.         <RETURN>            UE
)@@G@@          A0,A1 = <INTEGER SCANNED> @[@@@L.     @ @@@L          ON      UF
)@@G@@  ASCII     @]@@@LCOI$*     . @ @@@L          OFF       ASCII     @ @@@LUG
)@@G@@          ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@LUOI$*     . @ @@@L          OFF     UH
)@@G@@  1-ASCII   @E@@@L          SX        X11,RET             SAVE RETURN POUI
)@@G@@INT   @F@P@L          LA,U      A3                  SET TO SCAN SINGLE DUJ
)@@G@@IGITS @G@@@P          LA,U      A3,0                CLEAR COUNT OF DIGITUK
)@@G@@S SCANNED   @F@@@L          LMJ       X11,JSIGN$          SCAN THE SIGN UL
)@@G@@(IF ANY)    @E@@@LCOI       EX        LOOK                LOOK AT NEXT DUM
)@@G@@IGIT  @E@@@L          TG,U      A2,CZERO            IS IT NUMERIC ?     UN
)@@G@@@F@@@L          TG,U      A2,CZERO+8          YES.  VALID OCTAL DIGIT ? UO
)@@G@@@H@@@L          J         JFINI$              NO.  TREAT AS TERMINATING UP
)@@G@@DELIMITER   @ @P@L          ON        ASCII     @]@P@LCO$*      . @ @P@LUQ
)@@G@@          OFF       ASCII     @ @P@L          ON        1-ASCII   @]@P@LUR
)@@G@@UO$*      . @ @P@L          OFF       ASCII     @E@@@L          EX      US
)@@G@@  LOAD                LOAD NEXT CHARACTER @E@@@L          ANA,U     A2,CUT
)@@G@@ZERO            CONVERT TO BINARY   @E@@@L          LDSL      A0,3      UU
)@@G@@          SCALE RESULT SO FAR @G@@@L          SSC       A2,3            UV
)@@G@@    MOVE NEW DIGIT TO TOP 3 BITS    @F@@@L          SSL       A1,3      UW
)@@G@@          RIGHT JUSTIFY LOW WORD    @F@@@L          LDSL      A1,3      UX
)@@G@@          MOVE NEW DIGIT INTO TOTAL @F@@@L          AA,U      A3,1      UY
)@@G@@          INCREMENT DIGITS SCANNED  @G@@@L          J         COI       UZ
)@@G@@          CONTINUE UNTIL DELIMITER REACHED@[@@@P.     @[@@@P.     @D@@@PVA
)@@G@@.         SCAN A VARIABLE LENGTH HEXADECIMAL INTEGER  @[@@@P.     @ @@@PVB
)@@G@@.         LMJ       X11,JHI$  @F@@@P.         <RETURN>                  VC
)@@G@@    A0,A1 = <INTEGER SCANNED> @[@@@P.     @ @@@P          ON        ASCIVD
)@@G@@I     @]@@@PCHI$*     . @ @@@P          OFF       ASCII     @ @@@P      VE
)@@G@@    ON        1-ASCII   @]@@@PUHI$*     . @ @@@P          OFF       1-ASVF
)@@G@@CII   @E@@@P          SX        X11,RET             SAVE RETURN POINT   VG
)@@G@@@G@@@P          LA,U      A3,0                CLEAR COUNT OF DIGITS SCANVH
)@@G@@NED   @E@@@P          LMJ       X11,JSIGN$          SCAN SIGN, IF ANY   VI
)@@G@@@[@@@P.     @F@@@PCHI       EX        LOOK                LOOK AT NEXT CVJ
)@@G@@HARACTER    @D@@@P          TG,U      A2,CZERO            NORMAL DIGIT ?VK

)@@G@@    J         CHITH               NO.  TEST HEX DIGIT @G@@@P          ANVM
)@@G@@A,U     A2,CZERO            YES.  REMOVE CHARACTER BIAS     @[@@@P.     VN
)@@G@@@G@@@PCHIAC     LDSL      A0,4                MAKE ROOM FOR NYBBLE IN A0VO
)@@G@@, A1  @F@@@P          SSC       A2,4                MOVE NYBBLE TO TOP OVP
)@@G@@F A2  @F@@@P          SSL       A1,4                PACK LOWER WORD RIGHVQ
)@@G@@T     @F@@@P          LDSL      A1,4                COLLECT NEW NYBBLE IVR
)@@G@@N A1  @F@@@P          AA,U      A3,1                INCREMENT DIGITS SCAVS
)@@G@@NNED  @E@@@P          EX        LOAD                ADVANCE THE POINTER VT
)@@G@@@E@@@P          J         CHI                 SCAN NEXT CHARACTER @[@@@PVU
)@@G@@.     @]@@@PCHITH     . @ @@@P          ON        ASCII     @E@@@P      VV
)@@G@@    TG,U      A2,0140             IS IT LOWER CASE ?  @F@@@P          ANVW
)@@G@@A,U     A2,040              YES.  MAKE IT UPPER CASE  @ @@@P          OFVX
)@@G@@F       ASCII     @E@@@P          TG,U      A2,CLTRA            IS IT A VY
)@@G@@HEX DIGIT ? @F@@@P          TG,U      A2,CLTRA+6          BETWEEN 'A' ANVZ
)@@G@@D 'F' ?     @F@@@P          J         JFINI$              NO.  RETURN TOWA

)@@G@@LVE CHARACTERS  IN  A0  @C@@@ .                   AND A1 ARE TAKEN AS INDR
)@@G@@PUT.  @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         ECOPY$ -  COPIES  THE  A1 CHARACTERS SDS
)@@G@@TARTING AT A0 INTO THE  @E@@@ .                   IMAGE AND ADVANCES THEDT
)@@G@@ POINTER BY A1.   @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         EPACK$ -  SAME AS  ECOPY$ DU
)@@G@@ EXCEPT  THAT  MASTER  SPACES  ARE  @F@@@ .                   IGNORED ANDV
)@@G@@D MULTIPLE BLANKS ARE COMPRESSED.   @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         EMSG$  -DW
)@@G@@  COPIES  THE  CHARACTERS  STARTING  AT  A0 INTO THE  @G@@@ .           DX
)@@G@@        IMAGE. THIS PROCESS STOPS WHEN THE CHARACTER IN S2  @G@@@ .     DY
)@@G@@              OF  THE  FIRST  WORD  OF  THE PACKET IS FOUND. THE  @G@@@ DZ
)@@G@@.                   POINTER TO THIS STRING IS SAVED IN THE PACKET  AND  EA
)@@G@@@C@@@ .                   RETURN IS MADE TO THE USER. @[@@@ .     @F@@@ EB
)@@G@@.         EMSG1$ -  SAME AS EMSG$ EXCEPT THE POINTER IS NOT SAVED.@[@@@ EC
)@@G@@.     @G@@@ .         EMSGR$ -  THIS  ROUTINE PERFORMS THE SAME OPERATIOED
)@@G@@N AS EMSG$  @G@@@ .                   EXCEPT THAT THE POINTER TO  THE  IEE
)@@G@@NPUT  STRING  IS  @G@@@ .                   TAKEN  FROM THE PACKET. WITHEF
)@@G@@ THESE TWO ROUTINES IT  @G@@@ .                   IS POSSIBLE TO COPY A EG
)@@G@@STRING INTO  THE  IMAGE  AND  @G@@@ .                   OCCASIONALLY  INEH
)@@G@@TERRUPT  THIS  PROCESS  TO PERFORM  @G@@@ .                   OTHER EDITEI
)@@G@@ING FUNCTIONS AT CERTAIN SELECTED POINTS  @A@@@ .                   IN TEJ
)@@G@@HE STRING.  @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         EOCTV$ -  EDITS  A0 TO OCTAL. THEK
)@@G@@E NUMBER OF DIGITS GENERATED  @G@@@ .                   WILL DEPEND ON TEL
)@@G@@HE LOGICAL MAGNITUDE OF A0. IF  A0  @G@@@ .                   IS  LOGICAEM
)@@G@@LLY  GREATER  THAN  7  A LEADING ZERO IS  @ @@@ .                   ADDEEN
)@@G@@D.    @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         EOCTF$ -  EDITS A0 TO A1 OCTAL DIGITS.EO
)@@G@@ LEADING ZEROS ARE NOT  @ @@@ .                   SUPRESSED.@[@@@ .     EP
)@@G@@@G@@@ .         EDECV$ -  EDITS  A0  TO  A  DECIMAL NUMBER. A LEADING '-EQ
)@@G@@' IS  @G@@@ .                   ADDED IF A0 IS NEGATIVE. THE NUMBER OF  ER
)@@G@@CHARACTERS  @G@@@ .                   GENERATED  IS A FUNCTION OF THE SIES
)@@G@@GN AND MAGNITUDE  @ @@@ .                   OF A0.    @[@@@ .     @G@@@ ET
)@@G@@.         EDECF$ -  EDITS A0 TO A DECIMAL NUMBER RIGHT JUSTIFIED IN  A  EU
)@@G@@@G@@@ .                   FIELD  OF A1 CHARACTERS. A LEADING '-' IS ADDEEV
)@@G@@D IF  @G@@@ .                   A0 IS NEGATIVE. THE RESULT WILL OVERFLOWEW
)@@G@@ THE FIELD  @G@@@ .                   TO  THE  RIGHT IF IT DOES NOT FIT EX
)@@G@@IN THE SPECIFIED  @A@@@ .                   FIELD SIZE.     @[@@@ .     EY
)@@G@@@G@@@ .         EDECZ$ -  SAME AS EDECF$ EXCEPT LEADING ZEROS ARE EDITEDEZ
)@@G@@.     @[@@@ .     @G@@@ .         EFORM$ -  EDITS A0 TO A GENERAL FORM (FA
)@@G@@GROUPS OF OCTAL DIGITS  @G@@@ .                   SEPARATED BY SPACES) SFB
)@@G@@PECIFIED BY THE FORM WORD IN  @G@@@ .                   A1.  EACH BIT INFC
)@@G@@ THE FORM WORD DETERMINES THE LEFT  @G@@@ .                   BOUNDARY  FD
)@@G@@OF  A  GROUP.  IF THE 1*/35 BIT IS 0 THE  @G@@@ .                   FIRSFE
)@@G@@T GROUP WILL NOT BE EDITED.  IF THE FORM  WORD  @G@@@ .                 FF
)@@G@@  IS ZERO ALL 36 BITS WILL BE EDITED IN ONE GROUP.    @[@@@ .     @F@@@ FG
)@@G@@.         EFI$   -  EDITS A0 INTO THE I$ FORM (6,4,4,4,2,16).     @[@@@ FH
)@@G@@.     @D@@@ .         EFH$   -  EDITS A0 INTO 2 18 BIT GROUPS.    @D@^@[FI
)@@G@@.         EDIT$  -  INITIAL ENTRY (DESCRIBED ABOVE)   @[@^@[.     @B@^@[FJ
)@@G@@.         EDITX$ -  EXIT (DESCRIBED ABOVE)@[@^@[.     @C@^@[.         EDFK
)@@G@@ITR$ -  REENTRY (DESCRIBED ABOVE)   @[@^@[.     @E@^@[.         EDITZ$ -FL
)@@G@@  SAME AS EDITR$ EXCEPT THE COLUMN POINTER@A@^@[.                   IS SFM
)@@G@@ET TO ZERO. @[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         ECHAR$ -  EDITS THE CHARACTER INFN
)@@G@@ THE LOW ORDER 6 BITS   @F@^@[.                   OF A0 INTO THE IMAGE AFO
)@@G@@ND ADVANCES THE POINTER @B@^@[.                   BY ONE CHARACTER.     FP
)@@G@@@[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         ECOL$  -  POSITIONS THE POINTER TO THE COLUMFQ
)@@G@@N NUMBER    @F@^@[.                   GIVEN IN A0. THE FIRST CHARACTER PFR
)@@G@@OSITION OF  @B@^@[.                   THE IMAGE IS COLUMN 0.@[@^@[.     FS
)@@G@@@F@^@[.         ESKIP$ -  ADDS A0 TO THE POINTER. A0 MAY BE POSITIVE    FT
)@@G@@@A@^@[.                   OR NEGATIVE.    @[@^@[.     @E@^@[.         ECFU
)@@G@@OLN$ -  RETURNS WITH THE COLUMN NUMBER IN A0.   @[@^@[.     @E@^@[.     FV
)@@G@@    EFD1$  -  STORES THE SIX CHARACTERS IN A0 INTO THE@F@^@[.           FW
)@@G@@        IMAGE BUT IGNORES BLANKS AND MASTER SPACES.   @E@^@[.           FX
)@@G@@        THE POINTER IS ADVANCED BY ONE FOR EACH @B@^@[.                 FY
)@@G@@  CHARACTER STORED.     @[@^@[.     @G@^@[.         EFD2$  -  SAME AS EFFZ
)@@G@@D1$ EXCEPT THAT THE TWELVE CHARACTERS     @D@^@[.                   IN AGA
)@@G@@0 AND A1 ARE TAKEN AS INPUT.  @[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         EFD3$  -  SAMEGB
)@@G@@ AS EFD1$ EXCEPT BLANKS ARE NOT IGNORED.  @[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         EFGC
)@@G@@D4$  -  SAME AS EFD2$ EXCEPT BLANKS ARE NOT IGNORED.  @[@^@[.     @E@^@[GD
)@@G@@.         EFD5$  -  STORES THE SIX CHARACTERS IN A0 INTO THE@E@^@[.     GE
)@@G@@              IMAGE IGNORING ONLY TRAILING BLANKS.    @[@^@[.     @F@^@[GF
)@@G@@.         EFD6$  -  SAME AS EFD5$ EXCEPT THE TWELVE CHARACTERS    @D@^@[GG
)@@G@@.                   IN A0 AND A1 ARE TAKEN AS INPUT.  @[@^@[.     @F@^@[GH
)@@G@@.         ECOPY$ -  COPIES THE A1 CHARACTERS STARTING AT A0 INTO  @F@^@[GI
)@@G@@.                   THE IMAGE AND ADVANCES THE POINTER BY A1.     @[@^@[GJ
)@@G@@.     @F@^@[.         EPACK$ -  SAME AS ECOPY$ EXCEPT THAT MASTER SPACESGK
)@@G@@ ARE  @F@^@[.                   IGNORED AND MULTIPLE BLANKS ARE COMPRESSGL
)@@G@@ED.   @[@^@[.     @E@^@[.         EMSG$  -  COPIES THE CHARACTERS STARTIGM
)@@G@@NG AT A0    @E@^@[.                   INTO THE IMAGE. THIS PROCESS STOPSGN
)@@G@@ WHEN @E@^@[.                   THE CHARACTER IN S2 OF THE FIRST WORD OFGO
)@@G@@@E@^@[.                   THE PACKET IS FOUND. THE POINTER TO THIS@E@^@[GP
)@@G@@.                   STRING IS SAVED IN THE PACKET AND RETURN@B@^@[.     GQ
)@@G@@              IS MADE TO THE USER.  @[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         EMSG1$ -GR
)@@G@@  SAME AS EMSG$ EXCEPT THE POINTER IS NOT SAVED.@[@^@[.     @E@^@[.     GS
)@@G@@    EMSGR$ -  THIS ROUTINE PERFORMS THE SAME OPERATION@F@^@[.           GT
)@@G@@        AS EMSG$ EXCEPT THAT THE POINTER TO THE INPUT @F@^@[.           GU
)@@G@@        STRING IS TAKEN FROM THE PACKET. WITH THESE   @F@^@[.           GV
)@@G@@        TWO ROUTINES IT IS POSSIBLE TO COPY A STRING  @F@^@[.           GW
)@@G@@        INTO THE IMAGE AND OCCASIONALLY INTERRUPT THIS@F@^@[.           GX
)@@G@@        PROCESS TO PERFORM OTHER EDITING FUNCTIONS    @F@^@[.           GY
)@@G@@        AT CERTAIN SELECTED POINTS IN THE STRING.     @[@^@[.     @E@^@[GZ
)@@G@@.         EOCTV$ -  EDITS A0 TO OCTAL. THE NUMBER OF DIGITS @F@^@[.     HA
)@@G@@              GENERATED WILL DEPEND ON THE LOGICAL MAGNITUDE@F@^@[.     HB
)@@G@@              OF A0. IF A0 IS LOGICALLY GREATER THAN 7 A    @B@^@[.     HC
)@@G@@              LEADING ZERO IS ADDED.@[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         EOCTF$ -HD
)@@G@@  EDITS A0 TO A1 OCTAL DIGITS. LEADING ZEROS    @B@^@[.                 HE
)@@G@@  ARE NOT SUPRESSED.    @[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         EDECV$ -  EDITS A0 THF
)@@G@@O A DECIMAL NUMBER. A LEADING '-'   @F@^@[.                   IS ADDED IHG
)@@G@@F A0 IS NEGATIVE. THE NUMBER OF     @F@^@[.                   CHARACTERSHH
)@@G@@ GENERATED IS A FUNCTION OF THE     @C@^@[.                   SIGN AND MHI
)@@G@@AGNITUDE OF A0.   @[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         EDECF$ -  EDITS A0 TO A DEHJ
)@@G@@CIMAL NUMBER RIGHT JUSTIFIED  @F@^@[.                   IN A FIELD OF A1HK
)@@G@@ CHARACTERS. A LEADING '-'    @F@^@[.                   IS ADDED IF A0 IHL
)@@G@@S NEGATIVE. THE RESULT WILL   @F@^@[.                   OVERFLOW THE FIEHM
)@@G@@LD TO THE RIGHT IF IT DOES    @E@^@[.                   NOT FIT IN THE SHN
)@@G@@PECIFIED FIELD SIZE.    @[@^@[.     @G@^@[.         EDECZ$ -  SAME AS EDHO
)@@G@@ECF$ EXCEPT LEADING ZEROS ARE EDITED.     @[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         EFHP
)@@G@@ORM$ -  EDITS A0 TO A GENERAL FORM (GROUPS OF OCTAL   @E@^@[.           HQ
)@@G@@        DIGITS SEPARATED BY SPACES) SPECIFIED   @F@^@[.                 HR
)@@G@@  BY THE FORM WORD IN A1.  EACH BIT IN THE FORM @F@^@[.                 HS
)@@G@@  WORD DETERMINES THE LEFT BOUNDARY OF A GROUP. @F@^@[.                 HT
)@@G@@  IF THE 1*/35 BIT IS 0 THE FIRST GROUP WILL    @F@^@[.                 HU
)@@G@@  NOT BE EDITED.  IF THE FORM WORD IS ZERO ALL  @E@^@[.                 HV
)@@G@@  36 BITS WILL BE EDITED IN ONE GROUP.    @[@^@[.     @F@^@[.         EFHW
)@@G@@I$   -  EDITS A0 INTO THE I$ FORM (6,4,4,4,2,16).     @[@^@[.     @D@^@[HX
)@@G@@.         EFH$   -  EDITS A0 INTO 2 18 BIT GROUPS.    @[@@@[.     @@@@@[HY
)@@G@@@A@@@[.         INITIAL ENTRY TO EDIT MODE@@@@@[@G@@@[EDIT$*    SX      HZ
)@@G@@  PX,SAVE1-PKT,A0     SAVE THE NON-VOLATILE REGISTERS @A@@@[          SXIA
)@@G@@        CX,SAVE2-PKT,A0 @A@@@[          SX        WX,SAVE3-PKT,A0 @F@@@[IB
)@@G@@          LXM,U     PX,,A0              SET UP THE PACKET ADDRESS @E@@@[IC
)@@G@@          LR        R1,IL               R1 = IMAGE LENGTH   @F@@@[      ID
)@@G@@    LX        CX,(1,0)            SET UP THE CHARACTER INDEX@F@@@[      IE
)@@G@@    LX        WX,ILOC             SET UP THE WORD INDEX     @^@@@[      IF
)@@G@@    LXI,U     WX,1@E@@@[          LA,U      A0,('      ')       BLANK THIG
)@@G@@E LINE IMAGE@ @@@[          BT        WX,,*A0   @F@@@[          LXM     IH

)@@G@@  RETURN              FUDGE   @C@@@[          J         0,X11           IJ
)@@G@@    RETURN  @@@@@[@E@@@[.         RE-ENTRY TO EDIT MODE AND ZERO COLUMN IK

)@@G@@LUMN POINTER@ @@@[          SZ        WIX-PKT,A0@@@@@[@A@@@[.         REIM
)@@G@@-ENTRY TO EDIT MODE     @@@@@[@G@@@[EDITR$*   SX        PX,SAVE1-PKT,A0 IN
)@@G@@    SAVE THE NON-VOLATILE REGISTERS @A@@@[          SX        CX,SAVE2-PIO
)@@G@@KT,A0 @A@@@[          SX        WX,SAVE3-PKT,A0 @F@@@[          LXM,U   IP

)@@G@@@H@@@[          LXM       PX,SAVE1            RESTORE THE NON-VOLATILE RIZ

)@@G@@        WX,SAVE3-PKT,A0 @C@@@[          J         0,X11               REJB
)@@G@@TURN  @@@@@[@@@@@[@^@@@[.         STORE VECTOR  @@@@@[@ @@@[EDIT$T*   SAJC
)@@G@@,S1     A2,WI     @ @@@[          SA,S2     A2,WI     @ @@@[          SAJD
)@@G@@,S3     A2,WI     @ @@@[          SA,S4     A2,WI     @ @@@[          SAJE
)@@G@@,S5     A2,WI     @D@@@[          LMJ       CX,ET1              BREAK OUJF

)@@G@@ET1       SA,S6     A2,,*WX             STORE THE LAST CHARACTER  @D@@@[JH
)@@G@@ET$*      SX,H2     CX,RETURN           SET UP RETURN @F@@@[          LXJI
)@@G@@M,U     CX,,A2              SAVE THE CHARACTER IN A2  @F@@@[          LAJJ
)@@G@@,U      A2,0,WX             IS NEXT STORE IN IMAGE?   @ @@@[          TLJK
)@@G@@E       A2,ILOC   @^@@@[          J         ET2 @ @@@[          ANA     JL

)@@G@@  ET2 @F@@@[          L,U       A2,,CX              RESTORE THE CHARACTEJN
)@@G@@R     @G@@@[          LXM,U     CX,0                INITIALIZE THE CHARAJO

)@@G@@  CX,6                NO@^@@@[          ANX,U     WX,1@ @@@[          J JR
)@@G@@        *RETURN   @@@@@[@ @@@[.         STORE A CHARACTER   @@@@@[@C@@@[JS
)@@G@@ECHAR$*   LA,U      A2,,A0              A2 = A0 @E@@@[          STORE   JT
)@@G@@  .                   STORE THE CHARACTER @C@@@[          J         0,X1JU
)@@G@@1               RETURN  @@@@@[@A@@@[.         POSITION TO A FIXED COLUMNJV
)@@G@@@@@@@[@D@@@[ECOL$*    DSL       A0,36               SET UP DIVIDE @D@@@[JW
)@@G@@          DI,U      A0,6                DIVIDE BY 6   @F@@@[          AAJX
)@@G@@        A0,ILOC             GET THE WORD LOCATION     @F@@@[          LXJY
)@@G@@M,U     CX,,A1              SET UP THE CHARACTER INDEX@F@@@[          LXJZ
)@@G@@M,U     WX,,A0              SET UP THE WORD INDEX     @E@@@[          ANKA
)@@G@@U       A0,IL               IS IT IN IMAGE?     @ @@@[          TLE     KB
)@@G@@  A1,ILOC   @ @@@[          TLE       A0,ILOC   @B@@@[          J       KC
)@@G@@  ECOL                NO@ @@@[          J         0,X11     @@@@@[@D@@@[KD
)@@G@@ECOL      AX,U      CX,6                OUT OF IMAGE  @^@@@[          ANKE
)@@G@@X,U     WX,1@C@@@[          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@[KF
)@@G@@@^@@@[.         SKIP AN AREA  @@@@@[@F@@@[ESKIP$*   AA,U      A0,CI     KG
)@@G@@          ADD THE CHARACTER INDEX   @E@@@[          LA,U      A1,WI     KH
)@@G@@          A1 = WORD INDEX     @E@@@[          ANA       A1,ILOC         KI
)@@G@@    MAKE IT RELATIVE    @G@@@[          MSI,U     A1,6                GEKJ
)@@G@@T THE NUMBER OF CHARACTERS    @E@@@[          AA,U      A0,,A1          KK
)@@G@@    A0 = COLUMN NUMBER  @D@@@[          J         ECOL$               FIKL
)@@G@@NISH UP     @@@@@[@D@@@[.         CLEAR BUFFER TO SPACES AND RESET TO COKM

)@@G@@GTH   @E@@@[          LXM       WX,ILOC             SET UP WORD INDEX   KO

)@@G@@    RESET TO COLUMN 0   @ @@@[          LXM       WX,ILOC   @C@@@[      KR
)@@G@@    J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@[@A@@@[.         COMPUTE KS
)@@G@@THE COLUMN NUMBER @@@@@[@E@@@[ECOLN$*   LA,U      A0,WI               A0KT
)@@G@@ = WORD INDEX     @E@@@[          ANA       A0,ILOC             MAKE IT KU
)@@G@@RELATIVE    @G@@@[          MSI,U     A0,6                GET THE NUMBERKV
)@@G@@ OF CHARACTERS    @F@@@[          AA,U      A0,CI               ADD THE KW
)@@G@@CHARACTER INDEX   @C@@@[          J         0,X11               RETURN  KX
)@@G@@@@@@@[@@@@@[@C@@@[.         STORE FIELDATA (ONE OR TWO WORDS)     @@@@@[KY
)@@G@@@C@@@[EFD1$*    LA,U      A3,5                ONE WORD@C@@@[          J KZ
)@@G@@        EFD1                SKIP    @D@@@[EFD2$*    LA,U      A3,11     LA
)@@G@@          TWO WORDS     @G@@@[EFD1      DSC       A0,66               POLB
)@@G@@SITION THE NEXT CHARACTER     @E@@@[          AND,U     A1,1*/6-1       LC
)@@G@@    ISOLATE IT IN A2    @E@@@[          TE,U      A2,' '              ISLD
)@@G@@ IT A BLANK ?     @E@@@[          TNE,U     A2,'@'              OR A MASLE
)@@G@@TER-SPACE ? @C@@@[          J         $+2                 NO, SKIP@C@@@[LF
)@@G@@          STORE     .                   STORE IT@D@@@[          JGD     LG
)@@G@@  A3,EFD1             LOOP ON A3    @C@@@[          J         0,X11     LH
)@@G@@          RETURN  @@@@@[@C@@@[EFD3$*    LA,U      A3,5                ONLI
)@@G@@E WORD@^@@@[          J         EFD2@D@@@[EFD4$*    LA,U      A3,11     LJ
)@@G@@          TWO WORDS     @G@@@[EFD2      DSC       A0,66               POLK
)@@G@@SITION THE NEXT CHARACTER     @E@@@[          AND,U     A1,1*/6-1       LL
)@@G@@    ISOLATE IT IN A2    @D@@@[          TE,U      A2,'@'              MALM
)@@G@@STER SPACE? @D@@@[          STORE     .                   NO, STORE IT  LN
)@@G@@@D@@@[          JGD       A3,EFD2             LOOP ON A3    @C@@@[      LO
)@@G@@    J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@[@G@@@[EFD5$*    LA      LP
)@@G@@  A1,('      ')       MAKE IT LOOK LIKE TWO WORDS     @D@@@[EFD6$*    LALQ
)@@G@@,U      A3,11               TWO WORDS     @D@@@[          SX        X11,LR
)@@G@@RET             SAVE RETURN   @E@@@[          LX,U      X11,0           LS
)@@G@@    CLEAR SHIFT COUNT   @E@@@[EFD3      AND,U     A1,1*/6-1           GELT
)@@G@@T LAST CHARACTER  @D@@@[          TE,U      A2,' '              IS IT A LU
)@@G@@BLANK?@E@@@[          J         EFD4                NO. START EDITING   LV
)@@G@@@E@@@[          AX,U      X11,6               BUMP SHIFT COUNT    @E@@@[LW
)@@G@@          DSL       A0,6                SHIFT OFF THE BLANK @C@@@[      LX
)@@G@@    JGD       A3,EFD3             REPEAT  @E@@@[          LX        X11,LY
)@@G@@RET             IT WAS ALL BLANKS   @C@@@[          J         0,X11     LZ
)@@G@@          RETURN  @E@@@[EFD4      LDSL      A0,0,X11            RESTORE MA
)@@G@@THE WORD    @D@@@[          LX        X11,RET             GET RETURN    MB
)@@G@@@F@@@[EFD5      DSC       A0,72-6             POSITION NEXT CHARACTER   MC
)@@G@@@E@@@[          AND,U     A1,1*/6-1           GET NEXT CHARACTER  @C@@@[MD
)@@G@@          STORE     .                   STORE IT@C@@@[          JGD     ME
)@@G@@  A3,EFD5             REPEAT  @C@@@[          J         0,X11           MF
)@@G@@    RETURN  @@@@@[@@@@@[@A@@@[.         VARIABLE LENGTH OCTAL EDIT@@@@@[MG
)@@G@@@C@@@[EOCTV$*   LA,U      A3,0                A3 = 0  @F@@@[          DSMH
)@@G@@L       A0,3                SHIFT OFF LOW-ORDER DIGIT @F@@@[          JZMI
)@@G@@        A0,EOCTV2           ONLY ONE DIGIT - BYPASS   @C@@@[EOCTV1    AAMJ
)@@G@@,U      A3,1                ADD 1   @F@@@[          DSL       A0,3      MK
)@@G@@          SHIFT OFF THE NEXT DIGIT  @E@@@[          JNZ       A0,EOCTV1 ML
)@@G@@          MORE TO GO - LOOP   @E@@@[          LA,U      A2,'0'          MM
)@@G@@    STORE A LEADING ZERO@^@@@[          STORE     .   @C@@@[EOCTV2    LAMN
)@@G@@,U      A2,0                CLEAR A2@F@@@[          LDSC      A1,3      MO
)@@G@@          POSITION THE NEXT DIGIT   @E@@@[          AA,U      A2,'0'    MP
)@@G@@          MAKE IT FIELDATA    @C@@@[          STORE     .               MQ
)@@G@@    STORE IT@D@@@[          JGD       A3,EOCTV2           LOOP ON A3    MR
)@@G@@@C@@@[          J         0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@[@A@@@[.     MS
)@@G@@    FIXED LENGTH OCTAL EDIT   @@@@@[@C@@@[EOCTF$*   LA,U      A3,,A1    MT
)@@G@@          A3 = A1 @F@@@[          MSI,U     A1,3                COMPUTE MU
)@@G@@THE NUMBER OF BITS@D@@@[          DSL       A0,,A1              SHIFT THMV
)@@G@@EM OFF@D@@@[          ANA,U     A3,1                DECREMENT A3  @D@@@[MW
)@@G@@          J         EOCTV2              FINISH UP     @@@@@[@@@@@[@C@@@[MX
