)@@G@@D DWO DIGITS OF YEAR    @D@@@]          LMJ       A1,EDEC           EDITWI
)@@G@@ TO DECIMAL @G@@@]          LA        A2,R1             A2 = SECOND TWO WJ
)@@G@@DIGITS OF YEAR    @D@@@]EDAY41    LMJ       A1,EDEC           EDIT TO DEWK
)@@G@@CIMAL @D@@@]          AND,U     A0,0770000        GET THE MONTH   @C@@@]WL
)@@G@@          DSL       A1,48             A2 = MONTH@D@@@]          LMJ     WM
)@@G@@  A1,EDEC           EDIT TO DECIMAL @D@@@]          AND,U     A0,07700  WN
)@@G@@        GET THE DAY     @C@@@]          DSL       A1,42             A2 =WO
)@@G@@ DAY  @D@@@]          LMJ       A1,EDEC           EDIT TO DECIMAL @C@@@]WP
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             RETURN    @@@@@]@B@@@].         EDWQ
)@@G@@IT A DATE (FORMAT YYMMDD)     @@@@@]@E@@@]EDAY5$*   SSL       A0,18     WR
)@@G@@        GET RID OF THE TIME   @G@@@]          AND,U     A0,077          WS
)@@G@@  GET THE YEAR (RELATIVE TO 1964)   @C@@@]          LA,U      A2,64,A1  WT
)@@G@@        A2 = YEAR @D@@@]          TG,U      A2,100            3 DIGIT YEWU
)@@G@@AR?   @F@#@]          ANA,U     A2,100            YES--REDUCE TO 2 DIGITWV
)@@G@@S     @F@@@#          ANA,U     A2,100            YES.  REDUCE TO 2 DIGIWW
)@@G@@TS    @D@@@]          J         EDAY41            FINISH EDITING  @@@@@]WX
)@@G@@@A@@@].         EDIT THE DAY OF THE WEEK  @@@@@]@E@@@]EDAYW$*   SSL     WY
)@@G@@  A0,18               GET RID OF TIME     @D@@@]          AND,U     A0,0WZ
)@@G@@77              AND OFF YEAR  @D@@@]          LA,U      A3,64,A1        XA
)@@G@@    A3 = YEAR     @E@@@]          SA        A3,RET              SAVE IT XB
)@@G@@FOR NOW     @F@@@]          SSL       A3,2                GET NUMBER OF XC
)@@G@@LEAP YEARS  @E@@@]          LA        A2,A0               MOVE DATE TO AXD
)@@G@@2     @D@@@]          LA        A0,RET              RELOAD YEAR   @F@@@]XE
)@@G@@          MSI,U     A0,365              MULTIPLY BY NORMAL LENGTH @F@@@]XF
)@@G@@          AA,U      A0,1,A3             ACCOUNT FOR LEAP YEARS    @D@@@]XG
)@@G@@          DSL       A2,12               A2 = MONTH    @C@@@]          SSXH
)@@G@@L       A3,36-6             A3 = DAY@H@@@]          AA        A0,MONTH-1XI
)@@G@@,A2       ADD ON NUMBER OF DAYS SO FAR THIS YEAR@F@@@]          AA,U    XJ
)@@G@@  A0,FUDGE,A3         COMPENSATE FOR HISTORY    @E@@@]          LA      XK
)@@G@@  A1,RET              GET THE YEAR BACK   @^@@@]          SZ        RET XL
)@@G@@@^@@@]          TOP,U     A1,1@^@@@]          TEP,U     A1,3@^@@@]      XM
)@@G@@    J         $+3 @^@@@]          TLE,U     A2,3@^@@@]          ANA,U   XN
)@@G@@  A0,1@ @@@]          DSL       A0,36     @^@@@]          DI,U      A0,7XO
)@@G@@@F@@@]          LA        A0,DTAB,A1          AND IT COMES OUT HERE     XP
)@@G@@@ @@@]          LA,U      A1,'DAY'  @E@@@]          J         EFD2$     XQ
)@@G@@          EDIT IN THE DAY     @@@@@]@^@@@].         MONTH TABLE   @@@@@]XR
)@@G@@@^@@@]MTAB      EQU       $-2 @^@@@]          ' JAN UARY   '@^@@@]      XS
)@@G@@    ' FEB RUARY  '@^@@@]          ' MAR CH     '@^@@@]          ' APR ILXT
)@@G@@     '@^@@@]          ' MAY        '@^@@@]          ' JUN E      '@^@@@]XU
)@@G@@          ' JUL Y      '@^@@@]          ' AUG UST    '@^@@@]          ' XV
)@@G@@SEP TEMBER '@^@@@]          ' OCT OBER   '@^@@@]          ' NOV EMBER  'XW
)@@G@@@^@@@]          ' DEC EMBER  '@@@@@]@@@@@]@^@@@].         DAY TABLE     XX
)@@G@@@@@@@]@ @@@]DTAB      +         'SUN'     @ @@@]          +         'MONXY
)@@G@@'     @ @@@]          +         'TUES'    @ @@@]          +         'WEDXZ
)@@G@@NES'  @ @@@]          +         'THURS'   @ @@@]          +         'FRIYA
)@@G@@'     @ @@@]          +         'SATUR'   @@@@@]@D@@@].         TABLE OFYB
)@@G@@ CUMULATIVE DAY COUNT BY MONTHS     @@@@@]@F@@@].         THIRTY DAYS HAYC
)@@G@@VE SEPTEMBER, APRIL, JUNE, AND NOVEMBER   @^@@@]M$(4)     EQU       30  YD
)@@G@@@^@@@]M$(6)     EQU       30  @^@@@]M$(9)     EQU       30  @^@@@]M$(11)YE
)@@G@@    EQU       30  @B@@@].         ALL THE REST HAVE THIRTY-ONE    @^@@@]YF
)@@G@@M$(1)     EQU       31  @^@@@]M$(3)     EQU       31  @^@@@]M$(5)     EQYG
)@@G@@U       31  @^@@@]M$(7)     EQU       31  @^@@@]M$(8)     EQU       31  YH
)@@G@@@^@@@]M$(10)    EQU       31  @^@@@]M$(12)    EQU       31  @D@@@].     YI
)@@G@@    EXCEPT FOR FEBRUARY, WHICH HAS TWENTY-EIGHT @^@@@]M$(2)     EQU     YJ
)@@G@@  28  @F@@@].         OR TWENTY-NINE ON LEAP YEARS, WHICH IS HANDLED ABOYK
)@@G@@VE    @@@@@]@^@@@]X$(1)     EQU       0   @C@@@]I         DO        11 ,YL
)@@G@@X$(I+1) EQU X$(I)+M$(I) @[@@@]MONTH @A@@@]I         DO        12 , + X$(YM
)@@G@@I)    @#@@@]          END     ___HE TWO DIGITS  @E@@@]          JZ      YN
)@@G@@  A2,EDAY31           NO LEADING ZERO     @E@@@]*[@@@@*SDFF*@@@@@ @@@@@ YO

)@@G@@ HERE TO Z$F.A BY RJEND COMMAND << $$$$$  @G@@@A.              THIS ELEMYW

)@@G@@F  DAY.  THESE  ROUTINES EACH ACCEPT INPUT IN TDATE$  @B@@@A.         FOYY

)@@G@@@[@@@A.     @B@@@A.         F         FORM      6,6,6,18    @[@@@A.     ZB

)@@G@@.     @D@D@A.                             LMJ X11,ROUTINE NAME    @C@@@DZF

)@@G@@TO Z$F.A BY RJEND COMMAND << $$$$$  @F@@@B.         ATIM$  -  EDITS THE ZK
)@@G@@TIME PORTION OF A0 INTO THE FORMAT  @[@@@B.     @B@@@B.                 ZL
)@@G@@            HH:MM:SS    @[@@@B.     @G@@@B.                   AND ADVANCZM
)@@G@@ES THE POINTER 8 POSITIONS. HH, MM,  AND  @G@@@B.                   SS  ZN
)@@G@@ARE  THE TWO DIGITS OF THE HOURS, MINUTES, AND  @D@@@B.                 ZO
)@@G@@  SECONDS OF THE TIME, RESPECTIVELY.@[@@@B.     @G@@@B.         ATIM1$ -ZP
)@@G@@  SAME AS ATIM$ EXCEPT HH IS EDITED MODULO  12  WITH  @G@@@B.           ZQ
)@@G@@        LEADING  ZERO  SUPPRESSED  AND  AM OR PM IS EDITED  @G@@@B.     ZR
)@@G@@              AFTER THE TIME.  TOTAL LENGTH IS EITHER 10  OR  11  @A@@@BZS
)@@G@@.                   CHARACTERS.     @[@@@B.     @B@@@B.                 ZT
)@@G@@            HH:MM:SS XM @[@@@B.     @F@@@B.         ADAY1$ -  EDITS THE ZU
)@@G@@DATE PORTION OF A0 INTO THE FORMAT  @[@@@B.     @B@@@B.                 ZV
)@@G@@            MM/DD/YY    @[@@@B.     @G@@@B.                   AND  ADVANZW
)@@G@@CES THE POINTER 8 POSITIONS. DD, MM, AND  @G@@@B.                   YY AZX
)@@G@@RE THE TWO DIGITS OF THE DAY, MONTH, AND  YEAR  @A@@@B.                 ZY
)@@G@@  RESPECTIVELY.   @[@@@B.     @F@@@B.         ADAY2$ -  EDITS THE DATE PZZ
)@@G@@ORTION OF A0 INTO THE FORMAT  @[@@@B.     @B@@@B.                       AA
)@@G@@      DD MMM YY   @[@@@B.     @G@@@B.                   AND  ADVANCES  TAB
)@@G@@HE  POINTER 9 POSITIONS. DD AND YY  @G@@@B.                   ARE  THE  AC
)@@G@@TWO  DIGITS  OF  THE   DAY   AND   YEAR,  @G@@@B.                   RESPAD
)@@G@@ECTIVELY   AND   MMM   IS   A  THREE-CHARACTER  @C@@@B.                 AE
)@@G@@  ABBREVIATION FOR THE MONTH. @[@@@B.     @F@@@B.         ADAY3$ -  EDITAF
)@@G@@S THE DATE PORTION OF A0 INTO THE FORMAT  @[@@@B.     @C@@@B.           AG
)@@G@@                  MONTH DD, YEAR    @[@@@B.     @G@@@B.                 AH
)@@G@@  WHERE MONTH IS THE NAME OF  THE  MONTH  (UP  TO  9  @G@@@B.           AI
)@@G@@        CHARACTERS)  DD IS THE DAY (ONE OR TWO DIGITS) AND  @C@@@B.     AJ
)@@G@@              YEAR IS THE FOUR DIGIT YEAR.@[@@@B.     @F@@@B.         ADAK
)@@G@@AY4$ -  EDITS THE DATE PORTION OF A0 INTO THE FORMAT: @[@@@B.     @B@@@BAL

)@@G@@        WHERE YYYY IS THE YEAR, MM IS THE MONTH, AND DD IS  @ @@@B.     AN

)@@G@@@G@A@ .                   AND SS ARE THE TWO DIGITS OF THE HOURS, MINUTEBA
)@@G@@S,    @E@A@ .                   AND SECONDS OF THE TIME, RESPECTIVELY.  BB

)@@G@@@B@A@ .                             MM/DD/YY    @[@A@ .     @F@A@ .     BI
)@@G@@              AND ADVANCES THE POINTER 8 POSITIONS. DD, MM, @F@A@ .     BJ
)@@G@@              AND YY ARE THE TWO DIGITS OF THE DAY, MONTH,  @B@A@ .     BK
)@@G@@              AND YEAR RESPECTIVELY.@[@A@ .     @F@A@ .         ADAY2$ -BL

)@@G@@  AND ADVANCES THE POINTER 9 POSITIONS. DD AND YY     @E@A@ .           BO
)@@G@@        ARE THE TWO DIGITS OF THE DAY AND YEAR, @F@A@ .                 BP
)@@G@@  RESPECTIVELY AND MMM IS A THREE-CHARACTER     @C@A@ .                 BQ
)@@G@@  ABBREVIATION FOR THE MONTH. @[@A@ .     @F@A@ .         ADAY3$ -  EDITBR
)@@G@@S THE DATE PORTION OF A0 INTO THE FORMAT  @[@A@ .     @C@A@ .           BS
)@@G@@                  MONTH DD, YEAR    @[@A@ .     @F@A@ .                 BT
)@@G@@  WHERE MONTH IS THE NAME OF THE MONTH (UP TO   @G@A@ .                 BU
)@@G@@  9 CHARACTERS) DD IS THE DAY (ONE OR TWO DIGITS)     @D@A@ .           BV
)@@G@@        AND YEAR IS THE FOUR DIGIT YEAR.  @[@A@ .     @F@A@ .         ADBW
)@@G@@AY4$ -  EDITS THE DATE PORTION OF A0 INTO THE FORMAT: @[@A@ .     @B@A@ BX
)@@G@@.                             YYYYMMDD    @[@A@ .     @I@A@ .           BY

)@@G@@@[@A@ .     @F@A@ .         ADAY5$ -  EDITS THE DATE PORTION OF A0 INTO CA
)@@G@@THE FORMAT: @[@A@ .     @A@A@ .                             YYMMDD@[@A@ CB

)@@G@@.                   WHERE WEEKDAY IS THE DAY OF THE WEEK FOR THE DATE   CG
)@@G@@@ @A@ .                   SPECIFIED.@[@@@ .     @@@@@ @@@@@ @H@@@ CENTURCH
)@@G@@Y   EQU       20                  MUST BE CHANGED EVERY HUNDRED YEARS   CI
)@@G@@@B@@@ FUDGE     EQU       2+(CENTURY-1)*/-2     @@@@@ @A@@@ .         EDCJ
)@@G@@IT A TIME (HH:MM:SS)    @@@@@ @]@@@ ATIME$*   . @E@@@ ATIM$*    LA,U    CK
)@@G@@  A0,,A0              STRIP OFF THE DATE  @D@@@           DSL       A0,3CL
)@@G@@6               SET UP DIVIDE @D@@@           DI,U      A0,3600         CM
)@@G@@    GET THE HOURS @C@@@           LA,U      A2,,A0              A2 = A0 CN
)@@G@@@C@@@           LA,U      A0,,A1              A0 = A1 @E@@@           LMCO
)@@G@@J       A1,EDEC             EDIT THE DIGITS     @D@@@           STORE,U CP
)@@G@@  COLON               STORE A COLON @D@@@           DSL       A0,36     CQ
)@@G@@          SET UP DIVIDE @G@@@           DI,U      A0,60               GECR
)@@G@@T THE MINUTES AND SECONDS     @C@@@           LA,U      A2,,A0          CS
)@@G@@    A2 = A0 @C@@@           LA,U      A0,,A1              A0 = A1 @E@@@ CT
)@@G@@          LMJ       A1,EDEC             EDIT THE DIGITS     @D@@@       CU
)@@G@@    STORE,U   COLON               STORE A COLON @C@@@           LA,U    CV
)@@G@@  A2,,A0              A2 = A0 @H@@@           LA,U      A1,,X11         CW
)@@G@@    FUDGE RETURN POINT FROM SECONDS EDIT  @@@@@ @A@@@ .         INSERT TCX
)@@G@@WO DECIMAL DIGITS @@@@@ @D@@@ EDEC      DSL       A2,36               SECY
)@@G@@T UP DIVIDE @D@@@           DI,U      A2,10               DIVIDE BY 10  CZ
)@@G@@@E@@@           STORE,U   '0',A2              STORE FIRST DIGIT   @E@@@ DA
)@@G@@          STORE,U   '0',A3              STORE SECOND DIGIT  @C@@@       DB
)@@G@@    J         0,A1                RETURN  @@@@@ @@@@@ @A@@@ .         EDDC
)@@G@@IT A TIME (HH:MM:SS XM) @@@@@ @]@@@ ATIME1$*  . @E@@@ ATIM1$*   LA,U    DD
)@@G@@  A0,0,A0             STRIP OFF THE DATE  @ @@@           LXI,U     X11,DE
)@@G@@'AM'  @C@@@           TLE,U     A0,12*60*60         AM?     @C@@@       DF
)@@G@@    J         ETIM1               YES     @A@@@           ANA,U     A0,1DG
)@@G@@2*60*60     @ @@@           LXI,U     X11,'PM'  @D@@@ ETIM1     DSL     DH
)@@G@@  A0,36               SET UP DIVIDE @D@@@           DI,U      A0,3600   DI
)@@G@@          GET THE HOURS @C@@@           LA,U      A2,,A0              A2DJ
)@@G@@ = A0 @C@@@           LA,U      A0,,A1              A0 = A1 @ @@@       DK
)@@G@@    JNZ       A2,$+2    @ @@@           LA,U      A2,12     @D@@@       DL
)@@G@@    DSL       A2,36               SET UP DIVIDE @ @@@           DI,U    DM
)@@G@@  A2,10     @D@@@           JZ        A2,ETIM2            SKIP IF ZERO  DN
)@@G@@@ @@@           STORE,U   '0',A2    @ @@@ ETIM2     STORE,U   '0',A3    DO
)@@G@@@D@@@           STORE,U   COLON               STORE A COLON @D@@@       DP
)@@G@@    DSL       A0,36               SET UP DIVIDE @G@@@           DI,U    DQ
)@@G@@  A0,60               GET THE MINUTES AND SECONDS     @C@@@           LADR
)@@G@@,U      A2,,A0              A2 = A0 @C@@@           LA,U      A0,,A1    DS
)@@G@@          A0 = A1 @E@@@           LMJ       A1,EDEC             EDIT THEDT
)@@G@@ DIGITS     @D@@@           STORE,U   COLON               STORE A COLON DU
)@@G@@@C@@@           LA,U      A2,,A0              A2 = A0 @E@@@           LMDV
)@@G@@J       A1,EDEC             EDIT THE DIGITS     @ @@@           LA      DW
)@@G@@  A0,X11    @ @@@           SSL       A0,18     @G@@@           LXI,U   DX
)@@G@@  A0,BLANK            LOAD A SPACE BEFORE 'AM' OR 'PM'@D@@@           J DY
)@@G@@        AQW3$               EDIT AM OR PM @@@@@ @B@@@ .         EDIT A DDZ
)@@G@@ATE (FORMAT MM/DD/YY)   @@@@@ @E@@@ ADAY1$*   SSL       A0,18           EA
)@@G@@    GET RID OF THE TIME @D@@@           AND,U     A0,0770000          GEEB
)@@G@@T THE MONTH @D@@@           DSL       A1,48               A2 = MONTH    EC
)@@G@@@E@@@           LMJ       A1,EDEC             EDIT IT TO DECIMAL  @D@@@ ED
)@@G@@          STORE,U   SLASH               STORE A SLASH @D@@@           ANEE
)@@G@@D,U     A0,07700            GET THE DAY   @C@@@           DSL       A1,4EF
)@@G@@2               A2 = DAY@E@@@           LMJ       A1,EDEC             EDEG
)@@G@@IT IT TO DECIMAL  @D@@@           STORE,U   SLASH               STORE A EH
)@@G@@SLASH @D@@@           AND,U     A0,077              A1 = YEAR - 64@D@@@ EI
)@@G@@          AU,U      A1,64               A2 = YEAR     @E@@@           LMEJ
)@@G@@J       A1,EDEC             EDIT IT TO DECIMAL  @C@@@           J       EK
)@@G@@  0,X11               RETURN  @@@@@ @B@@@ .         EDIT A DATE (FORMAT EL
)@@G@@DD MMM YY)  @@@@@ @E@@@ ADAY2$*   SSL       A0,18               GET RID EM
)@@G@@OF THE TIME @D@@@           AND,U     A0,07700            GET THE DAY   EN
)@@G@@@C@@@           DSL       A1,42               A2 = DAY@E@@@           LMEO
)@@G@@J       A1,EDEC             EDIT IT TO DECIMAL  @E@@@           LA      EP
)@@G@@  A1,A0               LOAD THE TDATE$ WORD@D@@@           SSL       A1,1EQ
)@@G@@2               A1 = INDEX    @G@@@           MSI,U     A1,3            ER
)@@G@@    COMPUTE INDEX TO MONTH TABLE    @E@@@           LA        A1,MTAB,A1ES
)@@G@@          GET THE ABBREVIATION@C@@@           LA,U      A3,3            ET
)@@G@@    A3 = 3  @G@@@ EDAY21    LSSC      A1,9                POSITION THE NEU
)@@G@@EXT CHARACTER     @D@@@           AND,U     A1,1*/9-1           GET IT IEV
)@@G@@N A2  @E@@@           STORE     .                   STORE CHARACTER     EW
)@@G@@@D@@@           JGD       A3,EDAY21           LOOP ON A3    @F@@@       EX
)@@G@@    STORE,U   BLANK               PUT A SPACE AFTER MONTH   @D@@@       EY
)@@G@@    AND,U     A0,077              A1 = YEAR     @D@@@           AU,U    EZ
)@@G@@  A1,64               A2 = YEAR     @E@@@           LMJ       A1,EDEC   FA
)@@G@@          EDIT IT TO DECIMAL  @C@@@           J         0,X11           FB
)@@G@@    RETURN  @@@@@ @C@@@ .         EDIT A DATE (FORMAT MONTH DD, YEAR)   FC
)@@G@@@@@@@ @F@@@ ADAY3$*   SX        X11,RET             SAVE THE RETURN POINFD
)@@G@@T     @E@@@           SSL       A0,18               GET RID OF THE TIME FE
)@@G@@@C@@@           SA        A0,R1               SAVE A0 @E@@@           SSFF
)@@G@@L       A0,12               GET MONTH IN A0     @H@@@           MSI,U   FG
)@@G@@  A0,3                COMPUTE INDEX TO MONTH NAME TABLE     @E@@@       FH
)@@G@@    A$QW2     MTAB,A0             EDIT NAME OF MONTH  @F@@@           LAFI
)@@G@@        A0,R1               RESTORE THE TDATE$ WORD   @E@@@           SSFJ
)@@G@@L       A0,12               ISOLATE THE MONTH   @G@@@           MSI,U   FK
)@@G@@  A0,3                COMPUTE INDEX TO MONTH TABLE    @G@@@           A$FL
)@@G@@QW1     MTAB+2,A0           EDIT LAST PART OF MONTH NAME    @D@@@       FM
)@@G@@    STORE,U   BLANK               STORE A BLANK @C@@@           LA      FN
)@@G@@  A1,R1               A1 = R1 @D@@@           AND,U     A1,07700        FO
)@@G@@    GET THE DAY   @E@@@           DSL       A2,42               SET UP TFP
)@@G@@HE DIVIDE   @E@@@           DI,U      A2,10               GET THE TWO DIFQ
)@@G@@GITS  @E@@@           JZ        A2,EDAY31           NO LEADING ZERO     FR
)@@G@@@E@@@           STORE,U   '0',A2              STORE FIRST DIGIT   @E@@@ FS
)@@G@@EDAY31    STORE,U   '0',A3              STORE SECOND DIGIT  @D@@@       FT
)@@G@@    STORE,U   COMMA               STORE A COMMA @D@@@           AND,U   FU
)@@G@@  A1,077              GET THE YEAR  @D@@@           LA,U      A0,1964,A2FV
)@@G@@          A0 = THE YEAR @C@@@           LA,U      A1,5                A1FW
)@@G@@ = 5  @F@@@           LX        X11,RET             RESTORE THE RETURN PFX
)@@G@@OINT  @^@@@           SZ        RET @F@@@           J         ADECF$    FY
)@@G@@          EDIT THE YEAR AND RETURN  @@@@@ @B@@@ .         EDIT A DATE (FFZ
)@@G@@ORMAT YYYYMMDD)   @@@@@ @E@@@ ADAY4$*   SSL       A0,18               GEGA
)@@G@@T RID OF THE TIME @G@@@           AND,U     A0,077              GET THE GB
)@@G@@YEAR (RELATIVE TO 1964) @D@@@           LA,U      A2,1964,A1          A2GC
)@@G@@ = YEAR     @E@@@           DSL       A2,36               SET UP FOR DIVGD
)@@G@@IDE   @G@@@           DI,U      A2,100              A2 = FIRST TWO DIGITGE
)@@G@@S OF YEAR   @G@@@           LR        R1,A3               SAVE SECOND DWGF
)@@G@@O DIGITS OF YEAR  @E@@@           LMJ       A1,EDEC             EDIT TO GG
)@@G@@DECIMAL     @G@@@           LA        A2,R1               A2 = SECOND TWGH
)@@G@@O DIGITS OF YEAR  @E@@@ ADAY41    LMJ       A1,EDEC             EDIT TO GI
)@@G@@DECIMAL     @D@@@           AND,U     A0,0770000          GET THE MONTH GJ
)@@G@@@D@@@           DSL       A1,48               A2 = MONTH    @E@@@       GK
)@@G@@    LMJ       A1,EDEC             EDIT TO DECIMAL     @D@@@           ANGL
)@@G@@D,U     A0,07700            GET THE DAY   @C@@@           DSL       A1,4GM
)@@G@@2               A2 = DAY@E@@@           LMJ       A1,EDEC             EDGN
)@@G@@IT TO DECIMAL     @C@@@           J         0,X11               RETURN  GO
)@@G@@@@@@@ @B@@@ .         EDIT A DATE (FORMAT YYMMDD)     @@@@@ @E@@@ ADAY5$GP
)@@G@@*   SSL       A0,18               GET RID OF THE TIME @G@@@           ANGQ
)@@G@@D,U     A0,077              GET THE YEAR (RELATIVE TO 1964) @D@@@       GR
)@@G@@    LA,U      A2,64,A1            A2 = YEAR     @D@@@           TG,U    GS
)@@G@@  A2,100              3 DIGIT YEAR? @F@@@           ANA,U     A2,100    GT
)@@G@@          YES.  REDUCE TO 2 DIGITS  @D@@@           J         ADAY41    GU
)@@G@@          FINISH EDITING@@@@@ @A@@@ .         EDIT THE DAY OF THE WEEK  GV
)@@G@@@@@@@ @E@@@ ADAYW$*   SSL       A0,18               GET RID OF TIME     GW
)@@G@@@D@@@           AND,U     A0,077              AND OFF YEAR  @D@@@       GX
)@@G@@    LA,U      A3,64,A1            A3 = YEAR     @E@@@           SA      GY
)@@G@@  A3,RET              SAVE IT FOR NOW     @F@@@           SSL       A3,2GZ
)@@G@@                GET NUMBER OF LEAP YEARS  @E@@@           LA        A2,AHA
)@@G@@0               MOVE DATE TO A2     @D@@@           LA        A0,RET    HB
)@@G@@          RELOAD YEAR   @F@@@           MSI,U     A0,365              MUHC
)@@G@@LTIPLY BY NORMAL LENGTH @F@@@           AA,U      A0,1,A3             ACHD
)@@G@@COUNT FOR LEAP YEARS    @D@@@           DSL       A2,12               A2HE
)@@G@@ = MONTH    @C@@@           SSL       A3,36-6             A3 = DAY@H@@@ HF
)@@G@@          AA        A0,MONTH-1,A2       ADD ON NUMBER OF DAYS SO FAR THIHG
)@@G@@S YEAR@F@@@           AA,U      A0,FUDGE,A3         COMPENSATE FOR HISTOHH
)@@G@@RY    @E@@@           LA        A1,RET              GET THE YEAR BACK   HI
)@@G@@@^@@@           TOP,U     A1,1@^@@@           TEP,U     A1,3@^@@@       HJ
)@@G@@    J         $+3 @^@@@           TLE,U     A2,3@^@@@           ANA,U   HK
)@@G@@  A0,1@I@@@           DSL       A0,35               SHIFT FOR DIVIDE, COHL
)@@G@@MPENSATE FOR LENGTH     @F@@@           DI,U      A0,14               DIHM
)@@G@@VIDE BY DAYS PER WEEK   @E@@@           SX        X11,RET             SAHN
)@@G@@VE RETURN POINT   @F@@@           A$QW2     DTAB,A1             EDIT FIRHO
)@@G@@ST PART OF DAY    @F@@@           LX        X11,RET             LOAD RETHP
)@@G@@URN POINT BACK    @F@@@           SZ        RET                 MARK NO HQ
)@@G@@RETURN STORED     @F@@@           LA        A0,('DAY'+'   ')    LOAD 'DAHR
)@@G@@Y' (LOWER CASE)   @E@@@           J         AQW1$               APPEND THS
)@@G@@O DAY NAME  @@@@@ @^@@@ .         MONTH TABLE   @@@@@ @^@@@ MTAB      EQHT
)@@G@@U       $-3 @@@@@ @^@@@ P         PROC      1,3 @^@@@ MNAME*    NAME    HU
)@@G@@  0   @E@@@           +         P(1,1)+040000040040 FIRST THREE LETTERS HV
)@@G@@@F@@@ P(1,2)    EQU       P(1,2)+0D           CHANGE TO DOUBLE WORD     HW
)@@G@@@ @@@ I         DO        8 , ;     @G@@@           DO        (P(1,2)**(HX
)@@G@@0777D*/((I-1)*9)))>(0100D*/((I-1)*9)) ,;  @C@@@ P(1,2)    EQU       P(1,HY
)@@G@@2)+(040D*/((I-1)*9))    @ @@@           +         P(1,2)    @#@@@       HZ
)@@G@@    END     @@@@@ @A@@@           MNAME     'JAN','UARY'    @A@@@       IA
)@@G@@    MNAME     'FEB','RUARY'   @ @@@           MNAME     'MAR','CH'@ @@@ IB
)@@G@@          MNAME     'APR','IL'@ @@@           MNAME     'MAY',' ' @ @@@ IC

)@@G@@BER'  @A@@@           MNAME     'OCT','OBER'    @A@@@           MNAME   IF

)@@G@@@^@@@ .         DAY TABLE     @@@@@ @^@@@ DW        FORM      72  @@@@@ IH
)@@G@@@ @@@ DTAB      DW        'SUN'+'  '@ @@@           DW        'MON'+'  'II
)@@G@@@A@@@           DW        'TUES'+'   '    @A@@@           DW        'WEDIJ

)@@G@@.         TABLE OF CUMULATIVE DAY COUNT BY MONTHS     @@@@@ @F@@@ .     IM
)@@G@@    THIRTY DAYS HAVE SEPTEMBER, APRIL, JUNE, AND NOVEMBER   @^@@@ M$(4) IN
)@@G@@    EQU       30  @^@@@ M$(6)     EQU       30  @^@@@ M$(9)     EQU     IO
)@@G@@  30  @^@@@ M$(11)    EQU       30  @B@@@ .         ALL THE REST HAVE THIP

)@@G@@TA WORD FOR PRINT$@C@@@^FPRT1     EQUF      FDTDW,,S2           SPACING PU

)@@G@@    EDIT$/ADIT$ EDITING / SCANNING PACKAGE@@@@@@@@@@@@@D@@@@.         FLQF
)@@G@@OATING POINT NUMBER SCANNING SUBROUTINES  @@@@@@@@@@@@@G@@@@.           QG
)@@G@@                            JOHN WALKER   SEPTEMBER 1977    @@@@@@@G@@@@QH
)@@G@@.         THIS  ELEMENT  CONTAINS  SUBROUTINES  THAT ALLOW THE USER TO  QI
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         SCAN STRINGS OF FIELDATA AND ASCII  CHARACTERS  REPRESENQJ
)@@G@@TING  @G@@@@.         FLOATING  POINT  NUMBERS.   THE  FIRST  LINE  OF TQK
)@@G@@HE ELEMENT  @G@@@@.         DETERMINES WHETHER THIS ELEMENT IS  TO  HANDQL
)@@G@@LE  FIELDATA  OR  @G@@@@.         ASCII.   IF  ASCII  IS  SET  TO  ONE, QM
)@@G@@ THE ELEMENT ADIT$U IS  @G@@@@.         GENERATED FOR THE ADIT$ PACKAGE.QN
)@@G@@  IF IT IS SET TO ZERO,  THE  @G@@@@.         ELEMENT  EDIT$U  IS  GENERQO
)@@G@@ATED FOR THE EDIT$ PACKAGE.  THESE  @G@@@@.         ROUTINES FOLLOW ALL QP
)@@G@@ THE  EDIT$  /  ADIT$  CALLING  SEQUENCE  @G@@@@.         CONVENTIONS.  QQ
)@@G@@NOTE THAT THE LONG PACKET REQUIRED FOR EDITING  @G@@@@.         FLOATINGQR
)@@G@@ POINT NUMBERS IS ALSO REQUIRED FOR  SCANNING  THEM,  @G@@@@.         ANQS
)@@G@@D  THAT THE FIELDS 'SPC' AND 'DPC' ARE SIGNIFICANT TO THIS  @G@@@@.     QT
)@@G@@    ROUTINE.  IN ADDITION, THE FIELD 'EXP', WHICH IS S4  OF  THE  @G@@@@QU
)@@G@@.         SIXTH WORD OF THE PACKET FOR EDIT$ AND S4 OF THE EIGHTH WORD  QV
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         OF THE PACKET FOR ADIT$, DETERMINES WHETHER EXPONENTS ARQW
)@@G@@E TO  @G@@@@.         BE  SCANNED.   IF  LEFT  ZERO,  EXPONENTS  WILL  BQX
)@@G@@E  SCANNED  @G@@@@.         NORMALLY.   SETTING  THE  FIELD  NONZERO  WIQY
)@@G@@LL  INHIBIT  THE  @A@@@@.         SCANNING OF EXPONENTS.    @[@@@@.     QZ
)@@G@@@C@@@@.         THE FORMAT OF NUMBERS SCANNED IS:     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@RA
)@@G@@.                    SD---D.D---DCSEXP    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         WHRB
)@@G@@ERE S IS THE OPTIONAL SIGN, D---D ARE OPTIONAL STRINGS  OF  @G@@@@.     RC
)@@G@@    DIGITS, C IS THE OPTIONAL EXPONENT DELIMITER CHARACTER, S IS  @G@@@@RD
)@@G@@.         THE OPTIONAL EXPONENT SIGN, AND EXP  IS  THE  EXPONENT.   AT  RE
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         LEAST ONE DIGIT MUST APPEAR BEFORE THE EXPONENT.  @[@@@@RF
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         IN  EACH OF THE ROUTINE DESCRIPTIONS GIVEN BELOW, RG
)@@G@@THE LETTER  @G@@@@.         'J' WILL MEAN 'C' IF THE TAG ASCII IS SET TORH
)@@G@@ 1  AND  'U'  IF  @^@@@@.         SET TO ZERO.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     RI
)@@G@@    JFP$      SCAN A SINGLE  PRECISION  FLOATING  POINT  NUMBER.  @G@@@@RJ
)@@G@@.                   THE NUMBER WILL BE RETURNED IN A1 WITH A0 EQUAL TO  RK
)@@G@@@G@@@@.                   ZERO.  IF THE DOUBLE PRECISION  CHARACTER  APPRL
)@@G@@EARS  @G@@@@.                   BEFORE  THE EXPONENT, OR THE VALUE IS TORM
)@@G@@O LARGE TO  @G@@@@.                   REPRESENT AS A SINGLE PRECISION NURN
)@@G@@MBER,  A  DOUBLE  @F@@@@.                   PRECISION VALUE WILL BE RETURO
)@@G@@RNED IN A0 AND A1.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         JFP2$     SCAN  A  DOUBLE RP
)@@G@@ PRECISION  FLOATING POINT NUMBER.  @G@@@@.                   THE DOUBLERQ
)@@G@@ PRECISION VALUE WILL BE RETURNED IN  A0  @ @@@@.                   AND RR
)@@G@@A1.   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         THIS  PACKAGE  IS A COMPATRS
)@@G@@IBLE REIMPLEMENTATION OF A PACKAGE  @G@@@@.         ORIGINALLY DESIGNED RT
)@@G@@AND  IMPLEMENTED  BY  DAVE  REAM.   THAT  @G@@@@.         PACKAGE  HAD  RU
)@@G@@DIFFICULTY  HANDLING HIGH-PRECISION NUMBERS OR  @G@@@@.         NUMBERS RV
)@@G@@WITH VERY  LARGE  EXPONENTS  AND  WAS  REWRITTEN  TO  @G@@@@.         CORW
)@@G@@RRECT   THESE   PROBLEMS  AND  PROVIDE  THE  MERGED  ASCII  @G@@@@.     RX
)@@G@@    HANDLING.  THIS PACKAGE WAS DESIGNED  TO  SUPPORT  THE  FULL  @G@@@@RY
)@@G@@.         PRECISION  AND  EXPONENT RANGE AVAILABLE ON THE 1100 SERIES,  RZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         WHILE PROVIDING MAXIMUM SPEED AND MINIMUM  ROUND-OFF  ERSA
)@@G@@ROR.  @G@@@@.         THIS  ROUTINE WILL EXHIBIT PERFORMANCE UP TO THIRTSB
)@@G@@Y TIMES AS  @G@@@@.         FAST AS THE PREVIOUS PACKAGE.  ALL DIGIT STRSC
)@@G@@INGS ARE HANDLED  @G@@@@.         AS  DOUBLE-WORD  INTEGERS, WHICH PROVISD
)@@G@@DE TWELVE MORE BITS OF  @G@@@@.         PRECISION THAN  THE  FINAL  RESUSE
)@@G@@LT,  THUS  INSURING  AGAINST  @G@@@@.         ROUND-OFF  ERRORS.   SUPERSF
)@@G@@FLUOUS DIGITS OF PRECISION WILL BE  @G@@@@.         PROPERLY HANDLED, ANSG
)@@G@@D NEVER RESULT IN IMPROPER VALUES  BEING  @^@@@@.         RETURNED.     SH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         THIS ELEMENT ALSO CONTAINS THE 'SI
)@@G@@UNIVERSAL  NUMBER  SCANNER'.  @G@@@@.         THIS  ROUTINE  PERMITS  A SJ
)@@G@@ PROGRAM  TO  SCAN A NUMBER IN ANY  @G@@@@.         FORMAT ACCEPTED BY ASK
)@@G@@NY OF THE  SCANNERS,  AND  DETERMINE  BY  @G@@@@.         SYNTAX  WHAT  SL
)@@G@@KIND  OF  NUMBER  WAS SUPPLIED.  IF THE NUMBER  @G@@@@.         CONTAINSSM
)@@G@@ A DECIMAL POINT OR A VALID  EXPONENT,  IT  WILL  BE  @G@@@@.         SCSN
)@@G@@ANNED  AS  A  FLOATING  POINT NUMBER, OTHERWISE IT WILL BE  @G@@@@.     SO
)@@G@@    SCANNED AS AN  INTEGER.   A  FLOATING-POINT  VALUE  WILL  BE  @G@@@@SP
)@@G@@.         RETURNED  AS  SINGLE-PRECISION  UNLESS  THE DOUBLE PRECISION  SQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         CHARACTER APPEARS IN THE  NUMBER  OR  IT  IS  TOO  LARGESR
)@@G@@  TO  @G@@@@.         REPRESENT  AS  A  SINGLE-PRECISION  VALUE.   NOTE SS
)@@G@@ THAT  THE  @G@@@@.         APPEARANCE  OF  MORE  SIGNIFICANT   DIGITS  ST
)@@G@@ THAN   CAN   BE  @G@@@@.         REPRESENTED  BY  A SINGLE-PRECISION VASU
)@@G@@LUE DOES NOT BY ITSELF  @G@@@@.         FORCE RETURN OF A DOUBLE-PRECISISV
)@@G@@ON  VALUE.   IF  AN  INTEGER  @G@@@@.         CONTAINS  LEADING  ZEROES,SW
)@@G@@  IT  WILL  BE  SCANNED  AS OCTAL,  @G@@@@.         OTHERWISE  DECIMAL. SX
)@@G@@  LEADING  ZEROES  DO  NOT  AFFECT   THE  @G@@@@.         SCANNING OF FLSY
)@@G@@OATING-POINT NUMBERS.  IF THE CHARACTER STRING  @G@@@@.         IS NOT RSZ
)@@G@@ECOGNISABLE AS A NUMBER BY ANY SCANNER, THE  INTEGER  @G@@@@.         RETA
)@@G@@TURN  WILL  BE  TAKEN  WITH  THE VALUE SET TO ZERO AND THE  @G@@@@.     TB
)@@G@@    NUMBER OF  DIGITS  SCANNED  (IN  A3)  ZERO.   THE  UNIVERSAL  @B@@@@TC
)@@G@@.         SCANNER IS CALLED AS FOLLOWS:   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         JNTD
)@@G@@$       SCAN  A  NUMBER  AS  EITHER  A  DECIMAL  OR  OCTAL  @G@@@@.     TE
)@@G@@              INTEGER, OR A SINGLE- OR DOUBLE-PRECISION FLOATING  @G@@@@TF
)@@G@@.                   POINT NUMBER, DEPENDING UPON  THE  SYNTAX  OF  THE  TG
)@@G@@@G@@@@.                   NUMBER  SUPPLIED.   THE  NUMBER  IS RETURNED ITH
)@@G@@N A1  @G@@@@.                   WITH A0 ZERO OR A0 AND A1 DEPENDING  UPOTI
)@@G@@N  WHETHER  @G@@@@.                   IT  IS SINGLE OR DOUBLE PRECISION.TJ
)@@G@@  H1 OF X11 WILL  @G@@@@.                   INDICATE THE TYPE OF NUMBER TK
)@@G@@SCANNED.  IF  ZERO,  A  @G@@@@.                   DOUBLE  FLOATING NUMBETL
)@@G@@R WAS SCANNED.  IF NEGATIVE,  @G@@@@.                   A SINGLE FLOATINTM
)@@G@@G NUMBER WAS FOUND, AND IF ONE  AN  @G@@@@.                   INTEGER  WTN
)@@G@@AS RETURNED.  IF AN INTEGER WAS SCANNED,  @F@@@@.                   A3 WTO
)@@G@@ILL CONTAIN THE NUMBER OF DIGITS SCANNED. @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @@@@@@TP

)@@G@@ FLOATING POINT NUMBER.  NOTE THAT ALL DETERMINATION  @G@@@@.         OFVZ

)@@G@@  A3,JFP$             LOAD FLOATING POINT SCANNER ENTRY     @F@@@@      WC
)@@G@@    J         CNDOIT              GO DO FLOATING POINT SCAN @[@@@@/.    WD
)@@G@@@@@@@@@B@@@@.         FLOATING-POINT SCANNING ROUTINE @@@@@@@ @@@@      WE
)@@G@@    ON        ASCII     @]@@@@JFP$      . @G@@@@CFP$*     LXI,XU    X11,WF
)@@G@@-1              SELECT SINGLE PRECISION RESULT  @F@@@@          J       WG
)@@G@@  CFPCOM              ENTER COMMON SCANNING CODE@[@@@@.     @]@@@@CFP2$*WH
)@@G@@    . @ @@@@          OFF       ASCII     @@@@@@@ @@@@          ON      WI
)@@G@@  1-ASCII   @]@@@@JFP$      . @G@@@@UFP$*     LXI,XU    X11,-1          WJ
)@@G@@    SELECT SINGLE PRECISION RESULT  @F@@@@          J         CFPCOM    WK
)@@G@@          ENTER COMMON SCANNING CODE@[@@@@.     @]@@@@UFP2$*    . @ @@@@WL
)@@G@@          OFF       1-ASCII   @@@@@@@G@@@@          LXI,U     X11,0     WM
)@@G@@          MARK DOUBLE PRECISION REQUESTED @[@@@@.     @G@@@@CFPCOM    SXWN
)@@G@@        X11,RET             SAVE RETURN POINT TO CALLER     @G@@@@      WO
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,JSIGN$          SCAN THE SIGN FOR THE NUMBER    @G@@@@WP
)@@G@@          SZ        BIAS                CLEAR EXPONENT DECIMAL BIAS     WQ
)@@G@@@G@@@           SZ        VALNUM              CLEAR VALID NUMBER FOUND FWR
)@@G@@LAG   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         NOW SCAN THE DIGITS OF THE MANTISSA.  WS
)@@G@@THIS SAME LOOP HANDLES  @G@@@@.         DIGITS BEFORE  AND  AFTER  THE  WT
)@@G@@DECIMAL  POINT.   AFTER  THE  @G@@@@.         DECIMAL  POINT, THE CELL BWU
)@@G@@IAS WILL BE DECREMENTED BY ONE FOR  @G@@@@.         EACH DIGIT SCANNED. WV
)@@G@@ WHEN THE NUMBER IS FINALLY PACKED,  THE  @G@@@@.         BIAS  WILL BE WW
)@@G@@USED TO SCALE THE NUMBER TO ADJUST THE DECIMAL  @B@@@@.         POINT TOWX
)@@G@@ THE PROPER POSITION.   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          SZ        AFTRDP    WY
)@@G@@          MARK NOW BEFORE DECIMAL POINT   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@CFPND     EXWZ
)@@G@@        LOOK                LOOK AT THE NEXT CHARACTER@E@@@@          TGXA
)@@G@@,U      A2,CZERO            IS IT NUMERIC ?     @D@@@@          TG,U    XB
)@@G@@  A2,CZERO+10         WELL, IS IT ? @G@@@@          J         CFPNTN    XC
)@@G@@          NO.  CHECK TERMINATING DELIMITER@I@@@@          EX        LOADXD
)@@G@@                YES.  LOAD CHARACTER AND ADVANCE POINTER    @G@@@       XE
)@@G@@    SA        A2,VALNUM           DIGIT FOUND.  MARK VALID NUMBER @F@@@@XF
)@@G@@          TG        A0,(031463146314)   WILL MANTISSA OVERFLOW ?  @I@@@@XG
)@@G@@          J         CFPOVH              YES.  HANDLE TOO MANY SIGNIFICANXH
)@@G@@T DIGITS    @G@@@@          ANA,U     A2,CZERO            CONVERT CHARACXI
)@@G@@TER TO BINARY     @G@@@@          DS        A0,MAN              SAVE MANXJ
)@@G@@TISSA FOR ADD LATER     @F@@@@          LDSL      A0,2                MUXK
)@@G@@LTIPLY TOTAL BY FOUR    @G@@@@          DA        A0,MAN              ADXL
)@@G@@D TO GET TOTAL TIMES FIVE     @G@@@@          LDSL      A0,1            XM
)@@G@@    MULTIPLY BY TWO TO GET TIMES TEN@H@@@@          DSL       A2,36     XN
)@@G@@          SHIFT DIGIT SCANNED TO DOUBLE WORD    @F@@@@          DA      XO
)@@G@@  A0,A2               ADD LATEST DIGIT TO TOTAL @F@@@@          TNZ     XP
)@@G@@  AFTRDP              AFTER DECIMAL POINT ?     @F@@@@          J       XQ
)@@G@@  CFPND               NO.  KEEP ON SCANNING     @F@@@@          LA      XR
)@@G@@  A2,BIAS             YES.  LOAD EXPONENT BIAS  @F@@@@          ANA,U   XS
)@@G@@  A2,1                DECREMENT IT BY ONE PLACE @E@@@@          SA      XT
)@@G@@  A2,BIAS             UPDATE EXPONENT BIAS@E@@@@          J         CFPNXU
)@@G@@D               KEEP ON SCANNING    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         DELIMITEXV
)@@G@@R FOUND AFTER INITIAL DIGIT STRING.  EXAMINE IT.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@CFPNTNXW
)@@G@@    TNZ       AFTRDP              ALREADY FOUND DECIMAL POINT ?   @F@@@@XX
)@@G@@          TE,U      A2,CPERIOD          NO.  IS THIS THE DECIMAL ?@G@@@@XY
)@@G@@          J         CFPCKE              NO.  CHECK EXPONENT CHARACTER   XZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@          EX        LOAD                YES.  ADVANCE PAST DECIMALYA
)@@G@@ POINT@G@@@@          SA        A2,AFTRDP           SET AFTER DECIMAL POYB
)@@G@@INT FLAG    @F@@@@          J         CFPND               RETURN TO SCANYC
)@@G@@NING LOOP   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         TEST FOR EXPONENT CHARACTER IN NYD
)@@G@@UMBER @[@@@@.     @F@@@@CFPCKE    DS        A0,MAN              SAVE MANYE
)@@G@@TISSA IN PACKET   @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,0                CLEAR EXYF
)@@G@@PONENT VALUE@G@@@@          TZ        EXP                 SUPPRESS SCAN YG
)@@G@@FOR EXPONENT ?    @G@@@@          J         CFPACK              YES.  GOYH
)@@G@@ PACK WHAT WE'VE SCANNED@ @@@^          ON        ASCII     @F@@@#      YI
)@@G@@    TG,U      A2,0140             IS CHARACTER LOWER-CASE ? @G@@@#      YJ
)@@G@@    ANA,U     A2,040              YES.  CONVERT TO UPPER-CASE     @ @@@^YK
)@@G@@          OFF       ASCII     @G@@@@          TNE       A2,SPC          YL
)@@G@@    SINGLE PRECISION EXPONENT CHAR ?@F@@@@          J         CFPSPE    YM
)@@G@@          YES.  GO SCAN EXPONENT    @G@@@@          TNE       A2,DPC    YN
)@@G@@          DOUBLE PRECISION EXPONENT CHAR ?@G@@@@          J         CFPDYO
)@@G@@PE              YES.  FORCE DOUBLE PRECISION    @G@@@@          LMJ     YP
)@@G@@  X11,CXPSIGN         NO.  IS IT A SIGN CHARACTER ?   @F@@@@          J YQ
)@@G@@        CFPACK              NO.  PACK NUMBER SO FAR   @H@@@C          EXYR
)@@G@@        LOAD                YES.  ADVANCE PAST SIGN CHARACTER     @G@@@CYS
)@@G@@          EX        LOOK                LOAD THE CHARACTER AFTER IT     YT
)@@G@@@G@@@C          J         CFBKUP              TEST NUMERIC.  BACK UP IF YU
)@@G@@NOT   @G@C@@          EX        LOAD                YES.  LOAD THE SIGN YV
)@@G@@CHARACTER   @G@C@@          EX        LOOK                AND GET THE CHYW
)@@G@@ARACTER AFTER IT  @E@C@@          J         CFPEXS              GO SCAN YX
)@@G@@THE EXPONENT@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         DOUBLE  PRECISION  EXPONENT  CHAYY
)@@G@@RACTER  ENCOUNTERED.   FORCE  @F@@@@.         DOUBLE PRECISION RESULT REYZ
)@@G@@GARDLESS OF ENTRY CALLED.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@CFPDPE    LXI,U     X11,ZA
)@@G@@0               FORCE DOUBLE PRECISION RESULT   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     ZB
)@@G@@    SINGLE PRECISION EXPONENT CHARACTER ENCOUNTERED.  THE TYPE OF @G@@@@ZC
)@@G@@.         THE NUMBER RETURNED WILL REMAIN GOVERNED BY THE TYPE OF THE   ZD
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         CALL MADE BY THE USER.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@CFPSPE    EXZE
)@@G@@        LOAD                ADVANCE PAST EXPONENT CHARACTER @F@@@@      ZF
)@@G@@    EX        LOOK                LOOK AT NEXT CHARACTER    @F@@@@      ZG
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,CXPSIGN         LOOK FOR AN EXPONENT SIGN @F@@@@      ZH
)@@G@@    J         CFBKUP              NONE.  BACK UP TO NUMBER  @F@C@@      ZI
)@@G@@    EX        LOAD                FOUND.  SKIP PAST SIGN    @F@@@C      ZJ
)@@G@@    EX        LOAD                FOUND.  SKIP PAST SIGN    @G@@@@      ZK
)@@G@@    EX        LOOK                LOOK AT CHARACTER AFTER SIGN    @E@@@@ZL
)@@G@@          TG,U      A2,CZERO            IS IT NUMERIC ?     @D@@@@      ZM
)@@G@@    TG,U      A2,CZERO+10         WELL, IS IT ? @G@@@@          J       ZN
)@@G@@  CFBKUP2             NO.  PREVIOUS CHAR WASN'T REALLY@G@@@@.           ZO
)@@G@@                            EXPONENT DELIMITER AFTER ALL !  @[@@@@.     ZP
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         NOW SCAN THE EXPONENT.    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@CFPEXS    LAZQ
)@@G@@,U      A0,0                CLEAR EXPONENT VALUE@G@@@           TZ      ZR
)@@G@@  VALNUM              VALID NUMBER BEFORE EXPONENT ?  @F@@@           J ZS
)@@G@@        CSEXP               YES.  GO SCAN EXPONENT    @[@@@ .     @F@A@ ZT
)@@G@@$$$$$ >> TEXT MOVED FROM HERE TO Z$F.A BY RJEND COMMAND << $$$$$  @G@@@AZU
)@@G@@.         THE EXPONENT IS ALL THERE  IS  TO  THIS  NUMBER.   ASSUME  A  ZV
)@@G@@@ @@@A.         MANTISSA OF ONE.    @[@@@ .     @F@@@           LA,U    ZW
)@@G@@  A2,1                LOAD ONE FOR MANTISSA     @G@@@           SA      ZX
)@@G@@  A2,MAN+1            SET IN LOW WORD OF MANTISSA     @F@@@           SAZY
)@@G@@        A2,VALNUM           MARK VALID NUMBER FOUND   @F@@@@CSEXP     EXZZ
)@@G@@        LOOK                LOOK AT NEXT CHARACTER    @E@@@@          TGAA
)@@G@@,U      A2,CZERO            IS IT A NUMBER ?    @F@@@@          TG,U    AB
)@@G@@  A2,CZERO+10         IS IT REALLY NUMERIC ?    @E@@@@          J       AC
)@@G@@  CSEXPE              NO.  END OF EXPONENT@F@@@@          EX        LOADAD
)@@G@@                YES.  LOAD THE NEXT DIGIT @G@@@@          ANA,U     A2,CAE
)@@G@@ZERO            SUBTRACT THE CHARACTER BIAS     @F@@@@          MSI,U   AF
)@@G@@  A0,10               MULTIPLY TOTAL BY TEN     @E@@@@          AA      AG
)@@G@@  A0,A2               ADD IN THE NEW DIGIT@F@@@@          J         CSEXAH
)@@G@@P               CONTINUE SCANNING EXPONENT@[@@@@.     @F@@@@CSEXPE    TZAI
)@@G@@        XPSIGN              WAS EXPONENT NEGATIVE ?   @G@@@@          LNAJ
)@@G@@A       A0,A0               YES.  COMPLEMENT EXPONENT SIGN  @[@@@@.     AK
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         NOW  WE  ADD  THE  BIAS  WHICH  WAS  SET  WHILE SCANNINGAL
)@@G@@ THE  @G@@@@.         MANTISSA.  THE BIAS IS A NEGATIVE NUMBER EQUAL TO AM
)@@G@@THE NUMBER  @G@@@@.         OF DIGITS FOLLOWING THE DECIMAL POINT.  SUBTAN
)@@G@@RACTING THE BIAS  @G@@@@.         FROM THE DECIMAL EXPONENT RESULTS IN SAO
)@@G@@CALING THE  NUMBER  TO  @G@@@@.         PLACE  THE  DECIMAL POINT IN THEAP
)@@G@@ RESULT AT THE SAME PLACE IT  @G@@@@.         APPEARED IN THE INPUT TEXTAQ
)@@G@@ (WHICH RESULT IS MUCH APPRECIATED  @^@@@@.         BY THE USER). @[@@@@AR
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@CFPACK    AA        A0,BIAS             ADD IN DECIMAL POSITAS
)@@G@@ION BIAS    @F@@@@          SA        A0,BIAS             SAVE FOR POST-AT
)@@G@@PACK SCALING@F@@@@          DLSC      A0,MAN              NORMALISE THE AU
)@@G@@MANTISSA    @F@@@@          DJZ       A0,CFZMAN           SKIP EVERYTHINAV
)@@G@@G IF ZERO   @G@@@@          DSL       A0,11               SHIFT TO MAKE AW
)@@G@@ROOM FOR EXPONENT @G@@@@          LA,U      A3,02000+71         LOAD EXPAX
)@@G@@ONENT VALUE FOR NUMBER  @H@@@@          ANA       A3,A2               SUAY
)@@G@@BTRACT PLACES SHIFTED TO NORMALISE  @G@@@@          LDSL      A2,72-12  AZ
)@@G@@          LEFT JUSTIFY EXPONENT IN A2, A3 @F@@@@          DA        A0,ABA
)@@G@@2               FORM BASE FLOATING NUMBER @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         WEBB
)@@G@@  NOW  HAVE  A FLOATING-POINT NUMBER IN A0 AND A2 EQUAL TO  @G@@@@.     BC
)@@G@@    THE INTEGER MANTISSA IGNORING THE  DECIMAL  POINT.   NOW  WE  @G@@@@BD
)@@G@@.         MUST APPLY THE DECIMAL EXPONENT, INCLUDING ANY BIAS TO PLACE  BE
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         THE DECIMAL POINT IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NUMBER.    @[@@@@BF
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@          LMA       A2,BIAS             LOAD ABSOLUTE VALUE BG
)@@G@@OF EXPONENT @H@@@@          LA,U      A3,0                CLEAR POWERS OBH
)@@G@@F TEN TABLE POINTER     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         SHIFT  OFF THE EXPONBI
)@@G@@ENT AND MULTIPLY THE NUMBER BY POWERS OF  @E@@@@.         TEN CORRESPONDBJ
)@@G@@ING TO BITS SET IN THE EXPONENT.    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@CFPTEN    JNB     BK
)@@G@@  A2,CFPTENX          SKIP IF THIS BIT NOT SET  @E@@@@          TN      BL
)@@G@@  BIAS                POSITIVE EXPONENT ? @G@@@@          DFM       A0,PBM
)@@G@@TENP,A3         YES.  MULTIPLY BY SCALE FACTOR  @E@@@@          TP      BN
)@@G@@  BIAS                NEGATIVE EXPONENT ? @G@@@@          DFD       A0,PBO
)@@G@@TENP,A3         YES.  DIVIDE BY SCALE FACTOR    @H@@@@CFPTENX   SSL     BP
)@@G@@  A2,1                SHIFT NEXT EXPONENT BIT TO LOW-ORDER  @G@@@@      BQ
)@@G@@    AA,U      A3,2                ADVANCE POINTER TO POWERS OF TEN@F@@@@BR
)@@G@@          JNZ       A2,CFPTEN           CONTINUE IF MORE BITS SET @[@@@@BS
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@.         RETURN THE VALUE TO THE CALLER IN THE FORMAT REQUEBT
)@@G@@STED. @[@@@@.     @G@B@A          LA        A3,VALNUM           RETURN VBU
)@@G@@ALID NUMBER FLAG IN A3  @G@@@@          TN        X11                 SIBV
)@@G@@NGLE PRECISION REQUESTED ?    @G@B@@          J         JFINI$          BW
)@@G@@    NO.  RETURN DOUBLE PRECISION    @G@@@B          J         CFPOUT    BX
)@@G@@          NO.  RETURN DOUBLE PRECISION    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         WEBY
)@@G@@'RE  ABOUT TO COMPRESS THE DOUBLE-PRECISION QUANTITY WE'VE  @G@@@@.     BZ
)@@G@@    SCANNED TO THE  SINGLE-PRECISION  RESULT  REQUESTED  BY  THE  @G@@@@CA
)@@G@@.         USER.   FIRST  CHECK  WHETHER  COMPRESSING IT WOULD CAUSE AN  CB
)@@G@@@D@@@@.         OVERFLOW FAULT.  IF SO, GO HANDLE SPECIALLY.@[@@@@.     CC
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA        A2,A0               LOAD FIRST WORD OF RESULT CD
)@@G@@@G@@@@          SSL       A2,24               RIGHT JUSTIFY THE CHARACTECE
)@@G@@RISTIC@F@@@@          TLE,U     A2,02200            IS EXPONENT TOO BIG CF
)@@G@@?     @F@@@@          TLE,U     A2,01600            NO.  IS IT TOO SMALLCG
)@@G@@ ?    @G@@@@          J         CFPDPEX             YES.  HANDLER OVERFLCH
)@@G@@OW OF SINGLE@H@@@@          FCL       A1,A0               NO.  COMPRESS CI
)@@G@@TO SINGLE PRECISION     @H@B@@          LA,U      A0,0                LOCJ
)@@G@@AD ZERO TO INDICATE DOUBLE FORMAT   @H@@@B          LA,U      A0,0      CK
)@@G@@          LOAD ZERO TO INDICATE SINGLE FORMAT   @G@@@BCFPOUT    LA      CL
)@@G@@  A3,VALNUM           RETURN VALID NUMBER FLAG IN A3  @F@@@@          J CM
)@@G@@        JFINI$              RETURN THE VALUE TO CALLER@[@@@@.     @[@@@@CN
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         WE  GET  HERE  AFTER  LOOKING  FOR A SIGN AFTER THCO
)@@G@@E EXPONENT  @G@@@@.         CHARACTER (SPC OR DPC) AND FINDING SOME OTHECP
)@@G@@R CHARACTER.  IF  @G@@@@.         THE  CHARACTER IS NUMERIC, THIS IS AN CQ
)@@G@@UNSIGNED EXPONENT, AND  @G@@@@.         WE GO TO SCAN IT (CXPSIGN WILL HCR
)@@G@@AVE FLAGGED IT  AS  POSITIVE  @G@@@@.         ALREADY).  IF IT'S SOME OTCS
)@@G@@HER CHARACTER, WE ASSUME THE WHOLE  @G@@@@.         EXPONENT CONSTRUCTIOCT
)@@G@@N WAS UNWANTED, AND WE BACK UP  SO  THAT  @G@@@@.         THE  TERMINATICU
)@@G@@NG  DELIMITER  WILL  BE THE EXPONENT CHARACTER  @#@@@@.         ITSELF. CV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@CFBKUP    TG,U      A2,CZERO            IS CHARACTER NCW
)@@G@@UMERIC ?    @D@@@@          TG,U      A2,CZERO+10         WELL, IS IT ? CX
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         $+2                 NO.  RETURN ZERO EXPONENT CY
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         CFPEXS              YES.  GO SCAN THE EXPONENTCZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          LA,XU     A0,-1               LOAD COUNT TO BACK UP     DA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@CFBKUPN   . @G@@@@          LMJ       X11,JSKIP$      DB
)@@G@@    BACK UP TO EXPONENT CHARACTER   @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,0      DC
)@@G@@          SET EXPONENT TO ZERO@F@@@@          J         CFPACK          DD
)@@G@@    GO PACK AND RETURN RESULT @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         WE GET HERE UPDE
)@@G@@ON DISCOVERING THAT THE CHARACTER FOLLOWING AN  @G@@@@.         EXPONENTDF
)@@G@@ SIGN WAS NOT A NUMBER.  WHEN THIS HAPPENS, WE  BACK  @G@@@@.         UPDG
)@@G@@  TO  THE  EXPONENT  CHARACTER  (TWO  BACK) AND RETURN THE  @B@@@@.     DH
)@@G@@    NUMBER WITH A ZERO EXPONENT.    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@CFBKUP2   LA,XU   DI
)@@G@@  A0,-2               LOAD BACK UP COUNT  @D@@@@          J         CFBKDJ
)@@G@@UPN             GO BACK UP TWO@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         MADK
)@@G@@NTISSA WAS ZERO.  RETURN A TRUE ZERO TO THE CALLER.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@DL
)@@G@@CFZRET    DSL       A0,72               ENTER HERE TO RETURN ZERO @F@B@@DM
)@@G@@CFZMAN    J         JFINI$              RETURN ZERO TO CALLER     @F@@@BDN
)@@G@@CFZMAN    J         CFPOUT              RETURN ZERO TO CALLER     @[@@@@DO
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         WE  GET  HERE  UPON  DISCOVERING  THAT  THE  MANTIDP
)@@G@@SSA  WOULD  @G@@@@.         OVERFLOW ON THE MULTIPLY DONE IN  ACCUMULATIDQ
)@@G@@NG  THIS  DIGIT.  @G@@@@.         THIS  INDICATES  THAT  MORE  SIGNIFICADR
)@@G@@NT  DIGITS  HAVE  BEEN  @G@@@@.         SUPPLIED THAN CAN BE REPRESENTEDDS
)@@G@@ IN A  DOUBLE-WORD  INTEGER.  @G@@@@.         SINCE  A  DOUBLE-WORD  INTDT
)@@G@@EGER HAS 12 MORE BITS OF PRECISION  @G@@@@.         THAN A DOUBLE PRECISDU
)@@G@@ION FLOATING  POINT  NUMBER,  THE  EXTRA  @G@@@@.         PRECISION WILLDV
)@@G@@ BE LOST WHEN WE PACK THE NUMBER ANYWAY.  WHAT  @G@@@@.         WE DO INDW
)@@G@@ THIS CASE DEPENDS UPON WHAT  SIDE  OF  THE  DECIMAL  @G@@@@.         PODX
)@@G@@INT  WE'RE  ON.   IF  WE'RE  STILL  BEFORE THE DECIMAL, WE  @G@@@@.     DY
)@@G@@    INCREMENT THE EXPONENT BIAS BY ONE  FOR  EACH  DIGIT.   THIS  @G@@@@DZ
)@@G@@.         ACCUMULATES THE DIGIT AS A ZERO, PRESERVING THE PRECISION OF  EA
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         THE MORE SIGNIFICANT DIGITS.  IF WE'RE AFTER THE DECIMALEB
)@@G@@, WE  @G@@@@.         JUST  DISCARD  THE  DIGIT,  AS IT HAS NO CONTRIBUTEC
)@@G@@ION TO THE  @ @@@@.         VALUE OF THE NUMBER.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@CFPOVHED
)@@G@@    TZ        AFTRDP              AFTER THE DECIMAL POINT ? @G@@@@      EE
)@@G@@    J         CFPND               YES.  TOTALLY IGNORE THE DIGIT  @F@@@@EF
)@@G@@          LA        A2,BIAS             NO.  LOAD EXPONENT BIAS   @F@@@@EG
)@@G@@          AA,U      A2,1                INCLUDE AS A POWER OF TEN @E@@@@EH
)@@G@@          SA        A2,BIAS             UPDATE EXPONENT BIAS@E@@@@      EI
)@@G@@    J         CFPND               GO GET NEXT DIGIT   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@EJ
)@@G@@.         THIS  CODE  HANDLES  A POTENTIAL OVERFLOW OR UNDERFLOW FAULT  EK
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         WHEN COMPRESSING A VALUE SCANNED TO RETURN TO THE CALLEREL
)@@G@@  AS  @G@@@@.         A SINGLE PRECISION NUMBER.  IF THE ERROR IS AN UNDEM
)@@G@@ERFLOW, WE  @G@@@@.         RETURN ZERO TO THE CALLER.  IF THE ERROR IS EN
)@@G@@AN OVERFLOW,  WE  @G@@@@.         ACTUALLY  RETURN  THE UNREPRESENTABLE EO
)@@G@@DOUBLE-PRECISION VALUE  @G@@@@.         TO THE CALLER, CLEARING H1 OF X1EP
)@@G@@1 TO INDICATE WHAT WE DID.    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@CFPDPEX   TLE,U     A2,0EQ
)@@G@@2000            IS THE PROBLEM UNDERFLOW ?@G@@@@          J         CFZRER
)@@G@@ET              YES.  RETURN ZERO TO CALLER     @I@@@@          LXI,U   ES
)@@G@@  X11,0               NO.  INDICATE DOUBLE PRECISION RETURNED     @F@B@@ET
)@@G@@          J         JFINI$              RETURN RESULT TO CALLER   @F@@@BEU
)@@G@@          J         CFPOUT              RETURN RESULT TO CALLER   @[@@@@EV
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         SCAN SIGN OF EXPONENT     @[@@@@.     EW
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         LA,U      A2,<CHARACTER>  @A@@@@.         LMJ       X11,EX
)@@G@@CXPSIGN     @ @@@@.         <NOT A SIGN RETURN> @F@@@@.         <SIGN REEY
)@@G@@TURN>                 XPSIGN NONZERO IF NEGATIVE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@CXPSIGEZ
)@@G@@N   SZ        XPSIGN              CLEAR EXPONENT SIGN FLAG  @E@@@@      FA
)@@G@@    TNE,U     A2,CPLUS            IS IT A PLUS SIGN ? @G@@@@          J FB
)@@G@@        1,X11               YES.  RETURN WITH XPSIGN ZERO   @E@@@@      FC
)@@G@@    TE,U      A2,CMINUS           IS IT A MINUS SIGN ?@F@@@@          J FD
)@@G@@        0,X11               NO.  NO SIGN ON EXPONENT  @E@@@@          SAFE
)@@G@@        A2,XPSIGN           SET SIGN ON EXPONENT@F@@@@          J       FF
)@@G@@  1,X11               TAKE SIGN FOUND RETURN    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     FG
)@@G@@@@@@@@@B@@@@.         POSITIVE FLOATING POWERS OF TEN @@@@@@@@@@@@@^@@@@FH

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@@@@@@@@@@@@@A@@@@.         ADIT$ EDITING PACKAGE     @@@@@@YF
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@ @@@@.         INTERNAL DEFINITIONS@@@@@@@#@@@@      YG
)@@G@@    DEF     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         IF ALL OUTPUT IS TO BE GENERATEDYH
)@@G@@ WITH EVEN PARITY, THE  @F@@@@.         TAG 'PARGEN' SHOULD BE SET NONZEYI
)@@G@@RO.  OTHERWISE, PARITY  @F@@@@.         WILL NOT BE CHANGED, AND CANNED YJ
)@@G@@CHARACTERS WILL HAVE    @^@@@@.         RANDOM PARITY.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@YK
)@@G@@PARGEN    EQU       0                   DISABLE PARITY GENERATION @[@@@@YL
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.         IF THE PARITY BIT IS TO BE STRIPPED OFF CHARACTERSYM
)@@G@@ PASSED     @F@@@@.         TO ADIT$, THE TAG 'PARSTRIP' SHOULD BE SET NYN
)@@G@@ONZERO.     @G@@@@.         OTHERWISE, CHARACTERS WILL BE STORED WITH WHYO
)@@G@@ATEVER PARITY     @F@@@@.         BIT THEY WERE PASSED WITH.  NOTE THAT YP
)@@G@@IF PARGEN IS SET  @F@@@@.         NONZERO, PARSTRIP MUST BE SET NONZERO YQ
)@@G@@ALSO UNLESS ALL   @E@@@@.         CHARACTERS PASSED TO ADIT$ HAVE A ZEROYR
)@@G@@ PARITY BIT.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@PARSTRIP  EQU       0                   DIYS
)@@G@@SABLE PARITY STRIPPING  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         THE TAG 'SIXBIT' CONYT
)@@G@@TROLS GENERATION OF THE LITTLE-USED SIXBIT@H@@@@.         ASCII SUBROUTIYU
)@@G@@NES IN ADIT$.  IF SET TO ZERO, ALL CODE ASSOCIATED    @G@@@@.         WIYV
)@@G@@TH THE SIXBIT ROUTINES WILL BE TURNED OFF, AND CALLS TO THEM@C@@@@.     YW
)@@G@@    WILL RESULT IN UNDEFINED SYMBOLS.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@SIXBIT    EQYX
)@@G@@U       0                   TURN OFF SIXBIT ASCII     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@YY
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@PX        EQU       X1                  PACKET POINTER@E@@@@YZ
)@@G@@CX        EQU       X2                  CHARACTER POINTER   @D@@@@WX    ZA
)@@G@@    EQU       X3                  WORD POINTER  @@@@@@@E@@@@PKT       EQZB
)@@G@@UF      0,PX                PACKET LOCATION     @E@@@@CI        EQUF    ZC
)@@G@@  0,CX                CHARACTER INDEX     @D@@@@WI        EQUF      0,WXZD
)@@G@@                WORD INDEX    @@@@@@@D@@@@IL        EQUF      PKT,,Q2   ZE
)@@G@@          IMAGE LENGTH  @D@@@@ILOC      EQUF      PKT,,H2             IMZF
)@@G@@AGE LOCATION@G@@@@CIX       EQUF      PKT+1,,Q2           SAVE AREA FOR ZG
)@@G@@CHARACTER INDEX   @F@@@@WIX       EQUF      PKT+1,,H2           SAVE AREZH
)@@G@@A FOR WORD INDEX  @F@@@@EMSGC     EQUF      PKT+2,,Q1           AMSG$ SIZI
)@@G@@GNAL CHARACTER    @H@@@@CIM       EQUF      PKT+2,,Q2           SAVE AREZJ
)@@G@@A FOR AMSG$ CHARACTER INDEX   @G@@@@WIM       EQUF      PKT+2,,H2       ZK
)@@G@@    SAVE AREA FOR AMSG$ WORD INDEX  @G@@@@FPS       EQUF      PKT+3,,S1 ZL
)@@G@@          SCALE FOR FLOATING POINT EDIT   @G@@@@FPR       EQUF      PKT+ZM
)@@G@@3,,S2           FLOATING POINT ROUNDING OPTION  @F@@@@RETURN    EQUF    ZN
)@@G@@  PKT+3               RETURN POINT FOR VECTORS  @F@@@@RET       EQUF    ZO
)@@G@@  PKT+4,,H1           SAVE AREA FOR RETURN POINT@E@@@@SAVE1     EQUF    ZP
)@@G@@  PKT+4,,H2           SAVE AREA FOR PX    @E@@@@SAVE2     EQUF      PKT+ZQ
)@@G@@5               SAVE AREA FOR CX    @E@@@@SAVE3     EQUF      PKT+6     ZR
)@@G@@          SAVE AREA FOR WX    @H@@@@DPC       EQUF      PKT+7,,Q1       ZS
)@@G@@    CHARACTER FOR DOUBLE PRECISION SCALE  @H@@@@SPC       EQUF      PKT+ZT
)@@G@@7,,Q2           CHARACTER FOR SINGLE PRECISION SCALE  @G@@@@NDP       EQZU
)@@G@@UF      PKT+8,,S3           DIGITS BEFORE DECIMAL POINT     @G@@@@NDF   ZV
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+8,,S4           DIGITS FOLLOWING DECIMAL POINT  @D@@@@ZW
)@@G@@SIGN      EQUF      PKT+8,,S5           SIGN INDICATOR@G@@@@ZERO      EQZX
)@@G@@UF      PKT+8,,S6           FLOATING POINT ZERO INDICATOR   @E@@@@FCOL  ZY
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+9,,H1           FINAL COLUMN OR ZERO@D@@@@SCALE     EQZZ
)@@G@@UF      PKT+9,,XH2          POWER OF TEN  @E@@@@VALUE     EQUF      PKT+AA
)@@G@@10              SAVE AREA FOR DIGITS@@@@@@@^@@@@A$DEF*    PROC      *0  AB
)@@G@@@#@@@@$(1)      LIT     @^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @#@@@@STORE**   NAAC
)@@G@@ME    @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,P(0,1) A2,+(A$AD 1,1) @ @@@@AD
)@@G@@          EX        ADIT$T,*CX@#@@@@          END     @ @@@@P         PRAE
)@@G@@OC      1,2*PARGEN@#@@@@PARITY**  NAME    @ @@@@          ON        PARGAF
)@@G@@EN    @B@@@@          DO        P(1)=0 ,P(1,1) EQU A2 @A@@@@          TEAG
)@@G@@P,U     P(1,1),1*/7-1   @A@@@@          AA,U      P(1,1),1*/7     @ @@@@AH
)@@G@@          OFF       PARGEN    @#@@@@          END     @#@@@@          A$AI
)@@G@@SCII  @ @@@@NULL*     EQU       NULL7     @^@@@@BLANK*    EQU       SPC7AJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@BLANKS*   EQU       +(BLANK,BLANK,BLANK,BLANK)  @^@@@@MINUS*    EQAK
)@@G@@U       DSH7@^@@@@PLUS*     EQU       PLS7@^@@@@ZER*      EQU       A07 AL
)@@G@@@^@@@@COLON*    EQU       CLN7@^@@@@COMMA*    EQU       CMA7@^@@@@PERIODAM
)@@G@@*   EQU       PR7 @ @@@@SLASH*    EQU       SLSH7     @^@@@@ATSGN*    EQAN
)@@G@@U       ATS7@^@@@@LETTERA*  EQU       AA7 @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@AO

)@@G@@S FOR ADIT$ @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @E@@@@A$DIT*    NAME    IZ
)@@G@@  ADIT$               INITIAL ADIT$ ENTRY @D@@@@A$DITR*   NAME      ADITJA
)@@G@@R$              ADIT$ RE-ENTRY@H@@@@A$DITZ*   NAME      ADITZ$          JB
)@@G@@    ADIT$ RE-ENTRY AND ZERO COLUMN POINTER@E@@@@A$CHAR*   NAME      ACHAJC
)@@G@@R$              EDIT A CHARACTER    @F@@@@A$QCHR*   NAME      AQCHR$    JD
)@@G@@          ASCII QUARTER CHARACTER   @E@@@@A$COL*    NAME      ACOL$     JE
)@@G@@          POSITION TO A COLUMN@D@@@@A$SKIP*   NAME      ASKIP$          JF
)@@G@@    SKIP AN AREA  @E@@@@A$FCHR*   NAME      AFCHR$              FIELDATAJG
)@@G@@ CHARACTER  @F@@@@A$SCHR*   NAME      ASCHR$              ASCII SIXTH CHJH
)@@G@@ARACTER     @F@@@@A$MSGC*   NAME      *1                  STORE NEW AMSGJI
)@@G@@$ CHARACTER @F@@@@          DO        P(1)>1 , LA,15*(P(1)<3)+P(1,3) 12,JJ
)@@G@@+(A$AD 1,1) @C@@@@          DO        P(1)=1 , LA,15 12,P(1,1)    @G@@@@JK
)@@G@@          DO P(0,*0)=0 , LMJ       11,P(0,0) . CALL PROPER ROUTINE,     JL
)@@G@@@H@@@@          DO P(0,*0)=1 , SA,7      12,2,1    . OR STORE NEW MSG CHJM
)@@G@@ARACTER     @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  JN
)@@G@@@F@@@@A$OCTV*   NAME      AOCTV$              VARIABLE LENGTH OCTAL     JO
)@@G@@@F@@@@A$DECV*   NAME      ADECV$              VARIABLE LENGTH DECIMAL   JP
)@@G@@@E@@@@A$FD1*    NAME      AFD1$               ONE WORD FIELDATA   @C@@@@JQ
)@@G@@A$FD3*    NAME      AFD3$               FIELDATA@C@@@@A$FD5*    NAME    JR
)@@G@@  AFD5$               FIELDATA@C@@@@A$FI*     NAME      AFI$            JS
)@@G@@    I$ FORM @D@@@@A$FH*     NAME      AFH$                18,18 FORM    JT
)@@G@@@D@@@@A$SW1*    NAME      ASW1$               ASCII SIXTHS  @D@@@@A$SW3*JU
)@@G@@    NAME      ASW3$               ASCII SIXTHS  @D@@@@A$QW1*    NAME    JV
)@@G@@  AQW1$               ASCII QUARTERS@D@@@@A$QW3*    NAME      AQW3$     JW
)@@G@@          ASCII QUARTERS@G@@@@A$HEXV*   NAME      AHEXV$              VAJX
)@@G@@RIABLE LENGTH HEXADECIMAL     @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,P(1,JY
)@@G@@3) 12,+(A$AD 1,1) @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          ENJZ
)@@G@@D     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      0,1 @E@@@@A$DITX*   NAME      ADITKA
)@@G@@X$              EXIT FROM EDIT MODE @ @@@@A$DTX*    NAME      ADITX$    KB
)@@G@@@F@@@@A$COLN*   NAME      ACOLN$              COMPUTE COLUMN NUMBER     KC
)@@G@@@F@@@@A$MSGR*   NAME      AMSGR$              RE-ENTER MESSAGE EDITOR   KD
)@@G@@@I@@@@A$QMSR*   NAME      AQMSR$              RE-ENTER QUARTER WORD ASCIKE
)@@G@@I MESSAGE EDIT    @G@@@@A$FMSR*   NAME      AFMSR$              RE-ENTERKF
)@@G@@ FIELDATA MESSAGE EDITOR@G@@@@A$LMSR*   NAME      ALMSR$              REKG
)@@G@@-ENTER MONOCASE MESSAGE EDITOR@H@@@@A$CLEAR*  NAME      ACLEAR$         KH
)@@G@@    BLANK IMAGE AND RESET COLUMN POINTER  @ @@@@          LMJ       11,PKI
)@@G@@(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @E@@@@KJ
)@@G@@A$FD2*    NAME      AFD2$               TWO WORD FIELDATA   @C@@@@A$FD4*KK
)@@G@@    NAME      AFD4$               FIELDATA@C@@@@A$FD6*    NAME      AFD6KL
)@@G@@$               FIELDATA@D@@@@A$SW2*    NAME      ASW2$               ASKM
)@@G@@CII SIXTHS  @D@@@@A$SW4*    NAME      ASW4$               ASCII SIXTHS  KN
)@@G@@@D@@@@A$QW2*    NAME      AQW2$               ASCII QUARTERS@D@@@@A$QW4*KO
)@@G@@    NAME      AQW4$               ASCII QUARTERS@C@@@@          DO      KP
)@@G@@  P(1)>0 , DL 12,+(A$AD 1,1)  @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@KQ
)@@G@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @D@@@@A$MSG*    NAKR
)@@G@@ME      AMSG$               STRING EDIT   @D@@@@A$MSG1*   NAME      AMSGKS
)@@G@@1$              STRING EDIT   @G@@@@A$QMSG*   NAME      AQMSG$          KT
)@@G@@    QUARTER WORD ASCII STRING EDIT  @G@@@@A$QMS1*   NAME      AQMS1$    KU
)@@G@@          QUARTER WORD ASCII STRING EDIT  @E@@@@A$FMSG*   NAME      AFMSKV
)@@G@@G$              FIELDATA STRING EDIT@E@@@@A$FMS1*   NAME      AFMS1$    KW
)@@G@@          FIELDATA STRING EDIT@E@@@@A$LMSG*   NAME      ALMSG$          KX
)@@G@@    MONOCASE STRING EDIT@E@@@@A$LMS1*   NAME      ALMS1$              MOKY
)@@G@@NOCASE STRING EDIT@F@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14*(P(1)<3)+P(1,KZ
)@@G@@3) 12,+(A$AD 1,1) @F@@@@          DO        P(0)>1 , LXI,14*(P(0)<4)+P(0LA
)@@G@@,3) 12,+(A$AD 0,1)@ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          ENLB
)@@G@@D     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @E@@@@A$COPY*   NAME      ACOPLC
)@@G@@Y$              STRING COPY ROUTINE @F@@@@A$PACK*   NAME      APACK$    LD
)@@G@@          STRING COPY WITH PACKING  @G@@@@A$QCOP*   NAME      AQCOP$    LE
)@@G@@          QUARTER WORD ASCII STRING COPY  @G@@@@A$QPAC*   NAME      AQPALF
)@@G@@C$              QUARTER WORD ASCII STRING PACK  @E@@@@A$FCOP*   NAME    LG
)@@G@@  AFCOP$              FIELDATA STRING COPY@E@@@@A$FPAC*   NAME      AFPALH
)@@G@@C$              FIELDATA STRING PACK@F@@@@          DO        P(1)>1 , LLI
)@@G@@A,14*(P(1)<4)+P(1,4) 12,+(A$AD 1,2) @F@@@@          DO        P(0)>1 , LLJ
)@@G@@XI,14*(P(0)<4)+P(0,3) 12,+(A$AD 0,1)@C@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LLK
)@@G@@A,14 13,P(1,1)    @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          ENLL
)@@G@@D     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @F@@@@A$OCTF*   NAME      AOCTLM
)@@G@@F$              FIXED LENGTH OCTAL EDITOR @G@@@@A$DECF*   NAME      ADECLN
)@@G@@F$              FIXED LENGTH DECIMAL EDITOR     @H@@@@A$DECZ*   NAME    LO
)@@G@@  ADECZ$              FIXED LENGTH LEADING ZERO DECIMAL     @H@@@@A$DCFZLP
)@@G@@*   NAME      ADCFZ$              FIXED LENGTH LEADING ZERO DECIMAL     LQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@A$HEXF*   NAME      AHEXF$              FIXED LENGTH HEXADECIMAL  LR
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DO        P(1)>1 , LA,P(1,4) 12,+(A$AD 1,2) @C@@@@      LS
)@@G@@    DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14 13,P(1,1)    @ @@@@          LMJ       11,PLT
)@@G@@(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @E@@@@LU
)@@G@@A$FORM*   NAME      1                   GENERAL FORM EDIT   @D@@@@      LV
)@@G@@    DO        P(1)>1 , LA,P(1,4) 12,+(A$AD 1,2) @B@@@@          DO      LW
)@@G@@  P(1)>0 , LA 13,P(1,1) @ @@@@          LMJ       11,AFORM$ @#@@@@      LX
)@@G@@    END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @G@@@@A$FLS1*   NAME    LY
)@@G@@  AFLS1$              SINGLE PRECISION SCIENTIFIC     @H@@@@A$FLG1*   NALZ
)@@G@@ME      AFLG1$              SINGLE PRECISION GENERALIZED FORMAT   @G@@@@MA
)@@G@@A$FLF1*   NAME      AFLF1$              SINGLE PRECISION FIXED FORMAT   MB
)@@G@@@E@@@@A$FLN1*   NAME      AFLN1$              SINGLE NICE EDIT    @^@@@@MC
)@@G@@P(2,1)    EQU       1   @G@@@@A$FLS2*   NAME      AFLS2$              DOMD
)@@G@@UBLE PRECISION SCIENTIFIC     @G@@@@A$FLG2*   NAME      AFLG2$          ME
)@@G@@    DOUBLE PRECISION GENERALIZED    @F@@@@A$FLF2*   NAME      AFLF2$    MF
)@@G@@          DOUBLE PRECISION FIXED    @E@@@@A$FLN2*   NAME      AFLN2$    MG
)@@G@@          DOUBLE NICE EDIT    @E@@@@          DO        P(2,1)**(P(1)>1)MH
)@@G@@ , LA 13,+(A$AD 1,2)    @E@@@@          DO        (1-P(2,1))**(P(1)>1) ,MI
)@@G@@ DL 13,+(A$AD 1,2)@C@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14 12,P(1,1)    MJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@MK
)@@G@@P         PROC      *1  @C@@@@A$TIM*    NAME      ATIME$              HHML
)@@G@@:MM:SS@C@@@@A$TIME*   NAME      ATIME$              HH:MM:SS@C@@@@A$DAY1MM
)@@G@@*   NAME      ADAY1$              MM/DD/YY@D@@@@A$DAY2*   NAME      ADAYMN
)@@G@@2$              DD MMM YY     @D@@@@A$DAY3*   NAME      ADAY3$          MO
)@@G@@    MONTH DD, YEAR@C@@@@A$DAY4*   NAME      ADAY4$              YYYYMMDDMP
)@@G@@@C@@@@A$DAY5*   NAME      ADAY5$              YYMMDD  @C@@@@A$DAYW*   NAMQ
)@@G@@ME      ADAYW$              WEEKDAY @D@@@@A$TIM1*   NAME      ATIM1$    MR
)@@G@@          HH:MM:SS XM   @D@@@@A$TIME1*  NAME      ATIME1$             HHMS
)@@G@@:MM:SS XM   @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,P(1,3) 12,+(A$AD 1,1) MT
)@@G@@@ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@MU
)@@G@@P         PROC      0,2 @C@@@@A$TD*     NAME      ATIME$              HHMV
)@@G@@:MM:SS@C@@@@A$DAT1*   NAME      ADAY1$              MM/DD/YY@D@@@@A$DAT2MW
)@@G@@*   NAME      ADAY2$              DD MMM YY     @D@@@@A$DAT3*   NAME    MX
)@@G@@  ADAY3$              MONTH DD, YEAR@C@@@@A$DAT4*   NAME      ADAY4$    MY
)@@G@@          YYYYMMDD@C@@@@A$DAT5*   NAME      ADAY5$              YYMMDD  MZ
)@@G@@@C@@@@A$DATW*   NAME      ADAYW$              WEEKDAY @D@@@@A$TD1*    NANA
)@@G@@ME      ATIM1$              HH:MM:SS XM   @#@@@@          TDATE$  @ @@@@NB
)@@G@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@E@@@@A$AD* NC
)@@G@@    PROC      1,1        COMPUTE GENERALIZED ADDRESS  @ @@@@S         EQND
)@@G@@U       A$AD(1,1) @ @@@@T         EQU       A$AD(1,2) @F@@@@          +(NE
)@@G@@I$      0,0,0,P(S,T+1),2*P(S,*T+1)+P(S,*T),P(S,T))    @#@@@@          ENNF
)@@G@@D     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *10 @D@@@@A$PKT*    NAME      1   NG
)@@G@@       GENERATE SMALL PACKET  @D@@@@A$PKTF*   NAME      0          GENERNH
)@@G@@ATE BIG PACKET    @ @@@@A(0,1)    EQU       'MSG'     @ @@@@A(1,1)    EQNI
)@@G@@U       046 '&'   @ @@@@A(0,2)    EQU       'FPS'     @^@@@@A(1,2)    EQNJ
)@@G@@U       1   @ @@@@A(0,3)    EQU       'FPR'     @^@@@@A(1,3)    EQU     NK
)@@G@@  1   @ @@@@A(0,4)    EQU       'DPC'     @^@@@@A(1,4)    EQU       0   NL
)@@G@@@ @@@@A(0,5)    EQU       'SPC'     @^@@@@A(1,5)    EQU       0   @G@@@@NM
)@@G@@ DO P>2 ,I DO P-2 ,J DO A(1) , DO A(0,J)=P(I+1,1) ,A(1,J) EQU P(I+1,2)  NN
)@@G@@@ @@@@Y         FORM      9,9,18    @ @@@@Z         FORM      6,6,6,18  NO
)@@G@@@A@@@@          Y         0,P(1,1),P(1,2) @ @@@@          Y         0,0,NP
)@@G@@0     @ @@@@          Y         A(1,1),0,0@B@@@@          Z         A(1,NQ
)@@G@@2),A(1,3),0,0     @^@@@@          +         0,0 @^@@@@          +       NR
)@@G@@  0   @^@@@@          +         0   @A@@@@          DO        P(0,0) , ENS
)@@G@@ND    @B@@@@          +         A(1,4),A(1,5),0,0     @A@@@@          + NT
)@@G@@        0,0,0,0,0,0     @^@@@@          +         0,0 @^@@@@          + NU
)@@G@@        0   @^@@@@          +         0   @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@NV
)@@G@@@^@@@@P         PROC      1,1 @E@@@@A$FW*     NAME      1               NW
)@@G@@    GENERATE FORM WORD  @F@@@@I         DO        P(1) ,F(1) EQU (F(1)*/NX
)@@G@@P(1,I))++(1*/(P(1,I)-1))@^@@@@          +         F(1)@#@@@@          ENNY
)@@G@@D     @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@F@@@@P         PROC      *1                  EDNZ
)@@G@@IT USING COMMON PACKET  @^@@@@A$DT*     NAME      1   @^@@@@A$DTR*    NAOA
)@@G@@ME      2   @^@@@@A$DTZ*    NAME      3   @B@@@@          DO        P(0,OB
)@@G@@0)=1 , A$DIT AP$  @B@@@@          DO        P(0,0)=2 , A$DITR AP$ @B@@@@OC
)@@G@@          DO        P(0,0)=3 , A$DITZ AP$ @B@@@@          DO        P(1)OD
)@@G@@>0 , A$MSGC P(1,1)@#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC    OE
)@@G@@  *1  @#@@@@A$PRTX*   NAME    @#@@@@          A$DTX   @#@@@@A$PRT*    NAOF
)@@G@@ME    @C@@@@          APRINT$   AL$,ALL$,P(1,1)+(P(1)=0)    @#@@@@      OG
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@/.    @@@@@@@@@@@@@D@@@@.         INTERNAL DEFINITIONSOH
)@@G@@ FOR ADIT$S AND ADIT$U  @@@@@@@#@@@@          DEF     @@@@@@@G@@@@ISIGN OI
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+2,,Q2           INTEGER SIGN (ZERO IF PLUS)     @E@@@@OJ
)@@G@@BIAS      EQUF      PKT+7,,XH2          SAVE AREA FOR POWERS@D@@@@XPSIGNOK
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+8,,S3           EXPONENT SIGN @G@@@@EXP       EQUF    OL
)@@G@@  PKT+8,,S4           IF NONZERO, NO EXPONENT SCAN    @G@@@@AFTRDP    EQOM
)@@G@@UF      PKT+8,,S5           AFTER THE DECIMAL POINT FLAG    @F@@@@VALNUMON
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+8,,S6           VALID NUMBER FOUND FLAG   @F@@@@MAN   OO
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+9               FIRST PART OF MANTISSA    @@@@@@@^@@@@OP
)@@G@@C$DEF*    PROC      0,0 @F@@@@LOAD*     EQUF      ADIT$U,*CX          LOOQ
)@@G@@AD AND ADVANCE POINTER  @F@@@@LOOK*     EQUF      ADIT$K,CX           LOOR
)@@G@@AD WITHOUT ADVANCING    @^@@@@          END       .   @@@@@@@@@@@@@B@@@@OS
)@@G@@.         PROCEDURES FOR ADIT$S AND ADIT$U@@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC    OT
)@@G@@  0,1 @I@@@@C$POS3*   NAME      CPOS3$              POSITION BEFORE NEXTOU
)@@G@@ NON-BLANK CHARACTER    @I@@@@C$POS4*   NAME      CPOS4$              POOV
)@@G@@SITION AFTER NEXT NON-BLANK CHARACTER     @E@@@@C$CHAR*   NAME      CCHAOW
)@@G@@R$              A0 = 1 CHARACTER    @H@@@@C$LOOK*   NAME      CLOOK$    OX
)@@G@@          LOOK AT NEXT CHAR, POINTER UNTOUCHED  @E@@@@C$I*      NAME    OY
)@@G@@  CI$                 A0(A1) = INTEGER    @F@@@@C$DI*     NAME      CDI$OZ
)@@G@@                A0(A1) = DECIMAL INTEGER  @F@@@@C$OI*     NAME      COI$PA
)@@G@@                A0(A1) = OCTAL INTEGER    @G@@@@C$HI*     NAME      CHI$PB
)@@G@@                A0,A1 = HEXADECIMAL INTEGER     @ @@@@          LMJ     PC
)@@G@@  11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  PD
)@@G@@@G@@@@C$POS1*   NAME      CPOS1$              POSITION BEFORE CHARACTER PE
)@@G@@IN A0 @G@@@@C$POS2*   NAME      CPOS2$              POSITION AFTER CHARAPF
)@@G@@CTER IN A0  @E@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14 12,P(1,1)-(P(0,*0)=PG
)@@G@@1)    @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@PH
)@@G@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *0  @F@@@@C$FP*     NAME      CFP$            PI
)@@G@@    FLOATING POINT UNEDIT     @F@@@@C$FP2*    NAME      CFP2$           PJ
)@@G@@    DOUBLE PRECISION ENTRY    @E@@@@C$N*      NAME      CN$             PK
)@@G@@    ANY TYPE WHATSOEVER @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@      PL
)@@G@@    END     @@@@@@___ NAME      2   @^@@@@A$DTZ*    NAME      3   @B@@@@PM
)@@G@@          DO        P(0,*[S@@@*SDFF*@@@@@@@A@@@@.         ADIT$ EDITING PN
)@@G@@PACKAGE     @@@@@@@ @@@@.         PROCEDURES FOR BDIT$@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@PO
)@@G@@@^@@@@P         PROC      1,2 @#@@@@B$*       NAME    @ @@@@          LXPP
)@@G@@I,U     X11,P(1,1)@^@@@@          J         B$  @#@@@@          END     PQ
)@@G@@@@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      1,2 @G@@@@B$PRT*    NAME      1         PR
)@@G@@          PRINT, BLANK, AND ZERO COLUMN   @B@@@@          LA,U      12,(PS
)@@G@@P(1)=0)+P(1,1)    @ @@@@          LMJ       11,BPRT$  @#@@@@          ENPT
)@@G@@D     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @F@@@@B$DT*     NAME      BDT$PU
)@@G@@                BLANK AND ZERO COLUMN     @D@@@@B$DTZ*    NAME      BDTZPV
)@@G@@$               ZERO COLUMN   @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @B@@@@PW
)@@G@@          DO        P(1)>0 , B$MSGC P(1,1)@#@@@@          END     @@@@@@PX
)@@G@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @H@@@@B$DT1*    NAME      BDT1$           PY
)@@G@@    NEW ADDRESS, BLANK, AND ZERO COLUMN   @G@@@@B$DTZ1*   NAME      BDTZPZ
)@@G@@1$              NEW ADDRESS AND ZERO COLUMN     @D@@@@          DO      QA
)@@G@@  P(1)>0 , LA 12,(P(1,1),P(1,2))    @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) QB
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @E@@@@B$CHARQC
)@@G@@*   NAME      BCHAR$              EDIT A CHARACTER    @F@@@@B$QCHR*   NAQD
)@@G@@ME      BQCHR$              ASCII QUARTER CHARACTER   @E@@@@B$COL*    NAQE
)@@G@@ME      BCOL$               POSITION TO A COLUMN@D@@@@B$SKIP*   NAME    QF
)@@G@@  BSKIP$              SKIP AN AREA  @E@@@@B$FCHR*   NAME      BFCHR$    QG
)@@G@@          FIELDATA CHARACTER  @F@@@@B$SCHR*   NAME      BSCHR$          QH
)@@G@@    ASCII SIXTH CHARACTER     @F@@@@B$MSGC*   NAME      BMSGC$          QI
)@@G@@    STORE NEW BMSG$ CHARACTER @F@@@@          DO        P(1)>1 , LA,15*(QJ
)@@G@@P(1)<3)+P(1,3) 12,+(B$AD 1,1) @C@@@@          DO        P(1)=1 , LA,15 1QK
)@@G@@2,P(1,1)    @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          END     QL
)@@G@@@@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @F@@@@B$OCTV*   NAME      BOCTV$    QM
)@@G@@          VARIABLE LENGTH OCTAL     @F@@@@B$DECV*   NAME      BDECV$    QN
)@@G@@          VARIABLE LENGTH DECIMAL   @E@@@@B$FD1*    NAME      BFD1$     QO
)@@G@@          ONE WORD FIELDATA   @C@@@@B$FD3*    NAME      BFD3$           QP
)@@G@@    FIELDATA@C@@@@B$FD5*    NAME      BFD5$               FIELDATA@C@@@@QQ
)@@G@@B$FI*     NAME      BFI$                I$ FORM @D@@@@B$FH*     NAME    QR
)@@G@@  BFH$                18,18 FORM    @D@@@@B$SW1*    NAME      BSW1$     QS
)@@G@@          ASCII SIXTHS  @D@@@@B$SW3*    NAME      BSW3$               ASQT
)@@G@@CII SIXTHS  @D@@@@B$QW1*    NAME      BQW1$               ASCII QUARTERSQU
)@@G@@@D@@@@B$QW3*    NAME      BQW3$               ASCII QUARTERS@G@@@@B$HEXVQV
)@@G@@*   NAME      BHEXV$              VARIABLE LENGTH HEXADECIMAL     @D@@@@QW
)@@G@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,P(1,3) 12,+(B$AD 1,1) @ @@@@          LMQX
)@@G@@J       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC    QY
)@@G@@  0,1 @F@@@@B$COLN*   NAME      BCOLN$              COMPUTE COLUMN NUMBEQZ
)@@G@@R     @F@@@@B$MSGR*   NAME      BMSGR$              RE-ENTER MESSAGE EDIRA
)@@G@@TOR   @I@@@@B$QMSR*   NAME      BQMSR$              RE-ENTER QUARTER WORRB
)@@G@@D ASCII MESSAGE EDIT    @G@@@@B$FMSR*   NAME      BFMSR$              RERC
)@@G@@-ENTER FIELDATA MESSAGE EDITOR@G@@@@B$LMSR*   NAME      BLMSR$          RD
)@@G@@    RE-ENTER MONOCASE ASCII EDITOR  @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) RE
)@@G@@@#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @E@@@@B$FD2*RF
)@@G@@    NAME      BFD2$               TWO WORD FIELDATA   @C@@@@B$FD4*    NARG
)@@G@@ME      BFD4$               FIELDATA@C@@@@B$FD6*    NAME      BFD6$     RH
)@@G@@          FIELDATA@D@@@@B$SW2*    NAME      BSW2$               ASCII SIRI
)@@G@@XTHS  @D@@@@B$SW4*    NAME      BSW4$               ASCII SIXTHS  @D@@@@RJ
)@@G@@B$QW2*    NAME      BQW2$               ASCII QUARTERS@D@@@@B$QW4*    NARK
)@@G@@ME      BQW4$               ASCII QUARTERS@C@@@@          DO        P(1)RL
)@@G@@>0 , DL 12,+(B$AD 1,1)  @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@      RM
)@@G@@    END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @D@@@@B$MSG*    NAME    RN
)@@G@@  BMSG$               STRING EDIT   @D@@@@B$MSG1*   NAME      BMSG1$    RO
)@@G@@          STRING EDIT   @G@@@@B$QMSG*   NAME      BQMSG$              QURP
)@@G@@ARTER WORD ASCII STRING EDIT  @G@@@@B$QMS1*   NAME      BQMS1$          RQ
)@@G@@    QUARTER WORD ASCII STRING EDIT  @E@@@@B$FMSG*   NAME      BFMSG$    RR
)@@G@@          FIELDATA STRING EDIT@E@@@@B$FMS1*   NAME      BFMS1$          RS
)@@G@@    FIELDATA STRING EDIT@F@@@@B$LMSG*   NAME      BLMSG$              MORT
)@@G@@NOCASE ASCII STRING EDIT@F@@@@B$LMS1*   NAME      BLMS1$              MORU
)@@G@@NOCASE ASCII STRING EDIT@F@@@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14*(P(1)<3RV
)@@G@@)+P(1,3) 12,+(B$AD 1,1) @F@@@@          DO        P(0)>1 , LXI,14*(P(0)<RW
)@@G@@4)+P(0,3) 12,+(B$AD 0,1)@ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@      RX
)@@G@@    END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @E@@@@B$COPY*   NAME    RY
)@@G@@  BCOPY$              STRING COPY ROUTINE @F@@@@B$PACK*   NAME      BPACRZ
)@@G@@K$              STRING COPY WITH PACKING  @G@@@@B$QCOP*   NAME      BQCOSA
)@@G@@P$              QUARTER WORD ASCII STRING COPY  @G@@@@B$QPAC*   NAME    SB
)@@G@@  BQPAC$              QUARTER WORD ASCII STRING PACK  @E@@@@B$FCOP*   NASC
)@@G@@ME      BFCOP$              FIELDATA STRING COPY@E@@@@B$FPAC*   NAME    SD
)@@G@@  BFPAC$              FIELDATA STRING PACK@F@@@@          DO        P(1)SE
)@@G@@>1 , LA,14*(P(1)<4)+P(1,4) 12,+(B$AD 1,2) @F@@@@          DO        P(0)SF
)@@G@@>1 , LXI,14*(P(0)<4)+P(0,3) 12,+(B$AD 0,1)@C@@@@          DO        P(1)SG
)@@G@@>0 , LA,14 13,P(1,1)    @ @@@@          LMJ       11,P(0,0) @#@@@@      SH
)@@G@@    END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @F@@@@B$OCTF*   NAME    SI
)@@G@@  BOCTF$              FIXED LENGTH OCTAL EDITOR @G@@@@B$DECF*   NAME    SJ
)@@G@@  BDECF$              FIXED LENGTH DECIMAL EDITOR     @H@@@@B$DECZ*   NASK
)@@G@@ME      BDECZ$              FIXED LENGTH LOADING ZERO DECIMAL     @H@@@@SL
)@@G@@B$DCFZ*   NAME      BDCFZ$              FIXED LENGTH LOADING ZERO DECIMASM
)@@G@@L     @F@@@@B$HEXF*   NAME      BHEXF$              FIXED LENGTH HEXADECSN
)@@G@@IMAL  @D@@@@          DO        P(1)>1 , LA,P(1,4) 12,+(B$AD 1,2) @C@@@@SO
)@@G@@          DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14 13,P(1,1)    @ @@@@          LMJ     SP
)@@G@@  11,P(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  SQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@B$FORM*   NAME      1                   NERAL FORM EDIT     @D@@@@SR
)@@G@@          DO        P(1)>1 , LA,P(1,4) 12,+(B$AD 1,2) @B@@@@          DOSS
)@@G@@        P(1)>0 , LA 13,P(1,1) @ @@@@          LMJ       11,BFORM$ @#@@@@ST
)@@G@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @F@@@@B$FLS1*   NASU
)@@G@@ME      BFLS1$            SINGLE PRECISION SCIENTIFIC @H@@@@B$FLG1*   NASV
)@@G@@ME      BFLG1$            SINGLE PRECISION GENERALIZED FORMAT     @G@@@@SW
)@@G@@B$FLF1*   NAME      BFLF1$            SINGLE PRECISION FIXED FORMAT     SX
)@@G@@@D@@@@B$FLN1*   NAME      BFLN1$            SINGLE NICE EDIT@^@@@@P(2,1)SY
)@@G@@    EQU       1   @F@@@@B$FLS2*   NAME      BFLS2$            DOUBLE PRESZ
)@@G@@CISION SCIENTIFIC @F@@@@B$FLG2*   NAME      BFLG2$            DOUBLE PRETA
)@@G@@CISION GENERALIZED@E@@@@B$FLF2*   NAME      BFLF2$            DOUBLE PRETB
)@@G@@CISION FIXED@D@@@@B$FLN2*   NAME      BFLN2$            DOUBLE NICE EDITTC
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DO        P(2,1)**(P(1)>1) , LA 13,+(B$AD 1,2)    @E@@@@TD
)@@G@@          DO        (1-P(2,1))**(P(1)>1) , DL 13,+(B$AD 1,2)@C@@@@      TE
)@@G@@    DO        P(1)>0 , LA,14 12,P(1,1)    @ @@@@          LMJ       11,PTF
)@@G@@(0,0) @#@@@@          END     @@@@@@@^@@@@P         PROC      *1  @C@@@@TG
)@@G@@B$TIM*    NAME      BTIME$              HH:MM:SS@C@@@@B$TIME*   NAME    TH
)@@G@@  BTIME$              HH:MM:SS@C@@@@B$DAY1*   NAME      BDAY1$          TI
)@@G@@    MM/DD/YY@D@@@@B$DAY2*   NAME      BDAY2$              DD MMM YY     TJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@B$DAY3*   NAME      BDAY3$              MONTH DD, YEAR@C@@@@B$DAY4TK
)@@G@@*   NAME      BDAY4$              YYYYMMDD@C@@@@B$DAY5*   NAME      BDAYTL
)@@G@@5$              YYMMDD  @C@@@@B$DAYW*   NAME      BDAYW$              WETM
)@@G@@EKDAY @D@@@@B$TIM1*   NAME      BTIM1$              HH:MM:SS XM   @D@@@@TN

)@@G@@ COMPUTE GENERALIZED ADDRESS  @ @@@@S         EQU       E$AD(1,1) @ @@@@MP
